text: The book of the generation of Jesus Christ , the son of David , the son of Abraham .
text2: OTISU ie ' i msInukIn iaianke ' pmatse ' cuk iukwan Cisus Knayst we ' kwIsmukot Te ' pItun , ipi Te ' pIt we ' kwusmukcIn E ' pIne ' amun ;

text: Abraham begat Isaac ; and Isaac begat Jacob ; and Jacob begat Judas and his brethren ;
text2: E ' pIne ' e ' m okiwosmukon AysIkIn , ipi AysIk kiwosmukon Ce ' kapIn , ipi Ce ' kap kiwosmukon CotusIn , ipi niw wikane ' iIn ;

text: And Judas begat Phares and Zara of Thamar ; and Phares begat Esrom ; and Esrom begat Aram ;
text2: IcI Cotus kiwosmukon Pe ' nIsIn , ipi Se ' ne ' , Te ' me ' cI kao kie ' iwat , ipi Pe ' nIs kiwosmukon E ' snumIn , ipi E ' snum kiwosmukon E ' numIn ,

text: And Aram begat Aminadab ; and Aminadab begat Naasson ; and Naasson begat Salmon ;
text2: Ipi E ' num kiwosmukon E ' mInite ' pIn , ipi E ' mInite ' p kiwosmukon Ne ' e ' sunIn , ipi Ne ' e ' sun kiwosmukon SanmunIn ,

text: And Salmon begat Booz of Rachab ; and Booz begat Obed of Ruth ; and Obed begat Jesse ;
text2: Ipi Sanmun kiwosmukon Poe ' sIn , niwcI kaokie ' icIn Ne ' ke ' pIn , ipi Poe ' s kiwosmukon , OpItIn , kaokie ' icIn NwtIn ipi OpIt kiwosmukon Ce ' siIn ;

text: And Jesse begat David the king ; and David the king begat Solomon of her that had been the wife of Urias ;
text2: Ipi Ce ' si kiwosmukon Te ' pItIn kaokumawIt , ipi Te ' pIt kaokumawIt kiwosmukon Sanumun ; kaokie ' cIn kaowiwpninIn Ionaie ' s ;

text: And Solomon begat Roboam ; and Roboam begat Abia ; and Abia begat Asa ;
text2: Ipi Sanumun kiwosmukon NopoumIn , ipi Nopoum , kiwosmukon E ' pie ' In , ipi E ' pie ' kiwosmukon E ' se ' In ;

text: And Asa begat Josaphat ; and Josaphat begat Joram ; and Joram begat Ozias ;
text2: Ipi E ' se ' kiwosmukon Cose ' pe ' tIn , ipi CosIpe ' t kiwosmukon Cone ' mIn , ipi Cone ' m kiwosmukon Osaye ' sIn :

text: And Ozias begat Joatham ; and Joatham begat Achaz ; and Achaz begat Ezekias ;
text2: Ipi Osaye ' s kiwosmukon Cote ' mIn ipi Cote ' m kiwosmukon E ' ke ' sIn ipi E ' ke ' s kiwosmukon IsikayusIn ;

text: And Ezekias begat Manasses ; and Manasses begat Amon ; and Amon begat Josias ;
text2: Ipi Isikayus kiwosmukon Me ' ne ' se ' sIn , ipi Me ' ne ' se ' s kiwosmukon E ' munIn , ipi E ' mun kiwosmukon CosayusIn ;

text: And Josias begat Jechonias and his brethren , about the time they were carried away to Babylon :
text2: Ipi Cosayus kiwosmukon Ce ' koniasIn , ipi wikane ' iIn , iwcI ipic e ' kimacintwa Pe ' pinun ;

text: And after they were brought to Babylon , Jechonias begat Salathiel ; and Salathiel begat Zorobabel ;
text2: IcI kapie ' ntwa , ipI Pe ' pinun Ce ' konias kiwosmukon Se ' ne ' tie ' nIn , ipi Se ' ne ' tie ' n kiwosmukon Sonope ' pe ' nIn :

text: And Zorobabel begat Abiud ; and Abiud begat Eliakim ; and Eliakim begat Azor ;
text2: Ipi Sonope ' pe ' n kiwosmukon E ' ipie ' tIn , ipi E ' pie ' t kiwosmukon E ' naye ' kumIn , ipi E ' naye ' kum kiwosmukon E ' sunIn ;

text: And Azor begat Sadoc ; and Sadoc begat Achim ; and Achim begat Eliud ;
text2: Ipi E ' sun kiwosmukon Se ' takIn , ipi Se ' tak kiwosmukon E ' kImIn , ipi E ' kIm kiwosmukon InayiatIn ;

text: And Eliud begat Eleazar ; and Eleazar begat Matthan ; and Matthan begat Jacob ;
text2: Ipi Inayiat kiwosmukon Inie ' se ' nIn , ipi Inie ' se ' kiwosmukon Me ' te ' nIn , ipi Me ' te ' n kiwosmukon Ce ' kapIn ;

text: And Jacob begat Joseph the husband of Mary , of whom was born Jesus , who is called Christ .
text2: Ipi Ce ' kap kiwosmukon CosipIn , onape ' mIn o Me ' ni kanikukocIn Cisus oie ' o kashInkanIt Knayst .

text: So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations ; and from David until the carrying away into Babylon are fourteen generations ; and from the carrying away into Babylon unto Christ are fourteen generations .
text2: OtIcI ie ' i cak iaianke ' pmatsowunIn kaocukwat E ' pIne ' - e ' m nash Te ' pIt , Ke ' iapI mtatso shItnie ' w iaianke ' pmatsowunIn , ipi Te ' pIt nash kamacintwa Pe ' pe ' nunuk ke ' iapI mtatso shItInie ' w iaianke ' pmatsowunIn icI pic kamacintwa Pe ' pe ' nunuk nash Knayst , ke ' iapI mtatso shItInie ' w iaianke ' pmatsowunIn .

text: Now the birth of Jesus Christ was on this wise : When as his mother Mary was espoused to Joseph , before they came together , she was found with child of the Holy Ghost .
text2: OtIcI KanikIt Cisus Knayst otI kanomkuk , ni okie ' iIn Me ' niIn kakishknontwat ni CosipIn e ' pwamshI witike ' twat okikukIshkwan pInoce ' iIn e ' ki ne ' nmukot Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: Then Joseph her husband , being a just man , and not willing to make her a publick example , was minded to put her away privily .
text2: IcI CosipIn onape ' mun kimnoshuwe ' psin cowi kine ' ntusi , e ' wipwakuke ' ncukasnIt , ntawac kimoc e ' wipke ' at kine ' ntum .

text: But while he thought on these things , behold , the angel of the Lord appeared unto him in a dream , saying , Joseph , thou son of David , fear not to take unto thee Mary thy wife : for that which is conceived in her is of the Holy Ghost .
text2: Me ' kwacI otI e ' ie ' shite ' at , PInI Kshe ' mIne ' to omIshIne ' we ' mIn nkipie ' otusuk kinapitum , OtI okikon , Cosip we ' kwIsmukwiIn Te ' pIt ke ' ko kwtukIn e ' wiwicIt Me ' ni kiwish , iwsI otI e ' ncukot kane ' nmukot Kshe ' mIne ' to OcipamIn .

text: And she shall bring forth a son , and thou shalt call his name JESUS : for he shall save his people from their sins .
text2: KuokwIsI , Cisus cI kIshInkana , wino kuke ' skonan otInIshInape ' mIn , i e ' patasnIt .

text: Now all this was done , that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet , saying ,
text2: Caye ' k otI kanomkuk e ' wi te ' pwe ' mkuk Kshe ' mIne ' to ni iacimot otI kikIto :

text: Behold , a virgin shall be with child , and shall bring forth a son , and they shall call his name Emmanuel , which being interpreted is , God with us .
text2: PInI ! she ' shksi kIncuko ku ' okwIsIcI otI okishInkanawan Ime ' niun ; i ie ' i KshmIne ' to kuwice ' okonan e ' kItok .

text: Then Joseph being raised from sleep did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him , and took unto him his wife :
text2: Pic cI Cosip kaonIshkat me ' kwa e ' npapIt oki te ' pwe ' twan Kshe ' mIne ' ton omIshIne ' we ' mIn kakot , icI e ' kiw otapInImatsot ni wiwun .

text: And knew her not till she had brought forth her firstborn son : and he called his name JESUS .
text2: CocI okikuke ' nmasin nash ni onutmoshanIn okwIsIn ; kaniknIt Cisus cI okishInkanan .

text: Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judaea in the days of Herod the king , behold , there came wise men from the east to Jerusalem ,
text2: UPIC cI Cisus kanikIt , iukwanuk Pe ' tne ' um Otanuk Cwtie ' uk , me ' kwa E ' nut e ' ie ' okimawut ; PInI e ' pianIt ne ' pwakancIn nInwun we ' cmokuk Cinwse ' ne ' muk ; e ' pie ' shiawat ;

text: Saying , Where is he that is born King of the Jews ? for we have seen his star in the east , and are come to worship him .
text2: OtIcI kikItwuk , TInipicI okanikIt otokumamwan Cwiuk ? NkiwaptumwamIn otInukomIn we ' cmokuk ; ie ' i we ' cpie ' shiaiak e ' winume ' kItokIt .

text: When Herod the king had heard these things , he was troubled , and all Jerusalem with him .
text2: Pic E ' nut okuma kanotuk , notI kikicum mkoshkate ' ntum , ipi caye ' k Cinose ' ne ' muk kaie ' cuk .

text: And when he had gathered all the chief priests and scribes of the people together , he demanded of them where Christ should be born .
text2: IcI pic kakishmaosomat caye ' k kcI - me ' matmokcIn , ipi otonpie ' ke ' mwan ki nIshInape ' k , kakishmaoce ' tiwat win okinatawan , TInipi Knayst ke ' cInikIt ?

text: And they said unto him , In Bethlehem of Judaea : for thus it is written by the prophet ,
text2: IcI otI okinawan iukwanuksI Pe ' tnium Cwtie ' uk e ' kiwuk ; iw kashupie ' ike ' t iacimot :

text: And thou Bethlehem , in the land of Juda , art not the least among the princes of Juda : for out of thee shall come a Governor , that shall rule my people Israel .
text2: Ipi kin Pe ' tnium e ' kiwuk Cwtie ' uk , cosu kin , otapine ' kitupite ' ntakwsusi we ' kmaocuk Cwtie ' uk ; kin su kaotIna okuma ke ' tupakwnat ntInIshInape ' muk Isne ' iIn .

text: Then Herod , when he had privily called the wise men , inquired of them diligently what time the star appeared .
text2: IcI E ' nut pic kimoc e ' kintomat ni ne ' pwakancIn nInwun , e ' kin natowat me ' me ' cIk ; TInicI pic nuk kanakwsIt ?

text: And he sent them to Bethlehem , and said , Go and search diligently for the young child ; and when ye have found him , bring me word again , that I may come and worship him also .
text2: IcI e ' kinokanat Pe ' tniumuk , otI okinan , Wishiak , ipi pmawike ' ntone ' ok we ' shknikIt opInoce ' , icI kimkawe ' k , pie ' witumoshike ' k , ninke ' e ' wishiaian e ' wiwInume ' kituwuk .

text: When they had heard the king , they departed ; and , lo , the star , which they saw in the east , went before them , till it came and stood over where the young child was .
text2: IcI pInI , pic cI kanotwawat ni okuman kinmumacik , icI niw onukon kawapmawapIt we ' cmokuk , kinmInikanin , pama kinkase ' shikacIiIt we ' shknikIt pInoce ' kacIiIt .

text: When they saw the star , they rejoiced with exceeding great joy .
text2: Pic cI kawapmawat ni nukon kikcImnwe ' ntumwuk , ipi kimnawan koswuk .

text: And when they were come into the house , they saw the young child with Mary his mother , and fell down , and worshipped him : and when they had opened their treasures , they presented unto him gifts ; gold , and frankincense , and myrrh .
text2: IcI pic kapiawat wikwamuk okiwapmawan , niw kaoshkIniknIt pInoce ' iIn , ipi Me ' ni okie ' iIn , icI e ' kipmukocnowat , ipi e ' nume ' kitowawat ; icI pic kapaknumwat iukwanIn we ' onItnukIn , e ' kimawan mikwe ' wunIn osaw shonia , ipi mnomiakowun .

text: And being warned of God in a dream that they should not return to Herod , they departed into their own country another way .
text2: IcI e ' kiwitumakwat , Kshe ' mIne ' ton e ' kiapwawat ke ' kowi minI shiake ' k E ' nut e ' iIt , icI e ' kishiawat e ' tnukie ' wat ototanwak , pkan kinImIshie ' k .

text: And when they were departed , behold , the angel of the Lord appeareth to Joseph in a dream , saying , Arise , and take the young child and his mother , and flee into Egypt , and be thou there until I bring thee word : for Herod will seek the young child to destroy him .
text2: IcI pic kamaciwat PInI Cosip kiwapman Kshe ' mune ' to omIshInIwe ' mIn e ' napituk otI otukon , Psukwin ipi otapIn we ' shknikIt pInoce ' , ipi niw okie ' iIn , ipI cI Iciptuk oshumok ; icI shi iuk ; pama pie ' toian kikitowun , iukwanwi E ' nut okupantone ' wan we ' shknikIt pInoce ' iIn e ' winsat .

text: When he arose , he took the young child and his mother by night , and departed into Egypt :
text2: PicI win kapsukwit kiwtapInan niw we ' shkniknIt , pInoce ' iIn , ipi niw okie ' iIn , nipatipuk e ' kishumaciwat iukwanuk Iciptuk .

text: And was there until the death of Herod : that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet , saying , Out of Egypt have I called my son .
text2: IcI shi pIne ' e ' ikiiIt , pama kanponIt E ' nutIn , iwsI ie ' i ote ' pwe ' wun kakItot , Kshe ' munIto otacimonInwun , kItwak , iw ie ' i kaocIntomuk O nkwIs iukwanuk Iciptuk .

text: Then Herod , when he saw that he was mocked of the wise men , was exceeding wroth , and sent forth , and slew all the children that were in Bethlehem , and in all the coasts thereof , from two years old and under , according to the time which he had diligently inquired of the wise men .
text2: IcI E ' nut e ' kikike ' ntuk e ' ki papnInmukot ni ne ' pwakancIn nInwun , kikcInshkatsI e ' kinokashwe ' t , icI kaye ' k e ' kinsIckasnIt pInoce ' iIn e ' inIcIn shi Pe ' tniumuk ; ipi caye ' k pe ' shoc e ' inIcIn nashponkIsnIcIn , ipi iwpic e ' kiwi ke ' nata ‘ wat niw ne ' pwakancIn nInwun .

text: Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremy the prophet , saying ,
text2: Iw ie ' i , te ' pwe ' wun kakitot , iukwan Ce ' nimaye ' , iacimot otI kakItot ;

text: In Rama was there a voice heard , lamentation , and weeping , and great mourning , Rachel weeping for her children , and would not be comforted , because they are not .
text2: Iukwanuk Ne ' me ' uk okinotanawa notakwsuwun wishkwe ' we ' ksuwun , ipi moik , ipi kcIshke ' ntumwun ; Ne ' ce ' n otumwuman onicanse ' iIn , cowi kshkumnowankosi ; osam co wuie ' iwin .

text: But when Herod was dead , behold , an angel of the Lord appeareth in a dream to Joseph in Egypt ,
text2: Pic cI E ' nut kanpot PInI Kshe ' mIne ' to omIshIne ' we ' mIn okiwtuskon Cosip kinaptum shi Iciptuk ,

text: Saying , Arise , and take the young child and his mother , and go into the land of Israel : for they are dead which sought the young child ' s life .
text2: OtI okikon , Psukwin , ipi otapIn we ' shknikIt pInoce ' , ipi niw okie ' iIn , icIshiak e ' kiwuk Isne ' iIn , kinpokwshIki kapmIntone ' kuk , niw we ' shkniknIncIn pInoce ' iIn opumatsiwnInIn .

text: And he arose , and took the young child and his mother , and came into the land of Israel .
text2: IcI win e ' kipsukwit , e ' kiwtapnat , niw we ' shkniknIncIn pInoce ' iIn , ipi niw okie ' iIn , icI e ' kishiawat e ' kiwuk Isne ' iIn .

text: But when he heard that Archelaus did reign in Judaea in the room of his father Herod , he was afraid to go thither : notwithstanding , being warned of God in a dream , he turned aside into the parts of Galilee :
text2: Pic cI kanotuk Akine ' us kaokumawnIt Cwtie ' uk , e ' kinapshkumwat ni osIn E ' nutIn win kikwtacI ipI e ' wishiat ; kaian wuwitmakot Kshe ' mIne ' ton e ' kinaptuk , icI kipke ' wak e ' kishiat Ke ' niniuk .

text: And he came and dwelt in a city called Nazareth : that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophets , He shall be called a Nazarene .
text2: IcI kapiat e ' kiwutat kcI otanuk Ne ' sune ' t kishInkate ' , iw ie ' i te ' pwe ' wun kakItot iacimocuk Win kshInkaso Ne ' sIni nInI .

text: In those days came John the Baptist , preaching in the wilderness of Judaea ,
text2: ICI niw e ' kishkiwuk kipie ' wak Can , Ke ' ctapie ' nwe ' t , e ' pmukie ' kwe ' t no ‘ wmtukwakukik Cwtie ' uk .

text: And saying , Repent ye : for the kingdom of heaven is at hand .
text2: OtIcI kItwak , Kisate ' ntmok ; osam otokumauwun shpumuk pe ' shoc pie ' te ' mkIt .

text: For this is he that was spoken of by the prophet Esaias , saying , The voice of one crying in the wilderness , Prepare ye the way of the Lord , make his paths straight .
text2: OtI ie ' o kaiacImukocIn iacimoncIn Ise ' iusIn , kItwak , OwIiu otInwe ' wun nkot pe ' motnakwsIt na ‘ mtukwakukikumuk , Nikan oshInwitak , Te ' pe ' n mukwie ' kon wshItwuk tupasI mie ' we ' sIn .

text: And the same John had his raiment of camel ' s hair , and a leathern girdle about his loins ; and his meat was locusts and wild honey .
text2: OpshIie ' o Can , kamtItIkIn kcowe ' si wisiumIn , ipi mishakIn kcipsonIn , pe ' mkcipsocIn , ipi kaotumicimowut , iukwan e ' tsawe ' ncIn , ipi amo sispakwut ,

text: Then went out to him Jerusalem , and all Judaea , and all the region round about Jordan ,
text2: IwcI e ' kipie ' naskakot Cinose ' ne ' m , ipi caye ' k Cwtie ' , ipi caye ' k kiwtayiukwan e ' pmukiwuk Cantanuk .

text: And were baptized of him in Jordan , confessing their sins .
text2: IcI e ' ki kcitapie ' nat shi Cantanuk , e ' kiwitumake ' wat omIcshuwe ' psiwnawan .

text: But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees come to his baptism , he said unto them , O generation of vipers , who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come ?
text2: Pic kawapmat e ' mane ' nIt Pe ' nIsiIn , ipi Se ' cwsiIn , e ' pianIt e ' tshI kcItapie ' nwe ' t , otIcI okinan , O ! pe ' matsie ' k pwatacke ' ie ' k mIntoie ' k ! we ' nicI kakoie ' k e ' wioshImotme ' k , iw nshkatsowun wapiamkuk .

text: Bring forth therefore fruits meet for repentance :
text2: Pie ' toke ' , i we ' wnunuk pmatsowun e ' wiwapitI wuie ' k , kisate ' ntumwun .

text: And think not to say within yourselves , We have Abraham to our father : for I say unto you , that God is able of these stones to raise up children unto Abraham .
text2: Ke ' kowi , ke ' ko , ne ' ntuke ' k kiiwawa , E ' pIne ' - e ' mntoosmamIn , ktInum cI nin , Kshe ' mIne ' to otakshkIton , notI sIniIn , e ' wipsukwipnat pInoce ' iIn iukwanIn E ' pIne ' - e ' mIn .

text: And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees : therefore every tree which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down , and cast into the fire .
text2: Ipi iw iukwan pkumsakIn okitonawa e ' wce ' pkiwuk , iukwanIn ni mtukon , ipi cI niw mtukon pwapie ' tomkItnuk we ' onItnuk micum kukishkukaso , ipi cI , shkote ' k kupukcikaso .

text: I indeed baptize you with water unto repentance : but he that cometh after me is mightier than I , whose shoes I am not worthy to bear : he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost , and with fire :
text2: Nin we ' we ' nI , kitakcItapie ' num shi npik , e ' kisate ' ntume ' k , win cie ' ko ke ' pie ' pukwnIshkowut nin , win wusimI pite ' ntakwsI icI nin , coiI nin ntupit e ' ntakwsIsi , icIi e ' wipmaotawuk omuksInIn , win ie ' k kukcitapie ' nkowa shi Kshe ' mIne ' to ocipamIn ipi iukwan shkote ' k .

text: Whose fan is in his hand , and he will throughly purge his floor , and gather his wheat into the garner ; but he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire .
text2: WinsI kie ' nuk nonouwun one ' cik , icI we ' we ' nI okupinakwan opIskakomIn , ipi okumawtoston opukwe ' shkInum ; okIton mukukok , icIie ' k okIdakswan oshIikwe ' mnIn , shi kakuk shkote ' k .

text: Then cometh Jesus from Galilee to Jordan unto John , to be baptized of him .
text2: IcI e ' pie ' ocupiat Cisus iukwanuk Ke ' nIniuk , e ' shiat Catanuk e ' iInIt CanIn e ' wikcItapie ' nkot .

text: But John forbad him , saying , I have need to be baptized of thee , and comest thou to me ?
text2: CancI okikna ‘ moan , otI okinan , NinsI ie ' k ktakcItapie ' n ; TacI e ' pie ' naska ‘ wiIn , nin .

text: And Jesus answering said unto him , Suffer it to be so now : for thus it becometh us to fulfil all righteousness . Then he suffered him .
text2: Cisus cI okinkwe ' twan otI okinan , NocImasI i kInomkIt nkom , Iw ke ' shuwe ' pse ' ikon e ' wite ' pwe ' k , caye ' k mInoshuwe ' psiwun . IwcI e ' kite ' pwe ' twat .

text: And Jesus , when he was baptized , went up straightway out of the water : and , lo , the heavens were opened unto him , and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove , and lighting upon him :
text2: IcI Cisus kakishkcItapie ' nkot , iwcI papuk kashIpie ' kwashuk , icI pInI e ' kinsakwsanuk , Kishuk , ipi kiwapman Kshe ' mIne ' to OcipamIn , e ' pie ' nisashkanIt , ke ' cwa mIne ' to mimi ; e ' pie ' pkIshnInIt wiiwuk .

text: And lo a voice from heaven , saying , This is my beloved Son , in whom I am well pleased .
text2: IcI pInI , notakwsowun shpumuk , otI kikItomkIt , OtI ie ' o te ' panuk NkwIs , nin ke ' cmInonwe ' It .

text: Then was Jesus led up of the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted of the devil .
text2: IWCI Cisus e ' kimacinkot KcI CipamIn now ' mtukwakik , e ' wikwcItupe ' nmukot ni mIcImIne ' ton .

text: And when he had fasted forty days and forty nights , he was afterward an hungred .
text2: IcI pic , KapwawisnIt nie ' waptuk tso kishuk , ipi nie ' waptuk tso tpuk ; iwcI e ' pkIte ' t .

text: And when the tempter came to him , he said , If thou be the Son of God , command that these stones be made bread .
text2: IcI pic kakocItpe ' nmukocIn kapianIt e ' cIiIt otI okikon ; KishpIn kin We ' kwIsmukwiIn Kshe ' mIne ' to , kIton notI sIniIn e ' wiwshIckate ' k e ' wikwe ' shkInwuk .

text: But he answered and said , It is written , Man shall not live by bread alone , but by every word that proceedeth out of the mouth of God .
text2: Okinkwe ' twancI ipi otI okinan otI e ' shonupie ' kate ' k ; NInI cowitapmatsIsi , pe ' pshuk pkwe ' shkIn mtIno ; mtIno ie ' ki cak kikitowun we ' cpie ' sakumom kuk otonik Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: Then the devil taketh him up into the holy city , and setteth him on a pinnacle of the temple ,
text2: IucI mIcImIne ' ton okisho ' wnukon iukwuanuk kcI otanuk , e ' kiw cipitupukot shi kwItupuk nume ' okumkok .

text: And saith unto him , If thou be the Son of God , cast thyself down : for it is written , He shall give his angels charge concerning thee : and in their hands they shall bear thee up , lest at any time thou dash thy foot against a stone .
text2: OtIcI otukon , KishpIn kin , okwIsmukwiIn Kshe ' mIne ' to , pie ' ocIniswe ' pnItson ; otukwshI e ' shonIpie ' kate ' k , Win okuwitmowan omIshInIwe ' mIn , e ' wikuwapmukwiIn ipi onIciwak kupumukwitInukok wikake ' e ' wipwapaksite ' shnIn sInik .

text: Jesus said unto him , It is written again , Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy God .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , otukwshI e ' shwunIpie ' ka te ' k minI , Ke ' kowi kwcItupe ' nmakIn Te ' pe ' nmukwiIn Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: Again , the devil taketh him up into an exceeding high mountain , and sheweth him all the kingdoms of the world , and the glory of them ;
text2: MinI cI , mIcImIne ' to okishonan e ' cI kcI pkotnianuk e ' kiwaptuat , caye ' k okumauwun shotI kik , e ' pic wuntInuk .

text: And saith unto him , All these things will I give thee , if thou wilt fall down and worship me .
text2: Ipi otI okinan , caye ' k notI , kuminIn , KishpIn pmukocnIn , ipi nume ' kItoiIn .

text: Then saith Jesus unto him , Get thee hence , Satan : for it is written , Thou shalt worship the Lord thy God , and him only shalt thou serve .
text2: OtIcI Cisus okinan , Nkoci , shian , MIcImIne ' to , otukwshI e ' shwunupie ' kate ' k , Nume ' kito ‘ w Te ' pe ' nmukwuiIn , Kshe ' mIne ' to wintIno kie ' pmItwut .

text: Then the devil leaveth him , and , behold , angels came and ministered unto him .
text2: IwcIni , mIcImIne ' ton kashInkInkot , ipi pInI mIshInwe ' n e ' pianIt , icI e ' pie ' pmitakot .

text: Now when Jesus had heard that John was cast into prison , he departed into Galilee ;
text2: IcI pic Cisus kanotuk , ni CanIn e ' kikpakwukasnIt , kishImaci shi Ke ' niniuk ;

text: And leaving Nazareth , he came and dwelt in Capernaum , which is upon the sea coast , in the borders of Zabulon and Nephthalim :
text2: IcI e ' nkItuk Ne ' se ' nIt ; e ' kishiat e ' wIiIt cikcukum Ke ' panium e ' te ' nuk , ipi e ' pie ' kokumukianuk Se ' pwnIn , ipi Ne ' ptInum .

text: That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet , saying ,
text2: Niiw ie ' ni te ' pwe ' onIn kakitot Ise ' us iacimot otI kItwak ,

text: The land of Zabulon , and the land of Nephthalim , by the way of the sea , beyond Jordan , Galilee of the Gentiles ;
text2: Iw e ' kiwuk Se ' pwnIn , ipi e ' kiwuk Ne ' ptInum shiw cikcukum wus ipI Catan : o Ke ' nIni mawak Me ' ikIscIk ;

text: The people which sat in darkness saw great light ; and to them which sat in the region and shadow of death light is sprung up .
text2: Kiw nIshInape ' k kacipitupcuk , e ' kiskupkonianuk okiwaptanawa e ' kikcI wase ' anuk , kiw cI kacipitupIcuk , e ' tnukie ' wat , ipi e ' cipamtomkuk npowIn ; wase ' iak kipie ' mokse ' mkIt .

text: From that time Jesus began to preach , and to say , Repent : for the kingdom of heaven is at hand .
text2: IwcI pic Cisus e ' pmowe ' pkie ' kwe ' t , otI kikIto ; Kisate ' ntumok ; iukwankwshI okumauwun e ' te ' k shpumuk kishkot pe ' shoc pie ' iumkIt .

text: And Jesus , walking by the sea of Galilee , saw two brethren , Simon called Peter , and Andrew his brother , casting a net into the sea : for they were fishers .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' pmose ' t cikcukum Ke ' nIniuk , okiwapman nish we ' wikane ' itIncIn ; Sayiman e ' shnukasot Pitu , ipi E ' nto , ni wikane ' iIn , e ' tshI pukInanIt supiIn kiukumik ; kikikoske ' ‘ onInwuk .

text: And he saith unto them , Follow me , and I will make you fishers of men .
text2: IcI otI okinan , Naktone ' o ‘ shuk ; kaoshe ' num e ' wikikoskawe ' p nInwuk .

text: And they straightway left their nets , and followed him .
text2: IcI papuk e ' kinkaawat otIsupimwan , icI e ' kinaktone ' wawat .

text: And going on from thence , he saw other two brethren , James the son of Zebedee , and John his brother , in a ship with Zebedee their father , mending their nets ; and he called them .
text2: IcI e ' nmaocImacit shiw , okiwapman minI , anIt nish we ' wikane ' itIncIn , Ce ' ms , We ' kwIsmukot Se ' pitiIn , ipi Can wikane ' iIn pic napkwanuk , Se ' pitiIn , oswan e ' na ' towat , otusupimwan ; icI e ' kintomat .

text: And they immediately left the ship and their father , and followed him .
text2: IcI papuk e ' kinkItmowat onapkwanwa ipi oswan ; e ' kinaktone ' wawat .

text: And Jesus went about all Galilee , teaching in their synagogues , and preaching the gospel of the kingdom , and healing all manner of sickness and all manner of disease among the people .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kipashiat Ke ' nIniuk e ' pmuknomake ' t ; iukwanuk otInume ' okumkomwak , ipi e ' pmukie ' kwe ' t mnoacImowun , iukwan okumauwun , ipi e ' pmIne ' se ' we ' t cak , e ' shnakwuk iakwnoke ' wun , ipi cak e ' shnakwuk kwtuke ' ntumwun ki nIshInape ' k .

text: And his fame went throughout all Syria : and they brought unto him all sick people that were taken with divers diseases and torments , and those which were possessed with devils , and those which were lunatick , and those that had the palsy ; and he healed them .
text2: IcIi , otI win wiacmukwsIwun e ' kipashiamke ' tnuk kiswe ' shkie ' nI shi caye ' k Sinie ' uk ; okipie ' twawancI niw caye ' k iakwnokancIn ni nIshInape ' n , ipi ni na ‘ we ' napinIncIn , ipi kwe ' tukitoncIn , ipi niw packakwancIn mIcImIne ' ton , ipi ni ne ' kaptIncIn , ipi niw ne ' nie ' psIncIn , icI win e ' kine ' se ' at .

text: And there followed him great multitudes of people from Galilee , and from Decapolis , and from Jerusalem , and from Judaea , and from beyond Jordan .
text2: IcI okipme ' nashkakon ke ' cmaoce ' ‘ tincIn nIshInape ' n , pie ' ocupie ' n Ke ' nIniuk , ipi kiwcupie ' n Tike ' ponIsuk , ipi kiwcupie ' n Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi kiwcupie ' n Cwtie ' uk , ipi kiwcupie ' n wus ipI Catanuk .

text: And seeing the multitudes , he went up into a mountain : and when he was set , his disciples came unto him :
text2: ICI kawapmat niw maoce ' tincIn , e ' okwIcowe ' t , e ' shpItnianuk , icI kacipitupIt ni e ' knomowacIn okipie ' naskakon .

text: And he opened his mouth , and taught them , saying ,
text2: IcI e ' ki pakinuk ioton ; icI e ' ki knomowat , otI kikIto .

text: Blessed are the poor in spirit : for theirs is the kingdom of heaven .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik , ki ke ' tmake ' nkuk , ocipamwan ki ie ' ki , te ' pe ' ntukuk okumauwuni shpumuk kishkok .

text: Blessed are they that mourn : for they shall be comforted .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik ki kasate ' ntukuk ; ki ie ' ki ke ' mnwe ' ntukuk .

text: Blessed are the meek : for they shall inherit the earth .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik ki pwakcIne ' ntukuk wio ’ wawa ; ki ie ' ki ke ' tpe ' ntumwat kI .

text: Blessed are they which do hunger and thirst after righteousness : for they shall be filled .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik ki , pe ' kIte ' we ' ntukuk , ipi e ' kakaskite ' e ' skuk , iukwan mnoshuwe ' psowun ; ki ie ' ki ke ' moshkIne ' sanuk

text: Blessed are the merciful : for they shall obtain mercy .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik ki she ' we ' ncIke ' cIk ; ki ie ' ki ke ' kshkItocuk , she ' we ' ncuke ' wun .

text: Blessed are the pure in heart : for they shall see God .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik ki , kiw pante ' acIk ; kiie ' ki ke ' wapmacIk Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: Blessed are the peacemakers : for they shall be called the children of God .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik ki , tpantowun we ' shtocuk ; ki ie ' ki , ke ' shInkascIk Kshe ' mIne ' to onicansIn .

text: Blessed are they which are persecuted for righteousness ' sake : for theirs is the kingdom of heaven .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsik ki mnoshuwe ' psuwun , we ' ckwtukitowat ki ie ' ki te ' pe ' ntukuk okumauwun shpumuk kishkok .

text: Blessed are ye , when men shall revile you , and persecute you , and shall say all manner of evil against you falsely , for my sake .
text2: Kshuwe ' ntakwsum pic nInwuk , nshonasmukwie ' k , ipi miashtotakwuie ' k , ipi cake ' ko kItwat kukInwush kacimukwie ' k , nin ocItotakoie ' k .

text: Rejoice , and be exceeding glad : for great is your reward in heaven : for so persecuted they the prophets which were before you .
text2: Mnwankosuk , ipi kcImnwe ' ntumok ; waminkoie ' k kIcIne ' ntakwut shpumuk kishkok ; iwkwshI kashukwtukawat , iacimoncIn kaie ' cuk e ' pwam shIiIe ' k .

text: Ye are the salt of the earth : but if the salt have lost his savour , wherewith shall it be salted ? it is thenceforth good for nothing , but to be cast out , and to be trodden under foot of men .
text2: KinwakwshI kitowsiw taknawum shotI kik ; kishpIncI ponsiwtakunukpkok ; we ' kwnicI ke ' ocI siwtakunupok ’ CosI ke ' shI owunsInon mtIno e ' wisakcuwe ' pInIkate ' k , icI e ' wipInkatumowat , nInwuk .

text: Ye are the light of the world . A city that is set on an hill cannot be hid .
text2: Kinwasi , ktowawase ' shkanawa kI . KcI otan , kwutakik e ' te ' k , co takukIckate ' snon .

text: Neither do men light a candle , and put it under a bushel , but on a candlestick ; and it giveth light unto all that are in the house .
text2: Cowike ' nInwuk , otaskI ‘ sinawa waskone ' ncukIn , icI e ' witowat namiukwan tupu ‘ ke ' nuk ; mtIno ie ' k waskone ' ncukunatkok ; icI waskone ' ntakwnawa , caye ' k pituk e ' icuk wikwamuk ,

text: Let your light so shine before men , that they may see your good works , and glorify your Father which is in heaven .
text2: Nocma wawase ' shkmok e ' nasmupwat nInwuk e ' wiwaptumwat kmInototmonawan , ipie ' wi winwane ' k Koswa e ' iIt ; shpumuk kishkok .

text: Think not that I am come to destroy the law , or the prophets : I am not come to destroy , but to fulfil .
text2: Ke ' kowi ne ' ntuke ' kon ; otI we ' cpiaian e ' wipnactoian tpakwnuke ' wun , tanake ' iacimocuk ; cowi intoc piasi e ' wipnactoian ; mtIno e ' wikishtoian .

text: For verily I say unto you , Till heaven and earth pass , one jot or one tittle shall in no wise pass from the law , till all be fulfilled .
text2: We ' we ' nI KtInum , pamasI shpumuk kishkok , ipI kI , ke ' ntoshke ' mkIt , cotIna pke ' ci pwawe ' pnukate ' k tpakwnuke ' wun , pama caye ' k kicaktpIshkosak .

text: Whosoever therefore shall break one of these least commandments , and shall teach men so , he shall be called the least in the kingdom of heaven : but whosoever shall do and teach them , the same shall be called great in the kingdom of heaven .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' pnactokwIn notI nkot e ' Ii e ' kacinoiakIn kiIkwe ' we ' nIn , ipi ke ' knomowacIn nInwun ; kshInkaso oie ' o otapine ' kupite ' ntakwsI shiw okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok ; We ' kwe ' ntukcI ke ' totuk ipi ke ' knomowat ike ' win kshInkana oie ' oke ' cIpite ' ntakwsIt shi okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok .

text: For I say unto you , That except your righteousness shall exceed the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees , ye shall in no case enter into the kingdom of heaven .
text2: OtI KItInum ; KishpIn cI kmnoshuwe ' psiwnInawa wusimI pwashumnoshuwe ' psie ' k kotI we ' npie ' ke ' cIk ipi Pe ' nIsiuk ; cokitakshkItosim e ' wipitike ' ie ' k okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok .

text: Ye have heard that it was said by them of old time , Thou shalt not kill ; and whosoever shall kill shall be in danger of the judgment :
text2: Kinotake ' msI anwI pnowi kakItwapIt ; Ke ' kowi nshowe ' ke ' k icI we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' nshowe ' kwe ' n kInie ' sansI pictpakwnIt .

text: But I say unto you , That whosoever is angry with his brother without a cause shall be in danger of the judgment : and whosoever shall say to his brother , Raca , shall be in danger of the council : but whosoever shall say , Thou fool , shall be in danger of hell fire .
text2: OtI KtInum , We ' kwe ' ntuk kipinshInshkacitw at wikane ' iIn kInie ' sansI pic tpakwnIt , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' nat wikane ' iIn ; Ne ' ke ' , kInie ' sansI e ' tshI kikitokiwuk ; ke ' iapI we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' nat ; Kukie ' patIs , kInie ' sansI namkumuk shkote ' k .

text: Therefore if thou bring thy gift to the altar , and there rememberest that thy brother hath ought against thee ;
text2: KishpIn cI iw pie ' ton kmikwe ' wun e ' tc sku ‘ umatuk , icI shiw mikwe ' ntIn kikane ' , ke ' ko , e ' ne ' nmukwiIn .

text: Leave there thy gift before the altar , and go thy way ; first be reconciled to thy brother , and then come and offer thy gift .
text2: NkItIn shi ikmikwe ' wun e ' tshI sku ‘ umatuk , icI nmamacin ; ne ' tum pone ' ntuk kikane ' ‘ , icI , pianmikwe ' n iw kmikwe ' wun .

text: Agree with thine adversary quickly , whiles thou art in the way with him ; lest at any time the adversary deliver thee to the judge , and the judge deliver thee to the officer , and thou be cast into prison .
text2: Wikantuk kie ' nup ne ' shknmukwiIn , me ' kwa e ' iI pmowice ' otIie ' k ; kta nupkItnuk ne ' shke ' nmukwiIn tpakwnukie ' wunuk , icI o tpakwnukie ' onInI kupkItnuk kii ’ aw ni okumasIn icI ke ' cIpukinukon shi kpakwotiwkumkok .

text: Verily I say unto thee , Thou shalt by no means come out thence , till thou hast paid the uttermost farthing .
text2: We ' we ' nI ktInIn ; Cowi ktapie ' sakIsi , pama kiwike ' tpu ‘ umIn me ' skwapkIsiIt .

text: Ye have heard that it was said by them of old time , Thou shalt not commit adultery :
text2: Kinotake ' msI , kakItwapIt pnowi ; Ke ' ko win waonIshkaiwuke ' k .

text: But I say unto you , That whosoever looketh on a woman to lust after her hath committed adultery with her already in his heart .
text2: NincI , otI KtInum , We ' kwe ' nshe ' tuk ke ' wapmat ni kwe ' n naw ‘ ne ' nmat ; kowaonIshkaiwu kisha ‘ shiwo te ' ik .

text: And if thy right eye offend thee , pluck it out , and cast it from thee : for it is profitable for thee that one of thy members should perish , and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell .
text2: KishpIn cI , iw kite ' p shkishIk ocI mIcIshuwe ' psin kicIpIton , icI nkocipukiton ; wusimI ktate ' pIs kishpIn shkishuk pnacak , icIi caye ' k kii ‘ awe ' wipukci kate ' k shi namkumuk shkote ' k .

text: And if thy right hand offend thee , cut if off , and cast it from thee : for it is profitable for thee that one of thy members should perish , and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell .
text2: KishpIn kte ' pniw nak ocI mIcIshuwe ' psin , Kishkshun , icI nkoci pukuton ; wusimIcI kte ' pIs nkote ' iI knIce ' n pnacak ; cocI wii caye ' k kii ’ aw e ' wipukicikate ' k namkumuk shkote ' k .

text: It hath been said , Whosoever shall put away his wife , let him give her a writing of divorcement :
text2: OtIsI kikitom , We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' we ' pnakwe ' n wiwun , nocIma win , okuminan we ' npie ' kate ' nuk e ' we ' pnItwat .

text: But I say unto you , That whosoever shall put away his wife , saving for the cause of fornication , causeth her to commit adultery : and whosoever shall marry her that is divorced committeth adultery .
text2: OtI cI KItnum , We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' we ' pnakwe ' n wiwun ; pwawaonIshkaiwuto kwe ' , WinsI o nInI okItotwan , e ' wi waonIshkaiwunIt ; ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' wiwkwe ' n , niw kawe ' pnukasnIncIn waonIshkaiwI .

text: Again , ye have heard that it hath been said by them of old time , Thou shalt not forswear thyself , but shalt perform unto the Lord thine oaths :
text2: MinI ki notake ' m ; kakItwapIt pnowi , Ke ' kowinIshkItkIn ; Ke ' ko kItiIn , Kitotum kashuwawitmowut Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' wi totImIn .

text: But I say unto you , Swear not at all ; neither by heaven ; for it is God ' s throne :
text2: NincI otI , KtInum Ke ' ko wipapIsh kie ' tnamta kwsukIn shi ; ke ' ko wike ' shpumuk kishkok iwi e ' i Kshe ' mIne ' to ocipitupwun .

text: Nor by the earth ; for it is his footstool : neither by Jerusalem ; for it is the city of the great King .
text2: Ke ' kowike ' shotI kik , iw ie ' i otupsIte ' pwun ; ke ' kowike ' , Cinwse ' ne ' muk , iw ie ' i kcIotan o KcIokuma .

text: Neither shalt thou swear by thy head , because thou canst not make one hair white or black .
text2: Ke ' kowike ' kie ' tnamwe ' kIn ; shi ktupik ; cosI wi ktakshkItosin , e ' wiwshIton nkot kinsIs e ' wiwapshkiak , tanake ' e ' wi mkIte ' wak .

text: But let your communication be , Yea , yea ; Nay , nay : for whatsoever is more than these cometh of evil .
text2: NocImasI niw kitukinontiwnowan kitasIstonawa ; e ' ‘ , e ' , co , co ; we ' kwe ' ntuk wusimI icI notI , kupie ' ocipie ' mkIt me ' anuk .

text: Ye have heard that it hath been said , An eye for an eye , and a tooth for a tooth :
text2: KinotamsI e ' kitok ; kukItwapIt shkishuk ashkot shkishuk , ipi wipIt ashkot wipIt .

text: But I say unto you , That ye resist not evil : but whosoever shall smite thee on thy right cheek , turn to him the other also .
text2: Nin cI otI ktInum , ke ' kowi nakwnuke ' k iw me ' anuk ; we ' kwe ' ntuk cI ke ' we ' potakwiIn kte ' pnoiak kwe ' knoito ‘ w minI ashwayiukwan .

text: And if any man will sue thee at the law , and take away thy coat , let him have thy cloke also .
text2: KishpIn cI owIiI nInI witpakwnukwiIn , Ii tpakwnuke ' wunuk , icI otapnImakwiIn kpiskumwakIn ke ' iapI mish kIc - piskumwakIn .

text: And whosoever shall compel thee to go a mile , go with him twain .
text2: Ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk , ke ' wishte ' pmukwiIn , nkot e ' wiwice ' wIt tpukIn , showice ' o nish . 41 And whosoever shall compel thee to go a mile , go with him twain .

text: Give to him that asketh thee , and from him that would borrow of thee turn not thou away .
text2: Mish o ke ' ko ne ' tumakwiIn , ipi cI o ke ' pie ' waukon ke ' ko win koci ne ' nashkawakIn .

text: Ye have heard that it hath been said , Thou shalt love thy neighbour , and hate thine enemy .
text2: Kinotake ' msI kakItok , Tpash pe ' shoc e ' tacuk , ipi shike ' num me ' iashtotakwiIn .

text: But I say unto you , Love your enemies , bless them that curse you , do good to them that hate you , and pray for them which despitefully use you , and persecute you ;
text2: Nin cI otI KtInum , Tpanuk kiw me ' iashtotakwie ' k showe ' num kin me ' cI knonkoie ' k mnotota ‘ w kiw shake ' nmne ' konIk ipi nume ' kita ‘ w kiw ne ' shkacito nikonIk , ipi kiw kwe ' tukine ' kok .

text: That ye may be the children of your Father which is in heaven : for he maketh his sun to rise on the evil and on the good , and sendeth rain on the just and on the unjust .
text2: IwcI i e ' winicansunkoie ' k Koswa shpumuk e ' iIt kishkok ; win otashan otukisomIn e ' wipie ' moksanIt ni me ' ashowe ' psIncIn , ipi niw me ' noshuwe ' psIncIn , ipi onitaan e ' kmaonInuk ni me ' nototmIncIn , ipi niw me ' ashtotmIncIn .

text: For if ye love them which love you , what reward have ye ? do not even the publicans the same ?
text2: KishpIn Tpane ' k , kiw te ' pankoie ' k we ' kwnicI me ' se ' ntume ' k ? ConukwnukI maocIcke ' onInwuk shIcke ' sik ?

text: And if ye salute your brethren only , what do ye more than others ? do not even the publicans so ?
text2: KishpIn cI numkotwa kikane ' iwak , mtIno we ' kwnicI iw wusimI e ' shcI ke ' ie ' k ki anIt ? Conukwinuke ' , kiw maocIcke ' onInwuk totsik ?

text: Be ye therefore perfect , even as your Father which is in heaven is perfect .
text2: Nocma kwiuk showe ' psuk , ke ' cwa o Koswa kwiuk e ' shwe ' psIt shpumuk e ' iIt , kishkok .

text: Take heed that ye do not your alms before men , to be seen of them : otherwise ye have no reward of your Father which is in heaven .
text2: IKWAMSUK e ' wipwamnototwe ' k e ' nasmupwat nInwuk e ' wiwapmne ' k ie ' i ke ' pwaocI mnototone ' k Koswa shpumuk e ' iIt kishkok .

text: Therefore when thou doest thine alms , do not sound a trumpet before thee , as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets , that they may have glory of men . Verily I say unto you , They have their reward .
text2: IwcI ie ' i pic mnototake ' n ke ' kowi nikan notakwtoke ' n pe ' pkwe ' iak e ' shcuke ' wat , e ' nume ' kascuk e ' totkuk nume ' okumkok ; ipi niw otan mie ' we ' n e ' wimnowacimukwat nInwun . - - We ' we ' nI Kuwitmonum ote ' ionawa otIp ‘ okse ' onowa .

text: But when thou doest alms , let not thy left hand know what thy right hand doeth :
text2: Pic cI mnototake ' n , Ke ' kowi knumciwun okuke ' ntusin kte ' pniwun e ' shcuke ' mkuk .

text: That thine alms may be in secret : and thy Father which seeth in secret himself shall reward thee openly .
text2: Iw cI niw kmnototake ' wun e ' witotmIn kimoc , ipi oie ' o Kos wapItanIn pwawapcikate ' nuk winie ' k kuminuk ke ' wapcIkate ' nuk .

text: And when thou prayest , thou shalt not be as the hypocrites are : for they love to pray standing in the synagogues and in the corners of the streets , that they may be seen of men . Verily I say unto you , They have their reward .
text2: Pic cI numan ke ' kowi shIcke ' kIn ke ' cwa kiw e ' nume ' kascIk ; ome ' nwe ' ntanawa e ' numawat e ' nipwawat , otI num - e ' o kumkomwak , ipi otanuk mie ' wuk e ' pmIwawikwe ' anuk e ' wiwapmukwat nIniwun . We ' we ' nI KtInum ote ' ionawa otIp ‘ okse ' onowa ne ' twe ' ntumwat .

text: But thou , when thou prayest , enter into thy closet , and when thou hast shut thy door , pray to thy Father which is in secret ; and thy Father which seeth in secret shall reward thee openly .
text2: Pic cI kin wi numan pitike ' n e ' cI pitokInikate ' k icI ke ' cI kupakwa ‘ mIn shkwate ' m , nume ' kito ‘ w Kos kimoc e ' iIt ; ipi o Kos wiapmuk kimoc kutupamak , e ' wiwapmukon .

text: But when ye pray , use not vain repetitions , as the heathen do : for they think that they shall be heard for their much speaking .
text2: Pic cI numan ke ' kowi pIne ' ‘ nasap , kItke ' kon ke ' cwa Me ' ikIscIk e ' totmoat , winwashIte ' - e ' k ninan nkupsItakomIn , mce ' she ' kItiak .

text: Be not ye therefore like unto them : for your Father knoweth what things ye have need of , before ye ask him .
text2: Ke ' kowi kinwa shIcke ' ke ' k e ' shcike ' wat winwa , okuke ' ntankwshI Koswa ne ' twe ' ntme ' k e ' pwanshIn ntotmowe ' k .

text: After this manner therefore pray ye : Our Father which art in heaven , Hallowed be thy name .
text2: . OtIsI ktashI matumawa ; Nosnan e ' in shpumuk kishkok , ke ' cne ' ntakwuk ktIshnukaswun ,

text: Thy kingdom come . Thy will be done in earth , as it is in heaven .
text2: Kto kumau ’ wun kupie ' mkIt . Nocma kte ' ne ' ntumwun knomkIt shotI kik , ke ' cwa shpumuk kishkok .

text: Give us this day our daily bread .
text2: . MishInak otI nkom e ' kishkiwuk e ' tso kishkuk , e ' shwisIniak .

text: And forgive us our debts , as we forgive our debtors .
text2: Ipi pone ' ntumwIshnak mIsnukInanIn ninanke ' e ' shpone ' nmukIt me ' citotmoiImIt , mIsnumoiumke ' shiIk .

text: And lead us not into temptation , but deliver us from evil : For thine is the kingdom , and the power , and the glory , for ever . Amen .
text2: Ipi ke ' ko shonIshikak ke ' tshI kwcItipe ' nmukoiak , otapInIshnak caye ' k me ' anuk ; kin ktupe ' ntan okumauwun , ipi kshke ' e ' wsuwun , ipi iw kcIne ' ntakwsuwIn kakuk . E ' me ' n .

text: For if ye forgive men their trespasses , your heavenly Father will also forgive you :
text2: KishpIn pone ' ntumwe ' k ninwuk , omuiiashtotmonawa , ke ' iapukI Koswa shpumuk kishkok kupone ' ntmakwa .

text: But if ye forgive not men their trespasses , neither will your Father forgive your trespasses .
text2: KishpIn cI pwapone ' ntumwe ' k nInwuk omuashuwe ' psiwnawa ; CowikI Koswa kupone ' ntumakwsiwa kmIiashuwe ' psiwnawan .

text: Moreover when ye fast , be not , as the hypocrites , of a sad countenance : for they disfigure their faces , that they may appear unto men to fast . Verily I say unto you , They have their reward .
text2: Pic cI pwawisnie ' k ke ' ko wishuwe ' psuke ' k , ke ' cwa e ' nume ' kascuk e ' kisasnakwsawat oshkishkowak e ' miashtowat e ' wine ' nmukwat nInwun ie ' i we ' cpwawisnawat . We ' we ' nI otI KtInum , ote ' ionawasI i otIp ‘ okso - onowa .

text: But thou , when thou fastest , anoint thine head , and wash thy face ;
text2: Pic cI kin , pwawIsnin numukwin ktupik ipi ksikwan .

text: That thou appear not unto men to fast , but unto thy Father which is in secret : and thy Father , which seeth in secret , shall reward thee openly .
text2: Ke ' ocI pwamnone ' nmukwiIn nInwuk e ' pwawisnin mtInoie ' k Kos e ' ie ' t kimotsawunuk ; ipi Kos waptuk , kimotsawun kuminIk ne ' twe ' ntumIn ke ' cI we ' pcIkate ' nuk .

text: Lay not up for yourselves treasures upon earth , where moth and rust doth corrupt , and where thieves break through and steal :
text2: Ke ' kowi twakInukatsoke ' k ke ' cpite ' ntakwuk shotI kik , mIne ' tosiuk ipi e ' wikwakwnuk , e ' wipnack , ipi ki ke ' mote ' iuk e ' wipikpItowat e ' wi kmotwat .

text: But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven , where neither moth nor rust doth corrupt , and where thieves do not break through nor steal :
text2: MtIno twakInukatsok ktupnIo we ' osiwnawan shi shpumuk e ' cI pwaiawat , mIne ' to se ' iuk , cowike ' ke ' ocI kwakwnuk , e ' cI pwapnacak , ipi ki ke ' mote ' iuk e ' ci pwapikptaswat e ' wi kmotwat .

text: For where your treasure is , there will your heart be also .
text2: Shi ie ' shi ke ' cIte ' k ktupnowe ' wsiwnawa ke ' iapukI shi kte ' iwa ke ' cIte ' k .

text: The light of the body is the eye : if therefore thine eye be single , thy whole body shall be full of light .
text2: Wase ' aswun otI kia ‘ w i ie ' i kshkishuk ; kishpIncI nkotuk kshkishuk caye ' k kia ‘ w kawase ' ia .

text: But if thine eye be evil , thy whole body shall be full of darkness . If therefore the light that is in thee be darkness , how great is that darkness !
text2: KishpIn cI iw kshkishuk mianuk caye ' k kia ‘ w kukiskupkonia . KishpIn cI iw wase ' iak e ' te ' m kuk ki i wuk ; kishpIn kiskupkoniak ; knkicI pite ' ntakwut iw e ' kiskupkoniak .

text: No man can serve two masters : for either he will hate the one , and love the other ; or else he will hold to the one , and despise the other . Ye cannot serve God and mammon .
text2: Cowi wIiI nInI otakshkItosin e ' wite ' pwe ' twat nish te ' pe ' nmukwocIn ; nkot e ' iI otashikInman , icI niw nkot otatpanan ke ' iapI niw nkot otamackonan , iwcI niw nkot otamiane ' nman . Cowin ktakshkItosin e ' wi ie ' i pmitwat Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi Me ' mun .

text: Therefore I say unto you , Take no thought for your life , what ye shall eat , or what ye shall drink ; nor yet for your body , what ye shall put on . Is not the life more than meat , and the body than raiment ?
text2: NinsI otI KtInum , Ke ' kowi pame ' ntuke ' kon kpumatsiwnuwam , we ' kwe ' ntIk ke ' micwe ' kwe ' n , we ' kwe ' ntukie ' ke ' mnukwe ' okwe ' n , ipi iukwan kiwiwuwan ; we ' kwe ' ntuke ' ke ' piskumwe ' kwe ' n , ConukwnI pmatsowun wusimI pite ' ntakwse ' non icI i micum , ipi cI iw wia ‘ w wusimI pite ' ntakwut icI iw wapiskumuk .

text: Behold the fowls of the air : for they sow not , neither do they reap , nor gather into barns ; yet your heavenly Father feedeth them . Are ye not much better than they ?
text2: PInI kiw pne ' shiuk pe ' pamsakuk cowi otukikie ' sik , cowike ' okishksusinawa cowike ' omaoton sinawan e ' witowat micImaokumkok ; ke ' iapI shpumuk ktItshI Koswa otushman . ConI kinwa ktupite ' ntakwsusim , wusimI icI winwa ?

text: Which of you by taking thought can add one cubit unto his stature ?
text2: We ' nicI kinwa e ' wi mikwe ' ntume ' k akshkItot nkot otoskwun wusimI e ' wikosIt .

text: And why take ye thought for raiment ? Consider the lilies of the field , how they grow ; they toil not , neither do they spin :
text2: We ' kwnicI we ' cmikwe ' ntume ' k paskume ' konIn . Naktuwe ' ntumok , ni wawaskone ' toiun ktukanuk e ' mikwukuk , cowimikice ' wimke ' snon , cowikI pimnukwe ' mkIsnon .

text: And yet I say unto you , That even Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these .
text2: Ke ' iapI cI , nin KtInum , Win Sane ' mun kaye ' k okIcne ' ntakwsuwun , co kinapme ' nakwsIsi ke ' cwa notI nkot .

text: Wherefore , if God so clothe the grass of the field , which to day is , and to morrow is cast into the oven , shall he not much more clothe you , O ye of little faith ?
text2: KishpIn Kshe ' mIne ' to nukwinie ' tot mishkoiun ktukanuk , nkom e ' kishkiwuk , icI wapuk ke ' ci pukicukate ' k kpoce ' skInuk , conukwunI nowuc win ktanukwnie ' kosim , O pike ' ci te ' pwe ' ie ' ntume ' k .

text: Therefore take no thought , saying , What shall we eat ? or , What shall we drink ? or , Wherewithal shall we be clothed ?
text2: Ke ' kowi pame ' ntuke ' k otI e ' wikItie ' k ; We ' kwnicI ke ' miciIkon ? Ke ' iapukI we ' kwoni ke ' mnukwe ' ikon ? Ke ' iapukI wusimI we ' kwoni ke ' kwe ' iak ?

text: ( For after all these things do the Gentiles seek : ) for your heavenly Father knoweth that ye have need of all these things .
text2: OtI ie ' i tpe ' nwe ' osuwun Me ' ikIscIk kapme ' nton e ' mowat , iukwan suwi Koswa shpumuk , okuke ' ntan waioie ' k cak ke ' ko .

text: But seek ye first the kingdom of God , and his righteousness ; and all these things shall be added unto you .
text2: Ne ' tumsIe ' k ntowaptmok otokumauwun Kshe ' mIne ' to , ipi ome ' noshuwe ' pse ' wun , ipi cI cake ' ko ke ' anke ' stakom .

text: Take therefore no thought for the morrow : for the morrow shall take thought for the things of itself . Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof .
text2: Ke ' kocI pame ' ntuke ' k iw wapuk ; iw wapuk ke ' win kumikwe ' nte ' somkIt . Me ' anuk e ' kmukishuk ke ' iImIn .

text: Judge not , that ye be not judged .
text2: KE ' KO tpakwnuke ' ke ' kon ke ' ocI pwatpakwnukoie ' k .

text: For with what judgment ye judge , ye shall be judged : and with what measure ye mete , it shall be measured to you again .
text2: Iw ie ' i tpakwnuke ' wun ke ' ocI tpakwnukoie ' k , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk tpukIn , ke ' tpuke ' n , minI ke ' tpukate ' ne ' iap ,

text: And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother ' s eye , but considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye ?
text2: We ' kwnicI we ' cwaptumwut pe ' sIne ' kot kikane ' shkishkok ; cocu kin kowaptusin iw mtuk ke ' pakshkakwie ' n tpInowe ' kshkishkok .

text: Or how wilt thou say to thy brother , Let me pull out the mote out of thine eye ; and , behold , a beam is in thine own eye ?
text2: TInicI ke ' nIt kikanI , NkukcIpiton pe ' snukwiIn kshkishkok , ipi pInI , cocu kin kowaptusin , iw mtuk ke ' pakshkakwuiIn tpInowe ' kshkishkok .

text: Thou hypocrite , first cast out the beam out of thine own eye ; and then shalt thou see clearly to cast out the mote out of thy brother ' s eye .
text2: Kin e ' nume ' kasiIn , ne ' tum sakicowe ' pnun mtuko ke ' pakshkakwiIn tpInowe ' kshkishkok , icI ke ' cI mnowapiIn , iwcI e ' wikcuptowut pe ' snukot kikanI oshkishkok .

text: Give not that which is holy unto the dogs , neither cast ye your pearls before swine , lest they trample them under their feet , and turn again and rend you .
text2: Ke ' kominake ' k iw panakwuk , ke ' ko kiw wunumoshuk , ke ' koke ' pukitowake ' k ke ' cwunuk e ' nasmukapwowat kokoshuk , otanapIn katanawan namiukwuan osItiwak , icI kupie ' kwe ' kse ' k , minI knanisik mukwak .

text: Ask , and it shall be given you ; seek , and ye shall find ; knock , and it shall be opened unto you :
text2: Ntotumake ' kcI , icI ke ' cI minkoie ' k ntone ' mokcI icI kumkanawa , papakakwuke ' k cI icI ke ' nsakwnumakom cI .

text: For every one that asketh receiveth ; and he that seeketh findeth ; and to him that knocketh it shall be opened .
text2: E ' tshowat kiw ne ' totmake ' cuk okIionawa , ipi o ke ' ntone ' uk okumkan , icI win oke ' papakakwuke ' t kInsakwnumwa .

text: Or what man is there of you , whom if his son ask bread , will he give him a stone ?
text2: We ' nicI onInI kinwa kishpIn , natakot okwIsun pkwe ' shkIn ? okuminan nI sIn ?

text: Or if he ask a fish , will he give him a serpent ?
text2: KishpIn ke ' ntotmakot kikosIn okuminanI mIne ' ton ?

text: If ye then , being evil , know how to give good gifts unto your children , how much more shall your Father which is in heaven give good things to them that ask him ?
text2: KishpIncI kinuwa , e ' miashuwe ' psie ' k kuke ' ntume ' k washI mikwe ' ie ' k we ' wunuk ki knicansawak , TInicitso wusimI Koswa shpumuk e ' iIt kishkok , ke ' shIminat we ' onutnuk ni ke ' ntotmakwcIn .

text: Therefore all things whatsoever ye would that men should do to you , do ye even so to them : for this is the law and the prophets .
text2: Cake ' ko e ' shIntuwe ' nme ' k nInwuk watotakwie ' k ike ' kinwa ke ' totwe ' k ; otI ie ' i tpakwnuke ' wun , ie ' i iacimocuk .

text: Enter ye in at the strait gate : for wide is the gate , and broad is the way , that leadeth to destruction , and many there be which go in thereat :
text2: Pitike ' k i e ' kacIshkwate ' mwuk , ipi mukIte ' ia i shkwate ' m , ipi mkIte ' ia mie ' o , e ' suk nshonatsinak , ipi patike ' cuk mane ' k shiw .

text: Because strait is the gate , and narrow is the way , which leadeth unto life , and few there be that find it .
text2: Osam kacIshkwate ' m , ipi kacImie ' w e ' suk pmatsiwnuk , ipi pke ' ci shIiwik kiw me ' kumocuk .

text: Beware of false prophets , which come to you in sheep ' s clothing , but inwardly they are ravening wolves .
text2: Nakutowe ' nmuk iacimokascuk pie ' naskakwie ' k mantanshuk pie ' nukwnie ' k piciukwancI pe ' panshawe ' cuk moe ' k .

text: Ye shall know them by their fruits . Do men gather grapes of thorns , or figs of thistles ?
text2: Kukike ' n mawaksI e ' shomicumowat . - - IukwanuknI nInwuk omikitanawan , Siwnwe ' n kcIkunukaoshisuk tanake ' kcIshomnun otamikitanawan msanuk ?

text: Even so every good tree bringeth forth good fruit ; but a corrupt tree bringeth forth evil fruit .
text2: Caye ' ksI kiw me ' nomtukwucuk , mnomicImowuk me ' cI mtukwItcI mcImicmowuk .

text: A good tree cannot bring forth evil fruit , neither can a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit .
text2: We ' wunuk mtukcI cotamcI omicmosi cowi kI mcImtuk tamnoomicma ‘ o si .

text: Every tree that bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down , and cast into the fire .
text2: Caye ' k mtukok pwamnoomicmawut ; kukwu ‘ kaswuk ; icI shi pukInak shkote ' k .

text: Wherefore by their fruits ye shall know them .
text2: Ke ' iapI e ' shmicumowat , ke ' ocI kuke ' nme ' k .

text: Not every one that saith unto me , Lord , Lord , shall enter into the kingdom of heaven ; but he that doeth the will of my Father which is in heaven .
text2: Cowi caye ' k ke ' ke ' cuk , Te ' pe ' nmin , Te ' pe ' nmin , kupitike ' sik okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok , winsI ie ' ko mtIno ke ' shIcke ' t e ' shte ' anIt Nos shpumuk kishkok .

text: Many will say to me in that day , Lord , Lord , have we not prophesied in thy name ? and in thy name have cast out devils ? and in thy name done many wonderful works ?
text2: Mane ' kcI otI nkukok , iw kishkuk Te ' pe ' nmin , Te ' pe ' nmin , conI nki iacimotusimIn ktInoswunuk , conIke ' ktnoswunuk , nki sakcuwe ' pnasimun mcImIne ' tok ? conIke ' ktnoswunuk mane ' kIn , nkiwshItosim mamkate ' ntumwunIn shIcke ' wunIn ?

text: And then will I profess unto them , I never knew you : depart from me , ye that work iniquity .
text2: OtI cI nkInak , Cowi ka kikuke ' nmIsnonIm nkInshIn ; macin kinwa makItme ' k miashowe ' psuwun .

text: Therefore whosoever heareth these sayings of mine , and doeth them , I will liken him unto a wise man , which built his house upon a rock :
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk nwatmokwe ' n notI ntukitonIn , ipi ke ' pamtuk nkine ' nma win , ni pwakanInI kawshItot e ' tat kwIcsInik .

text: And the rain descended , and the floods came , and the winds blew , and beat upon that house ; and it fell not : for it was founded upon a rock .
text2: IcI e ' kmowuk kipie ' mkIt , ipi e ' moshkuk kipie ' mkIt , ipi kinotIn , ipi kipukitasIn kwIc wikwam ; cocI kipmukote ' snon osam kiwishkIckate ' kwIc sInik .

text: And every one that heareth these sayings of mine , and doeth them not , shall be likened unto a foolish man , which built his house upon the sand :
text2: Caye ' k kiw noatkuk notI ntukitonIn ; iwcI pwatotuk nkIne ' nma ke ' kie ' patsIt nInI kaoshItot e ' tat , shi pash kitaokokik .

text: And the rain descended , and the floods came , and the winds blew , and beat upon that house ; and it fell : and great was the fall of it .
text2: IcI e ' kmowuk kipie ' mkIt , ipi e ' moshkuk kipie ' mkIt , ipi kinotIn , ipi ki pukitasIn kwIc wikwam , icI e ' kipmukote ' k kikcInomkIt e ' kipmukote ' k .

text: And it came to pass , when Jesus had ended these sayings , the people were astonished at his doctrine :
text2: IcI otI kashuwe ' puk pic Cisus kaokishkItot notI kItwunIn , nIshInape ' k okimamkate ' ntumakon ni okukie ' kwe ' wun .

text: For he taught them as one having authority , and not as the scribes .
text2: Nkot ke ' cne ' ntakwsIt okishI knomowan cowike ' ke ' cwa we ' npie ' ke ' cuk .

text: When he was come down from the mountain , great multitudes followed him .
text2: ICI kapie ' niscowie ' t e ' pkotniak mce ' sh maoce ' tincIn oki pmInashkakon

text: And , behold , there came a leper and worshipped him , saying , Lord , if thou wilt , thou canst make me clean .
text2: IcI PInI e ' pianIt we ' mkincIn e ' pie ' nume ' kitakot kItwak , Te ' pe ' nmin kishpIn sI ne ' nmin ktakshkIton e ' wipinakwin .

text: And Jesus put forth his hand , and touched him , saying , I will ; be thou clean . And immediately his leprosy was cleansed .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' ki shipnIce ' not e ' kitakInat kItwak , Nta ‘ wac ; kupinakwIs . IcI papuk e ' cI omukit e ' kipinianuk .

text: And Jesus saith unto him , See thou tell no man ; but go thy way , shew thyself to the priest , and offer the gift that Moses commanded , for a testimony unto them .
text2: IcI Cisus otI e ' kinat ; ke ' ko wIiI witmowakIn nInI macincI washian owawapte ' ‘ kiow ki me ' matmot , nInI icI mikwe ' n mikwe ' wun Mosus kanukwiIn iwcI ke ' ocI kuke ' ntumwat .

text: And when Jesus was entered into Capernaum , there came unto him a centurion , beseeching him ,
text2: Pic cI Cisus e ' kipiat shi Ke ' paniamuk , kipie ' e ' cIiIt , iukwan Kapte ' n , okipie ' matmukon .

text: And saying , Lord , my servant lieth at home sick of the palsy , grievously tormented .
text2: IcI kItwak , Te ' pe ' nmin mpumitakium shkIshIn e ' taian iakwnoke ' wak nie ' psawak kcIkwtuke ' ntumwak .

text: And Jesus saith unto him , I will come and heal him .
text2: CisuscI otI okinan , ipI nkupia nkawe ' ‘ ne ' se ' a .

text: The centurion answered and said , Lord , I am not worthy that thou shouldest come under my roof : but speak the word only , and my servant shall be healed .
text2: Iukwan Kapte ' n e ' kinkwe ' twat ipi okinan , Te ' pe ' nmin , contupite ' ntakwsIsi e ' wi pitke ' n e ' taian , te ' pnak kikiton , icI mpumitakaium ke ' cine ' se ' t .

text: For I am a man under authority , having soldiers under me : and I say to this man , Go , and he goeth ; and to another , Come , and he cometh ; and to my servant , Do this , and he doeth it .
text2: Nin e ' nIniwian , ntupe ' nmak shmakne ' shuk ; otI mtIna nInI shian , ie ' shiat , ipi minI nkot pian , ie ' piat , ipi mpumitakaium , otI totIn i e ' totuk .

text: When Jesus heard it , he marvelled , and said to them that followed , Verily I say unto you , I have not found so great faith , no , not in Israel .
text2: IcI Cisus kanotwat kimamkate ' ntum ipi okinan , ni kapie ' mnashkakocIn , We ' we ' nI KtInum , Con nkimkIsin kcIte ' pwe ' tatwun , co ke ' iapI , Isne ' iuk .

text: And I say unto you , That many shall come from the east and west , and shall sit down with Abraham , and Isaac , and Jacob , in the kingdom of heaven .
text2: Ipi otI ktInum , kumane ' k ke ' ocI piacuk we ' cmokuk , ipi we ' cpkIshmok , ipi okupie ' witpumawan ni E ' pIne ' e ' mIn , ipi AysIkIn , ipi Ce ' kapIn , shi okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok .

text: But the children of the kingdom shall be cast out into outer darkness : there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth .
text2: NIshcI kote ' we ' nicansumkocuk i okumauwun ksakcowe ' pnukaswuk e ' tshI kiskupkonianuk , e ' tnIte ' mok , ipi e ' tnwe ' iapte ' shnuk .

text: And Jesus said unto the centurion , Go thy way ; and as thou hast believed , so be it done unto thee . And his servant was healed in the selfsame hour .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kinat , ni Kapte ' nIn ; Wimacin , i e ' shte ' pwe ' tmIn ike ' nomkIt . IcI ni opumitakaimIn , pic e ' kine ' se ' nIt .

text: And when Jesus was come into Peter ' s house , he saw his wife ' s mother laid , and sick of a fever .
text2: IcI Cisus kapiat pituk Pitu e ' tat , okiwapman osukwsIsIn e ' shkIshnInIt , ipi e ' iakwnokanIt e ' psIsnIt .

text: And he touched her hand , and the fever left her : and she arose , and ministered unto them .
text2: IcI e ' kitaknat onIcik , icI i psIswun ; e ' kimacimkItInuk ; icI e ' kipsukwit ipi e ' kipie ' pmitakwat .

text: When the even was come , they brought unto him many that were possessed with devils : and he cast out the spirits with his word , and healed all that were sick :
text2: IcI e ' nmupkonianuk okipie ' nawan e ' ciInIt packakocIk mcImIne ' ton , icI e ' kisakicowe ' pnat ni mcImIne ' ton okion okikitowun ; ipi okine ' se ' an caye ' k iakwnokancIn .

text: That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet , saying , Himself took our infirmities , and bare our sicknesses .
text2: Iw ie ' i te ' pwe ' wun , kakItot Ise ' us Iacimot kIto ; Win okiw tapInumakwnan kshe ' shwusiwnunanIn , ipi okipmooton kiakwnokie ' wunInanIn .

text: Now when Jesus saw great multitudes about him , he gave commandment to depart unto the other side .
text2: IcI Cisus kawapmat ke ' cmaoce ' tinIt e ' cIiIt , Okinan , e ' wimacinIt ashwe ' iukwan .

text: And a certain scribe came , and said unto him , Master , I will follow thee whithersoever thou goest .
text2: IcI knot we ' npie ' ke ' t nInI kipie ' , ipi okinan , E ' kinomakIn , kupme ' nashkon , ke ' pashishian .

text: And Jesus saith unto him , The foxes have holes , and the birds of the air have nests ; but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head .
text2: IcI Cisus okinan , Wakwshe ' iuk otawankomwuk , ipi pne ' shiuk pe ' pamsacuk ototsanmik , nIshcI We ' kwIsmukot NInwun co otutosin wapuk kwIshmot .

text: And another of his disciples said unto him , Lord , suffer me first to go and bury my father .
text2: IcI minI nkot e ' knomowacIn otI okikon ; Te ' pe ' nmin , pkIte ' nmIshIn ne ' tum , e ' wishiaian , Nos e ' winko - ok .

text: But Jesus said unto him , Follow me ; and let the dead bury their dead .
text2: IcI Cisus otI e ' kinat , PmInashkoshIn , icI ne ' pot okInkowan ne ' poncIn .

text: And when he was entered into a ship , his disciples followed him .
text2: IcI kaposIt napkwanuk ke ' knomowacIn okipmnashkakon .

text: And , behold , there arose a great tempest in the sea , insomuch that the ship was covered with the waves : but he was asleep .
text2: IcI e ' ki kcInotuk , kcIkumik ; icI e ' kisisikIte ' pie ' uk i napkwan e ' makashkak ; wincI e ' ie ' npat .

text: And his disciples came to him , and awoke him , saying , Lord , save us : we perish .
text2: IcI ke ' knomowacIn e ' kipianIt ; ipi okipie ' toknukon kItwuk ; Te ' pe ' nmiak ke ' skonshInak , nwipnatsImIn .

text: And he saith unto them , Why are ye fearful , O ye of little faith ? Then he arose , and rebuked the winds and the sea ; and there was a great calm .
text2: IcI otI e ' kinat Taki we ' ckwtacie ' k O ! puke ' ci te ' pwe ' tume ' k ? IcI e ' kipsukwit ; ipi e ' kiknotuk i e ' notnunuk ipi i kcukum ; icI e ' kitokmupie ' suk .

text: But the men marvelled , saying , What manner of man is this , that even the winds and the sea obey him !
text2: IcI ki nInwuk , kimamkate ' ntumwuk kItwuk ; We ' ni nInIcI otI ; ke ' iapI e ' notuk , ipi kcukum , ote ' pwe ' takonIn .

text: And when he was come to the other side into the country of the Gergesenes , there met him two possessed with devils , coming out of the tombs , exceeding fierce , so that no man might pass by that way .
text2: IcI ipI kapiat ashwe ' iukwan otukimwak Kukisi nInwuk ; okinkwe ' shkakon , nish packakowacIn mcImIne ' ton ; e ' pie ' sakumnIt e ' cI nkokaswat , kcIn shiw onakwsInIt ; co shi wIiI nInI tanI pmIshie ' si .

text: And , behold , they cried out , saying , What have we to do with thee , Jesus , thou Son of God ? art thou come hither to torment us before the time ?
text2: IcI pInI e ' kinotakwsawat kItwuk ; We ' kwnicI watotonak , Cisus We ' kwIsmukwiIn Kshe ' mIne ' to , inI shiI e ' pian e ' wikwtuke ' ak e ' pwamshI piamkuk e ' picak .

text: And there was a good way off from them an herd of many swine feeding .
text2: IcI pnoc pme ' in , mce ' sh kokoshIn e ' wisnInIt .

text: So the devils besought him , saying , If thou cast us out , suffer us to go away into the herd of swine .
text2: IcI ni mcImIne ' ton okintotumakon otI kItwuk ; KishpIn sakicowe ' pne ' ak , ne ' nmIshnak e ' wi pic kaokIt pe ' mso ‘ ticIk mane ' cIk kokoshuk .

text: And he said unto them , Go . And when they were come out , they went into the herd of swine : and , behold , the whole herd of swine ran violently down a steep place into the sea , and perished in the waters .
text2: IcI otI e ' kinat , Shiak , icI kapie ' sakumwat kishie ' k shi pe ' msotincIn kokoshIn , icI pInI ni caye ' k pe ' msotincIn kokoshIn , e ' kinispItonIt e ' kishkitakiwnInuk , pic kcukumik , ipi e ' kipnatsawat , shi npik .

text: And they that kept them fled , and went their ways into the city , and told every thing , and what was befallen to the possessed of the devils .
text2: IcI ki kakawapmacIk e ' kiw shumwat ; ipi e ' kishiawat kcI otanuk , ipi okiactanawa cake ' ko , i kashowe ' pse ' nIt kapickakwcuk ni mIcImIne ' ton .

text: And , behold , the whole city came out to meet Jesus : and when they saw him , they besought him that he would depart out of their coasts .
text2: IcI pInI caye ' k kcI otanuk e ' kiw cupianut e ' kipie ' nkwe ' shkwawat ni CisusIn icI kawapmawat , okimatmawan , e ' wi nkoci shi anIt shi e ' ci iuwat .

text: And he entered into a ship , and passed over , and came into his own city .
text2: ICI e ' kiposIt napkwanuk e ' kitkumot , icI e ' kishiat oto kIc otanuk .

text: And , behold , they brought to him a man sick of the palsy , lying on a bed : and Jesus seeing their faith said unto the sick of the palsy ; Son , be of good cheer ; thy sins be forgiven thee .
text2: IcI pInI e ' kipie ' nawat nInI iakwnokancIn , ne ' nie ' psIncIn , e ' shkIshnInIt npakInuk ; icI Cisus e ' waptumwat , te ' pwe ' ne ' ntumwun ; otI okinan , ni iakwnokancIn ne ' nie ' psIncIn ; NkwIs mInIwankosIn ; kimiashowe ' psuwunIn kpone ' ntumon .

text: And , behold , certain of the scribes said within themselves , This man blasphemeth .
text2: IcI pInI , anIt we ' npie ' ke ' cIk nInwuk otI KikItwuk ; otI nInI ; pcIkikito .

text: And Jesus knowing their thoughts said , Wherefore think ye evil in your hearts ?
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kuke ' ntumwat otIshte ' wna ‘ wan otI kIto TInicI we ' cImcIshIte ' aie ' k kte ' ‘ iwak .

text: For whether is easier , to say , Thy sins be forgiven thee ; or to say , Arise , and walk ?
text2: WnsimI nI we ' npInIt e ' wikItok , kimiashuwe ' psiwunIn kupone ' ntumwun ; tanake ' psukwin , ipi pInose ' n .

text: But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins , ( then saith he to the sick of the palsy , ) Arise , take up thy bed , and go unto thine house .
text2: I ie ' i ke ' ocI kuke ' ntume ' k We ' kwIsmukot NInwun ote ' ion kshkIe ' osuwun shotI kik ; pone ' ntumake ' t , miashuwe ' psiwunIn icI otI e ' kinat , ni iakwnokancIn ne ' nie ' psIncIn ; Psukwin , otapInIn knupakIn , ipi e ' tanshian .

text: And he arose , and departed to his house .
text2: IcI e ' kipsukwit , e ' kishiat e ' cI otu ‘ wikwamIt .

text: But when the multitudes saw it , they marvelled , and glorified God , which had given such power unto men .
text2: IcI ki maoce ' ticIk kawaptumwat , kimamkate ' ntumwuk , ipi okiuwinwanawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton , e ' mnat kshkIe ' osuwun ni nInwun .

text: And as Jesus passed forth from thence , he saw a man , named Matthew , sitting at the receipt of custom : and he saith unto him , Follow me . And he arose , and followed him .
text2: IcI Cisus kanmamacit okiwapman nInI , Me ' to oshInkaswun , e ' cipitupInIt e ' cI maocIstowat shonia ; icI otI e ' kinat ; PmnashkaoIshIn . IcI e ' kipsukwit e ' kipmInashkawat .

text: And it came to pass , as Jesus sat at meat in the house , behold , many publicans and sinners came and sat down with him and his disciples .
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk Cisus e ' ie ' wisnIt wikwamuk , pInI , kipatie ' n win maocIcke ' nInwuk ; ipi me ' cIshowe ' pse ' cuk , e ' pie ' witpumkot , ipi ke ' knomowacIn .

text: And when the Pharisees saw it , they said unto his disciples , Why eateth your Master with publicans and sinners ?
text2: IcI ki Pe ' nIsiuk kawaptumwat otI okinawan , ni ke ' knomowacIn , tacI we ' cwitopmat ke ' knomakwie ' k ni maocIcke ' onInwun , ipi me ' iashowe ' psIncIn .

text: But when Jesus heard that , he said unto them , They that be whole need not a physician , but they that are sick .
text2: Pic cI Cisus kanotuk , otI okinan , Kime ' nopmatsacIk conatwaasik ; mtIno ki iakwnokacuk .

text: But go ye and learn what that meaneth , I will have mercy , and not sacrifice : for I am not come to call the righteous , but sinners to repentance .
text2: Wu kuke ' ntumok otI e ' kitomkuk nkishwe ' ncukI ; coin nkupitakwe ' si ; Coin piasi e ' wintomkwa me ' noshuwe ' psucIk ; mtIno me ' iashowe ' pse ' cIk ; e ' wi kisate ' ntuswat .

text: Then came to him the disciples of John , saying , Why do we and the Pharisees fast oft , but thy disciples fast not ?
text2: IcI e ' kipianIt Can ke ' knomowacIn ; kItwun ; TacI ninan , ipi ki Pe ' nIsiuk we ' cpwawisniak mce ' shuk ; kicI ke ' knomocIk coponwisnIsik .

text: And Jesus said unto them , Can the children of the bridechamber mourn , as long as the bridegroom is with them ? but the days will come , when the bridegroom shall be taken from them , and then shall they fast .
text2: IcI Cisus otI okinan ; Tashke ' ntumwakinI wakime ' cIk shi e ' cI wikmItwak , e ' pic iInIt ni we ' shkowiwunIt shi e ' piciInIt pama wikupie ' mkIt e ' kishkiwuk , ke ' co - otapnumwutwa we ' shkwiwut , iwcI ke ' cI ponwisnawat ,

text: No man putteth a piece of new cloth unto an old garment , for that which is put in to fill it up taketh from the garment , and the rent is made worse .
text2: Cowi wIiI nInI otItosin oshkupukwoian shi ke ' te ' kwune ' iakwnuk iwcI i katok kapuu ‘ kwuasok , icI i we ' tapnmukpnI shi ke ' te ' kwune ' iaknuk , icI wusimI manisikshkak .

text: Neither do men put new wine into old bottles : else the bottles break , and the wine runneth out , and the bottles perish : but they put new wine into new bottles , and both are preserved .
text2: CowikI nInwuk otItosinawa oshkI shomnapo ke ' te ' motiuk iw ke ' ocI piwkshkak nimotie ' n , icI i shomnapo e ' siksak ; ipi nimotie ' n e ' pnacak ; kishpIn cI towat oshkIshomnapo shi oshkamotiuk nune ' ish mnosnon .

text: While he spake these things unto them , behold , there came a certain ruler , and worshipped him , saying , My daughter is even now dead : but come and lay thy hand upon her , and she shall live .
text2: Me ' kwa cI otI e ' ie ' tshe ' tuk , pInI kipie ' wak nkot okuma okiw wucikwnutakon , otI okikon ; NtanIs kishInpo , pie ' takIn , iwcI kie ' cIpmatsIt .

text: And Jesus arose , and followed him , and so did his disciples .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kipsukwit okiwice ' wan , ipi nike ' knomowacIn .

text: And , behold , a woman , which was diseased with an issue of blood twelve years , came behind him , and touched the hem of his garment :
text2: IcI pInI , kwe ' e ' piat mcInapine ' wun apIcikanuk mskwI mtatso shItInish tsopon , shkwe ' iak kipie ' tnIsi , icI e ' kitaknumwat e ' shkwe ' ie ' knonInuk e ' kwut .

text: For she said within herself , If I may but touch his garment , I shall be whole .
text2: OtI cI kine ' ntuso , KishpIn te ' pnak taknumwuk e ' kwut nkumnopmatIs .

text: But Jesus turned him about , and when he saw her , he said , Daughter , be of good comfort ; thy faith hath made thee whole . And the woman was made whole from that hour .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kwe ' knowit , okiwapman , otI cI okinan ; NtanIs , Mnone ' ntIn , kite ' pwe ' tatwun kimnopmatsikon . IcI o kwe ' e ' kimnopimatsut kie ' nup .

text: And when Jesus came into the ruler ' s house , and saw the minstrels and the people making a noise ,
text2: IcI Cisus kapiat kanmupitike ' t , okuma e ' tat ; e ' kiwapmat nwata kwcIke ' ncIn ipi ni nIshInape ' n , e ' nanotaksInIt .

text: He said unto them , Give place : for the maid is not dead , but sleepeth . And they laughed him to scorn .
text2: IcI otI okinan , Me ' nwushkmok coinposi kikiak ; npe ' waksI . IwcI e ' ki papshI waoshInwawat .

text: But when the people were put forth , he went in , and took her by the hand , and the maid arose .
text2: Pic cI ki nIshInape ' k kasakite ' ntwa kipitike ' wak , icI e ' kiw otapInat e ' kiskIncInat , icI e ' kipsukwit kikiak .

text: And the fame hereof went abroad into all that land .
text2: KikicI winwackate ' nI kashIcke ' t , caye ' k otukimwak .

text: And when Jesus departed thence , two blind men followed him , crying , and saying , Thou Son of David , have mercy on us .
text2: Pic cI Cisus kanmamacit , nish ke ' kie ' pikwancIn nInwun okipmnashkakon kipie ' nanotakwsin , otI cI okikon ; We ' kwIsmukwiIn Te ' pIt , shuwe ' numIshInak .

text: And when he was come into the house , the blind men came to him : and Jesus saith unto them , Believe ye that I am able to do this ? They said unto him , Yea , Lord .
text2: Pic cI kapiat kapitike ' t wikwamuk ; kipinaskakon ni ke ' kie ' pikwancIn nInwun , Cisus cI otI okinan , Kite ' pwe ' tanawanI e ' wikshkItoian otI ? IcI otI e ' nawat , E ' ‘ Te ' pe ' nmiak .

text: Then touched he their eyes , saying , According to your faith be it unto you .
text2: IcI e ' kitakinumwat oshkishkonuk , otI cI kIto , E ' shte ' pwe ' tume ' k ikInomkIt .

text: And their eyes were opened ; and Jesus straitly charged them , saying , See that no man know it .
text2: Oshkishkowan cI kinsakshkInI , icI Cisus cI okiakwaman otI cI kanat , Ke ' ko ikwamsuk wIiI nInI e ' wipwakuke ' ntuk .

text: But they , when they were departed , spread abroad his fame in all that country .
text2: IcI winwa kamaciwat okiacimawan kashIcke ' unut caye ' k otukimwak .

text: As they went out , behold , they brought to him a dumb man possessed with a devil .
text2: Kan msakumwat cI pInI kipie ' twawan ke ' kie ' ptonIt nInI packakwnIt mIcImIne ' ton .

text: And when the devil was cast out , the dumb spake : and the multitudes marvelled , saying , It was never so seen in Israel .
text2: IcI kasaktInat ni mIcImIne ' ton ke ' iie ' pitok kin ukikito kimamkate ' ntumwuk cI ‘ kimaoce ' ticuk otI cI kikItwuk ; Cowika wapicukate ' snon otI Isniuk .

text: But the Pharisees said , He casteth out devils through the prince of the devils .
text2: OtIcI Pe ' nisiuk kikItwuk , Osakicowe ' pinan mIcImIne ' ton , opic okuman mIcImIne ' ton .

text: And Jesus went about all the cities and villages , teaching in their synagogues , and preaching the gospel of the kingdom , and healing every sickness and every disease among the people .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kishiat caye ' k kcI otanIn , ipi otane ' sIn e ' pmukinomake ' t nume ' okumkok ipi iactuk mnoacumowun , shiw okumauwunuk , ipi e ' ne ' se ' at iakwnokancIn , ipi cak e ' napine ' ncIn ni nIshInape ' n .

text: But when he saw the multitudes , he was moved with compassion on them , because they fainted , and were scattered abroad , as sheep having no shepherd .
text2: Pic cI kawapmat maoce ' tincIn , okishuwe ' nman osam e ' pike ' ie ' kwsInIt , ipi e ' swe ' shkanIt ke ' cwa mantanshIn , owIiI e ' pwakawapmukwat .

text: Then saith he unto his disciples , The harvest truly is plenteous , but the labourers are few ;
text2: OtI cI okinan ni ke ' knomowacIn ; MicIm mane ' , nIshcI makice ' wicuk pike ' ci she ' iwik .

text: Pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest , that he will send forth labourers into his harvest .
text2: Mumatmuk o Te ' pe ' ntuk i micum e ' winokanat wusimI makice ' wincIn ; shi otItshI nmaotInkanuk .

text: And when he had called unto him his twelve disciples , he gave them power against unclean spirits , to cast them out , and to heal all manner of sickness and all manner of disease .
text2: ICI kakishntomat ni mtatso shItInish ke ' knomowacIn okiminan kshkI ‘ e ' wsuwun e ' wisak cowe ' pnanIt , wanakwsIncIn mIne ' ton , ipi e ' wine ' se ' anIt , cak e ' shnakwuk iakwnoke ' wun , ipi cak e ' shnakwuk napIne ' wun .

text: Now the names of the twelve apostles are these ; The first , Simon , who is called Peter , and Andrew his brother ; James the son of Zebedee , and John his brother ;
text2: OtI cI e ' shnukaswat kimtatso shItInish ke ' knomowacuk ; Ne ' tum Sayimun e ' shnukasit Pitu , ipi E ' ntoiun wikane ' iIn , Ce ' ms kaokwIsmukot Se ' pitiIn ; ipi CanIn wikane ' iIn .

text: Philip , and Bartholomew ; Thomas , and Matthew the publican ; James the son of Alphaeus , and Lebbaeus , whose surname was Thaddaeus ;
text2: PInip , ipi Patanumio , Tamus , ipi Me ' to maocIcke ' t ; Ce ' ms kaokwIsmukot E ' mpiusIn , ipi Ne ' pius , iukwan ke ' i otInawan Se ' tius ;

text: Simon the Canaanite , and Judas Iscariot , who also betrayed him .
text2: Sayiman Ke ' ne ' nInI , ipi Cotus , Iske ' niat nie ' ni kapkItnat ni CisusIn .

text: These twelve Jesus sent forth , and commanded them , saying , Go not into the way of the Gentiles , and into any city of the Samaritans enter ye not :
text2: Kie ' ki mtatso shItInish Cisus kakatonacIn ; otI cI kanat ; ke ' ko shiake ' k , e ' ciuwat Me ' ikIscIk , ipi ke ' ko pitike ' ke ' k ototanwak Se ' me ' ne ' onInwuk .

text: But go rather to the lost sheep of the house of Israel .
text2: WusimI shiak e ' cInkIckaswat mantanshuk shi Isniuk otuwikwamuk .

text: And as ye go , preach , saying , The kingdom of heaven is at hand .
text2: IcI pmIshiaie ' k mukie ' kwe ' k otukItok : Pe ' shoc pie ' mkIt okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok .

text: Heal the sick , cleanse the lepers , raise the dead , cast out devils : freely ye have received , freely give .
text2: Ne ' se ' uk iakwnokacuk , pinakwuk we ' mkicuk , psukwitnuk ne ' pcuk , sakicowe ' pnuk mcImIne ' tok ; we ' npIsh kitotapnanawa , we ' npIsh mikwe ' k .

text: Provide neither gold , nor silver , nor brass in your purses ,
text2: Ke ' ko maocIstoke ' k , osaw shonia ; tanake ' we ' ctI shonia ; tanake ' osawapuk shi kpic numkwanwak ;

text: Nor scrip for your journey , neither two coats , neither shoes , nor yet staves : for the workman is worthy of his meat .
text2: Ke ' kokI nwupke ' kon , coke ' nish - piskumwaknIn , coke ' mkIsnIn , coke ' iaptuowunIn ; pite ' ntakwsI makice ' wit nInI e ' wiwisnIt .

text: And into whatsoever city or town ye shall enter , inquire who in it is worthy ; and there abide till ye go thence .
text2: Pic pitike ' ie ' k kcI otanuk , tanake ' otane ' suk natake ' k we ' ni cI shi e ' pite ' ntakwsut ; shiw iuk , pama shi ocumaci ie ' k .

text: And when ye come into an house , salute it .
text2: Pic cI pitike ' ie ' k shi wikwamuk ; numkawuk .

text: And if the house be worthy , let your peace come upon it : but if it be not worthy , let your peace return to you .
