text2: KishpIn cI i wikwam pite ' ntakwuk nocma kushowe ' ncuke ' onawa kupie ' mkIt , shi kishpIn cI pwapite ' ntakwuk nocIma kushowe ' ncuke ' onawa ne ' iap kotIskonawa .

text: And whosoever shall not receive you , nor hear your words , when ye depart out of that house or city , shake off the dust of your feet .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk cI ke ' pwa pitike ' nkoie ' k , ipi ke ' pwapsItakwie ' k , pic shiw ocI sakume ' k shi wikwamuk , tanake ' kcI otanuk papiwshkumok ne ' kwuke ' , shi ksItiwak .

text: Verily I say unto you , It shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment , than for that city .
text2: We ' we ' nI kwiuk ktInum ; Nowuc kawe ' npe ' nsik e ' pmukiwuk shi Satum , ipi Komana ; pic tpakwnuke ' kishkuk , icI i ke ' showe ' puk kcI otan .

text: Behold , I send you forth as sheep in the midst of wolves : be ye therefore wise as serpents , and harmless as doves .
text2: PInI kukukatonum , ke ' cwa mantanshuk me ' kwe ' nawe ' nI ; mwoe ' k ; nIshcI shumpwakak ke ' cwa mInitok , ipi shumnoshuwe ' psuk ke ' cwa mIne ' to mimik .

text: But beware of men : for they will deliver you up to the councils , and they will scourge you in their synagogues ;
text2: NIshcI kawapmIk nInwuk kupkItnIkwak e ' tshI kikitowat , ipi kupsItie ' kowak shiw otI nume ' okumkomwak .

text: And ye shall be brought before governors and kings for my sake , for a testimony against them and the Gentiles .
text2: IcI ipI ke ' aonukom e ' nasmupwat okumak , ipi kcI okumak nin ke ' ocItotakoie ' k , iwcI ke ' ocI kuke ' ntumwat win wa , ipi Me ' ikIscIk .

text: But when they deliver you up , take no thought how or what ye shall speak : for it shall be given you in that same hour what ye shall speak .
text2: Pic cI pie ' nkoie ' k , ke ' ko nakituwe ' ntuke ' k wakItie ' k ; kuminkomsI pic , wakItie ' k ,

text: For it is not ye that speak , but the Spirit of your Father which speaketh in you .
text2: Cowi kinwa kukikitosim , OcipamIn Koswa kukikitotmakowa .

text: And the brother shall deliver up the brother to death , and the father the child : and the children shall rise up against their parents , and cause them to be put to death .
text2: Wie ' wikane ' iIt okupkItnan wikane ' iIn , e ' winsIckasnIt , ipi we ' osmIt onicansun , ipi we ' nicansumcIk okupatamawan omIsotanwan iwcI ke ' ocI nsIckasnIt .

text: And ye shall be hated of all men for my name ' s sake : but he that endureth to the end shall be saved .
text2: KIshi ke ' nmukowak caknInwuk , ninke ' ocI ne ' nmukoie ' k ; wincI ke ' mnoshIcke ' t pIne ' kuke ' skona .

text: But when they persecute you in this city , flee ye into another : for verily I say unto you , Ye shall not have gone over the cities of Israel , till the Son of man be come .
text2: Pic cI kwtukukoie ' k otI kcI otanuk , pe ' kanuk nInshumok , We ' we ' nI KitInum , Coki cak shkIsinawan otanIn e ' te ' k Isniuk e ' pwamshupiat We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: The disciple is not above his master , nor the servant above his lord .
text2: Ke ' knomowIt cowi pite ' ntakwsIsi , wusimI ni te ' pe ' nmukwocIn , cowoke ' pmitake ' , wusimI pite ' ntakwsIsi , icI ni te ' pe ' nmukwocIn .

text: It is enough for the disciple that he be as his master , and the servant as his lord . If they have called the master of the house Beelzebub , how much more shall they call them of his household ?
text2: TamnoiumkIt ke ' knomowut , icI e ' wi ie ' i pic showe ' psIt ni ke ' knomakwcIn , ipi ke ' win , pmitaka , ke ' cwa ni te ' pe ' nmukwocIn ; KishpIn cI shInkanawat te ' pe ' ntumnIt iw wikwam , Pie ' nsipup , tInicI wusimI ke ' shInkanawat we ' tu wikwamnIncIn .

text: Fear them not therefore : for there is nothing covered , that shall not be revealed ; and hid , that shall not be known .
text2: Ke ' ko kwsake ' kon ; cowi ke ' ko matkokate ' snon ke ' pwawapcukate ' k , coke ' kukIckate ' snon ke ' pwakuke ' ncukate ' k .

text: What I tell you in darkness , that speak ye in light : and what ye hear in the ear , that preach ye upon the housetops .
text2: Watumonkon e ' kiskupkoniak , iai ke ' kItie ' k shi e ' wase ' iak ; ipi nwatume ' k kto ‘ kak i ie ' ike ' mnwactume ' k wikwamuk kwItupuk .

text: And fear not them which kill the body , but are not able to kill the soul : but rather fear him which is able to destroy both soul and body in hell .
text2: Ke ' kowi kwsake ' k , ke ' n - towat kiiIwawa ianwutocuk e ' winsawat kcipamwan ; wusimI ktaksawa ke ' shkitot e ' wipnacat cipamwan , ipi kiiwawan mcIshote ' k .

text: Are not two sparrows sold for a farthing ? and one of them shall not fall on the ground without your Father .
text2: ConI nish shashawunupie ' iuk pite ' ntakwsik nkot shomanke ' ? coIn nkot pukshInsi shi ne ' kwukik pwane ' nmat Koswa .

text: But the very hairs of your head are all numbered .
text2: Ca ‘ kinsIsiwan ktupiwak e ' tsuk kIckate ' ton .

text: Fear ye not therefore , ye are of more value than many sparrows .
text2: Ke ' kowi kwtacke ' kon , wusimI ktupite ' ntakwsIm iwcI mane ' cuk shashawunupie ' iuk .

text: Whosoever therefore shall confess me before men , him will I confess also before my Father which is in heaven .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk cI ke ' mnoacimIt e ' nasmupwat , nInwuk , winke ' nkumnoacima e ' nasmupnIt NosIn shpumuk e ' iIt kishkok .

text: But whosoever shall deny me before men , him will I also deny before my Father which is in heaven .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk cI ke ' ia kwne ' twukwe ' n e ' nasmupnIt nInwun , winke ' nkiiakwne ' twa e ' nasmupnIt NosIn shpumuk e ' iIt kishkok .

text: Think not that I am come to send peace on earth : I came not to send peace , but a sword .
text2: Ke ' kokwi ne ' nmIshi ke ' kon , we ' cpia ian opie ' ton mnone ' nta ‘ wun shi kik , cosowin ntoc piasi e ' wipkItnuman mnone ' ntawun ; kishko ‘ wun ie ' k mtIno .

text: For I am come to set a man at variance against his father , and the daughter against her mother , and the daughter in law against her mother in law .
text2: Nin we ' cpiaian pie ' pkIt numwa nInI ke ' ocI shike ' nmat OsIn , ipi ke ' win we ' tansumIt okie ' iIn , ipi ke ' win nakInukwe ' osukwsusIn .

text: And a man ' s foes shall be they of his own household .
text2: Ipi nInI shake ' n mukwocIn te ' pe ' nwI wine ' tat e ' inIncIn .

text: He that loveth father or mother more than me is not worthy of me : and he that loveth son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me .
text2: WusimI cI te ' panat OsIn , tanake ' okie ' iIn wusimI Nin copite ' ntakwsIsi , icI Nin kishpIn kI tpanat okwIsIn , tanake ' otansIn wusimI Nin copite ' ntakwsIsi icI Nin , e ' wishwe ' nmuk .

text: And he that taketh not his cross , and followeth after me , is not worthy of me .
text2: IcI win ke ' pwa otapnat otashte ' iatIkomIn , ipi mnashkowut copite ' ntakwsIsi Nin e ' wishwe ' nmuk .

text: He that findeth his life shall lose it : and he that loseth his life for my sake shall find it .
text2: Win me ' kuk opumatsawun okInkIton ; win ke ' Nin ke ' ocI nkItot opumatsiwun okumkan .

text: He that receiveth you receiveth me , and he that receiveth me receiveth him that sent me .
text2: Win patke ' nkoie ' k mpitke ' nuk ; winke ' patike ' nut opitike ' nan nwakashIt .

text: He that receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet shall receive a prophet ' s reward ; and he that receiveth a righteous man in the name of a righteous man shall receive a righteous man ' s reward .
text2: Win patike ' nat iacimoncIn shi e ' shnukasnIt iacimot okuminkon nakanacimoncIn omikwe ' wIn ; win patike ' nat me ' noshuwe ' psIt nInI , otInoswunuk me ' noshuwe ' psIt nInI , okuminkon me ' noshuwe ' psIt nInI omikwe ' wIn .

text: And whosoever shall give to drink unto one of these little ones a cup of cold water only in the name of a disciple , verily I say unto you , he shall in no wise lose his reward .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' minat e ' wimnukwe ' nIt nkot notI e ' kacinIncIn , mnukwackIn , te ' kapokuk mpish mtIno shi otInoswunuk oke ' knomomIt ; we ' we ' nI KtInum ; cookInkItosin iw omikwe ' wun .

text: And it came to pass , when Jesus had made an end of commanding his twelve disciples , he departed thence to teach and to preach in their cities .
text2: OTI kishuwe ' put Cisus kapon kie ' kmat ni mtatso shItnish ke ' knomowacIn , kiwcI maci e ' kipaknomake ' t , ipi e ' ki kie ' kwe ' t kcI ototanwak .

text: Now when John had heard in the prison the works of Christ , he sent two of his disciples ,
text2: IcI Can kanotake ' t katshIkpakot omikice ' wiwun ni KnaystIn ; okikatonan nish ni ke ' knomowacIn .

text: And said unto him , Art thou he that should come , or do we look for another ?
text2: OtI cI okinan , Kin nI wapian tanake ' , knItwapmamIn pe ' kansIt .

text: Jesus answered and said unto them , Go and shew John again those things which ye do hear and see :
text2: Cisus cI Okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan Kiwe ' k , ipi wukInomak Can minI notI nwatme ' k , ipi waptume ' k .

text: The blind receive their sight , and the lame walk , the lepers are cleansed , and the deaf hear , the dead are raised up , and the poor have the gospel preached to them .
text2: Ke ' kie ' pikwacIk ntawapwuk , ipi ne ' nie ' pse ' cIk pmose ' k , ipi we ' mkicIk pinakwsik ipi ke ' kie ' pshacIk notake ' k , ne ' pcIk pusukwitnukaswuk , ipi ke ' tmakse ' cIk MnoacimowIn kie ' kmak .

text: And blessed is he , whosoever shall not be offended in me .
text2: Shuwe ' ntakwsI win we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' pwanshke ' nmIt Nin .

text: And as they departed , Jesus began to say unto the multitudes concerning John , What went ye out into the wilderness to see ? A reed shaken with the wind ?
text2: IcI pic e ' nImacinIt Cisus okiwe ' p witmowan ni maoce ' tincIn e ' kitshumat CanIn We ' kwonicI kaocishiaie ' k no ‘ wmtukwakik e ' wiwaptume ' k ? NasaknIshk e ' nanimasuk ?

text: But what went ye out for to see ? A man clothed in soft raiment ? behold , they that wear soft clothing are in kings ' houses .
text2: We ' kwonicI kaocIshiiaie ' k e ' wiwapme ' k ? NInI nI e ' piskonie ' t we ' wunItnuk paskukate ' kIn ? PInI KiwcI we ' onItnuk paskukuk kiie ' ki e ' icIk okumak wikwamuk .

text: But what went ye out for to see ? A prophet ? yea , I say unto you , and more than a prophet .
text2: We ' kwonicI kaocI shian e ' wiwapme ' k ? Nakanacimot nI ? E ' , iwcI KtInum , wusimI pite ' ntakwsI iwcI nakanacimot .

text: For this is he , of whom it is written , Behold , I send my messenger before thy face , which shall prepare thy way before thee .
text2: IwsI o nakanacmIt we ' npie ' kate ' k , PInI ninokana nmIshnowe ' m nikan e ' nasmupiIn okInowshIton , wanmIshian nikan .

text: Verily I say unto you , Among them that are born of women there hath not risen a greater than John the Baptist : notwithstanding he that is least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he .
text2: We ' we ' nI KtInum , e ' tshowat nakukwcukwe ' n cowi wIiI pie ' si wusimI pite ' ntakwsIsi , e ' pite ' ntakwsIt icI o , Can Ke ' ctapie ' nwe ' t , win suo mamokaciIt shi otukumauwunuk shpumuk , wusimI pite ' ntakwsI icI win .

text: And from the days of John the Baptist until now the kingdom of heaven suffereth violence , and the violent take it by force .
text2: E ' wshkawe ' pkie ' kwe ' t Can , Ke ' ctapie ' nwe ' t nash cI nkom , okumauwun , shpumuk kwtuke ' ntumwuk ; ipi cIki kwe ' tuke ' ntum owe ' cIk kwtwe ' ototapnan .

text: For all the prophets and the law prophesied until John .
text2: Caye ' k sI nakanacimocuk , ipi tpakwnuke ' wun ki nikanacIkate ' nash Can .

text: And if ye will receive it , this is Elias , which was for to come .
text2: IcI kishpIn wiotapne ' me ' k iukwansuwi otI Inaye ' s wapiapIt .

text: He that hath ears to hear , let him hear .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk we ' to ‘ kakwe ' n e ' winotuk , nocma oke ' notan .

text: But whereunto shall I liken this generation ? It is like unto children sitting in the markets , and calling unto their fellows ,
text2: TInicI ke ' ne ' nmukwa kotI iaianke ' pmatse ' cIk ? Ke ' cwasIshIna pInoce ' iuk e ' cipitupwat shi e ' tshItatuk , e ' ntomawat wikanwan .

text: And saying , We have piped unto you , and ye have not danced ; we have mourned unto you , and ye have not lamented .
text2: OtI cI e ' nawat , anwu ninan nkipukwe ' mIn , cocI kinimItisim ; anwukI ninan kimwuminInmIn cocukI kikitamaktakwsI sim .

text: For John came neither eating nor drinking , and they say , He hath a devil .
text2: Can kapiat co kiwisnIsi , ipi cokimnukwe ' si , icI otI kikItwuk ; Opic kakon mIcImIne ' ton .

text: The Son of man came eating and drinking , and they say , Behold a man gluttonous , and a winebibber , a friend of publicans and sinners . But wisdom is justified of her children .
text2: We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kipie ' wisnI , ipi kimnukwe ' , otI cI e ' nawat , PInI , nInI ne ' patsIt , ipi shomnapo ne ' tamnukwe ' t , ipi we ' wikanmacIn maocIckI onInwun , ipi ke ' kie ' patsIncIn . KicI we ' nicansun kowacIk , i npwakawIn , we ' we ' nI shIcke ' k otIne ' nmawan .

text: Then began he to upbraid the cities wherein most of his mighty works were done , because they repented not :
text2: IcI e ' we ' p kcIcshItuk ni kcI otanIn katshI mataw nukmuksIt kanInkie ' t osam e ' pwakisate ' ntusnIt .

text: Woe unto thee , Chorazin ! woe unto thee , Bethsaida ! for if the mighty works , which were done in you , had been done in Tyre and Sidon , they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes .
text2: Kokwansukumuk kin KanasIn , Kokwansukumuk , kin Pe ' tse ' te ' , kishpIn ke ' cne ' ntakwuk mikce ' wiwunIn kaoshIckate ' k kinwa oshIckate ' kpIn , iukwanuk , Taie ' n , ipi Saitan , pnowi winwa takikisate ' ntumwuk , pic , mcIshkumtaknuk ipi pkwikik .

text: But I say unto you , It shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the day of judgment , than for you .
text2: OtI cI KtInum wusimI kuwunIt , shi Taie ' n , ipi Saitan , pic tupakwnuke ' kishkuk , icI i kinwa ke ' showe ' psie ' k .

text: And thou , Capernaum , which art exalted unto heaven , shalt be brought down to hell : for if the mighty works , which have been done in thee , had been done in Sodom , it would have remained until this day .
text2: Ipi KinsI Ke ' paniam , kakukwitnukasiIn shpumuk , minI kupie ' niswunko namkumuk ; kishpIn ke ' cne ' ntakwuk mikce ' wiwun kaoshIc kate ' k , kin shiw oshIckate ' kpIn shi Satamuk ke ' iapI takite ' mkIt nkom otI e ' kishkiwuk .

text: But I say unto you , That it shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of judgment , than for thee .
text2: OtIsI KtInum , wusimI kuwunIt otukim - Satam , pic tupakwnuke ' okishkuk , icI kin .

text: At that time Jesus answered and said , I thank thee , O Father , Lord of heaven and earth , because thou hast hid these things from the wise and prudent , and hast revealed them unto babes .
text2: IwcI pic Cisus e ' kinkwe ' take ' t , otI kikito , We ' we ' nI ktInIn O Nose ' ; Te ' pe ' ntumIn shpumuk ipi kI , osam notI , e ' kIton , ktIshcIke ' onIn kotI ne ' pwakawe ' ntukuk , ipi me ' nototkuk , icI e ' kiknomotwa pInoce ' iuk .

text: Even so , Father : for so it seemed good in thy sight .
text2: IwsI Nose ' , kikishmnwaptansI , e ' shwunuk .

text: All things are delivered unto me of my Father : and no man knoweth the Son , but the Father ; neither knoweth any man the Father , save the Son , and he to whomsoever the Son will reveal him .
text2: CaksI ke ' ko npukitInmak Nos , cocI wIiI , nInI okuke ' nmasin , We ' kwIsmumcIn mtIno , We ' osIt , cowike ' wIiI , nInI kuke ' nmasin , ni We ' osmImcIn mtIno We ' kwIsmIt icI mtIno otI we ' kwe ' nshutuk We ' kwIsmIt ke ' waptuakwe ' n .

text: Come unto me , all ye that labour and are heavy laden , and I will give you rest .
text2: Pie ' naskawshuk caye ' k kinwa naskate ' ntume ' k ipi pwawune ' ie ' k kuminumcI nwashmowIn .

text: Take my yoke upon you , and learn of me ; for I am meek and lowly in heart : and ye shall find rest unto your souls .
text2: OtapInImok napkumwakun kinwa e ' wike ' nmie ' k e ' pic , pwakce ' ne ' ntuman niia ‘ w ipi e ' shkacwe ' ntusian nte ' ik , kumkanawacI wacI nwashmoat kcipamwak .

text: For my yoke is easy , and my burden is light .
text2: NapkumwakIn sI we ' npe ' nIt , ipi nwiwshawun pukiaiIn .

text: At that time Jesus went on the sabbath day through the corn ; and his disciples were an hungred , and began to pluck the ears of corn , and to eat .
text2: IW cI pic , Cisus e ' kinmamacit e ' nume ' kishkItInuk , e ' nmItkumshkuk , pukwe ' shkIn , icI ni ke ' knomowacIn pmupkIte ' n iwcI e ' pmI we ' pcishpItowat , pukwe ' shkIn , ipi e ' micwat .

text: But when the Pharisees saw it , they said unto him , Behold , thy disciples do that which is not lawful to do upon the sabbath day .
text2: Pic , cI Pe ' nIsiuk , kawaptumat , otI otInawan , pInI , e ' knomocuk , consItum totsik e ' shIcke ' wat , e ' nume ' kishkuk ,

text: But he said unto them , Have ye not read what David did , when he was an hungred , and they that were with him ;
text2: OtI cI okinan , ConI kiwaptusinawa , shiw msInukinuk , Te ' pIt katotuk , e ' kipkIte ' t , ipi ni kapmIwice ' okocIn .

text: How he entered into the house of God , and did eat the shewbread , which was not lawful for him to eat , neither for them which were with him , but only for the priests ?
text2: KashInmupitike ' t , Kshe ' mIne ' to O Wikwamuk , e ' kimicIt , wapicukate ' k pukwe ' shkIn , cowi kiw wunsInI win , e ' wimicIt ke ' iapI ni kapmIwice ' okocIn , mtIno winwaki me ' matmocuk .

text: Or have ye not read in the law , how that on the sabbath days the priests in the temple profane the sabbath , and are blameless ?
text2: ConI kiwaptIsinawa shi tpakwnuke ' wunuk shiwsI , e ' nume ' kishkuk , kiw me ' matmocuk onInwuk iukwanuk nume ' okumkok , e ' kipnactowat e ' nume ' kishkItnuk , ipi cocI kimiane ' ntakwsusik ?

text: But I say unto you , That in this place is one greater than the temple .
text2: OtI cI KtInum , wusimI shotI nkot , kcIpite ' ntakwsI icI i , Nume ' okumuk .

text: But if ye had known what this meaneth , I will have mercy , and not sacrifice , ye would not have condemned the guiltless .
text2: KishpIn sI , otI kike ' ntume ' kopIn , otI we ' ckitomkuk ; Nin , nke ' ion shuwe ' ntu ‘ wun ; cowi i e ' wisku ‘ omoat ; cowike ' tapatamasiwak , pwamiashuwe ' psucIk .

text: For the Son of man is Lord even of the sabbath day .
text2: We ' kwIsmukot NInwun ke ' iapI , Te ' pe ' ntuk i e ' nume ' kishkuk ,

text: And when he was departed thence , he went into their synagogue :
text2: IcI pic kanmamacit e ' kinmupitke ' t otI nume ' okumkomwak ,

text: And , behold , there was a man which had his hand withered . And they asked him , saying , Is it lawful to heal on the sabbath days ? that they might accuse him .
text2: IcI pInI nInI e ' ionIt , e ' nponcanIt , icI e ' kinatawat , otI kItwuk , conItawunsInon e ' wi e ' wine ' se ' e ' t , e ' nume ' kishkuk ? E ' wipatamawat .

text: And he said unto them , What man shall there be among you , that shall have one sheep , and if it fall into a pit on the sabbath day , will he not lay hold on it , and lift it out ?
text2: IcI otI e ' kinat ; We ' nicI nInI shotI e ' tshie ' k ke ' pme ' iIt , e ' iwat , nkot mantanshIn : kishpIn , pmukoc nInIt e ' wankate ' nuk e ' nume ' kishkItnuk , conI otamackonasin , ipi otakwitnasin .

text: How much then is a man better than a sheep ? Wherefore it is lawful to do well on the sabbath days .
text2: TInicItso wusimI onInI e ' pite ' ntakwsIt , icI o mantanIsh ? TInicI me ' noshuwe ' pIt sI , otI e ' shIcke ' k e ' nume ' kishkuk .

text: Then saith he to the man , Stretch forth thine hand . And he stretched it forth ; and it was restored whole , like as the other .
text2: IcI otI e ' kinat , ni nInI , ShipinIce ' non , icI e ' kishipnIce ' not , icI kashIne ' se ' t , ke ' cwa inkot , e ' shnakwtunuk .

text: Then the Pharisees went out , and held a council against him , how they might destroy him .
text2: Iw cI Pe ' nisiuk e ' kisakumwat , e ' ki wutshumawat ; washIpnacawat .

text: But when Jesus knew it , he withdrew himself from thence : and great multitudes followed him , and he healed them all ;
text2: Pic cI Cisus kake ' ntuk , shiw kipie ' ocImaci , icI maoce ' tincIn okipmInashkakon , icI e ' kine ' se ' at , caye ' k .

text: And charged them that they should not make him known :
text2: IcI okiiakwaman e ' wipwa wIiI iacmukot .

text: That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet , saying ,
text2: OtI ie ' i tate ' pwe ' wunuwuk , iukwan kakItot Ise ' us nakanacimot otI kItwak ;

text: Behold my servant , whom I have chosen ; my beloved , in whom my soul is well pleased : I will put my spirit upon him , and he shall shew judgment to the Gentiles .
text2: PInI , mpumitakam nin kwae ' napmuk , te ' panuk shi o Ncipam ke ' cmnwe ' ntuk ; nkupikItnumwa ncipamIn , iwcI okuknomowan npwakawIn ni Me ' taosIncIn .

text: He shall not strive , nor cry ; neither shall any man hear his voice in the streets .
text2: Cowike ' kauwawikwsoke ' si coke ' kawishkwe ' we ' ksIsi , cowike ' wIiI nInIwun oke ' notakwsin i onotakwsIwun shi otanmie ' we ' n .

text: A bruised reed shall he not break , and smoking flax shall he not quench , till he send forth judgment unto victory .
text2: Shashak shkanuk nasaknIshk co okupokptosin , ipi pe ' kwe ' ne ' nuk sukipian cooke ' iate ' ‘ sin , pama npwakawun nshiw tomkuk .

text: And in his name shall the Gentiles trust .
text2: IcI otIshInukaswun ke ' pe ' nmowat Mataose ' cIk .

text: Then was brought unto him one possessed with a devil , blind , and dumb : and he healed him , insomuch that the blind and dumb both spake and saw .
text2: Kipie ' twa nkot iukwanIn packakwnIt MIcIme ' ton , ke ' kie ' pikwat , ipi ke ' kie ' pitok , icI e ' kine ' se ' at , icI ke ' kie ' pikwat ; ipi ke ' kie ' pitok , ne ' ish ki - kikito , ipi kintawapI .

text: And all the people were amazed , and said , Is not this the son of David ?
text2: IcI caye ' k nishInape ' k kimamkate ' ntumwuk , otI cI kikItwut ; ConI wiotI we ' kwIsmukot iukwanIn Te ' pItun ?

text: But when the Pharisees heard it , they said , This fellow doth not cast out devils , but by Beelzebub the prince of the devils .
text2: Pic cI otI Pe ' nisiuk kanotmoat , otI kItwuk , Cosuwi otI nInI otasakcuwe ' pnasin mIcImIne ' ton , nutmakot se ' ie ' k Pie ' nsipapun okuma mIcImIne ' ton .

text: And Jesus knew their thoughts , and said unto them , Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation ; and every city or house divided against itself shall not stand :
text2: IcI Cisus kike ' ntumwan e ' shte ' anIt , icI , otI okinan ; Cak okumawIn , kwe ' knowitatsomkuk okipie ' tonawa e ' wipnacak , ipi cak kcI - otan tanake ' wikwam kwe ' knowitatsomkuk coin knipwimkIsnon .

text: And if Satan cast out Satan , he is divided against himself ; how shall then his kingdom stand ?
text2: KishpIncI mIcImIne ' ton sakcuwe ' pnat mIcImIne ' ton kwe ' knowitatso tInicI ke ' shuwishkukapwimkItnuk i otokmauwun .

text: And if I by Beelzebub cast out devils , by whom do your children cast them out ? therefore they shall be your judges .
text2: KishpIn cI Nin Pie ' nsipup natmowIt sakicuwe ' pInukwa mIcImIne ' tok we ' nicI natmakwat knicansowak , e ' wisakcuwe ' pnawat , KiiwsIie ' ki ke ' tpakwnukwie ' k .

text: But if I cast out devils by the Spirit of God , then the kingdom of God is come unto you .
text2: KishpIn su Nin Ke ' shmIne ' to ocipamIn sakicuwe ' pnukwa mIcImIne ' tok ; iwsI e ' wtIskoie ' k Kshe ' mIne ' to otokumauwun .

text: Or else how can one enter into a strong man ' s house , and spoil his goods , except he first bind the strong man ? and then he will spoil his house .
text2: TInicI ashukshkItot wIiI e ' wipitike ' t washkIsIt nInI , otI wikwamuk e ' winactot otI nkackIn ; ne ' tumse ' ie ' k tkopnat , ni washkIsnIncIn nInI ? icI mcupshuk tacIpnactawat iukwan i wikwamnInIn .

text: He that is not with me is against me ; and he that gathereth not with me scattereth abroad .
text2: Winsu o pwapmawice ' wut nme ' iane ' nmuk ; pwawitokwutkI e ' maotIn ke ' ian otuswe ' we ' pnan .

text: Wherefore I say unto you , All manner of sin and blasphemy shall be forgiven unto men : but the blasphemy against the Holy Ghost shall not be forgiven unto men .
text2: OtI sI ktInum , Cak e ' shnakwuk miashuwe ' psiwun , ipi miashkikitowun kupone ' ntumwak nInwuk ; OtI ie ' k mIcIkikitowun ke ' shumawat Kshe ' mIne ' to ocipamIn i ie ' k co kupone ' ntumwasik nInwuk .

text: And whosoever speaketh a word against the Son of man , it shall be forgiven him : but whosoever speaketh against the Holy Ghost , it shall not be forgiven him , neither in this world , neither in the world to come .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' mcIcshImat We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kupone ' ntumwa win ; we ' kwe ' ntuk mIcIkikitowun ke ' nat Ke ' shmIne ' to ocipamIn cokupone ' ntumwasi win coi shotI kik , ipi kishkwakiwuk .

text: Either make the tree good , and his fruit good ; or else make the tree corrupt , and his fruit corrupt : for the tree is known by his fruit .
text2: Tanake ' ktaoshaawa mtuk e ' wiwunsIt , ipi e ' wiwuntInuk omicImowun , tanake ' ktaosha ‘ awa e ' wi micum tukowIt , ipi e ' wi micImicmawIt , i mtuk we ' ckake ' ncukate ' k omicmowun .

text: O generation of vipers , how can ye , being evil , speak good things ? for out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaketh .
text2: O ! me ' ntoie ' k iaiankie ' pmatsIie ' k tInicI ke ' shI kshkItoie ' k e ' miashowe ' psie ' k e ' wimnotshItme ' k ke ' ko ? E ' shmoshkIne ' suk ote ' ima iw otonima e ' shkikitomkuk .

text: A good man out of the good treasure of the heart bringeth forth good things : and an evil man out of the evil treasure bringeth forth evil things .
text2: Ne ' pwakat nInI we ' onItuk shIte ' ‘ e ' ‘ pie ' mkItnukI ke ' ko , we ' onItnuk , WincIke ' me ' cshowe ' psIt nInI , winke ' mIcIshIte ' e ' wun pie ' mkItnI mIciukwanI ke ' ko .

text: But I say unto you , That every idle word that men shall speak , they shall give account thereof in the day of judgment .
text2: OtI cI ktInum cak mIcIkikitowIn nInwuk , ke ' kItwat okInkwe ' tanawa upic tpakwnuke ' okishkuk .

text: For by thy words thou shalt be justified , and by thy words thou shalt be condemned .
text2: Iw sI ni kikitonIn ke ' ocI mnone ' ntakwsin icI ke ' niw kikitonIn iw ie ' ike ' ocI ianwe ' ntakwsin .

text: Then certain of the scribes and of the Pharisees answered , saying , Master , we would see a sign from thee .
text2: KiwcI anIt we ' npie ' ke ' cuk , ipi Pe ' nisiuk okinkwe ' twawan kItwuk , Ke ' knomoiak ninan kwshukI nwiwaptamIn kmataoshuwe ' psiwun kin .

text: But he answered and said unto them , An evil and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign ; and there shall no sign be given to it , but the sign of the prophet Jonas :
text2: Okinkwe ' twan , ipi otI kanat , miashowe ' psIt , ipi waonIshkaiwIt iaianke ' pmatse ' cuk pe ' pantone ' ukuk e ' wiwaptumwat mataoshuwe ' psowun ; cowikI mataoshuwe ' psowun wiminasik , mtIno omataoshuwe ' psowun iukwan nakanacimot Cone ' s .

text: For as Jonas was three days and three nights in the whale ' s belly ; so shall the Son of man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth .
text2: IukwansI Cone ' s kiiuwak nsokishuk , ipi nsotpuk , kcIkikos w ‘ shukinuk winsI ke ' o We ' kwIsmukot NInwun ke ' iIwak nsokishuk ipi nsotpuk e ' ote ' imkItnuk shi kik .

text: The men of Nineveh shall rise in judgment with this generation , and shall condemn it : because they repented at the preaching of Jonas ; and , behold , a greater than Jonas is here .
text2: Kiw e ' icIk NInIpiuk okuwic psukwimawan notI ianiankie ' pmatsIncIn pic tpakwnItwa oke ' ianwe ' nmawan - cI osam e ' kikisate ' ntuswat e ' kikie ' kwe ' nIt Cone ' sIn , ipi pInI wusimI nkot , ke ' cne ' ntakwsIncIn , icI Cone ' s shotI iuwak .

text: The queen of the south shall rise up in the judgment with this generation , and shall condemn it : for she came from the uttermost parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon ; and , behold , a greater than Solomon is here .
text2: Okumakwe ' we ' c shawunu ‘ uk winkI okawicpsukwiman , pic notI iaianke ' pmatsIncIn , pic tpakwnItwa oke ' ianwe ' nmawan cI , kcIpInoc win kiwcI pie ' awak shotI kik , e ' winotuk onIpwakawIn Sanamun : icI , pInI wusimI nkot e ' pite ' ntakwsInIt icI Sanamun shotI iuwak .

text: When the unclean spirit is gone out of a man , he walketh through dry places , seeking rest , and findeth none .
text2: Pic su win wansIt mIne ' to , kanmIsakuk wiwunuk nInI , icI e ' pamse ' t kaskiw onInuk , opumtone ' an wacI nwashmot cocu omuksin .

text: Then he saith , I will return into my house from whence I came out ; and when he is come , he findeth it empty , swept , and garnished .
text2: IcI e ' kitot ; Umpe ' ‘ se ' nkukiwe ' e ' taian kapie ' ocusaku ‘ man icI kapiat omukancI e ' nshuke ' ote ' nuk e ' ciktukate ' nuk , ipi e ' mnoscukate ' nuk .

text: Then goeth he , and taketh with himself seven other spirits more wicked than himself , and they enter in and dwell there : and the last state of that man is worse than the first . Even so shall it be also unto this wicked generation .
text2: Iw cI Kanmamacit , e ' notapnat nouk tso pe ' kansIncIn mIne ' ton wusimI ke ' kie ' patsIncIn , icI win , icI e ' nmupitike ' wat shi cI e ' iuwat ; icI shkwe ' iak kashuwe ' psIt onInI wusimI shInshonatsI ; icI ne ' tum . Iw sI nasap ke ' shwe ' psuwat , kotI ke ' kie ' patse ' cIk iaianke ' pmatse ' cIk .

text: While he yet talked to the people , behold , his mother and his brethren stood without , desiring to speak with him .
text2: Me ' kwacI e ' ie ' knone ' t ni nIshInape ' n , PInI okie ' iIn , ni ipi ni wikane ' iIn sakiciiukwan nipwin e ' ntuwe ' nmawat e ' wiknonawat .

text: Then one said unto him , Behold , thy mother and thy brethren stand without , desiring to speak with thee .
text2: NkotcI owitmakon ; PInI kiI ipi kikane ' iuk nipwik sakIc knItwe ' nmukok , e ' wiknonte ' ie ' k .

text: But he answered and said unto him that told him , Who is my mother ? and who are my brethren ?
text2: IcI okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan , kapie ' witmakot ; We ' nicI nkiI , ipi we ' ninukcI nikane ' iuk ?

text: And he stretched forth his hand toward his disciples , and said , Behold my mother and my brethren !
text2: IcI e ' kishipnuke ' not ocIiukwan e ' ciiInIt ke ' knomowacIn , icI otI kIto , PInI nkiI ipi nikane ' iuk .

text: For whosoever shall do the will of my Father which is in heaven , the same is my brother , and sister , and mother .
text2: We ' kwe ' nshutuk sI kie ' totmokwe ' n otIne ' ntumwun , Nos shpumuk e ' iIt kishkok , oie ' o nikane ' , ipi nmIsi , ipi nkiI .

text: The same day went Jesus out of the house , and sat by the sea side .
text2: IWPSHI i e ' kishkiwuk Cisus kisakum wikwuamuk kiwIcipitupI cikcukum .

text: And great multitudes were gathered together unto him , so that he went into a ship , and sat ; and the whole multitude stood on the shore .
text2: KikcImane ' k , maoce ' ticuk , shi e ' ciInIt , icI e ' kiposIt napkwanuk e ' kicipitupIt , icI caye ' k ki maoce ' ticuk ki nipwik cikcukumik .

text: And he spake many things unto them in parables , saying , Behold , a sower went forth to sow ;
text2: IcI e ' kinat cake ' ko iacimonIn otI kItwak ; PInI pe ' mswe ' we ' pne ' ke ' t e ' nmamacit e ' wuswe ' we ' pne ' ke ' t .

text: And when he sowed , some seeds fell by the way side , and the fowls came and devoured them up :
text2: IcI win kaswe ' we ' pnuk , anIt , minkanIn kipkIsnInI cik mie ' wuk , icI pIne ' ‘ shiuk e ' kipie ' micwat .

text: Some fell upon stony places , where they had not much earth : and forthwith they sprung up , because they had no deepness of earth :
text2: AnIt kipkIsnInI sInkukik , kwe ' ckacI pwamane ' k ne ' kwukI ke ' iapIcI , kie ' nup kipie ' sakwe ' ton osam cokwIc kimane ' snon ne ' kwukI .

text: And when the sun was up , they were scorched ; and because they had no root , they withered away .
text2: IcI kisIs kapie ' mokuk e ' ki - kishakite ' k osam co kiw oke ' pkiwse ' non , icI kaocInpikwe ' te ' k .

text: And some fell among thorns ; and the thorns sprung up , and choked them :
text2: AnIt kI kipukse ' non cI cukInIkaoshukik , icI kiw cukInIkaoshisuk e ' pie ' sakwe ' wat ikikpopie ' mkIshkanawa cI .

text: But other fell into good ground , and brought forth fruit , some an hundredfold , some sixtyfold , some thirtyfold .
text2: NiiwcIie ' k , anIt kipukse ' non , e ' cIwunuk kI kipie ' tomkIt micum , anIt nkotwak tso wusimI , ipi anIt nkotwatsomtInI wusimI , ipi anIt nswapituk wusimI .

text: Who hath ears to hear , let him hear .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk we ' ta ‘ okakwe ' n e ' wiuotnk nocma win okInotan .

text: And the disciples came , and said unto him , Why speakest thou unto them in parables ?
text2: IcI ni ke ' knomowacIn kipie ' n , ipi okipie ' kon , TacishIna we ' ciactumwItwa ni iacmonIn ?

text: He answered and said unto them , Because it is given unto you to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven , but to them it is not given .
text2: IcI okinkwe ' twan , ipi otI okinan , Anwucuke ' kiminkom , kinwa e ' wike ' ntume ' k pwake ' ntakwuk shiw okumauwun shpumuk kishkok , winwacIwico minasik .

text: For whosoever hath , to him shall be given , and he shall have more abundance : but whosoever hath not , from him shall be taken away even that he hath .
text2: We ' kwe ' nshutuksI e ' ikwe ' n kuminawak wusimI mce ' sh cI oke ' iIn ; we ' kwe ' nshutuk pwaiIt win kaotapnumwa ke ' iapI ie ' iIt .

text: Therefore speak I to them in parables : because they seeing see not ; and hearing they hear not , neither do they understand .
text2: IwsI ie ' i we ' cwitmokwa notI iacimonIn osam e ' ntawapwat cowapsik , ipi e ' notmowat notake ' sik ; coke ' pshI e ' wi nsItake ' wat .

text: And in them is fulfilled the prophecy of Esaias , which saith , By hearing ye shall hear , and shall not understand ; and seeing ye shall see , and shall not perceive :
text2: IwsI i we ' cte ' pwe ' mkuk wiacimowun Ise ' us , otI kikIto , We ' cnotmuk ktaocinotanawa , ipi cowike ' , ktansItake ' sim , ipi ntowapuk , ktawapke ' m , coke ' ktansItwunake ' sim .

text: For this people ' s heart is waxed gross , and their ears are dull of hearing , and their eyes they have closed ; lest at any time they should see with their eyes , and hear with their ears , and should understand with their heart , and should be converted , and I should heal them .
text2: KotIsI nishInape ' k ote ' iwan mukwitmomkItne ' e ' pic miante ' nuk ; ipi oto ‘ wkawan iapie ' tsimkItnI e ' winotake ' wat , ipi kie ' pikwe ' nwuk e ' kwtumwat e ' wiwapke ' wat , w ‘ shkishkowan ipi anInotake ' k shiwtokawak , ipi ansItake ' k , shiw ote ' iwak iwcI taocI kwe ' kapowawat , icI tacI ne ' se ' ukwa .

text: But blessed are your eyes , for they see : and your ears , for they hear .
text2: Kinwa cI shuwe ' ntakwton , kshkishkowan e ' ntowapimkuk , ipi kta ‘ okawan e ' notake ' mkuk ;

text: For verily I say unto you , That many prophets and righteous men have desired to see those things which ye see , and have not seen them ; and to hear those things which ye hear , and have not heard them .
text2: We ' we ' nI ktInum , Mane ' k , iacimocuk ipi me ' noshuwe ' psIcuk , okintuwe ' ntanawa e ' wiwaptumwat notI , kawaptume ' k , ipi cocu okiwaptusinawan , ipi e ' winotmoat nwatme ' konIn , cocu okinotsinawan .

text: Hear ye therefore the parable of the sower .
text2: Notmok , cI iacimowIn , o e ' swe ' we ' pnike ' t .

text: When any one heareth the word of the kingdom , and understandeth it not , then cometh the wicked one , and catcheth away that which was sown in his heart . This is he which received seed by the way side .
text2: Pic wIiI noatkIn o kikitowun okumauwn , ipi pwansItuk , icI e ' piat me ' iashuwe ' psIt icI e ' mshInuk iw kaswe ' we ' pnukate ' nuk shi ite ' ‘ inuk , osIie ' o kaotapnuk kwe ' minkanIn ci kimie ' wuk .

text: But he that received the seed into stony places , the same is he that heareth the word , and anon with joy receiveth it ;
text2: OtIsI ie ' o kaiIt kwe ' minkan sInkukik ke ' cwashIna nwatuk i kikitowun , ipi e ' nup e ' nciwe ' nmot , e ' wtapnuk .

text: Yet hath he not root in himself , but dureth for a while : for when tribulation or persecution ariseth because of the word , by and by he is offended .
text2: Cowike ' oce ' pkiwsi win nomukcie ' k ikwamsI , kishpIncie ' k kwtuke ' ntumwun tanake ' , miashtotatwIn ocIpsukwimkuk osam o kikitowun , pama shkIc , comnwe ' ntusi .

text: He also that received seed among the thorns is he that heareth the word ; and the care of this world , and the deceitfulness of riches , choke the word , and he becometh unfruitful .
text2: Winsuke ' kaiIt kwe ' minkan me ' kwe ' kcIkinIkaoshukik , winsIo pe ' stuk kikitowun e ' wtme ' ntuk , shotI kik , ipi wie ' shta ‘ wun tpe ' nwe ' osuwun , ipi okikpopie ' mkIshkanawa i kikitowun , cocI kiwcI micmaosi .

text: But he that received seed into the good ground is he that heareth the word , and understandeth it ; which also beareth fruit , and bringeth forth , some an hundredfold , some sixty , some thirty .
text2: WinsI o kaiIt kwe ' minkan e ' cIowuntunuk ne ' kowukik oie ' o nwatuk i kitowun , ipi ne ' stotuk ke ' iapI macmowIt , anIt nkotwat tso wusimI ipi anIt nkotwatsomtInI wusimI , ipi anIt nswaptuk wusimI .

text: Another parable put he forth unto them , saying , The kingdom of heaven is likened unto a man which sowed good seed in his field :
text2: MinI nkot iacimowIn , okipkItnumwan , otI kItwak okumauwun shpumuk e ' ne ' ntakwuk ke ' cwa nInI kapmIswe ' we ' pnuk we ' onItnuk kwe ' minkan okItkanuk .

text: But while men slept , his enemy came and sowed tares among the wheat , and went his way .
text2: NIshcI me ' kwa nInwun , e ' ie ' npanIt me ' iane ' nmukwocIn , kipie ' n , icI e ' kiswe ' we ' pnuk mIcimishkwIn e ' cIte ' nuk pkwe ' shkInshkik , icI e ' kimacit .

text: But when the blade was sprung up , and brought forth fruit , then appeared the tares also .
text2: Pic cI kapie ' sakwe ' k , icI kipie ' micImowun ie ' ipic , kipie ' nakwton niw mIcImishkwIn .

text: So the servants of the householder came and said unto him , Sir , didst not thou sow good seed in thy field ? from whence then hath it tares ?
text2: IcI ni opmitakaimIn shiw wikwamuk kipie ' n , okipie ' kon , Te ' pe ' nmiak , ConukwnI , kiswe ' pnIsin we ' onuk minkan shi kItkanuk , TInipinukwe ' we ' cpiamkuk mIcImishkwIn ?

text: He said unto them , An enemy hath done this . The servants said unto him , Wilt thou then that we go and gather them up ?
text2: OtI cI okinan me ' iane ' nmItsI otI , kitotum OpumitakaimIn cI , otI okikon ; ConI kitonwacisi e ' wishiaiak , ipi e ' wimaotInmak ?

text: But he said , Nay ; lest while ye gather up the tares , ye root up also the wheat with them .
text2: OtI cI okinon , Coin me ' ic e ' ie ' maotInme ' k ni mIcimishkwIn kitapkocwe ' pitonawan , ke ' i pkwe ' shkIn .

text: Let both grow together until the harvest : and in the time of harvest I will say to the reapers , Gather ye together first the tares , and bind them in bundles to burn them : but gather the wheat into my barn .
text2: Nocma ne ' ish kumace ' kinon , pama cI pic , wima ‘ otonkate ' k , otI nkInak , maotonke ' cuk , wimaotonmok , iw ne ' tum ni mIcimishkwIn , icI ke ' cIsusuptoie ' k e ' wicaksume ' k ; icI ie ' k kmaotInanawa mpukwe ' shkInum , kupitkItonawa micIma o kumkok .

text: Another parable put he forth unto them , saying , The kingdom of heaven is like to a grain of mustard seed , which a man took , and sowed in his field :
text2: MinI nkot iacimowIn okiwitmoan , otI cI kIto shpumuk okumauwun ke ' cwa nish e ' opukomnanwuk iukwan waskuk minkan ; nInI kaotapInuk e ' kiswe ' we ' pInuk okItkanuk .

text: Which indeed is the least of all seeds : but when it is grown , it is the greatest among herbs , and becometh a tree , so that the birds of the air come and lodge in the branches thereof .
text2: Iw sI ie ' i mamwe ' kacinoiak caye ' k e ' tsuk kwe ' minkanIn , pic cInIsh kakishkuk mamwe ' mshamkuk caye ' k mishkwIn ipi ke ' pie ' mtukowI icI ki pne ' ‘ shiuk pe ' pamsacuk pie ' pkIshnok shiw e ' otukwnowuk e ' winpawat .

text: Another parable spake he unto them ; The kingdom of heaven is like unto leaven , which a woman took , and hid in three measures of meal , till the whole was leavened .
text2: MinI nkot iacimowIn , oki witmowan okumauwun shpumuk kishkok ; e ' shnakwuk ke ' cwa okwe ' opce ' skIn kaotapnuk , icI e ' kikitot nsotupukInuk napani nashcI caye ' k e ' ope ' ce ' shkanuk .

text: All these things spake Jesus unto the multitude in parables ; and without a parable spake he not unto them :
text2: Caye ' ksI notI Cisus kiwitmowan , maoce ' tincIn ni iacimowInIn , icI ke ' iacimowIn pwaiactuk cokiknonasin .

text: That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet , saying , I will open my mouth in parables ; I will utter things which have been kept secret from the foundation of the world .
text2: IwcI i te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun kakitot nakanacimot otI kItwak ; NkInsakwnan nton , niwiacmowunIn nincI nkukIt niw katIpackate ' k kItwunIn , pic e ' oshkukiwuk .

text: Then Jesus sent the multitude away , and went into the house : and his disciples came unto him , saying , Declare unto us the parable of the tares of the field .
text2: IcI Cisus kimace ' nashkawan , maoce ' tincIn e ' kipitike ' t wikwamuk , ipi ke ' knomowacIn kipie ' naskakon , otI kItwun , WitmoshInak , iacimowIn iacIkate ' k ni mIcimishkwIn shi ktukanuk .

text: He answered and said unto them , He that soweth the good seed is the Son of man ;
text2: IcI okinkwe ' twan , ipi okinan , WinsI o e ' se ' we ' pnuk we ' onItnuk kwe ' minkan winsI o We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: The field is the world ; the good seed are the children of the kingdom ; but the tares are the children of the wicked one ;
text2: Iw ktukan i ie ' i kI ; ipi we ' onuk minkan kiw ie ' ki we ' nicansumcuk shiw Okumauwunuk ni ce ' ie ' k mIcimishkwIn kiw ie ' ki we ' nicansum kowacIn ni me ' ashuwe ' psIncIn .

text: The enemy that sowed them is the devil ; the harvest is the end of the world ; and the reapers are the angels .
text2: IcI me ' iane ' nke ' t kapie ' swe ' pnuk oie ' o mIcImIne ' to ; pic cI maotonmuk iw ie ' i wishkwakiwuk ; ipi cI ki kamaotInke ' cIk ki ie ' ki mshInwe ' k .

text: As therefore the tares are gathered and burned in the fire ; so shall it be in the end of this world .
text2: E ' shmaoton kate ' k , niw mIcimishkwe ' n , ipi e ' cakse ' kate ' k shkote ' k iw sI ke ' showe ' puk wishkwakiwuk .

text: The Son of man shall send forth his angels , and they shall gather out of his kingdom all things that offend , and them which do iniquity ;
text2: We ' kwIsmukot NInwun okupie ' nokanan omIshInIwe ' mIn , icI ke ' cI maotInmowat shiw otokumauwunuk cake ' ko nIshka ‘ we ' mkukIn , ipi niw me ' iashtotmoncIn .

text: And shall cast them into a furnace of fire : there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth .
text2: IcI ke ' cI pukinawat shkote ' k kposke ' nuk iwcI shi e ' tnIte ' mok ipi e ' tnwe ' iapte ' shnuk .

text: Then shall the righteous shine forth as the sun in the kingdom of their Father . Who hath ears to hear , let him hear .
text2: KiwcI mInoshuwe ' pse ' cIk , kawasok ke ' cwa kisIs , shi Oswan otokumauwunuk . We ' kwe ' ntuk we ' ta ‘ okakwe ' n e ' wi notake ' t , nocima knotake ' .

text: Again , the kingdom of heaven is like unto treasure hid in a field ; the which when a man hath found , he hideth , and for joy thereof goeth and selleth all that he hath , and buyeth that field .
text2: MinI okumauwun shpumuk , ke ' cwa ne ' n - - kwIt kcItupInwe ' osawun e ' kIckate ' k ktukanuk ; pic o nInI kamkuk okukiton e ' pic nciwe ' nmot maciwak , icI e ' wutawe ' t cake ' tot ; icI e ' kishpIne ' tot i ktukan .

text: Again , the kingdom of heaven is like unto a merchant man , seeking goodly pearls :
text2: MinI shpumuk okumauwun ke ' cwa ne ' ntakwIt tawe ' wunInI pe ' pantowaptuk we ' anItnuk MikIs SIniIn .

text: Who , when he had found one pearl of great price , went and sold all that he had , and bought it .
text2: I pic cI kamkuk nkot MikIs sIn ke ' cmIskIte ' nuk , e ' shiat icI e ' wutawe ' t caye ' k , e ' tot icI e ' kishpIne ' tot .

text: Again , the kingdom of heaven is like unto a net , that was cast into the sea , and gathered of every kind :
text2: MinI shpumuk okumauwun ke ' cwa ne ' ntakwIt sup , kapukicikate ' k shi kiukumik e ' kimaotonat cak e ' shnakwsIncIn .

text: Which , when it was full , they drew to shore , and sat down , and gathered the good into vessels , but cast the bad away .
text2: Pic cI kamoshkIne ' nIt e ' kiw tapInawat cik pie ' k ; icI e ' cipitupwat e ' kiwe ' napmawat we ' wnIsnIncIn e ' kisawat mkukok ; me ' iansIncIn cIie ' k okiwe ' pnawan .

text: So shall it be at the end of the world : the angels shall come forth , and sever the wicked from among the just ,
text2: Iw sI ke ' showe ' puk wishkwakiwuk mshInwe ' k kupie ' k , okupkie ' pnawan ke ' kie ' patsIncIn e ' ciiInIt ni me ' noshuwe ' psIncIn .

text: And shall cast them into the furnace of fire : there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth .
text2: IcI ke ' cI pukinawat shkote ' k , kuposke ' nuk shiw cI e ' tnIte ' mok , ipi e ' tnwe ' iapte ' shnuk .

text: Jesus saith unto them , Have ye understood all these things ? They say unto him , Yea , Lord .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , KinIstotanawanI notI cake ' ko ? OtI cI okinawan ; E ' , Te ' pe ' nmiak .

text: Then said he unto them , Therefore every scribe which is instructed unto the kingdom of heaven is like unto a man that is an householder , which bringeth forth out of his treasure things new and old .
text2: OtI ci okinan e ' tshowat , we ' npie ' ke ' t e ' knomocIk shpumuk okumauwunuk iwsI e ' ne ' ntakwsIt nInI te ' pe ' ntuk wikwam okipie ' sakcotonIn otIpnIwe ' oso ‘ nIn , we ' shkiamkuk , ipi ke ' te ' ianuk .

text: And it came to pass , that when Jesus had finished these parables , he departed thence .
text2: IcI otI kashuwe ' puk , pic Cisus , kakishwawituk notI iacimonIn , icI e ' kinmamacit .

text: And when he was come into his own country , he taught them in their synagogue , insomuch that they were astonished , and said , Whence hath this man this wisdom , and these mighty works ?
text2: IcI win kapiat e ' citnukie ' t okiknomowan shiw otInume ' okumkomwak , okimamkate ' nmawan , ipi kikItwuk ; TInipicI otI nInI we ' tnuk npwakawun , ipi notI kcItotmonIn .

text: Is not this the carpenter ' s son ? is not his mother called Mary ? and his brethren , James , and Joses , and Simon , and Judas ?
text2: ConIwi otI oshuke ' wunInI okwIsun ? conIwi okie ' iIn shInkasin Me ' ni ? ipi wikane ' iIn Ce ' ms , ipi Cosus ipi Sayman , ipi Cote ' s ?

text: And his sisters , are they not all with us ? Whence then hath this man all these things ?
text2: Ipi omIse ' iIn conI caye ' k kwitkie ' mkosinanuk ? TInipicI we ' tnuk otI nInI cake ' ko ?

text: And they were offended in him . But Jesus said unto them , A prophet is not without honour , save in his own country , and in his own house .
text2: Okinshke ' nmawancI Cisus cI otI okinan ; nakanacimot coi pwawinwanasi mtInoie ' k e ' tnukie ' t ipi owikwamuk .

text: And he did not many mighty works there because of their unbelief .
text2: Cowike ' win kimataototsi shiw osam co okite ' pwe ' takwsin .

text: At that time Herod the tetrarch heard of the fame of Jesus ,
text2: IWPICI E ' nut okuma , kanotuk e ' winwananIt CisusIn ,

text: And said unto his servants , This is John the Baptist ; he is risen from the dead ; and therefore mighty works do shew forth themselves in him .
text2: IcI otI okinan , ni opmitakaimIn , iukwan sI otI Can Ke ' ctapie ' nwe ' t ; kiwnIshke ' tuk e ' kinpopIt , icI i we ' tshowe ' puk notI mata ’ wmikce ' wiwunIn e ' waptuwe ' t shi wiia ‘ w .

text: For Herod had laid hold on John , and bound him , and put him in prison for Herodias ' sake , his brother Philip ' s wife .
text2: E ' nut okimshInapIninIn CanIn , okitkopInat , icI e ' kipitike ' nat , kupakotiwkumkok , E ' notius owie ' o shiw kaocupukcukasot ; wikane ' iIn PinIp wiwun .

text: For John said unto him , It is not lawful for thee to have her .
text2: Can kinakpIn Coswi wunse ' non kin e ' wiwiwiun .

text: And when he would have put him to death , he feared the multitude , because they counted him as a prophet .
text2: OtakinsancI nIshte ' wi okikwsan ni maoce ' tincIn , osam okine ' nmawan nakanacimocIn .

text: But when Herod ' s birthday was kept , the daughter of Herodias danced before them , and pleased Herod .
text2: Pic cI E ' nut e ' kinikIt kishuk e ' kiiu ‘ mowIt E ' notie ' s otansIn kinime ' tin e ' nasmupwat ; E ' nut , cI kimnwe ' ntum .

text: Whereupon he promised with an oath to give her whatsoever she would ask .
text2: IwcI ie ' i kaocI wawitmowat e ' wiminat we ' kwe ' ntuk wantotmakokwe ' n .

text: And she , being before instructed of her mother , said , Give me here John Baptist ' s head in a charger .
text2: IcI okwe ' ne ' tum , e ' kikiIkmukot niw kie ' iIn , kikito mi ! In iw iukwan , Can ke ' ctapie ' nwe ' t otup , shi onakunuk .

text: And the king was sorry : nevertheless for the oath ' s sake , and them which sat with him at meat , he commanded it to be given her .
text2: O kumacI , kikisate ' ntum , e ' ki anwu kcIwishkItakwsIt , ipi niw kawitpumkocIn e ' wisnawat , win okinan e ' wiminanIt niw kwe ' n .

text: And he sent , and beheaded John in the prison .
text2: IcI e ' kinokashwe ' t e ' wiwukishkwe ' kasnIt ni CanIn , shi kpakwuke ' otiwkumkok .

text: And his head was brought in a charger , and given to the damsel : and she brought it to her mother .
text2: IcI i otup kipie ' ckate ' ne ' shiw onakunuk , icI e ' kiminIt we ' shkukIt kwe ' , icI e ' kimacitwat okie ' iIn .

text: And his disciples came , and took up the body , and buried it , and went and told Jesus .
text2: IcI niw Ke ' knomowacIn kipie ' n otapne ' kon iw wia ‘ w e ' kiwunkowawat , icI e ' kimaciwat e ' kiwawitmowawat CisusIn .

text: When Jesus heard of it , he departed thence by ship into a desert place apart : and when the people had heard thereof , they followed him on foot out of the cities .
text2: Pic Cisus kanotuk e ' kiposIt napkwanuk e ' kimacit wIiI e ' cupwaie ' nIt , icI pic nIshInape ' k kanotmowat okipmnashkawawan kipmose ' k e ' kipie ' ocI sakumwat , otI okIc - otanmowak .

text: And Jesus went forth , and saw a great multitude , and was moved with compassion toward them , and he healed their sick .
text2: IcI Cisus kanamacit , okiwapman ke ' cmaoce ' tincIn , icI okiktumake ' nman , ipi ke ' okine ' se ' an kapme ' iakwnokancIn .

text: And when it was evening , his disciples came to him , saying , This is a desert place , and the time is now past ; send the multitude away , that they may go into the villages , and buy themselves victuals .
text2: IcI kanmupkonianuk ni ke ' knomowacIn kipie ' naskakon otI kItwuk , OsamsInI otI wIiI e ' cI pwaotukit , shiI mupkonia , mace ' nashka ‘ w ki maoce ' ticuk , tanak shiawat otane ' suk e ' wikishpIne ' tatsowat wamicwat .

text: But Jesus said unto them , They need not depart ; give ye them to eat .
text2: Cisus otI okinan , Coin kumacisik ; minuk iw wamicwat .

text: And they say unto him , We have here but five loaves , and two fishes .
text2: OtIcI , okikon , mtIno nte ' iomIn nianIn pkwe ' shkInIn , ipi nish kikosuk .

text: He said , Bring them hither to me .
text2: OtI cI kikIto , Pie ' twushuk .

text: And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the grass , and took the five loaves , and the two fishes , and looking up to heaven , he blessed , and brake , and gave the loaves to his disciples , and the disciples to the multitude .
text2: IcI niw e ' kinat ni maoce ' tincIn e ' wicipitupnIt shi skupkIshktokik , icI e ' kiw tapnuk niw nianIn pkwe ' shkInIn , ipi ni nish kikosIn , icI e ' kinapIt shpumuk , e ' ki numat , ipi e ' kipikupitot , e ' kiminat , pkwe ' shkInIn , e ' knomowacIn , icI niw ke ' knomowacIn , e ' kiminawat maoce ' tincIn .

text: And they did all eat , and were filled : and they took up of the fragments that remained twelve baskets full .
text2: IcI caye ' k e ' kiwisnawat , ipi kite ' psInie ' k ; icI kiw tapnanawan kaiashuwe ' sanuk mtatso shItnish kokpInaknIn , kimoshkIne ' tonawan .

text: And they that had eaten were about five thousand men , beside women and children .
text2: KicI kawisne ' cuk ; Nianuk tsuk mtatswak kitshik nInwuk ; e ' pwatkokcIkaswat kwe ' k , ipi pInoce ' iuk .

text: And straightway Jesus constrained his disciples to get into a ship , and to go before him unto the other side , while he sent the multitudes away .
text2: Okiwe ' witpamancI , Cisus e ' winImacinIt ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' wiposnIt napkwanuk e ' winmInikaninIt e ' wishiawat ashwe ' iukwan me ' kwa , e ' wi mace ' nashkawat , ni maoce ' tincIn .

text: And when he had sent the multitudes away , he went up into a mountain apart to pray : and when the evening was come , he was there alone .
text2: Pic cI kakishmacInashkawat , ni maoce ' tincIn kishie ' wak shi e ' pkotnianuk winshuke ' e ' winumat iwcI e ' nmupkonianuk winshi nshuke ' kiiI .

text: But the ship was now in the midst of the sea , tossed with waves : for the wind was contrary .
text2: IwcI i napkwan nmItnIsimkuk , naokamkcukImik e ' makashkak , osam e ' miananmuk .

text: And in the fourth watch of the night Jesus went unto them , walking on the sea .
text2: E ' pwamshuwapuk , cI e ' ie ' pkonianuk , Cisus kishie ' wak e ' cIiInIt , kinmupmose ' kwItIpie ' k , shi kcukumik .

text: And when the disciples saw him walking on the sea , they were troubled , saying , It is a spirit ; and they cried out for fear .
text2: IcI ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' wapmukot e ' pie ' pmose ' nIt kwItIpie ' k kcukImik , kise ' ksik otIcI kikItwuk iukwansI o cipe ' ‘ i ; iwcI e ' kiwishkwe ' we ' ksawat , e ' pic kwsawat .

text: But straightway Jesus spake unto them , saying , Be of good cheer ; it is I ; be not afraid .
text2: Kie ' nupcI Cisus e ' kinat , kItwak , Mnowankosuk , Nin kwshe ' ke ' ko se ' ksuke ' k .

text: And Peter answered him and said , Lord , if it be thou , bid me come unto thee on the water .
text2: IcI pitu e ' kinkwe ' twat , ipi okiknonan , Te ' pe ' nme ' ak , kishpInsu kin ntomshIn , e ' winaskonan , kwtIpie ' k .

text: And he said , Come . And when Peter was come down out of the ship , he walked on the water , to go to Jesus .
text2: OtIcI kItwak Wipian . IcI pic PiIu kapie ' nisasit , shi napkwanuk , kipmose ' kwtIpie ' k e ' shiat , e ' cIiInIt ni CisusIn .

text: But when he saw the wind boisterous , he was afraid ; and beginning to sink , he cried , saying , Lord , save me .
text2: Pic cI , kawaptuk e ' kcInotnunuk kise ' ksuwak , pic cI wanmukwsapie ' t , icI kinotakwse ' kItwak , Te ' pe ' nmin ke ' skonshIn .

text: And immediately Jesus stretched forth his hand , and caught him , and said unto him , O thou of little faith , wherefore didst thou doubt ?
text2: IcI papuk , Cisus , e ' kishipnuke ' not e ' kimshInat , otI cI okinan , O kin pke ' ci te ' pwe ' tmIn ! tacIshIna kaocI ianwe ' ntumIn ?

text: And when they were come into the ship , the wind ceased .
text2: IcI pic kanmuposwat shi napkwanuk , kipon notIn .

text: Then they that were in the ship came and worshipped him , saying , Of a truth thou art the Son of God .
text2: KicI kaie ' cuk shi napkwanut okipie ' wucikwnItwawan , otI cI kikItwuk , Kinsu we ' we ' nI , Kshe ' mIne ' to KtokwIsmuk .

text: And when they were gone over , they came into the land of Gennesaret .
text2: IcI kanmukupawat ashowe ' iukwan , kipie ' k Ce ' ne ' se ' nIt ukik .

text: And when the men of that place had knowledge of him , they sent out into all that country round about , and brought unto him all that were diseased ;
text2: Pic cI ki nInwuk shiw e ' icuk kake ' nmawat , kimace ' acimok caye ' k caknkoci , ipi kipie ' twawan caye ' k iakwnokancIn .

text: And besought him that they might only touch the hem of his garment : and as many as touched were made perfectly whole .
text2: IcI e ' kimatmawat mtIno te ' pnak e ' witaknumwawat e ' tupkwate ' nuk , i e ' kwut , icI kiw caye ' k katakne ' cuk kwe ' ie ' k kine ' se ' k .

text: Then came to Jesus scribes and Pharisees , which were of Jerusalem , saying ,
text2: IWCI e ' kipie ' naskawawat CisusIn , We ' npie ' ke ' cuk , ipi Pe ' nisiuk kiwcupie ' k Cinosne ' muk katacuk , otIcI kikItwuk ;

text: Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders ? for they wash not their hands when they eat bread .
text2: TacIshIna ke ' knomotwa we ' cpikupitowat . kapie ' shIcke ' nIt ke ' ctaosIncIn ? Coke ' ksince ' sik pic wawisnawacIn .

text: But he answered and said unto them , Why do ye also transgress the commandment of God by your tradition ?
text2: OtI cI okishInkwe ' twan , ipi okinan , TacIke ' kinwa we ' cpikupitoie ' k , i Kshe ' mIne ' to okukie ' kwe ' wun , e ' te ' pwe ' tme ' k kapie ' shIcke ' wat ke ' ctaosIcIk .

text: For God commanded , saying , Honour thy father and mother : and , He that curseth father or mother , let him die the death .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to kikie ' kwe ' , otI kItwak , Kcupite ' num Kos , ipi ke ' ‘ . WincIke ' o ke ' miashtotwat , osIn tanake ' okie ' iIn , nocma we ' we ' nI win kInpowak .

text: But ye say , Whosoever shall say to his father or his mother , It is a gift , by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me ;
text2: KinwacI ktukitom ; We ' kwe ' nshItuk ke ' nakwe ' n osIn tanake ' okie ' iIn , I ie ' i mikwe ' wIn , kishpIn ke ' ko nishokmonan co otI okIc - pite ' nmasin ni osIn , tanake ' , okie ' iIn .

text: And honour not his father or his mother , he shall be free . Thus have ye made the commandment of God of none effect by your tradition .
text2: Iw ie ' i we ' cpnactoie ' k ni Kshe ' mIne ' to okukie ' kwe ' wIn ni ktIshcIke ' onawan .

text: Ye hypocrites , well did Esaias prophesy of you , saying ,
text2: E ' numIe ' kasie ' k ; we ' we ' nI Ise ' us , ki nikanacimukwa , otI kItwak ;

text: This people draweth nigh unto me with their mouth , and honoureth me with their lips ; but their heart is far from me .
text2: KotI nIshInape ' k pe ' shoc e ' ciian pie ' ik , ipi npie ' kcImnotshumkok otoniwak nicu ‘ wi ote ' ‘ iwan pnocte ' nI .

text: But in vain they do worship me , teaching for doctrines the commandments of men .
text2: Coin nkot , nomkIsnon e ' nume ' kita ‘ wat me ' kwa e ' shkukinomake ' wat , okukie ' kwe ' onawan ki nInwuk , icI ni nkukie ' kwe ' onIn .

text: And he called the multitude , and said unto them , Hear , and understand :
text2: IcI e ' kintomat maoce ' tincIn e ' kinat ; PsItImok , ipi nsItomok .

text: Not that which goeth into the mouth defileth a man ; but that which cometh out of the mouth , this defileth a man .
text2: Cowi patike ' mkuk otonik winukwsin nInI iwsIie ' k pie ' sakumomkItnuk shiw otonik nInI , i ie ' k wanakwu ‘ ukot .

text: Then came his disciples , and said unto him , Knowest thou that the Pharisees were offended , after they heard this saying ?
text2: IcI kipie ' n ke ' knomowacIn , icI e ' kikot ; KikInmaknI ki Pe ' nisiuk e ' kipwamnwe ' ntumwat kakishnotmowat , otI kakItiIn .

text: But he answered and said , Every plant , which my heavenly Father hath not planted , shall be rooted up .
text2: IcI okinkwe ' twan , ipi kikIto , Caye ' k sakwe ' k Nos shpumuk e ' iIt , kapwaktIkatuk , kupkocwe ' pcIkate ' .

text: Let them alone : they be blind leaders of the blind . And if the blind lead the blind , both shall fall into the ditch .
text2: Ponikaki kiw ; winwa kie ' pikwe ' k pumskapie ' nawan ke ' kie ' pikwancIn kishpIncI ke ' kie ' pikwat pme ' skapie ' nat , ni ke ' kie ' pikwancIn ne ' ne ' ish kupitse ' k e ' cIwankate ' nuk .

text: Then answered Peter and said unto him , Declare unto us this parable .
text2: IcI kinkwe ' take ' t Pitu , ipi otI e ' kinat ; WitmoshInak ninan , iw iacimown .

text: And Jesus said , Are ye also yet without understanding ?
text2: IcI Cisus okinan , Kinwanuke ' , me ' kwa comshe ' , kinIstotake ' sim ?

text: Do not ye yet understand , that whatsoever entereth in at the mouth goeth into the belly , and is cast out into the draught ?
text2: ConukwnI , ke ' kinwa mshIknIstotsinawa we ' kwe ' ntuk patke ' mkuk ktoniwakshie ' mkIt shi , kshukiwak , iwcI sakcIwe ' pinukate ' k nkoci ?

text: But those things which proceed out of the mouth come forth from the heart ; and they defile the man .
text2: IwcI ie ' k pie ' ocIsakumomkuk otonik pie ' osukie ' nI ote ' ‘ ik , ie ' i wanakwukot nInI .

text: For out of the heart proceed evil thoughts , murders , adulteries , fornications , thefts , false witness , blasphemies :
text2: Pie ' osukamkuk ote ' ‘ ima sakumomkIt mIcIshIte ' ‘ e ' wunIn nsItwunIn waonIshkaiwunIn kie ' patsuwunIn kmotwunIn kno ‘ skacmowInIn mIcIkikitowInIn .

text: These are the things which defile a man : but to eat with unwashen hands defileth not a man .
text2: Niw notI wanakwukot nInI , otI cI , e ' wisnIt e ' pwamshIksincat coin winakwuksin nInI .

text: Then Jesus went thence , and departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon .
text2: IcI Cisus kanmamacit kishie ' wak e ' pie ' kokmukianuk Taine ' ipi Saitan .

text: And , behold , a woman of Canaan came out of the same coasts , and cried unto him , saying , Have mercy on me , O Lord , thou Son of David ; my daughter is grievously vexed with a devil .
text2: IcI pInI e ' wcIpianIt e ' pie ' kokmukianuk , Ke ' nIni kwe ' , otI cI , okikon , Shuwe ' nmIshIn O Te ' pe ' nmin , We ' kwIsmukwiIn Te ' pIt ; ntanIs okIckwtukukon MIcImIne ' ton .

text: But he answered her not a word . And his disciples came and besought him , saying , Send her away ; for she crieth after us .
text2: CocI okinkwe ' twasin . IcI ke ' knomowawIncI kipie ' shie ' n otIcI , okinan ; mace ' nashk ‘ o osam kwako - omkonan .

text: But he answered and said , I am not sent but unto the lost sheep of the house of Israel .
text2: Okinkwe ' twancI , otI cI , okinan ; Coin nokankosi , mtIno ne ' kcIkascuk mantanshuk shi wikwamuk IsniIn .

text: Then came she and worshipped him , saying , Lord , help me .
text2: IcI e ' kipiat okwe ' , ipi okiowucikwne ' takot kItwak ; Te ' pe ' nmin natmoshIn .

text: But he answered and said , It is not meet to take the children ' s bread , and to cast it to dogs .
text2: OkiknonancI otI okinan , Cosuwi wunse ' non e ' witapnumwutwa , pInoce ' iuk macwat , icI e ' wipukitotwa wunumoshuk .

text: And she said , Truth , Lord : yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their masters ' table .
text2: OtIcI , Otukon , Kte ' pwe ' , Te ' pe ' nmin nIshcI kiw wunumokuk omicnawa papiwe ' shkanuk , pe ' mkote ' nuk te ' pe ' nmukwat otopwunuk .

text: Then Jesus answered and said unto her , O woman , great is thy faith : be it unto thee even as thou wilt . And her daughter was made whole from that very hour .
text2: IcI Cisus cI , Okinkwe ' twan OtI okinan ; O kwe ' ce ' pite ' ntakwut kte ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun , knomkIt e ' shntuwe ' ntumIn . IcI ni pic otansIn e ' kine ' se ' nIt .

text: And Jesus departed from thence , and came nigh unto the sea of Galilee ; and went up into a mountain , and sat down there .
text2: IcI , CisuscI , kiwcI maci kishie ' wak cikcukumik Ke ' nIniuk , icI shi e ' pkotnianuk e ' ki wuciptupIt shi .

text: And great multitudes came unto him , having with them those that were lame , blind , dumb , maimed , and many others , and cast them down at Jesus ' feet ; and he healed them :
text2: IcI ke ' cmaoce ' tinIt kipie ' otIskot , okipie ' nawancI me ' iakatancIn , ke ' kie ' pikwancIn , ipi ke ' kie ' ptoncIn , ipi kipie ' nawan , pe ' kansIncIn icI e ' kipukinawat Cisus osItik . icI e ' kine ' se ' at .

text: Insomuch that the multitude wondered , when they saw the dumb to speak , the maimed to be whole , the lame to walk , and the blind to see : and they glorified the God of Israel .
text2: KikcI mamkate ' ntumwukcI kimaoce ' ticuk pic , e ' wapmawat nike ' kie ' pitoncIn e ' kikikitonIt , ipi kashkunukancIn e ' kine ' se ' nIt , ipi me ' ‘ akatancIn e ' pmose ' nIt ; ipi ke ' kie ' pikwancIn e ' ntuwapnIt , icI e ' kiwinwanawat , O Kishe ' mIne ' tomwan Isne ' iIn .

text: Then Jesus called his disciples unto him , and said , I have compassion on the multitude , because they continue with me now three days , and have nothing to eat : and I will not send them away fasting , lest they faint in the way .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kintomat ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' ciiIt , otI cI okinan , Nshuwe ' nmak kotI maoce ' ticuk osam shiInsokwnuktInI e ' koiuwat shotI cocumshI ke ' ko omitsinawa ; ipi co nkumaci nashkawasik e ' pkIte ' wat tane ' ie ' k nkoci , ianwutok .

text: And his disciples say unto him , Whence should we have so much bread in the wilderness , as to fill so great a multitude ?
text2: IcI ke ' knomowacIn otI okikon , TInipicI ke ' otInmukon mce ' sh pkwe ' shkIn shotI no ‘ wmtukwakik e ' wite ' psInie ' wat kotI ke ' cmaoce ' ticIk .

text: And Jesus saith unto them , How many loaves have ye ? And they said , Seven , and a few little fishes .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan ; TInicItso pkwe ' shkInIn e ' ie ' k ? IcI otI kikItwuk , Nouksu ipi onatso kikose ' suk .

text: And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground .
text2: IcI e ' kinat ni maoce ' tincIn , e ' wicipitupnIt , mcIiukwan .

text: And he took the seven loaves and the fishes , and gave thanks , and brake them , and gave to his disciples , and the disciples to the multitude .
text2: IcI e ' kiwtapInuk ni nouk pkwe ' shkInIn , ipi ni kikosIn , icI e ' kiwawiwe ' t icI okipikupitonIn , icI e ' kiminat ni ke ' knomowacIn , icI ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' kiminanIt , ni maoce ' tincIn .

text: And they did all eat , and were filled : and they took up of the broken meat that was left seven baskets full .
text2: IcI caye ' kcI kiwisnik ipi kite ' psInie ' k icI e ' kiw tapInumwat pakIshkanuk i micIm kashkotmoat , nouk kokpInaknIn moshkIn .

text: And they that did eat were four thousand men , beside women and children .
text2: KicI kawisne ' cuk kitshik , nie ' wuk tsuk mtatswak nInwuk , e ' pwatkokcIkaswat kwe ' k , ipi pInoce ' iuk .

text: And he sent away the multitude , and took ship , and came into the coasts of Magdala ,
text2: IcI e ' kimace ' nashkawat ni maoce ' tincIn napkwanuk cI kiposI e ' kishiat e ' pmukokumukiak Me ' kte ' ne ' .

text: The Pharisees also with the Sadducees came , and tempting desired him that he would shew them a sign from heaven .
text2: KIWCI Pe ' nisiuk ipi Se ' cwsiuk okipie ' naskawawan e ' wi kwcItupe ' nmawat e ' natowawat e ' wiwaptukowat mataonInkie ' wun shpumuk shi .

text: He answered and said unto them , When it is evening , ye say , It will be fair weather : for the sky is red .
text2: WincI okinkwe ' twan , ipi otI Okinan , E ' nmupkoniak , otI kitukitom kumnokishkIt , osam mskwankot .

text: And in the morning , It will be foul weather to day : for the sky is red and lowring . O ye hypocrites , ye can discern the face of the sky ; but can ye not discern the signs of the times ?
text2: IcI kukishie ' p , kumiashkishkIt e ' kishkiwuk osam , e ' mskwankok , ipi wunsiwun . O e ' nmue ' kasie ' k , knIstonanawa e ' nankok kishuk ; conukwnI ktansItwunsinawa mataonInkie ' wun , notI e ' kishkiwuk .

text: A wicked and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign ; and there shall no sign be given unto it , but the sign of the prophet Jonas . And he left them , and departed .
text2: KotI me ' iashuwe ' psucIk , ipi waonIshkaiuk iaianke ' pmatsIt onItwaptanawa e ' wiwaptumwat mataototmowIn ; cocI mataototmowIn kuminasik , mtIno omataototmowIn o nakanacimot Cone ' s ; icI e ' kinkInat e ' kinmamacit .

text: And when his disciples were come to the other side , they had forgotten to take bread .
text2: IcI pic ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' kipianIt ashwIiukwan okiwne ' ntanawa pkwe ' shkIn e ' witapnumwat .

text: Then Jesus said unto them , Take heed and beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan ; ikwamsuk kawaptumwuk otopce ' skInmawa , ki Pe ' nisiuk ipi Se ' cwsiuk .

text: And they reasoned among themselves , saying , It is because we have taken no bread .
text2: WinwacI kiknontik otI cI , kikItwuk ; iwsI ie ' i e ' kipwamacitoikon pkwe ' shIn .

text: Which when Jesus perceived , he said unto them , O ye of little faith , why reason ye among yourselves , because ye have brought no bread ?
text2: Pic Cisus kakuke ' ntuk , otI okinan , O pke ' ci te ' pwe ' ie ' ntume ' k , We ' kwonicI we ' cknonte ' ie ' k kinwa osam e ' kipwapie ' toie ' k pkwe ' shkIn .

text: Do ye not yet understand , neither remember the five loaves of the five thousand , and how many baskets ye took up ?
text2: ConI knIstotsinawa , conukI kmikwe ' ntusinawa , ni nianIn pkwe ' shkInIn e ' kite ' psak ki nianIn tsuk mtatswak ; ipi tso kokpInaknIn , kaotapne ' me ' k ?

text: Neither the seven loaves of the four thousand , and how many baskets ye took up ?
text2: Conuke ' ni nouk pkwe ' shkInIn kate ' ponkwa nie ' wuk tsuk mtataswak ipi tso kokpInaknIn , kaotapne ' me ' k ?

text: How is it that ye do not understand that I spake it not to you concerning bread , that ye should beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees ?
text2: TInicI e ' shpwansItme ' k , i e ' kikItian cowi i pkwe ' shkIn nkiwcukItsi e ' wikawaptme ' k iw otopce ' skInmawa ki Pe ' nisiuk ipi Se ' cwsiuk .

text: Then understood they how that he bade them not beware of the leaven of bread , but of the doctrine of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees .
text2: IcI e ' kinsItawawat e ' kikowat e ' wip wakawaptumwat we ' pce ' tnuk pkwe ' shkIn icie ' k otIshkie ' kwe ' onawa ki Pe ' nisiuk ; ipi Se ' cwsiuk ,

text: When Jesus came into the coasts of Caesarea Philippi , he asked his disciples , saying , Whom do men say that I the Son of man am ?
text2: Pic cI Cisus kapiat , e ' pie ' kokumukianuk Sise ' ne ' , Pinipiuk , okinatawan ni ke ' knomowacIm otI cI , okinan , We ' nicI Nin e ' kitowat nInwuk We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: And they said , Some say that thou art John the Baptist : some , Elias ; and others , Jeremias , or one of the prophets .
text2: OtI cI okinawan ; anIt ktukok Can su o ke ' ctapie ' nwe ' t ; anIt Inaie ' s ipi anIt CInimIie ' s tanake ' nkot e ' iI nakanacimocuk .

text: He saith unto them , But whom say ye that I am ?
text2: OtI cI okinan , We ' nicI kinwa e ' shnukanie ' k ?

text: And Simon Peter answered and said , Thou art the Christ , the Son of the living God .
text2: IcI Sayman Pitu okinkwe ' twon otI cI okinan , Kinsu Knayst , We ' kwIsmukwiIn kake ' pmatsIt Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And Jesus answered and said unto him , Blessed art thou , Simon Barjona : for flesh and blood hath not revealed it unto thee , but my Father which is in heaven .
text2: IcI Cisus okinkwe ' twan otI cI okinan , Shuwe ' ntakwsI Sayman we ' kwIsmuk Cone ' s : cosI i wias , ipi imskwI kiwaptu ‘ kosim , mtIno Nos shpumuk , e ' iIt kishkok .

text: And I say also unto thee , That thou art Peter , and upon this rock I will build my church ; and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it .
text2: OtI ke ' ke ' iapI ktInIn ; Kinsu Pitu wiIn ipi otI kwucsInik nkaoshIton Te ' pwe ' ie ' tukuk , icI i e ' shkwate ' mkate ' k namkumuk cotakwushkakwsinawa .

text: And I will give unto thee the keys of the kingdom of heaven : and whatsoever thou shalt bind on earth shall be bound in heaven : and whatsoever thou shalt loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven .
text2: KuminIncI ni kitapkukinIn shi okumauwunuk , shkwumuk kishkok , We ' kwe ' ntukcI ke ' tkoptonIn shotI kik , ipukI kItkoptI shpumuk , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' ke ' apskonmInIn , shotI kik ke ' iapskonkatI , ipI shpumuk .

text: Then charged he his disciples that they should tell no man that he was Jesus the Christ .
text2: IcI oki iakwamancI ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' wipwawitmowanIt , nInwun , win e ' nIt Cisus Knayst .

text: From that time forth began Jesus to shew unto his disciples , how that he must go unto Jerusalem , and suffer many things of the elders and chief priests and scribes , and be killed , and be raised again the third day .
text2: IcI pic Cisus e ' we ' pknomowat , ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' wishiat Cinose ' ne ' muk ; ipi washu , mce ' shke ' ko kwtukukot , ni ke ' ctaosIncIn ipi kcI me ' matmocuk , ipi we ' npie ' ke ' ncIn , ipi e ' winsIckasot , icI minI e ' wipsukwit nsokishkItnuk .

text: Then Peter took him , and began to rebuke him , saying , Be it far from thee , Lord : this shall not be unto thee .
text2: IcI Pitu , kiw tapnan , icI e ' we ' piaiaishumat otI cI , otInan , Ke ' kone ' ntukIn Te ' pe ' nmin ; cowi otI kitotakosi .

text: But he turned , and said unto Peter , Get thee behind me , Satan : thou art an offence unto me : for thou savourest not the things that be of God , but those that be of men .
text2: IcI kikwe ' knoi , otI cI okinan ni PituiIn , Shian npukwnak me ' ctotwin kinknIshkI ‘ ; cosu kupupame ' ntusinIn te ' pe ' ntukIn Kshe ' mInto , mtIno ni te ' pe ' ntumwat , nInwuk .

text: Then said Jesus unto his disciples , If any man will come after me , let him deny himself , and take up his cross , and follow me .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kinat , ke ' knomowacIn kishpIn wIiI nInI wipie ' pmnashkawut nocma win ke ' iakwne ' tatso ipi okaotapnan wIiashte ' iatkomIn , ipi nkupme ' nashkak .

text: For whosoever will save his life shall lose it : and whosoever will lose his life for my sake shall find it .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' ke ' skwe ' ntuk opmatsiwun okInkIton ; we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' nin ke ' ocI nkItot opumat suwun okumkan .

text: For what is a man profited , if he shall gain the whole world , and lose his own soul ? or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul ?
text2: We ' kwnicI ke ' napcItopI nInI kishpIn tpe ' ntuk caye ' k ukI ; icI nukuat ocikwamIn ? Tanake ' , We ' pe ' ntuk ke ' mikwe ' pI nInI e ' wiashtonat ocipamIn ?

text: For the Son of man shall come in the glory of his Father with his angels ; and then he shall reward every man according to his works .
text2: We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kupie ' wak , okIcne ' ntakwsowounuk ni OsIn , ipi okupie ' wice ' owan , ni omIshInwe ' mIn ; icI pic win ke ' cIminat , e ' tshe ' nIt nInwun , kashI mikce ' winIt .

text: Verily I say unto you , There be some standing here , which shall not taste of death , till they see the Son of man coming in his kingdom .
text2: We ' we ' nI ktInum shotI anIt knipwik ke ' pwawapitumwat npowIn , pama wapmawat WakwIsmukot NInwun pie ' iInIt otokuma uwunuk .

text: And after six days Jesus taketh Peter , James , and John his brother , and bringeth them up into an high mountain apart ,
text2: ICI kankotwatsokwnukte ' nuk , Cisus okimacinan Pitu , Ce ' ms , ipi Can , Wikane ' iIn , okisha ‘ wnan e ' cI pkotnianuk .

text: And was transfigured before them : and his face did shine as the sun , and his raiment was white as the light .
text2: IcI shi e ' kikwe ' knao - ot e ' nasmukapowunIt , kisokcI kishuwase ' ikwe ' , ipi paskukIn e ' wase ' ak kishuwapshkianI .

text: And , behold , there appeared unto them Moses and Elias talking with him .
text2: PInI , kashu mataowapmawan , ni MosusIn , ipi InaisIn e ' knonanIt .

text: Then answered Peter , and said unto Jesus , Lord , it is good for us to be here : if thou wilt , let us make here three tabernacles ; one for thee , and one for Moses , and one for Elias .
text2: OtI okishInkwe ' twan Pitu ; ipi okinan , ni CisusIn Te ' pe ' nmae ' k owunIt shotI e ' iIiak , kishpIn onwacin nkowiwshItomIn shotI , nswI wikwamIn , nkot kin , e ' wi - in Mosuske ' nkot , ipi Inaie ' s nkot .

text: While he yet spake , behold , a bright cloud overshadowed them : and behold a voice out of the cloud , which said , This is my beloved Son , in whom I am well pleased ; hear ye him .
text2: Me ' kwacI e ' iItnankitok , pInI , e ' wase ' iak ankot okiiakwate ' shkumakwnawa pInI , okinotanawacI e ' notakwsInIt shi ankotuk ; otI kikItwun ; OtI ie ' o te ' panuk nkwIs me ' nonwe ' It ; psItak .

text: And when the disciples heard it , they fell on their face , and were sore afraid .
text2: Pic cI e ' knomowacIn kanot mowat kip , mukocInok shkishkowak e ' pic kwtacwat .

text: And Jesus came and touched them , and said , Arise , and be not afraid .
text2: Cisus cI okipie ' taknan otI cI , okinan , Psukwik , ipi ke ' ko kwtacke ' k .

text: And when they had lifted up their eyes , they saw no man , save Jesus only .
text2: Iw cI kantawapwat cowe ' iI ‘ kiwapmasiwan , nInI , mtIno CisusIn .

text: And as they came down from the mountain , Jesus charged them , saying , Tell the vision to no man , until the Son of man be risen again from the dead .
text2: IcI kapie ' niscowe ' wat shi e ' pkotnianuk Cisus okiiakwaman , otI cI okinan , ke ' ko we ' iI witmoake ' k nInI kanaptme ' k , pama , o We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kiwnIshkat minI ‘ e ' nponIt .

text: And his disciples asked him , saying , Why then say the scribes that Elias must first come ?
text2: E ' knomowacIn okinatakon , otI kikItwuk , TacI i we ' ckItwat ki - we ' npie ' ke ' cuk Inaius ne ' tum kupie ' ?

text: And Jesus answered and said unto them , Elias truly shall first come , and restore all things .
text2: Cisus cI okinkwe ' twan otI okinan Inaius we ' we ' nwI , ne ' tum kupie ' , cakicI ke ' ko okaocston .

text: But I say unto you , That Elias is come already , and they knew him not , but have done unto him whatsoever they listed . Likewise shall also the Son of man suffer of them .
text2: OtI cI ktInum , InaiusI shiI kipie ' cocI okike ' nmasiwan okitotwawancI e ' shwunwaciwat , winke ' o nasap We ' kwIsmukot NInwun okukwtuke ' ntumokon .

text: Then the disciples understood that he spake unto them of John the Baptist .
text2: IcI ni ke ' knomowacIn e ' kinsItakot e ' kitshImanIt ni CanIn ke ' ctapie ' we ' ncIm .

text: And when they were come to the multitude , there came to him a certain man , kneeling down to him , and saying ,
text2: Pic cI kapiawat e ' cIiInIt ni maoce ' tincIn , okipie ' naskakon nkot nInI kipie ' wucikwnItakon , otI cI okikon ;

text: Lord , have mercy on my son : for he is lunatick , and sore vexed : for ofttimes he falleth into the fire , and oft into the water .
text2: Te ' pe ' nmin shuwe ' numsI npIs , nkInkapitum , ipi wiwtawe ' ntum , nanakIc mukocIn shkote ' k , ipi nane ' kIc , shi npik ;

text: And I brought him to thy disciples , and they could not cure him .
text2: IcI e ' kipiatwukwa ke ' knomocuk cocu okikshkaasiwan e ' wine ' se ' awat .

text: Then Jesus answered and said , O faithless and perverse generation , how long shall I be with you ? how long shall I suffer you ? bring him hither to me .
text2: Cisus cI okinkwe ' twan ; otI cI okinan , O ! pwate ' pwe ' take ' ie ' k , ipi pwakwIiuk showe ' pse ' ie ' k pe ' matse ' e ' k tInicI pic ke ' kowice ' onukon ? tInicI pic , ke ' kowikwce ' ne ' kon ? pie ' tuwushuk shotI .

text: And Jesus rebuked the devil ; and he departed out of him : and the child was cured from that very hour .
text2: Cisus cI , okishuke ' nonan ni mIcImIne ' ton , icI e ' kisakuk , icI o pInoce ' e ' kine ' se ' t pic .

text: Then came the disciples to Jesus apart , and said , Why could not we cast him out ?
text2: IcI e ' kipie ' naskakot ni e ' knomowacIn ni CisusIn nshukI , otI cI okikon , TInicI ninan kaocI ianwakIt e ' wisakitInkIt ?

text: And Jesus said unto them , Because of your unbelief : for verily I say unto you , If ye have faith as a grain of mustard seed , ye shall say unto this mountain , Remove hence to yonder place ; and it shall remove ; and nothing shall be impossible unto you .
