text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , Osam sI e ' pwate ' pwe ' ie ' nte ' me ' k , We ' we ' nI , ktInum , KishkwIn otI shIt ‘ e ' te ' kwe ' ie ' ntume ' k ke ' cwa e ' opukomnanwuk i mastat , minkan , otI kitatanawa e ' pkotniak , owushi , shian , iwke ' nomkuk , coike ' ko ktaianwutosinawa .

text: Howbeit this kind goeth not out but by prayer and fasting .
text2: OtIsI e ' shnakwuk , copie ' sakumomkIsnon , pama ie ' k e ' numak , ipi e ' pwawisnuk .

text: And while they abode in Galilee , Jesus said unto them , The Son of man shall be betrayed into the hands of men :
text2: Me ' kwa cI e ' ie ' iuwat shi Ke ' nIniuk , Cisus otI okinan , We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kupkItnukaso shiw onIcinuk nInwun .

text: And they shall kill him , and the third day he shall be raised again . And they were exceeding sorry .
text2: OkInsawancI , icI nso kishkItnuk minI kaonIshke ' . IcI kikcI kisatantumwuk .

text: And when they were come to Capernaum , they that received tribute money came to Peter , and said , Doth not your master pay tribute ?
text2: IcI kapiawat Ke ' paniumuk ; kiwe ' tapnukuk maocIckate ' k shonia , kipie ' naskawawan ni PituIin , otI okinawan , ConI ke ' knomakwie ' k otupIsin i maocIcke ' wun ?

text: He saith , Yes . And when he was come into the house , Jesus prevented him , saying , What thinkest thou , Simon ? of whom do the kings of the earth take custom or tribute ? of their own children , or of strangers ?
text2: OtI cI okinan E ' ‘ IcI kapiat kanmupitike ' t , Cisus ne ' tum kiknonan , otI okinan ; TInicI e ' shte ' an Sayiman ? We ' ninIn shotI kik kiw okumak we ' tapnumwawat maocIcke ' wun ? nine ' , tupe ' nwe ' nicasawan , tanake ' , me ' mataosIncIn ?

text: Peter saith unto him , Of strangers . Jesus saith unto him , Then are the children free .
text2: Pitu cI otI okinan , me ' mataosincInsI ; Cisus cI otI okinan , Cocu pe ' noce ' iuk pame ' ntakwsusik .

text: Notwithstanding , lest we should offend them , go thou to the sea , and cast an hook , and take up the fish that first cometh up ; and when thou hast opened his mouth , thou shalt find a piece of money : that take , and give unto them for me and thee .
text2: NocmasI , e ' pwamshu nshku ‘ we ' ikon shian kcukimik , ipi kupukiton kwtImockIn , ipi kaotapina kikos ne ' tum kie ' kwtumonIt ; icI ke ' cI pakitone ' nIt kumkancI nkot wapuk shonia ; kaotapinan , ipi kaocIminak nin ipi kin .

text: At the same time came the disciples unto Jesus , saying , Who is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven ?
text2: ICI pic kipie ' naskakon ke ' knomocIk , ni CisusIn , otI cI , okinawan , We ' nicI wusimI e ' pite ' ntakwsIt shi okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok

text: And Jesus called a little child unto him , and set him in the midst of them ,
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kintomat e ' kacinIncIn pInoce ' iIn e ' cIiIt , icI nawiukwan e ' kicipitupat .

text: And said , Verily I say unto you , Except ye be converted , and become as little children , ye shall not enter into the kingdom of heaven .
text2: OtI cI kikito , We ' we ' nI ktInum KishpIn pwawe ' we ' nI ne ' ntume ' k , ipi e ' shwe ' psuwat pe ' piwsicIk pInoce ' iuk , co kupitike ' sim ; shi okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok .

text: Whosoever therefore shall humble himself as this little child , the same is greatest in the kingdom of heaven .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntukI ke ' shI kacwe ' ntumkwe ' n wia ‘ w ke ' cwa e ' kciIt pInoce ' oie ' o ke ' kcI pite ' ntakwsIt okumauwunuk shpumuk kishkok .

text: And whoso shall receive one such little child in my name receiveth me .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuke ' ke ' otapnakwe ' n nkot e ' kaciIt pInoce ' ntI ‘ noswunuk ntotapnuk Nin .

text: But whoso shall offend one of these little ones which believe in me , it were better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck , and that he were drowned in the depth of the sea .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuke ' , ke ' nkshaat nkot notI e ' kacinIncIn , te ' pwe ' ie ' nmIt , wusimI taowunIt win , potakIn sIn e ' wi napkuk , ipi wupukinIt e ' cIk mitmianuk kcukImik .

text: Woe unto the world because of offences ! for it must needs be that offences come ; but woe to that man by whom the offence cometh !
text2: Kwo kwansukumuk shotI kik , osam ni nshke ' ntuwunIn iw sI ke ' nomkuk e ' wipiamkuk nshke ' ntuwunIn kokwansukumuk cI onInIpie ' tot i nshke ' ntuwun .

text: Wherefore if thy hand or thy foot offend thee , cut them off , and cast them from thee : it is better for thee to enter into life halt or maimed , rather than having two hands or two feet to be cast into everlasting fire .
text2: KishpIn iknIc , tanake ' i ksIt , ocImiashtotmIn kishkshIn , ipi nkoci pukiton , wusimI wunIt , kin pitike ' n pmatsiwunuk knIce ' n , ipi ksIte ' n pnacak , icI i e ' wi in nish knIce ' n tanake ' ksIte ' n , icI e ' wipuke ' nukon kakuk shkote ' k .

text: And if thine eye offend thee , pluck it out , and cast it from thee : it is better for thee to enter into life with one eye , rather than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire .
text2: KishpIn ke ' ikshkishuk ocImiashtotmIn kcIpiton nkoci pukiton ; wusimI owunIt kin pitike ' n shi pmatsowunuk ; mtIno nkotuk kshkishuk , icI e ' wi - ion nish kshkishkwe ' n e ' wipukicikasiIn namkumuk shkote ' k .

text: Take heed that ye despise not one of these little ones ; for I say unto you , That in heaven their angels do always behold the face of my Father which is in heaven .
text2: Akwamsuk e ' wipwa ianwe ' nme ' k otI nkot e ' kaciIt , OtI ktInum , IpI shpumuk mishInwe ' mwan pIne ' ’ wapmawan shiw oshkishkonuk ni NosIn e ' ciIt shpumuk kishkok .

text: For the Son of man is come to save that which was lost .
text2: O We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kipie ' e ' wike ' skonat ni kakiwanincIn ,

text: How think ye ? if a man have an hundred sheep , and one of them be gone astray , doth he not leave the ninety and nine , and goeth into the mountains , and seeketh that which is gone astray ?
text2: TInicI e ' shte ' aie ' k ? KishpIn nInI iuwat nkotwak mantanshIn , icI nkot kiwaninIt , conI onukinasin ni shak tso mtInIshIshaka , icI e ' shiat shi e ' pmIkwtakiw onunuk , icI e ' pantawapmat ni kakiwanincIn .

text: And if so be that he find it , verily I say unto you , he rejoiceth more of that sheep , than of the ninety and nine which went not astray .
text2: KishpIn cI mkuwat , we ' we ' nI ktInum , wusimI su mciwe ' nmo ni nkot mantanshIn , icI ni shaktso mtInI shI shaka ; kapwakiwanincIn .

text: Even so it is not the will of your Father which is in heaven , that one of these little ones should perish .
text2: Iw sI nasap ; cowin otIne ' nmasin ; Koswa e ' iIt shpumuk , notI nkot e ' kacinIncIn e ' wipnatsInut .

text: Moreover if thy brother shall trespass against thee , go and tell him his fault between thee and him alone : if he shall hear thee , thou hast gained thy brother .
text2: MinI kishpIn kikane ' mIcitotakwiIn , shian , ipi witmo iw omIcshowe ' psowun te ' pnak kin , ipi win , nshukI kishpIn cI psItakwiIn ; kikshkaase ' kikane ' .

text: But if he will not hear thee , then take with thee one or two more , that in the mouth of two or three witnesses every word may be established .
text2: KishpIn kI pwapsItakwiIn moice ' o nkot tanake ' , nish , wusimI , icI winwa otukitowunawa ki nish , tanake ' nswI , ke ' ocI wishkIsuk i kitukitonuwan .

text: And if he shall neglect to hear them , tell it unto the church : but if he neglect to hear the church , let him be unto thee as an heathen man and a publican .
text2: KishpIn cI ni pwaopsItwat witmoki e ' cmaacIk , kishpIn cI pwapsItwat ni anmue ' ancIn , ne ' num ke ' cwa me ' mataosIt , ipi maocIcke ' onInI .

text: Verily I say unto you , Whatsoever ye shall bind on earth shall be bound in heaven : and whatsoever ye shall loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven .
text2: We ' we ' nI ktInum , We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' tkoptoie ' k shotI kik , shi ke ' tkopte ' shpumuk , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' iapskonme ' k shotI kik , ke ' iapskonkate ' shi shpumuk .

text: Again I say unto you , That if two of you shall agree on earth as touching any thing that they shall ask , it shall be done for them of my Father which is in heaven .
text2: MinI otI ktInum ; KishpIn nish kinwa ie ' ne ' ntume ' k shotI kik tshItme ' ke ' ko ; winwa ntotmowat iw ke ' nomkItnuk Nos e ' iIt , shpumuk kishkok .

text: For where two or three are gathered together in my name , there am I in the midst of them .
text2: KishpIn nish , tanake ' nswI , ocI maoce ' tiwat nin tnoswunuk shiw nkIiI nawi iukwan e ' ciiuwat .

text: Then came Peter to him , and said , Lord , how oft shall my brother sin against me , and I forgive him ? till seven times ?
text2: IcI Pitu okipie ' naskawan , otI cI okinan , Te ' pe ' nmin , TInicItsuk nikane ' miashtotwut icI nin , e ' wipone ' nmuk ? nashnI nouksuk ?

text: Jesus saith unto him , I say not unto thee , Until seven times : but , Until seventy times seven .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , otIsI cokite ' nse ' non nash nouktsuk , otIsI nush nouktsomtInI tsuk nouk .

text: Therefore is the kingdom of heaven likened unto a certain king , which would take account of his servants .
text2: OtIsI she ' nakwIt okumauwun shpumuk ke ' cwa kcI - okuma , ne ' twe ' nmat opmitakaimIn e ' witpukot .

text: And when he had begun to reckon , one was brought unto him , which owed him ten thousand talents .
text2: Pic cI wawe ' pktasot , nkot kipie ' twa mtatsuk mtatswak kcIshoniaiIn me ' snamakot .

text: But forasmuch as he had not to pay , his lord commanded him to be sold , and his wife , and children , and all that he had , and payment to be made .
text2: CocI ke ' ko okiiIsin e ' witpuwe ' k , Te ' pe ' nmukwocIn , kishawe ' win e ' witawe ' k ipi niwiwun , ipi onicanse ' iIn , ipi caye ' k ka ‘ tot icI e ' witpukate ' nuk iw , omIsInukIn .

text: The servant therefore fell down , and worshipped him , saying , Lord , have patience with me , and I will pay thee all .
text2: NicI pmitakaimIn okiowucikwnItakon , otI cI okinan , Te ' pe ' nmin nocma pwishIn , icI caye ' k kIshtpuon .

text: Then the lord of that servant was moved with compassion , and loosed him , and forgave him the debt .
text2: NicI te ' pe ' nmukwocIn , okishuwe ' nmukon , ipi okipkItnukon , icI e ' kiwe ' pne ' makot i me ' snamowat .

text: But the same servant went out , and found one of his fellowservants , which owed him an hundred pence : and he laid hands on him , and took him by the throat , saying , Pay me that thou owest .
text2: IcI o pmtaka e ' kisakuk , icI nkot e ' kimkawat wic pmitakaiIn kamsInamakot , nkotwak shomanke ' In , icI e ' kimackonat , e ' ki kpe ' ne ' we ' nat ; otI cI okinan , tpuoshIn me ' snumoiIn .

text: And his fellowservant fell down at his feet , and besought him , saying , Have patience with me , and I will pay thee all .
text2: IcI ni wic pmitakaiIn kipukson osItik , e ' kimatmat ; otI cI okinan , PwishIn icI caye ' k ke ' cI tpu ‘ onan .

text: And he would not : but went and cast him into prison , till he should pay the debt .
text2: Cocu papIsh , ikiwupitke ' we ' pnan shi kpakwotiwkomkok , i e ' witpu ukot i me ' sna ‘ makot .

text: So when his fellowservants saw what was done , they were very sorry , and came and told unto their lord all that was done .
text2: Pic cI ni wic pmitakaiIn kawaptumwat e ' totwumIt cicIkisate ' ntumwuk , icI e ' kinaskawawat , ipi okiwit mowawan , ni te ' pe ' nmukwacIn caye ' k katotwumIt ,

text: Then his lord , after that he had called him , said unto him , O thou wicked servant , I forgave thee all that debt , because thou desiredst me :
text2: IcI ni te ' pe ' nmukwcIn kakishntomkot otI okinan , O ! ke ' kie ' patsin pmitaka kipone ' ntumon caye ' k me ' snamoiIn , osam i kishIntawe ' num ,

text: Shouldest not thou also have had compassion on thy fellowservant , even as I had pity on thee ?
text2: ConukwnI ke ' kin i ktakishIshuwe ' nmasi , o kicpmitaka . nin kashIshuwe ' nme ' nan .

text: And his lord was wroth , and delivered him to the tormentors , till he should pay all that was due unto him .
text2: IcI ni te ' pe ' nmukwcIn kin shkatsin , ipi okipkItnumwan , ni ke ' tmakawe ' ncIn , pama kitpu ‘ uk caye ' k i kamsInamakwcIn .

text: So likewise shall my heavenly Father do also unto you , if ye from your hearts forgive not every one his brother their trespasses .
text2: Iwsuke ' win nasap shpumuk Nos , ke ' totakwie ' k , kishpIn kte ' iwak pwapone ' ntumwe ' k cak kikane ' iwa me ' ctotakwie ' k .

text: And it came to pass , that when Jesus had finished these sayings , he departed from Galilee , and came into the coasts of Judaea beyond Jordan ;
text2: Iw kashowe ' puk pic Cisus kakishkitot , shi kiwcImaci Ke ' ne ' niuk , icI e ' kishiat e ' kokmukwe ' anak Cwtie ' uk e ' shwIiokwan Catanuk .

text: And great multitudes followed him ; and he healed them there .
text2: Kicmaoce ' tincIn cI okpmInashkakon ; shiwcI okine ' se ' an .

text: The Pharisees also came unto him , tempting him , and saying unto him , Is it lawful for a man to put away his wife for every cause ?
text2: KicI kI Pe ' nisiuk kipie ' naskakon , e ' wikwcI te ' pe ' nmawat , otI cI okinawan ; Ta ‘ wunItnI nInI we ' pinat wiwun cak ke ' ko ?

text: And he answered and said unto them , Have ye not read , that he which made them at the beginning made them male and female ,
text2: Okinkwe ' twe ' ncI , otI okinan , conu wikakwaptusinawa , mIsInukInuk win kaoshaat ne ' tum okiwshuan nInIwun ipi kwe ' n .

text: And said , For this cause shall a man leave father and mother , and shall cleave to his wife : and they twain shall be one flesh ?
text2: OtI kakItot iw ie ' i nInI ke ' ocI nkInat , osun ipi okie ' iIn ; icI ke ' cI iuwat wiwun , ipi e ' nishwawat kInkot nInI otIwiasmawa .

text: Wherefore they are no more twain , but one flesh . What therefore God hath joined together , let not man put asunder .
text2: IwcI ie ' i we ' cpwanishwawat , mtIno nkotnInI otI wiasmawa ; IwcI Kshe ' mIne ' to kanishostot coin ntoac nInI okupapkie ' ptosin .

text: They say unto him , Why did Moses then command to give a writing of divorcement , and to put her away ?
text2: OtI cI okinawan , TacI Mosus kashukatokie ' t e ' wiminkIt we ' npie ' kate ' k msInukIn icI e ' wiwe ' pnukIt .

text: He saith unto them , Moses because of the hardness of your hearts suffered you to put away your wives : but from the beginning it was not so .
text2: OtI cI okinan , E ' iwishkiaksIni kte ' ‘ iwan , Mosus kaocI ne ' nmukwie ' k e ' wiwe ' pne ' k kiwuwak ; ke ' i ! aie ' k coi konomkIsnon .

text: And I say unto you , Whosoever shall put away his wife , except it be for fornication , and shall marry another , committeth adultery : and whoso marrieth her which is put away doth commit adultery .
text2: NincI ktInum , We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' we ' pnakwan wiwun , kishpIn pwa waonIshkawanIt okwe ' ipi pe ' kansIncIn wiwut waonIshkaiwI , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' owiwkwe ' n niwe ' pnukasnIt win waonIshkaiwI .

text: His disciples say unto him , If the case of the man be so with his wife , it is not good to marry .
text2: E ' knomowacIn otI okikon , KishpIn wIiI showe ' ‘ psIt otI nInI ni wiwun ; cota owunse ' non e ' wiwiwuk .

text: But he said unto them , All men cannot receive this saying , save they to whom it is given .
text2: OtI cI okinan , Caye ' k nInwuk co otaotapnIsinawa , otI kikitowun ; mtIno ki ke ' mincIk .

text: For there are some eunuchs , which were so born from their mother ' s womb : and there are some eunuchs , which were made eunuchs of men : and there be eunuchs , which have made themselves eunuchs for the kingdom of heaven ' s sake . He that is able to receive it , let him receive it .
text2: AnIt ionukuk kishI nikwuk , kashu nikukwat okie ' owan , ipi anIt ionukuk kiwshiak ionukuk ni nInwun , ipi anIt ionukuk okiwshItonawa wiwuwa ionukuk , shpumukcI okumauwun , we ' ctotatsowat , Win ke ' kshkItot wiwtapnuk , nocma okaotapnan .

text: Then were there brought unto him little children , that he should put his hands on them , and pray : and the disciples rebuked them .
text2: IcI e ' kipie ' twawat akacinIncIn pInoce ' iIn e ' wipkItnuk , niw onIce ' n wiwunuk , ipi e ' winumat , icI ni ke ' knomowacIn ; okimiashknonawan .

text: But Jesus said , Suffer little children , and forbid them not , to come unto me : for of such is the kingdom of heaven .
text2: OtI cI Cisus kikIto , Nocma pkItnuk ki pe ' piwsicuk pInoce ' iuk , ipi ke ' ko knumoake ' kon e ' wipie ' naskawat , iwkshe ' e ' shnakwuk okumauwun shpumuk kishkok .

text: And he laid his hands on them , and departed thence .
text2: IcI e ' kipkItnuk nione ' ce ' n wiwunuk , kinmamacicI .

text: And , behold , one came and said unto him , Good Master , what good thing shall I do , that I may have eternal life ?
text2: PInI cI , nkot okipie ' naskakon , ipi otI , okikon Manoshuwe ' psin Ke ' knomake ' n ; we ' kwnicI ke ' totman we ' onuk e ' wikshkItoian , kake ' pmatsowun ?

text: And he said unto him , Why callest thou me good ? there is none good but one , that is , God : but if thou wilt enter into life , keep the commandments .
text2: IcI otI okinan , TacI we ' tshInkashiIn me ' noshuwe ' psin ? Cosuwi wIiI mnoshuwe ' psusi , mtIno nkot , ocI Kshe ' mIne ' to : kishpIn , wiwikwcIpitike ' n shi pmatsonuk nakitowe ' ntum ni okukie ' kwe ' wunun .

text: He saith unto him , Which ? Jesus said , Thou shalt do no murder , Thou shalt not commit adultery , Thou shalt not steal , Thou shalt not bear false witness ,
text2: OtI cI okinan , TIninIncI ni ? Cisus cI okikito , Ke ' ko nshowe ' kIn ; Ke ' ko , waonIshkaiwukIn , Ke ' ko kmotkIn , Ke ' ko wIiI knoshkacimakIn ;

text: Honour thy father and thy mother : and , Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself .
text2: KcIpite ' num Kos ipi kie ' ‘ , ipi Tpash kic pmatsi , e ' pic tpantIsiun .

text: The young man saith unto him , All these things have I kept from my youth up : what lack I yet ?
text2: OcI oshkInwe ' otI okinan , Caye ' ksI notI , kapie ' shIcke ' ian e ' kopie ' kishkiian , We ' kwnicI nowate ' shIcke ' ian .

text: Jesus said unto him , If thou wilt be perfect , go and sell that thou hast , and give to the poor , and thou shalt have treasure in heaven : and come and follow me .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan ; KishpIn waowike ' swune ' n , shian , ipi tawe ' n e ' ton icI kuminak ke ' tmakse ' cuk ; te ' pe ' nwe ' osawun ke ' iIn , ipI shpumuk , ipi pie ' pmInashkaoshIn .

text: But when the young man heard that saying , he went away sorrowful : for he had great possessions .
text2: NIsh cI o oshkInwe ' kanotuk ; i kItwun ; kin mamaci kikisate ' ntum , osam kikcI tpe ' nwe ' osI .

text: Then said Jesus unto his disciples , Verily I say unto you , That a rich man shall hardly enter into the kingdom of heaven .
text2: IcI kanat Cisus ni e ' knomowacIn , We ' we ' nI ktInum , ke ' ctpe ' nwe ' osIt nshnI kawa okIshkiton e ' wipitike ' t shi okumau wunuk shpumuk .

text: And again I say unto you , It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle , than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God .
text2: MinI otI ktInum , WusimI tawe ' npInsI o kcIwe ' si shipanote ' t e ' wankoianuk , shapnukIn , icI ke ' ctpe ' nwe ' osIt nInI e ' wipitike ' t shiw otokumauwunuk Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: When his disciples heard it , they were exceedingly amazed , saying , Who then can be saved ?
text2: IcI ni kiknomowacIn , kanotmowat kikcImamkate ' ntumwuk , otI kikItwuk , We ' nicI ke ' ke ' skwit ?

text: But Jesus beheld them , and said unto them , With men this is impossible ; but with God all things are possible .
text2: Cisus cI okiwapman , ipi otI okinan , NInwuk sI , co otI otakshkItosinawa , winie ' k , Kshe ' mIne ' to cake ' ko otakshkIton .

text: Then answered Peter and said unto him , Behold , we have forsaken all , and followed thee ; what shall we have therefore ?
text2: IcI e ' kinkwe ' twat Pitu ipi otI okinan PInI ninan nkinkItamIn caye ' k , icI e ' kipmnashkonkon : We ' knicI ke ' ie ' iak ?

text: And Jesus said unto them , Verily I say unto you , That ye which have followed me , in the regeneration when the Son of man shall sit in the throne of his glory , ye also shall sit upon twelve thrones , judging the twelve tribes of Israel .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , We ' we ' nI ktInum Kinwa pie ' pmnashkawie ' k shi iacnikiItiwnuk , pic We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kicipitupIt , shiw ome ' nwankocipitupwunuk ; kinwa ke ' kcipitupum mtatso shIntInish cipitupwukwuk tpakwne ' k ki mtatso shIntInish e ' tswe ' nkIswat Isniuk .

text: And every one that hath forsaken houses , or brethren , or sisters , or father , or mother , or wife , or children , or lands , for my name ' s sake , shall receive an hundredfold , and shall inherit everlasting life .
text2: E ' tshuwat , ki kankItikuk e ' tawacIn tanaka , wikae ' iIn , tanake ' omIse ' iIn , tanake ' osIn , tanake ' okie ' iIn , tanaka wiwun , tanake ' onicansIn , tanaka otukim , nin ocInkItmowat , ntInoswunuk , oke ' ie ' nawa nkotwak tso , ipi oke ' ie ' nawa ke ' ciiuwat kake ' pmatsowunuk .

text: But many that are first shall be last ; and the last shall be first .
text2: NIsh cI kumane ' k kie ' ne ' tumIscuk kiw kIshkwIshnok ; ipi ki kIshkwIshkuk kne ' tmIshnok .

text: For the kingdom of heaven is like unto a man that is an householder , which went out early in the morning to hire labourers into his vineyard .
text2: OTI sI okumauwun shpumuk e ' shnakwuk ke ' cwa nInI katpe ' ntuk wikwam , kasakuk kukishie ' p e ' winokanat wamice ' witakwcIn , shiw siwnokamshu ktukanuk .

text: And when he had agreed with the labourers for a penny a day , he sent them into his vineyard .
text2: Pic cI kanat ni makicIwincIn , nkot shInIn e ' kishkiwuk , okikatonan shi siwnokamshu ktukanuk .

text: And he went out about the third hour , and saw others standing idle in the marketplace ,
text2: IcI e ' kimacit cI , e ' iaptu naokwe ' nuk icI e ' kiwapmat pakansIncIn e ' nipwunIt , ke ' ko e ' pwamiktumnIt shiw e ' tshitatuk .

text: And said unto them ; Go ye also into the vineyard , and whatsoever is right I will give you . And they went their way .
text2: IcI otI okinan . Shiak ke ' kinwa , shiw siwnokamshI ktukanuk , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' shI wunuk , i ke ' shIminukon . IcI e ' kimaciwat .

text: Again he went out about the sixth and ninth hour , and did likewise .
text2: MinI Kimaci naokwe ' nuk , ipi kaiaptosanuk icI nasap kishIcke ' .

text: And about the eleventh hour he went out , and found others standing idle , and saith unto them , Why stand ye here all the day idle ?
text2: NkotupukIn e ' pwamshu pkIshmok kishie ' wak , ipi okimkawan anIt e ' ni powe ' nIt ke ' ko e ' pwamiktumnIt , icI otI okinan , We ' kwnicI shotI we ' cnipoie ' k ne ' ie ' kIn ke ' ko e ' pwamiktme ' k ?

text: They say unto him , Because no man hath hired us . He saith unto them , Go ye also into the vineyard ; and whatsoever is right , that shall ye receive .
text2: OtI cI okikon , osam cowIiI nInI nokankosinan . IcI otI okinan , Shiak , ke ' kinwa shi siwnokamshI ktukanuk ; we ' we ' nIcI ke ' pite ' ntakwtokwe ' n kuke ' ie ' nawa .

text: So when even was come , the lord of the vineyard saith unto his steward , Call the labourers , and give them their hire , beginning from the last unto the first .
text2: PamacI pic , e ' nmupkonianuk , te ' pe ' ntuk , i siwnokamshu ktukan otI okinan , ni pmitakaimIn ; Ntom ki makice ' wicuk mish ke ' shkitowat , shkwe ' iak o kapiat tpa ‘ o ne ' tum icI o ne ' tum kapiat shkwe ' iak tpa ‘ o .

text: And when they came that were hired about the eleventh hour , they received every man a penny .
text2: Pic kapishiawat kikanokancuk nkot tpukIn e ' pwamshI pkIshmok , e ' tshawat kiminak nkot shInIn .

text: But when the first came , they supposed that they should have received more ; and they likewise received every man a penny .
text2: Pic cI kapiIshawat ne ' ptum , kanokancuk wusimI nkuminkomIn kine ' ntum wuk . winwa ke ' nasap kiminak e ' tshawat nInI nkot shInIn .

text: And when they had received it , they murmured against the goodman of the house ,
text2: IcI kakIshminkowat , okimto ‘ mawan me ' noshuwe ' psIncIn ni nInwun , we ' tu wikwamnIncIn .

text: Saying , These last have wrought but one hour , and thou hast made them equal unto us , which have borne the burden and heat of the day .
text2: OtI kikItwuk , KotI shkwe ' iak kimikce ' wik , mtIno nkot tpukIn , icI kin kiie ' i naoshiImIn ninancI , wi nkipi ke ' ie ' kwsImIn , shi e ' wiskate ' k e ' kishkiwuk .

text: But he answered one of them , and said , Friend , I do thee no wrong : didst not thou agree with me for a penny ?
text2: Okinkwe ' twancI ninkit , otI okinan , Nikan , cosuwi kimiashtotosnon , conukwI kiwnwacisi e ' witponan , nkot shInIn ?

text: Take that thine is , and go thy way : I will give unto this last , even as unto thee .
text2: OtapnIn te ' pe ' ntumIn , ipi macin . Nkumina ote ' shkwe ' iak pie ' mikce ' wit kin kashuminan .

text: Is it not lawful for me to do what I will with mine own ? Is thine eye evil , because I am good ?
text2: ConI owunse ' non nin e ' wi totman e ' shte ' aian te ' pe ' ntuman ? InI kshkishuk we ' cmiashu we ' psinkuk , osam nin e ' mnoshuwe ' pse ' an ?

text: So the last shall be first , and the first last : for many be called , but few chosen .
text2: Kisu shkwe ' iak kne ' tmIswuk , ipi ki ne ' tum shkwe ' iak ; anwu mce ' shntomak nIshce ' pke ' ci we ' napcIkaswuk ,

text: And Jesus going up to Jerusalem took the twelve disciples apart in the way , and said unto them ,
text2: Cisus cI e ' nmapiskat e ' ishat Cinose ' numuk , okimacinan ni mtatso shItnish ke ' knomowacIn , icI e ' nmInshIke ' osawat e ' nmIshiawat , otI okinan .

text: Behold , we go up to Jerusalem ; and the Son of man shall be betrayed unto the chief priests and unto the scribes , and they shall condemn him to death ,
text2: PInI , ktIshamIn ipI Cinose ' ne ' muk , icI We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kupkItna shi kcI me ' matmocuk ipi ki we ' npie ' ke ' ncIn , icI ke ' cI pkIte ' nmawat e ' winsIckasnIt .

text: And shall deliver him to the Gentiles to mock , and to scourge , and to crucify him : and the third day he shall rise again .
text2: OkupkItnumwawancI , ni me ' mataosIncIn e ' winaptotwanIt , ipi e ' wipsItie ' wanIt , ipi e ' wiskakwukasnIt , icI nso kishkuk minI kupsukwi .

text: Then came to him the mother of Zebedee ' s children with her sons , worshipping him , and desiring a certain thing of him .
text2: IcI e ' kipie ' naskakot niw kie ' iwan ni Se ' piti nicansIn , okipie ' wice ' okon ni okwIsIn , e ' pie ' owuciwkwnItakot e ' ntuwe ' ntumakot ke ' ko .

text: And he said unto her , What wilt thou ? She saith unto him , Grant that these my two sons may sit , the one on thy right hand , and the other on the left , in thy kingdom .
text2: OtI cI okinan , We ' kwnicI ne ' twe ' ntumIn ? OtI cI okinan , Ne ' num , kotI nish nkwIsuk , e ' wicipitupwat , nkot kte ' pniwnak , ipi o nkot knumciwnak , shiw ktokumauwunuk .

text: But Jesus answered and said , Ye know not what ye ask . Are ye able to drink of the cup that I shall drink of , and to be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with ? They say unto him , We are able .
text2: Cisus cI okinkwe ' twan , otI kikIto , CosI kuke ' ntusinawa ne ' totmoie ' k , KtakshkItonawanI e ' wimnukwe ' ie ' k shi mnukwackInuk , nin watshumnukwe ' ian , ipi e ' wi kcitapie ' nkoie ' k i kcitapie ' nwe ' wun , e ' shIkcitapie ' nkoian . OtI ci okinawan ntakshkItomInsI .

text: And he saith unto them , Ye shall drink indeed of my cup , and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with : but to sit on my right hand , and on my left , is not mine to give , but it shall be given to them for whom it is prepared of my Father .
text2: IcI otI okinan . We ' we ' nIsI kamnukwe ' nawa i nmInkwackIn , ipi kukcitapie ' nkom , i kcitapie ' nwe ' wun e ' sh kcitapie ' nkoian , icI ie ' k e ' wi cipitupie ' k shi nte ' pniwnak , ipi numciwnak coin nin i ntpe ' ntusin e ' wimikwian , kisie ' k kuminak e ' twaknukwacIn Nos .

text: And when the ten heard it , they were moved with indignation against the two brethren .
text2: Pic cI ki mtatso kanotmoat , okinsItawe ' nmawan , ni nish we ' wikane ' itIncIn .

text: But Jesus called them unto him , and said , Ye know that the princes of the Gentiles exercise dominion over them , and they that are great exercise authority upon them .
text2: Cisus cI okintoman e ' ciIt , otI kikIto , Kuke ' nmawaksI ki okumak ki Me ' mataose ' cuk , otI tpakwnukwan ; ipi cIki ke ' cne ' ntakwse ' cuk okIcnapne ' nkwan .

text: But it shall not be so among you : but whosoever will be great among you , let him be your minister ;
text2: Cocu wi kinwa a knomkIsnon ; we ' kwe ' ntuk kinwa ke ' kcine ' ntakwsukwe ' n , oie ' o , nocma win kupmitakwa .

text: And whosoever will be chief among you , let him be your servant :
text2: We ' kwe ' ntukI kinwa ke ' okumaokwe ' n ; nocma win kupmitakwa .

text: Even as the Son of man came not to be ministered unto , but to minister , and to give his life a ransom for many .
text2: Ie ' inomkIt ke ' cwa We ' kwIsmukot NInwun e ' ki pwapie ' pmitwut ; mtIno e ' kipie ' pmitake ' t , ipi e ' wimikoe ' t , opmatsuwun e ' witpuke ' t ni mane ' ncIn .

text: And as they departed from Jericho , a great multitude followed him .
text2: Pic cI e ' nmumaciwat Cunikoiuk ; ke ' cmaoce ' tincIn , okipmInashkakon ,

text: And , behold , two blind men sitting by the way side , when they heard that Jesus passed by , cried out , saying , Have mercy on us , O Lord , thou Son of David .
text2: PInI , nish ke ' kie ' pikwancIn nInwun , e ' cipitupnIt cikimie ' w kanotake ' wat , ni CisusIn e ' pmose ' nIt kinotaksik , otI kikItwuk , Shuwe ' nmIshInak O Te ' pe ' nmiak , We ' kwIsmukwiIn Te ' pIt .

text: And the multitude rebuked them , because they should hold their peace : but they cried the more , saying , Have mercy on us , O Lord , thou Son of David .
text2: KicI maoce ' ticIk okiknuumowawan , e ' wi tokmupinIt ; wusimIcI kinotaksik otI kikItwuk , Shuwe ' nmIshInak O Te ' pe ' nmiak We ' kwIsmukwiIn Te ' pIt .

text: And Jesus stood still , and called them , and said , What will ye that I shall do unto you ?
text2: IcI Cisus tokum , e ' kinipwIt , ipi okintomat , otI okinan , We ' kwnicI pe ' kose ' nmie ' k , i watotonkon ?

text: They say unto him , Lord , that our eyes may be opened .
text2: OtI cI okikon , Te ' pe ' nmiak , notI nshkishkonanIn e ' winsakwnImIn .

text: So Jesus had compassion on them , and touched their eyes : and immediately their eyes received sight , and they followed him .
text2: IcI Cisus okishuwe ' nman , ipi okitaknumwan , niw shkishkonIn , icI papuk e ' kintawapwat , ipi okipmInashkakon .

text: And when they drew nigh unto Jerusalem , and were come to Bethphage , unto the mount of Olives , then sent Jesus two disciples ,
text2: PIC cI pe ' shoc e ' nme ' iawat Cinose ' numuk shi kapiawat Pe ' pe ' ciuk , shi e ' pkotniak AnIpiuk , icI Cisus e ' ki nokanat nish ke ' knomowacIn ;

text: Saying unto them , Go into the village over against you , and straightway ye shall find an ass tied , and a colt with her : loose them , and bring them unto me .
text2: OtI cI okinan , Shiak sI shi otane ' suk wusoci iukwan e ' ie ' k kie ' nup cI kumkuwawa me ' makshe ' e ' tkopsot , ipi ne ' makshe ' sun , e ' wickapwItwat , iapskopinuk , icI ke ' cI pie ' twe ' ie ' k .

text: And if any man say ought unto you , ye shall say , The Lord hath need of them ; and straightway he will send them .
text2: KishpIn cI wIiI nInI , ke ' ko koie ' k ; otI knawa , Te ' pe ' nke ' t onItwe ' nman , icI papuk kupkIte ' ntumakwa .

text: All this was done , that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet , saying ,
text2: Caye ' ksI otI kitotam , e ' wite ' pwe ' wunukuk kakitot Nakanacimot otI kItwak .

text: Tell ye the daughter of Sion , Behold , thy King cometh unto thee , meek , and sitting upon an ass , and a colt the foal of an ass .
text2: Witomouk otansun , Sayan , PInI kitokumam , kupie ' naskak , kacwe ' nmo e ' pie ' tomkot me ' makshe ' iIn , ipi me ' makshe ' sIn , we ' nicansumacIn me ' makshe ' .

text: And the disciples went , and did as Jesus commanded them ,
text2: Kimacik cI ni ke ' knomawacIn , icI kiwIshIcke ' k Cisus kanat .

text: And brought the ass , and the colt , and put on them their clothes , and they set him thereon .
text2: Okipie ' nawancI ni me ' makshe ' iIn , ipi ni me ' makshe ' sIn , okitonawancI paskumwacIn ; icI kwuciukwan e ' ki cipitupawat .

text: And a very great multitude spread their garments in the way ; others cut down branches from the trees , and strawed them in the way .
text2: Ke ' cmaoce ' ticuk cI , okishuwe ' ksItonawan opiskumwaknawan shi mie ' wuk anItkI okikishktukwne ' anawan ni mtukwe ' n , icI e ' kipukitowat shi mie ' wuk .

text: And the multitudes that went before , and that followed , cried , saying , Hosanna to the Son of David : Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord ; Hosanna in the highest .
text2: IcI ki maoce ' ticIk kanmI nikanicIk , ipi kanmupme ' nashkawacuk , kinmI wishkwe ' we ' ksik , otI kikItwuk , Ke ' skonwe ' n We ' kwIsmukwiIn , Te ' pIt Mnawankose ' o , pie ' iat otunoswunuk Kshe ' mIne ' ton , Nocma kinwusimI ke ' skonwe ' n !

text: And when he was come into Jerusalem , all the city was moved , saying , Who is this ?
text2: Pic kapiat shi Cinose ' numuk ; caye ' k shi kaicuk kcI otanuk kimacik , otI kikItwuk , We ' nicI otI ?

text: And the multitude said , This is Jesus the prophet of Nazareth of Galilee .
text2: KicI maoce ' ticuk kikItwuk , Cisus sI otI Nakanacimot we ' cpiat , Ne ' se ' nut iukwanuk Ke ' niniuk .

text: And Jesus went into the temple of God , and cast out all them that sold and bought in the temple , and overthrew the tables of the moneychangers , and the seats of them that sold doves ,
text2: Cisus cI kipitike ' , Kshe ' mIne ' to okIcnume ' okumkok , okisakicuwe ' pnancI , caye ' k e ' tawe ' n cIn , ipi kashpInItasnIncIn , shi kcI nume ' okumkok ipi okikwe ' npowe ' pnanIn ni topwonIn , e ' icuk iashtonkuk shonia , ipi ki otuptie ' pwunwan , e ' tawe ' cuk , ni mIne ' to mimin .

text: And said unto them , It is written , My house shall be called the house of prayer ; but ye have made it a den of thieves .
text2: OtI cI okinan , OtI kikishnupie ' kate ' e ' taian kshInkate ' e ' tshu nume ' okumuk ; kinwa cI kmotiwkumuk kiwshItonawa .

text: And the blind and the lame came to him in the temple ; and he healed them .
text2: Ke ' kie ' pikwacuk , ipi me ' akatacuk okipie ' naskakon , shi kcInume ' okumkok icI e ' kine ' se ' at .

text: And when the chief priests and scribes saw the wonderful things that he did , and the children crying in the temple , and saying , Hosanna to the Son of David ; they were sore displeased ,
text2: IcI ki kcI - me ' matmocIk , ipi we ' npie ' ke ' cIk kawapitumwawat , i kashumataocIke ' nIt , ipi pInoce ' iIn ; e ' wIshkwe ' we ' ksInIt shi kcI - nume ' okumkok , ipi otI e ' kItwat , Ke ' skonwe ' n We ' kwIsmukwiIn o Te ' pIt ; icI kikcIn shke ' ntumwuk .

text: And said unto him , Hearest thou what these say ? And Jesus saith unto them , Yea ; have ye never read , Out of the mouth of babes and sucklings thou hast perfected praise ?
text2: OtI cI okikon , KnotwaknukotI e ' kItowat , icI Cisus otI okinan ; E ' ; Conu wikakwaptIsinawa e ' shpie ' kate ' k misInukIn ; Shiw otoniwak ki pInoce ' ie ' k , ipi nwancuk , kitockishton kwiuk winwate ' ntumwun .

text: And he left them , and went out of the city into Bethany ; and he lodged there .
text2: OkinknancI , kiw cI maci shi kcIotanuk e ' kishiat Pe ' te ' ne ' iuk , icI shi e ' kikIshIt .

text: Now in the morning as he returned into the city , he hungered .
text2: IcI e ' kishie ' pwunuk , ne ' iap e ' nmupiskat , e ' shiat shi kcIotanuk kipkIte ' ,

text: And when he saw a fig tree in the way , he came to it , and found nothing thereon , but leaves only , and said unto it , Let no fruit grow on thee henceforward for ever . And presently the fig tree withered away .
text2: Pic cI e ' wapmat kcI siwnokamIshe ' n shiw kpumie ' kIn , okinaskawan , cocI ke ' ko okimkusin mtIno tukupukwe ' n , otI cI okishitan , Cowi ka minI kumicImosi . IcI kie ' nup kcI siwnokamIsh kinpopkIso .

text: And when the disciples saw it , they marvelled , saying , How soon is the fig tree withered away !
text2: IcI ki kiknomowacIn kawaptumwat , kimamkate ' ntumwuk , otIcI kikItwuk , TInicI kie ' nup otI kcI SiwnokamIsh e ' sh npopkIsot .

text: Jesus answered and said unto them , Verily I say unto you , If ye have faith , and doubt not , ye shall not only do this which is done to the fig tree , but also if ye shall say unto this mountain , Be thou removed , and be thou cast into the sea ; it shall be done .
text2: Cisus cI okinkwe ' twan otI ikinan , We ' we ' nI ktInum , KishpIn ie ' ie ' k i te ' pwe ' we ' ntumwun , ipi pwaianwe ' ntusie ' k , cowi otI kashIcke ' sin , katotwut otI kcIsiwno kamIsh ike ' kishpIn ke ' itume ' k otI e ' pkotniak , KikshkansI , ipi wupukson shi kcukumik , ike ' nomkuk .

text: And all things , whatsoever ye shall ask in prayer , believing , ye shall receive .
text2: Ipi cak ke ' ko we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' ntotmowe ' kwe ' n numaie ' k , te ' pwe ' ie ' ntume ' k iwsu ke ' shuminkoie ' k .

text: And when he was come into the temple , the chief priests and the elders of the people came unto him as he was teaching , and said , By what authority doest thou these things ? and who gave thee this authority ?
text2: Pic cI kapitike ' t shi kcI - nume ' okumkok , ki kcI me ' matmocIk ipi ki oke ' ctaosunmwan kinIshInape ' k , kipie ' naskakon , me ' kwa e ' ie ' kinomake ' t , otI cI okinawan , TInipi we ' tnumIn , otI wishkIswun otI e ' shIcke ' n ? We ' ni cI ke ' kaminkon otI wishkIswun ? .

text: And Jesus answered and said unto them , I also will ask you one thing , which if ye tell me , I in like wise will tell you by what authority I do these things .
text2: IcI Cisus okinkwe ' twan otI cI okinan , Ninke ' kInatonum nkot ke ' ko ; kishpIn cI witmoie ' k , ninke ' kuwitmonum we ' tnuman otI wishkIswun we ' ctotman .

text: The baptism of John , whence was it ? from heaven , or of men ? And they reasoned with themselves , saying , If we shall say , From heaven ; he will say unto us , Why did ye not then believe him ?
text2: Iw kIctapie ' nwe ' wun o Can ; tInipi cI we ' piamkuk , shpumukinI tanake ' nInik ? IcI e ' kinatatwat otI kikItwuk , KishpIn otI kItie ' kon , shpumuk sI otI kukonan , TacIshIna kapwao cI te ' pwe ' twe ' k .

text: But if we shall say , Of men ; we fear the people ; for all hold John as a prophet .
text2: KishpIn cI kItie ' kon ; ni nInwun , kokwIsamIn ki nIshInape ' k , osam caye ' k ote ' ne ' nmawan ni CanIn ke ' cwa nakanacimot .

text: And they answered Jesus , and said , We cannot tell . And he said unto them , Neither tell I you by what authority I do these things .
text2: Okinkwe ' twawan cI ni CisusIn , otI okinawan , co nkuke ' ntusimIn ; icI otI okinan ; Cosu ke ' nin ku ‘ witmosnonum , otI we ' tnaman ot nwishkIswun we ' k totman otI .

text: But what think ye ? A certain man had two sons ; and he came to the first , and said , Son , go work to day in my vineyard .
text2: TInicI e ' ne ' ntume ' k ? Nkot nInI kinish win , okwIsun icI e ' kinaskawIt , ni ke ' ctaosincIn , otI cI okinan , NkwIs , wumikice ' win e ' kom e ' kishkiwuk , shi nsiwonokamshI ktukanuk .

text: He answered and said , I will not : but afterward he repented , and went .
text2: Okinkwe ' twan cI , otI okikon , Coin ; icI shkIc kikisate ' ntum , icI e ' kishiat .

text: And he came to the second , and said likewise . And he answered and said , I go , sir : and went not .
text2: Okinaskawan cI ni e ' kacinIncIn , icI nasapkinan , icI okinkwe ' twan otI okikon , NkIshia sI Nos , cocI kishie ' si .

text: Whether of them twain did the will of his father ? They say unto him , The first . Jesus saith unto them , Verily I say unto you , That the publicans and the harlots go into the kingdom of God before you .
text2: We ' nicI , ki nish kashIcke ' t osIn kashIntuwe ' n mukot ? OtI cI okinawan ; Ke ' ctaosItsI . Cisus cI otI okinan , We ' we ' nI ktInum , kimaocIke ' onInwuk , ipi kiwaonIshkaiuk , kupitike ' k otokumauwunuk Kshe ' mIne ' to kinwa e ' pwamshu pitike ' ie ' k .

text: For John came unto you in the way of righteousness , and ye believed him not : but the publicans and the harlots believed him : and ye , when ye had seen it , repented not afterward , that ye might believe him .
text2: Can kipie ' kuke ' nakakwa i , we ' we ' nI shiwe ' psowun , co cI nIsh kite ' pwe ' twasiwa ; kicI wi maocIshke ' onInwuk , ipi ki waonIshkaiuk kite ' pwe ' twawan , icI kinwa kakish waptume ' k , co kikisate ' ntusinI i e ' wite ' pwe ' twe ' k .

text: Hear another parable : There was a certain householder , which planted a vineyard , and hedged it round about , and digged a winepress in it , and built a tower , and let it out to husbandmen , and went into a far country :
text2: PsItumok , minI nkot iacimowIn , Ke ' iapI nkot we ' towikwamIt kaktukatuk , siwnokamIsh ktukan , ipi okiwakaan , kiwtaiukwan , ipi okiwankatan watsho oshItot shomnapo , ipi kiwshIton wikwam e ' shpianuk , okiwaancI ktukie ' wunInwan , icI pe ' noc e ' ki shumacit , otanuk .

text: And when the time of the fruit drew near , he sent his servants to the husbandmen , that they might receive the fruits of it .
text2: Cikiaukwan cI pic e ' wikishkInuk i micum , okinokanan opmitakiamIn e ' ci iInIt ni ktukie ' onInwun e ' wi wtapnumwat i micum .

text: And the husbandmen took his servants , and beat one , and killed another , and stoned another .
text2: KicI ktukie ' onInwuk okimshunawan , niw opmitakaimIn , nkot cI ni okipsItie ' wawan , icI nkot cI niw okinsawan , ipi nkot sInie ' n okipkamawan .

text: Again , he sent other servants more than the first : and they did unto them likewise .
text2: MinI pe ' kansIncIn , okinokanan opmitakaimIn wusimI ni kitshin , icI ni ne ' tum nasap cI , ke ' niw kitotwawan .

text: But last of all he sent unto them his son , saying , They will reverence my son .
text2: Shkwe ' iak cI , okinokanan ni okwIsun , otI cI kikIto , Okupite ' nmawan sI nkwIsun .

text: But when the husbandmen saw the son , they said among themselves , This is the heir ; come , let us kill him , and let us seize on his inheritance .
text2: Pic cI ki ktukie ' onInwuk kawapmawat ni okwIsnInIn otI kinItwuk , OtI sie ' o shakwune ' t ; aw nsatan , kinan cI ke ' tpe ' ntamIn i te ' pe ' ntukipIn .

text: And they caught him , and cast him out of the vineyard , and slew him .
text2: IcI e ' kimshInawat , ipi okisakcIwe ' pInawan shi siwnokam shI ktukanuk , icI e ' kinsawat .

text: When the lord therefore of the vineyard cometh , what will he do unto those husbandmen ?
text2: Pic cI pie ' t te ' pe ' ntuk i siwnokamshI ktukan ; tInicI ke ' napnInat notI ktukie ' onInwun ,

text: They say unto him , He will miserably destroy those wicked men , and will let out his vineyard unto other husbandmen , which shall render him the fruits in their seasons .
text2: OtI cI okinawan , okukokwansukIne ' nan sI ni mcInInwun pe ' kansIncIn ni ktukie ' onInwun okuwuan i siwnokamshI ktukan , ke ' monkocIn i micum e ' tso kishkInuk .

text: Jesus saith unto them , Did ye never read in the scriptures , The stone which the builders rejected , the same is become the head of the corner : this is the Lord ' s doing , and it is marvellous in our eyes ?
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , ConI wika otI kiwatusinawa mIsInukInuk , I sIn kiwe ' shke ' cuk kaianwe ' ntumwat iw ie ' i ke ' ne ' tmIsuk shi e ' wikwe ' iak . Kshe ' mIne ' to sIiw otIshcIke ' wun kumamkasaptamIn cI .

text: Therefore say I unto you , The kingdom of God shall be taken from you , and given to a nation bringing forth the fruits thereof .
text2: Iw sI otI we ' cne ' nkon otokumauwun , Kshe ' mIne ' to , kuotapnamakom icI kuminak ki nIshInape ' k ke ' pie ' tocuk i micumowun .

text: And whosoever shall fall on this stone shall be broken : but on whomsoever it shall fall , it will grind him to powder .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk cI ke ' pmukocnokwe ' n shi sInik , kupikwshIn , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk cI ke ' tsoskwe ' n , kupisposo .

text: And when the chief priests and Pharisees had heard his parables , they perceived that he spake of them .
text2: Pic cIki , kcI - me ' matmocIk onInwuk , ipi Pe ' nisiuk , kanotmoat ni iacmonIn , okikuke ' ntanawa , winwa e ' kowat .

text: But when they sought to lay hands on him , they feared the multitude , because they took him for a prophet .
text2: Pic cI wamshInawat okikwsawan , ni maoce ' tincIn Nakanacimot Osam winwa okine ' nmawan .

text: And Jesus answered and spake unto them again by parables , and said ,
text2: CISUS cI okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan , minI ni acimonIn otI kItwe ' k ;

text: The kingdom of heaven is like unto a certain king , which made a marriage for his son ,
text2: Okumauwun i shpumuk , otI e ' ne ' ntakwuk ke ' cwa nkot okuma kaoshInwiat okwIsIn , e ' wi wiwunIt ;

text: And sent forth his servants to call them that were bidden to the wedding : and they would not come .
text2: Okimace ' nashkawan , ni opmitakaimIn , e ' wintomanIt ni wakumIncIn ; co cI kipie ' sin .

text: Again , he sent forth other servants , saying , Tell them which are bidden , Behold , I have prepared my dinner : my oxen and my fatlings are killed , and all things are ready : come unto the marriage .
text2: MinI cI pe ' kansIncIn ni opmitakaimIn , okimace ' nashkawan , otI cI okinan , Wuwitmowuk kiwakmIcIk , PInI , shiI nkishwshuston i naokwe ' wisnuwun , mpIshkimuk , ipi wanoukuk kishInsawak ; ipi cake ' ko nkishwshuston , pie ' shiak sI nwikwke ' wunuk .

text: But they made light of it , and went their ways , one to his farm , another to his merchandise :
text2: Ke ' koishukcI okine ' ntanawa icI pape ' kan e ' kishishiawat ; nkot otItshI ktukie ' wunuk , kishiI ocI ke ' nkot e ' tshe ' tawe ' t .

text: And the remnant took his servants , and entreated them spitefully , and slew them .
text2: KicI kashkwicuk OkimshInawan niw OpmitakaimInIn , ipi na ‘ okitotwawan , icI e ' kinsawat .

text: But when the king heard thereof , he was wroth : and he sent forth his armies , and destroyed those murderers , and burned up their city .
text2: Pic cI o kcI okuma kanotake ' t , i ki kcInshkatsI , okinInashkawan cI ni otI shumaknIshimIn , e ' kiwnusanIt ni kanshowe ' ncIn , ipi okicaksumwawan , iw ototanInIn .

text: Then saith he to his servants , The wedding is ready , but they which were bidden were not worthy .
text2: IcI okinan , ni opmitakaimIn , shiI sI kishwsusIn , i wikwtowIn , kicI kawikmIcuk copite ' ntakwsIsik ,

text: Go ye therefore into the highways , and as many as ye shall find , bid to the marriage .
text2: Shiak ntoac ipI mie ' wuk ; tsocI ke ' mkowe ' kwe ' n , ku ‘ wikmawak .

text: So those servants went out into the highways , and gathered together all as many as they found , both bad and good : and the wedding was furnished with guests .
text2: IcI ki pmitakaiuk e ' kishiawat shi mie ' wuk , icI e ' ki maote ' nawat , caye ' k tso kamkawawat , niw me ' iashowe ' psIncIn , ipi me ' noshowe ' psIncIn ; icI kite ' pse ' k shi e ' tshi wikwtuk .

text: And when the king came in to see the guests , he saw there a man which had not on a wedding garment :
text2: Pic , cI okcI okuma kapitike ' t , e ' pie ' wapmat , ni kawikmacIn , okiwapman , nkot nInIwun shi e ' iInIt kapwa piskumnIt wikwtatikwowun .

text: And he saith unto him , Friend , how camest thou in hither not having a wedding garment ? And he was speechless .
text2: OtI cI okinan , Nikan tacI kapie ' shupitike ' n , e ' pwa piskumIn i wikwtatikwowun ? CocI okIshkitosin e ' wi kikitot .

text: Then said the king to the servants , Bind him hand and foot , and take him away , and cast him into outer darkness ; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth .
text2: IwcI kanat , o kcI okuma ni opmitakaimIn , TkopInuk one ' cik osItik , ipi maciwunuk , ipi wupukinuk , me ' kwe ' kiskupkonia , shi e ' tnIte ' mok ipi e ' tnwe ' iapte ' shnuk .

text: For many are called , but few are chosen .
text2: Mce ' sh ntomak ; nIshcI puke ' ci we ' napmak .

text: Then went the Pharisees , and took counsel how they might entangle him in his talk .
text2: IcI okiwutshItanawa ki Pe ' nisiuk , washI nkwapnawat , shiw okikitonuk .

text: And they sent out unto him their disciples with the Herodians , saying , Master , we know that thou art true , and teachest the way of God in truth , neither carest thou for any man : for thou regardest not the person of men .
text2: OkinInashkawawan cI e ' ciiIt ni ke ' knomowacIn , ipi ni Knotiunun , otI e ' wi nunanIt , Ke ' knomakIn nkuke ' ntamIn tpasI e ' shuwe ' psin ipi we ' we ' nI e ' shknomake ' n o Kshe ' mIne ' to otIshcIke ' wun ipi co ke ' wIiI kitupate ' nmasi ,

text: Tell us therefore , What thinkest thou ? Is it lawful to give tribute unto Caesar , or not ?
text2: WitmoshInak e ' ne ' ntumIn ? Ntamno shIcke ' mInI minkIt Sisu i maocIcke ' wun tanake ' co ?

text: But Jesus perceived their wickedness , and said , Why tempt ye me , ye hypocrites ?
text2: Cisus cI okike ' ntumwan iomIcshowe ' psiwnInawa otI okinan , We ' kwnicI we ' ckwcItupe ' nmie ' k , e ' nume ' kasie ' k ?

text: Shew me the tribute money . And they brought unto him a penny .
text2: WaptIIshuk i tpaomatwun i shonia . Nkot shInIn cI kipie ' twawan .

text: And he saith unto them , Whose is this image and superscription ?
text2: OtI cI okinan ; We ' nicI otI e ' shnakwsIt ; ipi we ' npie ' kasot ?

text: They say unto him , Caesar ' s . Then saith he unto them , Render therefore unto Caesar the things which are Caesar ' s ; and unto God the things that are God ' s .
text2: OtI cI okikon , Sisu sI . IcI otI okinan , Minuk Sisu tso te ' pe ' ntuk Sisu ; ipi minuk Kshe ' mIne ' to tso tpe ' ntuk o Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: When they had heard these words , they marvelled , and left him , and went their way .
text2: IcI kanotmowawat i kakItnIt , kimamkate ' ntumwuk , ipi okinknawan , icI e ' kimaciwat .

text: The same day came to him the Sadducees , which say that there is no resurrection , and asked him ,
text2: MinI cI i e ' kishkiwuk kipie ' naskakon ni Se ' cwsiIn , ki e ' kitocIk , cowIiI taiapsisi icI e ' kinatawat .

text: Saying , Master , Moses said , If a man die , having no children , his brother shall marry his wife , and raise up seed unto his brother .
text2: OtI okinawan , Ke ' knomake ' n , Mosus kikito , KishpIn nInI npot , pwa onicansIt , wikane ' iIn cI taowiwunIn ni wiwun ; e ' wiw cI onicansItmowat ni wi kane ' ipIninIn .

text: Now there were with us seven brethren : and the first , when he had married a wife , deceased , and , having no issue , left his wife unto his brother :
text2: Ki ipIninIn sI e ' cIiIiak , nouk ki shik we ' wikane ' ite ' cuk , ocI ke ' ctaosIt kauwiwut kinpo , icI e ' pwanicansIt , okinkItmowan ni wiwun wikane ' iIn .

text: Likewise the second also , and the third , unto the seventh .
text2: IcI ke ' winwa caye ' k okiianke ' owiwmawan caye ' k nouk katshIcIk .

text: And last of all the woman died also .
text2: IcI mamo shkwe ' iak o kwe ' kinpo winke ' ?

text: Therefore in the resurrection whose wife shall she be of the seven ? for they all had her .
text2: Pic cI iapsishnowat , we ' ninIncI ke ' wiwmukocIn ni nouk , caye ' k e ' ki wiwmukot .

text: Jesus answered and said unto them , Ye do err , not knowing the scriptures , nor the power of God .
text2: Cisus cI okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan , KiwaonIshnomsI , e ' pwakuke ' ntume ' k , i msInukIn , ipi i wishkIswun Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: For in the resurrection they neither marry , nor are given in marriage , but are as the angels of God in heaven .
text2: Pic sI iapsishnuk , cowiwsik , ipi co mintusik wiwtowun nasap sI e ' ne ' ntakwsInIt ni omIshInuwe ' mIn o Kshe ' mIne ' to shi shpumuk , iw se ' e ' ne ' ntakwse ' wat .

text: But as touching the resurrection of the dead , have ye not read that which was spoken unto you by God , saying ,
text2: OtI cI wi iapsishkuk kanocuk , conI kiwaptusinawa i msInukInuk i kashu knonkoie ' k o Kshe ' mIne ' to , otI e ' kitot ?

text: I am the God of Abraham , and the God of Isaac , and the God of Jacob ? God is not the God of the dead , but of the living .
text2: Nin sI Nto Kshe ' mIne ' to iumuk E ' pIne ' e ' m , ipi Nto Kshe ' mIne ' to iumuk AysIk , ipi Nto Kshe ' mIne ' to iumuk Ce ' kap , Cosu wi Kshe ' mIne ' to oto Kshe ' mIne ' to omukwsin ni ne ' poncIn , mtIno ie ' k pe ' matsIncIn .

text: And when the multitude heard this , they were astonished at his doctrine .
text2: Pic cI kimaoce ' ticuk kanotwawat Kimamkate ' ntumwawan , iw okukie ' kwe ' wunInIn .

text: But when the Pharisees had heard that he had put the Sadducees to silence , they were gathered together .
text2: Pic cI ki Pe ' nIsiuk kanotmoat , niw e ' kiwaonmanIt ni Se ' cwsiIn , kimaoce ' tik ; e ' ciInIt .

text: Then one of them , which was a lawyer , asked him a question , tempting him , and saying ,
text2: Ice ' nkot ni tpakwnuke ' onInI , okinatakon i natatwun , e ' wikwcIte ' pe ' nmukot , otI cI okikon ?

text: Master , which is the great commandment in the law ?
text2: Ke ' knomake ' n , TIni cI ie ' i kcI kie ' kwe ' wun shi tpakwnuke ' wunuk .

text: Jesus said unto him , Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart , and with all thy soul , and with all thy mind .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , Tpash o Te ' pe ' nmukwiIn , Kshe ' mIne ' to , caye ' k shi kte ' ik , ipi caye ' k shi kcipamuk , ipi caye ' k shi ktIne ' ntumwunuk .

text: This is the first and great commandment .
text2: OtI se ' ie ' i kie ' kwe ' wun ne ' tmIsuk , ipi ke ' c pite ' ntakwuk .

text: And the second is like unto it , Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself .
text2: IcI i e ' nishuk ike ' win e ' ne ' ntakwuk , Tpash kic pmatsi e ' shtpantusiIn .

text: On these two commandments hang all the law and the prophets .
text2: IwsI notI nish kie ' kwe ' wunIn e ' cIkote ' k , caye ' k tpakwnuke ' wun , ipi i nakanacimonIn .

text: While the Pharisees were gathered together , Jesus asked them ,
text2: Me ' kwace ' e ' maoce ' tiwat ki Pe ' nisiuk Cisus okinatawan .

text: Saying , What think ye of Christ ? whose son is he ? They say unto him , The Son of David .
text2: OtI Okinan ; TInicI e ' ne ' nme ' k o Knayst ? We ' ninIncI we ' kwIsmukwocIn ? otI cI okinawan , Te ' pItsI , otokwIsnun .

text: He saith unto them , How then doth David in spirit call him Lord , saying ,
text2: OtI cI okinan , We ' kwnicI Te ' pIt kaoce ' shInkanat shi KcI cipamuk Te ' pe ' nmIt , otI e ' kikItot ?

text: The LORD said unto my Lord , Sit thou on my right hand , till I make thine enemies thy footstool ?
text2: O Kshe ' mIne ' to otI okinan , Te ' pe ' nmIt , cipitupIn shi nte ' pniwnak , nash kiwshukwa ki me ' iane ' nmukwie ' nuk namiukwan ksItik .

text: If David then call him Lord , how is he his son ?
text2: KishpIn Te ' pIt ishuwawinat Te ' pe ' nmin tInicI e ' shaokwIsmat .

text: And no man was able to answer him a word , neither durst any man from that day forth ask him any more questions .
text2: CocI wIiI nInI okikshkItosin washIiaishe ' mat , icI i e ' kikishkiwuk wIiI nInI cominI ke ' ko okishI natawasiwan .

text: Then spake Jesus to the multitude , and to his disciples ,
text2: ICI e ' kiknonat Cisus ni maocatincIn , ipi ni ke ' knomoacIn ;

text: Saying , The scribes and the Pharisees sit in Moses ' seat :
text2: OtI kikito , kisI We ' npie ' ke ' cuk , ipi ki Pe ' nisiuk cipitupwuk shi Mosus o cipitupwunuk ,

text: All therefore whatsoever they bid you observe , that observe and do ; but do not ye after their works : for they say , and do not .
text2: Caye ' k cI we ' kwe ' ntuk kie ' shI kie ' kumukuwe ' kwe ' n , iw ke ' shI naktuwe ' ntume ' k ipi i ke ' totme ' k , ke ' kowi i shIcke ' ke ' kon , i e ' shcIke ' wat kItwuk sI mtIno cocowi i shIcke ' sik .

text: For they bind heavy burdens and grievous to be borne , and lay them on men ' s shoulders ; but they themselves will not move them with one of their fingers .
text2: NapItmake ' k sI ni wiwsha ‘ wunIn kwe ' skonuk e ' wipmotmuk , icI shi e ' towawat otInmaknInuk ninInwun , winwa cowi co e ' winmatnumwat tIna nkot onIciwan .

text: But all their works they do for to be seen of men : they make broad their phylacteries , and enlarge the borders of their garments ,
text2: E ' wiwipmukwat sI ni nInwun , i caye ' k we ' cnInkie ' wat ; ipi omukite ' tonawan ke ' ni wiasotkwe ' psonawan ipi omukite ' tonawan ni se ' kacknIn shiw piskumwakInawak .

text: And love the uppermost rooms at feasts , and the chief seats in the synagogues ,
text2: Ipi , ome ' nwe ' ntanawa e ' shpI oshIckate ' nuk , e ' tshI wikwtowut , ipi ni nakansIncIn e ' ci cipitupnIt , shi nume ' okumkok .

text: And greetings in the markets , and to be called of men , Rabbi , Rabbi .
text2: Ipi e ' numkotwa shiw e ' tshutatuk , ipi e ' wikowat ni nInwun , Ke ' knomake ' t , Ke ' knomake ' t .

text: But be not ye called Rabbi : for one is your Master , even Christ ; and all ye are brethren .
text2: Ke ' ko wi kinwa , Ke ' knomake ' , ShInkaske ' k , mtIno nkot we ' Ke ' knomakwie ' k Knayst cI o kinwacI caye ' k ktowikane ' itum .

text: And call no man your father upon the earth : for one is your Father , which is in heaven .
text2: Ke ' ko wi wIiI nInI Nos shInkanake ' k shotI kik nkotwe ' mtIno Koswa shpumuk e ' iIt , kishkok .

text: Neither be ye called masters : for one is your Master , even Christ .
text2: Ke ' kowike ' Te ' pe ' nke ' t , shInkaske ' kon , nkot wI Te ' pe ' nmukwie ' k o Knayst ,

text: But he that is greatest among you shall be your servant .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' cI pite ' ntakwsIt kinwa , oie ' o ke ' pmitakaiwut .

text: And whosoever shall exalt himself shall be abased ; and he that shall humble himself shall be exalted .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' ke ' kcI pite ' ntuk wia ‘ w , oie ' o ke ' niswe ' ntakwsIt , ipi ke ' o ke ' psuwe ' ntuk wia ‘ w oie ' o ke ' kcI pite ' ntakwsIt .

text: But woe unto you , scribes and Pharisees , hypocrites ! for ye shut up the kingdom of heaven against men : for ye neither go in yourselves , neither suffer ye them that are entering to go in .
text2: Kokwansukumuk kinwa we ' npie ' ke ' ie ' k , ipi kinwa Pe ' nisiuk , e ' nume ' kasie ' k ! kikupakwumwawa kinInwuk shpumuk iw okumauwun , cocke ' kinwa tpInwe ' kpitike ' sim , coke ' kitine ' nmasiwak wanmupitike ' cuk e ' wi pitike ' wat .

text: Woe unto you , scribes and Pharisees , hypocrites ! for ye devour widows ' houses , and for a pretence make long prayer : therefore ye shall receive the greater damnation .
text2: Kokwansukumuk kinwa we ' npie ' ke ' ie ' k , ipi kinwa Pe ' nisiuk e ' nume ' kasie ' k ; kcakitumwawak shakaocIk , otowikwamwam , ipi nIsh knoe ' sh ktItnankitonum , e ' mumatumoie ' k ; iwcI i kotIskonawa wusimI mIcitotatwun .

text: Woe unto you , scribes and Pharisees , hypocrites ! for ye compass sea and land to make one proselyte , and when he is made , ye make him twofold more the child of hell than yourselves .
text2: Ko kwansukumuk sI kinwa we ' npie ' ke ' ie ' k , ipi kinwa Pe ' nisiuk , e ' nume ' kasiuk ! kiwtashkanawa i kcukum , ipi ikI , e ' wimkowe ' k nkot , wawitokwe ' k , pic cI witokone ' k , nishuk wusimI kitIshawa win , onicansumkot shi namkumuk , icI kinwa e ' shwe ' psie ' k .

text: Woe unto you , ye blind guides , which say , Whosoever shall swear by the temple , it is nothing ; but whosoever shall swear by the gold of the temple , he is a debtor !
text2: Kokwansukumuk kinwa ke ' kie ' pikwaie ' k nakanwusie ' k , otI e ' kItie ' k , We ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsukwe ' n , i kcI nume ' okumuk , coke ' ko nomkIsnon , we ' kwe ' ntuk cie ' k ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsukwe ' n i osawshonia kcInumie ' okumkok , kawite ' pwe ' .

text: Ye fools and blind : for whether is greater , the gold , or the temple that sanctifieth the gold ?
text2: Kukie ' patsIm , ipi kukie ' pikwam , We ' kwni cI wusimI e ' pite ' ntakwuk i osawshonia tanake ' i kcInume ' okumuk we ' c te ' pe ' ntakwuk i osawshonia ?

text: And , Whosoever shall swear by the altar , it is nothing ; but whosoever sweareth by the gift that is upon it , he is guilty .
text2: Ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsukwe ' n shi e ' tshipitakwe ' k , coke ' ko nomkIsnon we ' kwe ' ntukie ' k ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsukwe ' n i kie ' pitakwe ' k , ka ‘ wite ' pwe ' .

text: Ye fools and blind : for whether is greater , the gift , or the altar that sanctifieth the gift ?
text2: Kukie ' patsIm , ipi kukie ' pikwam , We ' kwni cI wusimI e ' pite ' ntakwuk , ipatakwe ' k , tanake ' i e ' tshI pitakwe ' k , te ' pe ' ntuk i pitakwe ' wun .

text: Whoso therefore shall swear by the altar , sweareth by it , and by all things thereon .
text2: Wikwe ' ntuke ' ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsukwe ' n , shi e ' tshi pitakwe ' k , ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsu shi ipi ni caye ' k ke ' ko kwIciukwan e ' te ' nuk .

text: And whoso shall swear by the temple , sweareth by it , and by him that dwelleth therein .
text2: Ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsukwe ' n i kcI nume ' okumuk ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsu , ipi ni shi pituk e ' inIncIn .

text: And he that shall swear by heaven , sweareth by the throne of God , and by him that sitteth thereon .
text2: Ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsukwe ' n , shi shpumuk kishkok , ke ' kie ' tnamtakwsu shi Kshe ' mIne ' to Ocipitupwun , ipi ni shi capitupnIt .

text: Woe unto you , scribes and Pharisees , hypocrites ! for ye pay tithe of mint and anise and cummin , and have omitted the weightier matters of the law , judgment , mercy , and faith : these ought ye to have done , and not to leave the other undone .
text2: Kokwansukumuk kinwa we ' npie ' ke ' ie ' k , ipi kinwa , Pe ' nisiuk , e ' nume ' kasie ' k ! me ' tatsukIn kitpumakIn , i mInIt ipi e ' nIs , ipi kumIn , icI kiswe ' tonawa ke ' c pite ' ntakwukIn , i tpakwnuke ' e ' wun ; shuwe ' ntuwun , ipi te ' pwe ' ne ' ntumwun ; notI sI i e ' ni takitotme ' k ; cocI ktakinkItsinawan i nomkukipIn .

text: Ye blind guides , which strain at a gnat , and swallow a camel .
text2: Ke ' kie ' pikwaie ' k nakaniie ' k ! e ' cikwakmIshkane ' k , nIshpukos , icI wi e ' kme ' k kco we ' si .

text: Woe unto you , scribes and Pharisees , hypocrites ! for ye make clean the outside of the cup and of the platter , but within they are full of extortion and excess .
text2: Kokwansukumuk kinwa , we ' npie ' ke ' ie ' k , ipi , kinwa Pe ' nisiuk e ' nume ' kasie ' k , kinwa kpintonawa Sakiciiukwan i mnukwackIn , ipi i onakIn , shi cowi pic iukwan moshkine ' mkIt wie ' shke ' wun , ipi me ' anuk .

text: Thou blind Pharisee , cleanse first that which is within the cup and platter , that the outside of them may be clean also .
text2: Kin ke ' kie ' pikwan e ' Pe ' nisiwin ! Pinakwton ne ' tum , shi piciukwan i mnukwackIn , ipi onakIn , icI shi sakici iukwan ke ' kupinakwton .

text: Woe unto you , scribes and Pharisees , hypocrites ! for ye are like unto whited sepulchres , which indeed appear beautiful outward , but are within full of dead men ' s bones , and of all uncleanness .
text2: Kokwansukumuk kinwa , we ' npie ' ke ' ie ' k ipi kinwa Pe ' nisiuk , e ' nume ' kasie ' k ! ke ' cwa kinwa e ' shnakwse ' ie ' k i wapshkIckate ' k cipe ' ‘ okumkwe ' n , we ' we ' nI e ' mnwapme ' nakwuk sakici iukwan shi ca ‘ wi pic iukwan moshkIne ' ton ne ' pcuknInwuk otoknimwan , ipi caye ' k wanakwuk .

text: Even so ye also outwardly appear righteous unto men , but within ye are full of hypocrisy and iniquity .
text2: IusukI kinwa ; nasap sakici iukwan kte ' napme ' nakwsum me ' noshuwe ' psukIn e ' wi napmukwie ' k nInwuk , piciukwan ca ‘ wi kmoshknIstonawa nume ' kaswun , ipi mIcIshuwe ' psuwun .

text: Woe unto you , scribes and Pharisees , hypocrites ! because ye build the tombs of the prophets , and garnish the sepulchres of the righteous ,
text2: Kokwansukumuk kinwa , we ' npie ' ke ' ie ' k , ipi kinwa , Pe ' nisiuk e ' nume ' kasie ' k ! kitoshtawawak maokiocipe ' ‘ kumukom - wan , ki nakanacimocuk ipi kiakume ' tum - wawak , ni ocipe ' ‘ kumukomwan ki ne ' pwaka pIninuk .

text: And say , If we had been in the days of our fathers , we would not have been partakers with them in the blood of the prophets .
text2: OtI e ' kItie ' k kishpIn ie ' iakpIn e ' ie ' pmatsuwat nosnanuk , contakinatmoasimIn , pic ne ' sawat ni nakanacimoncIn .

text: Wherefore ye be witnesses unto yourselves , that ye are the children of them which killed the prophets .
text2: TInicI kwawintusom sI kinwa , e ' winicansumkoie ' k kikansacuk nakanacimoncIn .

text: Fill ye up then the measure of your fathers .
text2: MoshkInitok sI i , otpukInwan kikoswak .

text: Ye serpents , ye generation of vipers , how can ye escape the damnation of hell ?
text2: MIntoie ' k ; iaianke ' pmatsie ' k pwatacke ' ie ' kme ' ntoie ' k tInicI ke ' cI ktIski - ie ' k shi pnatsowun namkumuk : shkote ' k ?

text: Wherefore , behold , I send unto you prophets , and wise men , and scribes : and some of them ye shall kill and crucify ; and some of them shall ye scourge in your synagogues , and persecute them from city to city :
text2: PInI , kipukite ' nmonum ki nakanacimocuk ipi ne ' pwakacuk nInwuk , ipi we ' npie ' ke ' cuk , anIt cI kInsawak , ipi kIskakwawak , anIt ke ' kupsItie ' wawak shi kte ' nume ' okumkowak , ipi kukwtukawak onukmuk otanuk .

text: That upon you may come all the righteous blood shed upon the earth , from the blood of righteous Abel unto the blood of Zacharias son of Barachias , whom ye slew between the temple and the altar .
text2: Kinwa cI ktakshkakwnawa piamkuk caye ' k i maywakawun mskwI kasikwe ' pnukate ' k shotI kik , omuskwim E ' pun , kanpwakat , nash mIskwim o Se ' kinaye ' s kaokwIsmukot Pe ' nukaye ' s , katpIne ' k na ‘ oiukwan shi kcI - nume ' okumkok , ipi shi e ' tshi pitakwe ' k .

text: Verily I say unto you , All these things shall come upon this generation .
text2: We ' we ' nI ktInum caye ' k notI okupie ' naskakwnawa kotI pe ' matse ' cuk .

text: O Jerusalem , Jerusalem , thou that killest the prophets , and stonest them which are sent unto thee , how often would I have gathered thy children together , even as a hen gathereth her chickens under her wings , and ye would not !
text2: O Cinose ' nam ! Cinose ' nam ! kin kansItwa ki nakanacimocuk ipi e ' ki pmIsInwutwa , ki kapkItnumakon ; tunitsuk taki maotInkwa knicansuk , ke ' cwa pkuakwa e ' maotoshmat opunsha ne ' imIn , namiukwan onukwiknuk ; co cI kine ' ntusinawa ?

text: Behold , your house is left unto you desolate .
text2: PInI ! ku wikwamwa kinukitumakom pe ' pshukwu ‘ te ' .

text: For I say unto you , Ye shall not see me henceforth , till ye shall say , Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord .
text2: OtI ktInum , Co wi minI kuwapmIsim , nash , pama otI kItie ' k , MnawankosI o pie ' iat shiw otunoswunuk Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And Jesus went out , and departed from the temple : and his disciples came to him for to shew him the buildings of the temple .
text2: CISUS cI kisakum kiw cImaci shi kcInume ' okumkok ; nicI e ' knomowacIn , okipie ' naskakon e ' wiwaptukot e ' shcI kate ' nuk i kcI nume ' okumuk .

text: And Jesus said unto them , See ye not all these things ? verily I say unto you , There shall not be left here one stone upon another , that shall not be thrown down .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , kuwaptanawa nI caye ' k notI ? We ' we ' nI kItInum , Co wi nkot sIn kwucie ' kwan kte ' snon , caye ' k kniswe ' pnukate ' ton .

text: And as he sat upon the mount of Olives , the disciples came unto him privately , saying , Tell us , when shall these things be ? and what shall be the sign of thy coming , and of the end of the world ?
text2: Ka cipitupIt shi e ' pkotnianuk Anipik , e ' knomowacIn cI kimoc okipie ' naskakon , otI cI okikon , WitmoshInak tapicI otI ike ' nomkuk ? ipi E ' ni cI ke ' shu kInwa sapmnakwuk pic wipian ? ipi i washu kInwasapmnakwuk pic wishkwakiwuk ?

text: And Jesus answered and said unto them , Take heed that no man deceive you .
text2: Cisus cI okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan akwamsuk sI owIiI nInI e ' wipwawie ' shmukwie ' k .

text: For many shall come in my name , saying , I am Christ ; and shall deceive many .
text2: Cumane ' k sI ntunoswunuk ke ' pie ' shiacuk otI kukItwuk , Nin su Knayst ; icI mce ' sh ke ' cowie ' shmat .

text: And ye shall hear of wars and rumours of wars : see that ye be not troubled : for all these things must come to pass , but the end is not yet .
text2: Ipi Knotanawa i mikatwunun , ipi ianmukumukuk , i mikatwunIn , ikwamsuk kcI e ' wipwa mkoshkate ' ntume ' k iwsI caye ' k notI ke ' showe ' puk , icI wi e ' wishkwuakiwuk ; comshI pie ' mkIsnon .

text: For nation shall rise against nation , and kingdom against kingdom : and there shall be famines , and pestilences , and earthquakes , in divers places .
text2: Kupsukwik cI papukan e ' shumcuk ke ' cI mikatwat , ipi papukan okumawunIn , ipi kukicupikIte ' kiwun ipi kukicI iakwnoke ' kiwun , ipi knanImshke ' onukmuk nkoci kI .

text: All these are the beginning of sorrows .
text2: IwsI caye ' k notI we ' cmacimkuk mkoshkate ' ntumwunIn .

text: Then shall they deliver you up to be afflicted , and shall kill you : and ye shall be hated of all nations for my name ' s sake .
text2: IwcI pic ke ' cipkItnukoie ' k , shi watshI kwtukukoie ' k , ipi kInsukom , ipi kshike ' nmukwak caye ' k e ' tsoshumocuk nin ke ' o te ' nmukoie ' k ntInoswunuk .

text: And then shall many be offended , and shall betray one another , and shall hate one another .
text2: IwcI pic mce ' sh kInshke ' ntik , ipi kawie ' shtik , ipi onukumuk kIshI shi ke ' ntik .

text: And many false prophets shall rise , and shall deceive many .
text2: Ipi kumane ' k ke ' psukwicuk nakanacimokascuk mce ' sh cI okawie ' shmawan .

text: And because iniquity shall abound , the love of many shall wax cold .
text2: McI showe ' psowun cI osam e ' mane ' k mce ' sh cI tpantowun kItkIsnunI .

text: But he that shall endure unto the end , the same shall be saved .
text2: WincI pIne ' ke ' iakwamsIt oie ' o ke ' ke ' skonIt ,

text: And this gospel of the kingdom shall be preached in all the world for a witness unto all nations ; and then shall the end come .
text2: Ipi otI okumauwun mnoacmowIn ke ' iacIkate ' caye ' k shotI kik , ke ' kI kukInwa te ' ntumwat caye ' k e ' tso shumocuk , icI ke ' cI piamkuk e ' wishkwakiwuk .

text: When ye therefore shall see the abomination of desolation , spoken of by Daniel the prophet , stand in the holy place , ( whoso readeth , let him understand : )
text2: Pic cI wapmie ' k ki shake ' ntakwse ' cuk ke ' pnactocuk , kashInikanacimot nakanacimot Te ' niunIn , ni pwowat shi e ' tshe ' mno shIcke ' wat ( we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' waptumkwe ' n shiw msInukInuk uocma okInsItan , )

text: Then let them which be in Judaea flee into the mountains :
text2: IcI ki ke ' ie ' cuk Cwtie ' uk , nocma knInshumwuk , shi e ' cI pkotnianuk .

text: Let him which is on the housetop not come down to take any thing out of his house :
text2: Winke ' o kwItIpuk e ' iIt co kupie ' nisasisi e ' wiwtapnuk ke ' ko shi wikwamuk .

text: Neither let him which is in the field return back to take his clothes .
text2: Winke ' o ktIkanuk ke ' iIt cocupie ' kiwe ' si e ' wiwtapnuk otikwame ' iIn .

text: And woe unto them that are with child , and to them that give suck in those days !
text2: Kukokwansuksik ki ke ' ncukwcuk , ipi ki ke ' nonaosocuk , shi niw e ' kishkiwuk .

text: But pray ye that your flight be not in the winter , neither on the sabbath day :
text2: Numak e ' wi pwapomkuk pic oshumie ' k nainIta ke ' e ' wipwa nume ' kishkuk .

text: For then shall be great tribulation , such as was not since the beginning of the world to this time , no , nor ever shall be .
text2: IwcI pic ke ' cu kcI ianmukiwuk , cowikakinomkIsnon e ' kowe ' pkiwuk , otI pic coke ' minI i knomkIsnon .

text: And except those days should be shortened , there should no flesh be saved : but for the elect ' s sake those days shall be shortened .
text2: KishpIn sI notI e ' kishkiwuk pke ' ci shIckate ' k , co wIiI pe ' matsIt kuke ' skonasi ; kiw cie ' k we ' we ' napcukascuk , e ' kishkiwuk ke ' ocI , pke ' ciw shItok .

text: Then if any man shall say unto you , Lo , here is Christ , or there ; believe it not .
text2: KishpIn sI wIiI nInI otIkoie ' k , PInI otukw ‘ shI Knayst , Tanake ' ako , ke ' ko tpwe ' twake ' k .

text: For there shall arise false Christs , and false prophets , and shall shew great signs and wonders ; insomuch that , if it were possible , they shall deceive the very elect .
text2: Kupsukwik kwshI nIsh Knayst ke ' shInkatsocIk , ipi nakanacimokascuk , ipi kuwaptuukowak kawimataonokie ' k e ' wimamkate ' ntakwsIwat , kishpIn cI kshkItowat nike ' otawie ' shmawan ni kaowe ' napcIkasnIncIn .

text: Behold , I have told you before .
text2: PInI kisha sI kowitmonum .

text: Wherefore if they shall say unto you , Behold , he is in the desert ; go not forth : behold , he is in the secret chambers ; believe it not .
text2: KipIn cI wIiI otukoie ' k , PInI , ipI sI iuwak na , wiukwan , ke ' ko ipI shiake ' k , PInI kimoc iawak shi wikwamuk ke ' ko wi te ' pwe ' twake ' k .

text: For as the lightning cometh out of the east , and shineth even unto the west ; so shall also the coming of the Son of man be .
text2: Ke ' cwa pwawasmok e ' wcipiamkuk we ' cmokuk , ipi e ' wawase ' shkuk nash ipI we ' cpkIshmok , iw sI ke ' nomkuk pic piat We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: For wheresoever the carcase is , there will the eagles be gathered together .
text2: E ' ciiukwe ' n ne ' pot , wiio ’ w , shiw ce ' ci maoce ' tiwat ki knowuk .

text: Immediately after the tribulation of those days shall the sun be darkened , and the moon shall not give her light , and the stars shall fall from heaven , and the powers of the heavens shall be shaken :
text2: Kie ' nup cI kikishianmukiwuk , ni kishkiwunIn , kisIs ke ' o kukisupkoniawapmnakwsI ; ipi tpuk kisIs co kawawase ' shkmake ' si , ipi ki nukok shpumuk kaotukocnok , ipi nishke ' e ' osawunIn ipI shpumuk kInukshke ' non .

text: And then shall appear the sign of the Son of man in heaven : and then shall all the tribes of the earth mourn , and they shall see the Son of man coming in the clouds of heaven with power and great glory .
text2: IcI pic ke ' cinakwte ' nuk otI kinwaciawun o We ' kwIsmukot NInwun shiw shpumuk , iwcI ke ' ki caye ' k e ' tsoshumowat , shotI kik kukitImake ' nmok , ipi kowapmawan , ni We ' kwIsmImcIn NInwun pie ' tnIsnIt ankwotok , shi shpumuk , okupie ' iIn cI okIshkIe ' wsowun , ipi okcImnowankoswun .

text: And he shall send his angels with a great sound of a trumpet , and they shall gather together his elect from the four winds , from one end of heaven to the other .
text2: IcI ke ' cI pie ' mace ' nashkawat omIshInIwe ' mIn kupie ' kcI notakwtonawa i notakwcIkIn , icI ke ' cI maotonawat , win kawe ' napmacIn e ' nkokwak otI kI .

text: Now learn a parable of the fig tree ; When his branch is yet tender , and putteth forth leaves , ye know that summer is nigh :
text2: Mpe ' wi kuke ' ntumok iaiacimowIn i cIsiwnokamIsh , pic saknumkwicIn shiw otukwasuk , ipi sakpuksicIn kukuke ' ntanawa shiI ci kiukwan e ' mnokumuk .

text: So likewise ye , when ye shall see all these things , know that it is near , even at the doors .
text2: IwsI kinwa pic waptme ' k caye ' k notI kukne ' tmok e ' cikiukwanwuk shishkwate ' muk .

text: Verily I say unto you , This generation shall not pass , till all these things be fulfilled .
text2: We ' we ' nI KtInum ; Cowi kumacisik kotI pe ' matse ' cuk , pama caye ' k notI kitpIsak .

text: Heaven and earth shall pass away , but my words shall not pass away .
text2: Kishuk ipi cI , kupinaca , otIie ' k ntuktowun co kupnacasnon .

text: But of that day and hour knoweth no man , no , not the angels of heaven , but my Father only .
text2: Pic i e ' kishkiwuk , ipi tupukIn , co wIiI okuke ' ntusin , nInI mocki co mIshInwe ' k ipI shpumuk mtIno ie ' k Nos .

text: But as the days of Noe were , so shall also the coming of the Son of man be .
text2: Ka nomkItInuk Noe ' , okishkomIn , i sI ke ' win nasap , ke ' nomkItInuk piat o We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: For as in the days that were before the flood they were eating and drinking , marrying and giving in marriage , until the day that Noe entered into the ark ,
text2: Iw e ' shkishkiwuk e ' pwamshumoshkuk kiwisnik , ipi kimnukwe ' k , kiwiwtik ipi kimamintik e ' wi wiwtowat , nash i e ' kishkuk , Noe ' e ' kiposIt shi napkwanuk .

text: And knew not until the flood came , and took them all away ; so shall also the coming of the Son of man be .
text2: Co cI okike ' ntusinawa nash e ' moshkInuk kapiamkItInuk icI caye ' k e ' ki we ' pokwat , iwsI nasap ke ' nomkItInuk pic piat o We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: Then shall two be in the field ; the one shall be taken , and the other left .
text2: Iw cI pic nish ke ' ik ktukanuk nkot cI kaotapna , ocI nkot kInkIna .

text: Two women shall be grinding at the mill ; the one shall be taken , and the other left .
text2: Nish kwe ' k kupispotaswuk , shi potakunuk , nkot cI kaotapna , ocI nkot kInkIna .

text: Watch therefore : for ye know not what hour your Lord doth come .
text2: Kawapuk cI co ku ke ' ntusinawa i tpukIn , pic ke ' piat o Te ' pe ' nmukwie ' k .

text: But know this , that if the goodman of the house had known in what watch the thief would come , he would have watched , and would not have suffered his house to be broken up .
text2: Kuke ' ntumok cI otI , KishpIn nInI te ' pe ' ntuk wikwam kuke ' ntuk pic ke ' mockIncIn wipianIt , otakawapman coke ' otakine ' ntusin ie ' tat e ' wipikw ukate ' nuk .

text: Therefore be ye also ready : for in such an hour as ye think not the Son of man cometh .
text2: TInicI oshInwiksuke ' kinwa , e ' pwamshI shIte ' aie ' k kupie ' wak We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: Who then is a faithful and wise servant , whom his lord hath made ruler over his household , to give them meat in due season ?
text2: We ' ni cI iakwamsIt , ipi ne ' pwakat pmitaka kaokmaoukot ni te ' pe ' nmukocIn shi e ' tat e ' wiminat wisnuwun mno opi ?

text: Blessed is that servant , whom his lord when he cometh shall find so doing .
text2: KIshuwe ' ntakwsI su o pmitaka , pic pianIt ni te ' pe ' nmukwocIn mkumakot i shIcke ' t .

text: Verily I say unto you , That he shall make him ruler over all his goods .
text2: We ' we ' nI sI otI KtInum , okItIpIntumokon caye ' k i otupunowe ' wsowun .

text: But and if that evil servant shall say in his heart , My lord delayeth his coming ;
text2: KishpIn ke ' o me ' iashuwe ' psIt pmitaka , ote ' ‘ ik cI otI kitot , Te ' pe ' nmIt kcukinowe ' sh e ' pwamshupiat .

text: And shall begin to smite his fellowservants , and to eat and drink with the drunken ;
text2: IcI ke ' cI we ' pwe ' potwat wic pmitakaiIn , ipi witopmat , ipi mnukwe ' t , ni kawshkwe ' pie ' ncIn .

text: The lord of that servant shall come in a day when he looketh not for him , and in an hour that he is not aware of ,
text2: Te ' pe ' nmukwocIn o pmitaka kupie ' n e ' kishkiwnunuk , e ' pwam shI ntawapme ' t pic ke ' i tpukInuk e ' pwamshI pame ' nmat .

text: And shall cut him asunder , and appoint him his portion with the hypocrites : there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth .
text2: Okukishkokon cI , ipi okupukinukon e ' ciInIt ni e ' nume ' kasnIncIn , shi cI ke ' tne ' te ' mok ipi ke ' tnwe ' iapte ' shnuk .

text: Then shall the kingdom of heaven be likened unto ten virgins , which took their lamps , and went forth to meet the bridegroom .
text2: OTI sI ke ' ne ' ntakwuk shpumuk okumawIn Ke ' cwa mtatso , she ' shksiuk , kaotapnumwat ni Wase ' ncIkInumwan , icI e ' ki wunkwe ' shkwawat we ' shkuwi winIncIn .
