text: And five of them were wise , and five were foolish .
text2: NianIn cI ki , kinpwakak , kicI nianIn kikie ' patsik .

text: They that were foolish took their lamps , and took no oil with them :
text2: KicI kakie ' patse ' cuk pe ' ' pshuk okimacitonawan wase ' ncIknumwan , cocI i pmIte ' okimacitosinawa .

text: But the wise took oil in their vessels with their lamps .
text2: Ne ' pwakacuk ie ' k okimacitonawa pmIte ' , pic iukwan otutaswunwak , ipi ni wase ' ncIknumwan .

text: While the bridegroom tarried , they all slumbered and slept .
text2: E ' pwamshIpianIt ni we ' shkwi wunIncIn , caye ' k ki note ' npe ' k ,

text: And at midnight there was a cry made , Behold , the bridegroom cometh ; go ye out to meet him .
text2: IcI e ' iaptItpukuk okinotanawa otI e ' kcI notakwtunuk , PInI , owe ' shkwiwut shiI pie ' wak ; Shiak we ' nkwe ' shkowuk .

text: Then all those virgins arose , and trimmed their lamps .
text2: IcI kotI caye ' k she ' shksiuk , e ' kipsukwiwat e ' kina ' towat wase ' ncIkunumwan .

text: And the foolish said unto the wise , Give us of your oil ; for our lamps are gone out .
text2: IcI ki ke ' kie ' patse ' cuk , okinawan ni ne ' pwakancIn mishInak i kpumte ' mwa , osam ninan nwase ' ncIk e ' numnanIn iate ' on .

text: But the wise answered , saying , Not so ; lest there be not enough for us and you : but go ye rather to them that sell , and buy for yourselves .
text2: KicI napwakacuk okin kwe ' twawan , otI okinawan ; Coin , cotanak tate ' pse ' snon kinwa , e ' wi ie ' ie ' k , ipi ninan , kitashiam e ' tshu tatuk , ipi kita kishpIne ' tatsom .

text: And while they went to buy , the bridegroom came ; and they that were ready went in with him to the marriage : and the door was shut .
text2: IcI pic e ' ie ' shiawat e ' wu kishpIne ' towat , kipie ' n owe ' shkwiwinIncIn , ipi kapwiacuk okinmowice ' wawan e ' kipitke ' nsht shi watshI owiwunIt icI i shkwate ' m e ' kikpakwukate ' k .

text: Afterward came also the other virgins , saying , Lord , Lord , open to us .
text2: Pama ; ke ' winwa nakIc kipie ' k kianIt she ' shksiuk ; otI cI kikItwuk Te ' pe ' nmiak , Te ' pe ' nmiak , nsakwunumwushnak .

text: But he answered and said , Verily I say unto you , I know you not .
text2: Okinkwe ' twan cI , otI okinan ; We ' we ' nI ktInum ; Cokuke ' nmIsnonum .

text: Watch therefore , for ye know neither the day nor the hour wherein the Son of man cometh .
text2: KuwapuksI co kuke ' ntusinawa , i e ' kishkiwuk , tankake ' , tpukIn , pic ke ' piat We ' kwIsmukot NInwun .

text: For the kingdom of heaven is as a man travelling into a far country , who called his own servants , and delivered unto them his goods .
text2: OtIsI e ' ne ' ntakwuk iw okumauwun shpumuk kishkok ; ke ' cwa nInI , e ' wipamatsIt , pnoc e ' shiatotanuk ; e ' kintomat opmitakaimIn , icI e ' kiswe ' nmowat , otInkackIn .

text: And unto one he gave five talents , to another two , and to another one ; to every man according to his several ability ; and straightway took his journey .
text2: Nkot cI okimiman , Nianuk mtatswak tso shonia ; icI minI nkot , nishuk mtatswak tso shonia , icI minI nkot , nkotuk mtatswak tso shonia ; e ' ne ' ntakwse ' nIt sI okinu ' onan icI papuk ki maci .

text: Then he that had received the five talents went and traded with the same , and made them other five talents .
text2: IcI ke ' win kaminIt , Nianuk mtatswak tso shonia , kiwutawe ' i , icI e ' kiwtutuuk minI wusimI nianuk mtatswak tso shonia .

text: And likewise he that had received two , he also gained other two .
text2: Winke ' nishIk mtatswak kaminIt , winke ' nishIk mtatswak , wusimI okiiIn .

text: But he that had received one went and digged in the earth , and hid his lord ' s money .
text2: IcI ke ' wi o kaminIt nkotuk mtatswak kishie ' wak icI e ' kiwanke ' t ukik , e ' kikItwat te ' pe ' nmukocIn oshoniaimInIn .

text: After a long time the lord of those servants cometh , and reckoneth with them .
text2: Pama cowika te ' pe ' nmat , notI pmitakaimIn kipie ' ; e ' wike ' nmat kanInkie ' nIt ,

text: And so he that had received five talents came and brought other five talents , saying , Lord , thou deliveredst unto me five talents : behold , I have gained beside them five talents more .
text2: IcI o kaminIt nianuk mtatswak tso shonia , kipie ' wak , okipie ' ton nianuk mtatswak tso shonia wusimI ; otIcI kikito , Te ' pe ' nmin , kimishInapIn nianuk mtatswak tso shonia , pInI wusimI nianuk mtatswak tso shonia , nkikshkIton .

text: His lord said unto him , Well done , thou good and faithful servant : thou hast been faithful over a few things , I will make thee ruler over many things : enter thou into the joy of thy lord .
text2: IcI ni te ' pe ' nmukocIn ' otI okikon , We ' we ' nI kitotum me ' noshuwe ' psin , ipi me ' nototmIn pmitakIn , kimnototanIn ; otI pke ' ' cicoiIn mane ' kIn kako kuminIn wakawakawaptumIn ; Pitike ' n e ' tshI mnowankosIt te ' pe ' nmukwiIn .

text: He also that had received two talents came and said , Lord , thou deliveredst unto me two talents : behold , I have gained two other talents beside them .
text2: Winke ' o kaminIt nishuk mtatswak tso shonia , kipie ' , otIcI , okinan ; Te ' pe ' nmin , kimish nishuk mtatswak tso shonia ; pInI wusimI nishuk mtatswak tso shonia , nkikshkIton .

text: His lord said unto him , Well done , good and faithful servant ; thou hast been faithful over a few things , I will make thee ruler over many things : enter thou into the joy of thy lord .
text2: IcI ni te ' pe ' nmukocIn otI okikon We ' we ' nI kitotum me ' noshuwe ' psin , ipi me ' nototmIn pmitakIn , kimnototanIn OtI pke ' ' cikaiIn , mane ' kIn ke ' ko kuminIn wakawaptumIn ; Pitike ' n e ' tshe ' mnowankosIt , te ' pe ' nmukwiIn .

text: Then he which had received the one talent came and said , Lord , I knew thee that thou art an hard man , reaping where thou hast not sown , and gathering where thou hast not strawed :
text2: IcI ke ' wi o e ' kipiat kaminIt nkotuk mtatswak tso shonia , otI cI okinan , Te ' pe ' nmin kike ' nmIn , e ' shsnuksiwnunwin , e ' kishkIshke ' n kacupwa swe ' we ' pnuke ' n ipi e ' maotInkIn kacupwa nisknukIn .

text: And I was afraid , and went and hid thy talent in the earth : lo , there thou hast that is thine .
text2: Nkikwtac icI e ' ki shiaie ' n , ipi e ' ki wukIto ian ikshoniaium , ne ' kwukik , pInI otI cI kte ' iIn te ' pe ' ntumIn .

text: His lord answered and said unto him , Thou wicked and slothful servant , thou knewest that I reap where I sowed not , and gather where I have not strawed :
text2: Te ' pe ' nmukocIn okinkwe ' takon , otI cI , oki kon , E ' ukie ' patIs , ipi kiapie ' tus , pmitaka , kike ' num , e ' kish kshkuke ' ian kacupwa swe ' we ' pnuke ' ian , ipi e ' naotInke ' ian kacupwa swe ' we ' pnuke ' ian , ipi e ' maotInke ' ian kaucupwapmnisknIke ' ian .

text: Thou oughtest therefore to have put my money to the exchangers , and then at my coming I should have received mine own with usury .
text2: Kitakiwuton sIi nshoniam ki iashtonke ' cIk , piaiancI ntaki tkotapinan te ' pe ' ntuman ipi i takikshkIcke ' mkukIpIn .

text: Take therefore the talent from him , and give it unto him which hath ten talents .
text2: OtapInImak i nkotuk mtatswak tso shonia , icI minuk i e ' iIt mtatsuk mtatswak tso shonia .

text: For unto every one that hath shall be given , and he shall have abundance : but from him that hath not shall be taken away even that which he hath .
text2: We ' kwe ' ntuksI e ' ie ' kwe ' n kumina , icI mce ' sh ke ' ciIt , ocI ke ' pwaiIt , kaotapnumwa ike ' ian nwe ' iIt .

text: And cast ye the unprofitable servant into outer darkness : there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth .
text2: Pukinuk cI o ke ' ko pwanaptIsIt pmitaka me ' kwe ' kiskupkonia e ' tshI tnIte ' mok , ipi e ' tnwe ' iapitshe ' nuk .

text: When the Son of man shall come in his glory , and all the holy angels with him , then shall he sit upon the throne of his glory :
text2: Pic cI We ' kwIsmukot NInwun , kupie ' wak okIcpite ' ntakwsowunuk , ipi ni caye ' k me ' noshuwe ' psIncIn omIshIne ' we ' mIn okupie ' wice ' okon , icI ke ' cI cipitupIt okIcne ' ntakwse ' wunuk cipitupwunuk .

text: And before him shall be gathered all nations : and he shall separate them one from another , as a shepherd divideth his sheep from the goats :
text2: IcI e ' nasmupIt kumaotInkaswun cak e ' shumInIt nIshInape ' n ; icI ke ' cI papke ' pnat ; ke ' cwa e ' shpapke ' pnat nInI omantanshImIn ipi nimotoiun .

text: And he shall set the sheep on his right hand , but the goats on the left .
text2: IcI ke ' cI cipitupat nimantanshIn ote ' pniwnak , nicI motoiIn onumciwnak .

text: Then shall the King say unto them on his right hand , Come , ye blessed of my Father , inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world :
text2: OtI cI okInan , KcI okuma niw e ' inIt ote ' pniwnak , Pie ' macik she ' winmukwie ' k Nos , pitike ' k okumauwunuk kaoshItakoie ' k e ' kowe ' pkiwuk .

text: For I was an hungred , and ye gave me meat : I was thirsty , and ye gave me drink : I was a stranger , and ye took me in :
text2: Npukite ' napInsI , icI e ' kishumie ' k ; nkikakas kIte ' ' e ' s , icI e ' ki mnIie ' k conkikuke ' ncukasi , icI e ' kipitkIshie ' k .

text: Naked , and ye clothed me : I was sick , and ye visited me : I was in prison , and ye came unto me .
text2: Nki shashakiti icI e ' kikwe ' ' ie ' k , ipi nki iakwnoka , icI e ' kipie ' wapme ' ie ' k , nkikupakwukaske ' , icI e ' ki pie ' naskawie ' k .

text: Then shall the righteous answer him , saying , Lord , when saw we thee an hungred , and fed thee ? or thirsty , and gave thee drink ?
text2: IcI ke ' cInkwe ' t - wawat ki me ' noshuwe ' pse ' cIk , otI cI kukItwuk , Te ' pe ' nmiak , TapicI , kawapmInkon e ' pkIte ' n , icI e ' shumnukon tanake ' e ' kakaskIte ' - e ' siIn , icI e ' kimne ' ' nukon .

text: When saw we thee a stranger , and took thee in ? or naked , and clothed thee ?
text2: TapicI kawapme ' nkon e ' pwake ' ncukasiIn , icI e ' pitike ' nkon tanake ' e ' shashakitin , icI e ' kwe ' inukoncI .

text: Or when saw we thee sick , or in prison , and came unto thee ?
text2: TapicI kawapme ' nkon e ' iakwnokan , tanake ' , e ' kupakokon , icI e ' kipie ' shi iIiak .

text: And the King shall answer and say unto them , Verily I say unto you , Inasmuch as ye have done it unto one of the least of these my brethren , ye have done it unto me .
text2: IwcI KcI - okuma okinkwe ' twan , otI cI okInan , We ' we ' nI , KtInum , otI e ' kitotwe ' k nkot otI mamwI kaciIt kotI ni kane ' iuk , isI nasap e ' totwe ' ie ' k Nin .

text: Then shall he say also unto them on the left hand , Depart from me , ye cursed , into everlasting fire , prepared for the devil and his angels :
text2: OtI cI kie ' win ni pic kie ' nat e ' inIncIn onumciwnak ; Wus macik ; e ' pukicukasie ' k kakuke ' shkote ' k , kaoshItwut mIcImIne ' to , ipi niw omushIne ' we ' mIn .

text: For I was an hungred , and ye gave me no meat : I was thirsty , and ye gave me no drink :
text2: NkipkIte ' cocI kishumsim ; nkikakaskite ' e ' s , cocI kimnIsim .

text: I was a stranger , and ye took me not in : naked , and ye clothed me not : sick , and in prison , and ye visited me not .
text2: Conkikike ' ntakwsIsi , cocI kipitike ' shsim , nkishashakiti , cocI kikwe ' ' sim ; nkiiakwnoka , ipi nkikpakwukas ; cocI kimpoace ' sim .

text: Then shall they also answer him , saying , Lord , when saw we thee an hungred , or athirst , or a stranger , or naked , or sick , or in prison , and did not minister unto thee ?
text2: IcI ke ' ke ' winwa ke ' cInkwe ' twawat otI okInawan , te ' pe ' nmiak , tapicI kawapmInkon e ' pkIte ' n tanake ' , e ' kakaskIte ' - e ' siIn , tanake ' e ' pwake ' ntakwsin tanake ' , e ' shashakitin , tanake ' e ' iakwnkan tanake ' , e ' kupakwukasiIn ; cocI nkipmitosnonmIn .

text: Then shall he answer them , saying , Verily I say unto you , Inasmuch as ye did it not to one of the least of these , ye did it not to me .
text2: IcI ke ' cInkwe ' twat , otI cI okInan ; We ' we ' nI KtInum , KashI pwatotwe ' k nkot otI mamwI kaciIt ; coi kitotwusim .

text: And these shall go away into everlasting punishment : but the righteous into life eternal .
text2: KotIcI kishie ' k kake ' kwtuksonk ; KotI cI ie ' k me ' noshuwe ' pse ' cuk kIshie ' k kake ' pmatsowunuk .

text: And it came to pass , when Jesus had finished all these sayings , he said unto his disciples ,
text2: ICI Cisus kakishkitot caye ' k note ' , kikitonIn , otI okinan e ' knomowacIn .

text: Ye know that after two days is the feast of the passover , and the Son of man is betrayed to be crucified .
text2: Kuke ' ntanawa kikish nish konkuk , ke ' cI iashwe ' sak wikwta ‘ wun iwcI We ' kwIsmukot NInwun kupkIte ' ncikaso e ' wiskakwukasot .

text: Then assembled together the chief priests , and the scribes , and the elders of the people , unto the palace of the high priest , who was called Caiaphas ,
text2: IcI e ' kimaoce ' ‘ tiwat , kcI - me ' matmocuk onInimwan ipi ki we ' npie ' mowacuk , ipi oke ' ctaosimwan , ki nIshInape ' k , shi e ' citanIt ni kcIme ' matmot nInI e ' shnukasot Ke ' ie ' pus .

text: And consulted that they might take Jesus by subtilty , and kill him .
text2: IcI e ' kinatatwat , e ' wiwie ' shawat ni CisusIn , ipi e ' winsawat .

text: But they said , Not on the feast day , lest there be an uproar among the people .
text2: OtI cI kikItwuk , Coin nkom e ' kishkiwuk e ' wikwtuk , tanshonatkumkIswuk ki nIshIape ' k .

text: Now when Jesus was in Bethany , in the house of Simon the leper ,
text2: Me ' kwa Cisus e ' ie ' iIt Pe ' te ' niuk shi e ' tanIt Sayiman we ' mkit .

text: There came unto him a woman having an alabaster box of very precious ointment , and poured it on his head , as he sat at meat .
text2: Kipie ' naskakon e ' ciIt kwe ' n okipie ' iIn , SInmkukos ke ' cwunItnuk nmukwiwun , icI e ' kisiknamakot otupik ; me ' kwa e ' cipitupnIt e ' ie ' wisnInIt .

text: But when his disciples saw it , they had indignation , saying , To what purpose is this waste ?
text2: IcI ni ke ' knomowacIn kawaptumwawat , kinshkatsiwe ' n tumwuk otI cI kikItwuk ; TInicI e ' napciak otI e ' nshonac cIkate ' k .

text: For this ointment might have been sold for much , and given to the poor .
text2: OtI nmukwiwun tawe ' ‘ kpIn mce ' sh , takipite ' ntakwut , icI takicI mintwa ke ' tmakse ' cuk ,

text: When Jesus understood it , he said unto them , Why trouble ye the woman ? for she hath wrought a good work upon me .
text2: Pic cI Cisus kakwiuk kwe ' nmat , otI okinan , We ' kwnicI we ' cmkoshkate ' nme ' k otI kwe ' ? Nme ' nototak sI i e ' totwut .

text: For ye have the poor always with you ; but me ye have not always .
text2: PIne ' kinwa kie ' tmakse ' cuk kpumiuwawak , nin ca ‘ wi co pIne ' ‘ nte ' ‘ isi .

text: For in that she hath poured this ointment on my body , she did it for my burial .
text2: IwsI i e ' kisiknuk otI nmukwiwun shi niiwukwe ' ctotuk i e ' winkokasian .

text: Verily I say unto you , Wheresoever this gospel shall be preached in the whole world , there shall also this , that this woman hath done , be told for a memorial of her .
text2: We ' we ' nI KtInum ; ke ' pashiamkuk , i otI mInwacimowun , ke ' iacukate ' , caye ' k shotI kik ; otIke ' , ke ' iapI kwe ' ke ' iacIkate ' ne ' katotuk ; e ' wipwawaone ' nciasot .

text: Then one of the twelve , called Judas Iscariot , went unto the chief priests ,
text2: IcI nkot kimtatso shItInish kashInkasot Cwte ' s Iske ' niut , kishie ' wak e ' ciiInIt ni kcI me ' matmocuk onInwun .

text: And said unto them , What will ye give me , and I will deliver him unto you ? And they covenanted with him for thirty pieces of silver .
text2: OtI cI okinan , We ' kwnicI tamishie ' k ktapkItnumonum . IcI e ' ki wawitmowawat nswapituk tso shonia .

text: And from that time he sought opportunity to betray him .
text2: IcI iwpi e ' ki kwinwune ' ntuk washIpataat .

text: Now the first day of the feast of unleavened bread the disciples came to Jesus , saying unto him , Where wilt thou that we prepare for thee to eat the passover ?
text2: IcI i e ' ne ' tmukishkuk iw wikwtowun opwaopuce ' te ' k pkwe ' shkIn , ni ke ' knomawacIn kipie ' naskawawan CisusIn , otI cI okinawan TInipi cI ke ' cI wa ‘ wshustoiak ; i e ' wimiciIn iashwe ' saki wikwtowun .

text: And he said , Go into the city to such a man , and say unto him , The Master saith , My time is at hand ; I will keep the passover at thy house with my disciples .
text2: OtI cI okinan , Shiak kcI otanuk , nInI otI cI ; knawa ; Ke ' knomake ' t kIto , Pe ' shoc pie ' mkIt , e ' wimacian iashwe ' sak wikwtowun shiw nke ' ‘ iIn , i shi e ' tan , ipi ki ke ' knomokwa .

text: And the disciples did as Jesus had appointed them ; and they made ready the passover .
text2: IcI ni ke ' knomowacIn kitotmok kakowat ni CisusIn ; icI e ' ki oshInwitowat , i iashwe ' sak wikwtowun .

text: Now when the even was come , he sat down with the twelve .
text2: IcI wanmupkonianuk okiwitpaman ni mtatso shItnish .

text: And as they did eat , he said , Verily I say unto you , that one of you shall betray me .
text2: IcI e ' iI wisnawat otI kikito ; We ' we ' nI KtInum , Nkote ' iI kinwa kupataum .

text: And they were exceeding sorrowful , and began every one of them to say unto him , Lord , is it I ?
text2: IcI kikcI kisate ' ntumwuk icI e ' we ' p cacipnowe ' ‘ otI e ' nawat , Te ' pe ' nke ' n nin nI ‘ ?

text: And he answered and said , He that dippeth his hand with me in the dish , the same shall betray me .
text2: E ' kinkwe ' twancI otI cI okinan , WinsI wacpmukamIt niw onIce ' n shiw onakunuk , owiie ' o ke ' patamIt .

text: The Son of man goeth as it is written of him : but woe unto that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed ! it had been good for that man if he had not been born .
text2: We ' kwIsmukot NInwun maciwok e ' shpie ' kasot ; kokwan sukukumuk o nInI , pataat , ni We ' kwIsmukot NInwun ; wusimI takiwunIt o nInI wika pwanikpIt .

text: Then Judas , which betrayed him , answered and said , Master , is it I ? He said unto him , Thou hast said .
text2: IcI Cwte ' s kapataat okinkwe ' twan otI cI okinan , Ke ' knomakIn nin nI ? IcI otI okinan KikishkItsI .

text: And as they were eating , Jesus took bread , and blessed it , and brake it , and gave it to the disciples , and said , Take , eat ; this is my body .
text2: IcI me ' kwa e ' iI wisne ' wat Cisus okiw tapnan pkwe ' shkIn , ipi kinume ' ; icI e ' kipikupitot ; icI e ' kiminat , ni ke ' knomowacIn , otI cI kikito , Otapne ' mok micuk , otI ie ' i niia ‘ w .

text: And he took the cup , and gave thanks , and gave it to them , saying , Drink ye all of it ;
text2: Ipi okiwtapnan i mnukwackIn , ipi kiwawiiwe ' icI e ' kiminat otI okinan ; Mnukwe ' k i e ' tshie ' k .

text: For this is my blood of the new testament , which is shed for many for the remission of sins .
text2: OtI ie ' i nmIskwim oshkawawitmake ' wnuk we ' csikwe ' pnukate ' k mce ' sh e ' wi we ' pnukate ' nuk ome ' iashuwe ' psiwnawan .

text: But I say unto you , I will not drink henceforth of this fruit of the vine , until that day when I drink it new with you in my Father ' s kingdom .
text2: OtI cI ktInum , Cowi minI nkumnukwe ' sin , e ' micmowuk iw siwnokamIsh , pama i e ' kishkiwuk , ke ' cI oshku wic mnukwe ' nmukon shi Nos otokumauwunuk .

text: And when they had sung an hymn , they went out into the mount of Olives .
text2: IcI kakish nkumwat i nkumwun ; kisakumwuk , kishie ' k shi e ' pkotniak AnipIk .

text: Then saith Jesus unto them , All ye shall be offended because of me this night : for it is written , I will smite the shepherd , and the sheep of the flock shall be scattered abroad .
text2: IcI Cisus otI okinan , Caye ' k kinwa kInshke ' nmIm nin , nkom e ' pkoniak , otI e ' shpie ' kate ' k ; Nkuwe ' potwa mantanshIn e ' kwapmat , icI ki mantanshuk pe ' msokapwucuk onukmuk ke ' shI sowe ' ptowat .

text: But after I am risen again , I will go before you into Galilee .
text2: IcI ki kish onIshkaian nkInmI ‘ nikani , ipI Ke ' ne ' niuk .

text: Peter answered and said unto him , Though all men shall be offended because of thee , yet will I never be offended .
text2: Pitu cI okinkwe ' twan , OtI okinan , KishpIn msote ' kaye ' k nInwuk , nshke ' nmukwiIn , coin nin nash ktanshke ' nmIsnon .

text: Jesus said unto him , Verily I say unto thee , That this night , before the cock crow , thou shalt deny me thrice .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan ; We ' we ' nI KtInum , nkom e ' pkoniak e ' pwamshI notakwsIt pkaukwa nsuk conkuke ' nmasi kIshI .

text: Peter said unto him , Though I should die with thee , yet will I not deny thee . Likewise also said all the disciples .
text2: Pitu cI otI , okinan wic npotonan konkuke ' nmasi coi ntakItsi , Nasap ke ' ni caye ' k okikon , nike ' knomowacIn .

text: Then cometh Jesus with them unto a place called Gethsemane , and saith unto the disciples , Sit ye here , while I go and pray yonder .
text2: IcI e ' ki pie ' wice ' wat Cisus , e ' kipie ' shiawat shi Ke ' t - se ' mIni e ' shnukate ' k otI cI okinan , ni ke ' knomowacIn ; Cipitupuk shotI e ' ie ' shiaian e ' shi e ' winumaian .

text: And he took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee , and began to be sorrowful and very heavy .
text2: OtInI macinan cI PituiIn ipi ni nish okwIsun Se ' pe ' ti , icI e ' we ' pme ' nshonate ' ntuk , ipi ki kcI kwsukwe ' ntum .

text: Then saith he unto them , My soul is exceeding sorrowful , even unto death : tarry ye here , and watch with me .
text2: IcI otI okinan , Nin cipam kcI nshonate ' ntum , ke ' cwa npowIn ; shotIiuk , ipi wic kawapmie ' k .

text: And he went a little further , and fell on his face , and prayed , saying , O my Father , if it be possible , let this cup pass from me : nevertheless not as I will , but as thou wilt .
text2: Pe ' shoc cI wusimI kishiI ; ipi kicicikwe ' se ' , ipi kinume ' , otI cI kikito , O ! Nose ' kishpIn sI e ' ne ' ntumwune ' n , nocma nkukwe ' pmosankon otI mnukwackIn ; Coin Nin e ' ne ' ntuman ’ kin sI e ' ne ' ntumIn .

text: And he cometh unto the disciples , and findeth them asleep , and saith unto Peter , What , could ye not watch with me one hour ?
text2: Kipie ' shie ' cI ni ke ' knomowcIn , okimakawan e ' npanIt , otI cI okinan , ni PituiIn , TIni conukwnI ktanu kawapsim nkot tupkIn .

text: Watch and pray , that ye enter not into temptation : the spirit indeed is willing , but the flesh is weak .
text2: Kuwapuk , ipi numak , e ' wikwe ' ctpe ' nmukosie ' k , onwaciwak cipam , wiasma cI ninwusimkIt .

text: He went away again the second time , and prayed , saying , O my Father , if this cup may not pass away from me , except I drink it , thy will be done .
text2: IcI minI e ' ki macit , iw nishuk , ipi kinume ' ‘ otI kikito , O ! Nose ' , kishpIn otI mnukwackIn wipwakwe ' pmosankoian mnukwe ' ian ie ' k , kin e ' shte ' an knomkIt .

text: And he came and found them asleep again : for their eyes were heavy .
text2: IcI minI e ' kipie ' shiat okimkawan e ' npanIt minI ‘ , osam e ' kikipkoshwat .

text: And he left them , and went away again , and prayed the third time , saying the same words .
text2: Okinknan cI e ' kishiat minI e ' kiwunumat , iw otI nsuk , nasap cI minI kiwukIto .

text: Then cometh he to his disciples , and saith unto them , Sleep on now , and take your rest : behold , the hour is at hand , and the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners .
text2: IcI e ' kipiat ni ke ' knomowacIn otI cI okinan npak , ipi nwashmok , pInI , pe ' shoc pie ' mkIt , tpukIn icI We ' kwIsmukot NInwun e ' wiwie ' shIt one ' cinuk me ' iashowe ' psIncIn .

text: Rise , let us be going : behold , he is at hand that doth betray me .
text2: Psukwik kInmamacimIn ; pe ' shoc iuwak wapataIt .

text: And while he yet spake , lo , Judas , one of the twelve , came , and with him a great multitude with swords and staves , from the chief priests and elders of the people .
text2: Me ' kwa cI e ' iIt nankitok , pInI , Cwte ' s nkot ki mtatso shItInish e ' tshIcIk , kipie ' okipie ' wice ' okon ke ' cmaoce ' ‘ tinIt , e ' pie ' ionIt kishkonIn , ipi iaptuwunIn e ' ocIpiawat kcIme ' matmocuk onInimwan , ipi oke ' ctaosimwan ki nIshInape ' k .

text: Now he that betrayed him gave them a sign , saying , Whomsoever I shall kiss , that same is he : hold him fast .
text2: IcI o wawie ' shat okiwitmowan washI kInwatInmawat , otI cI okinan . Osu ke ' oce ' muk , oie ' o mackonuk .

text: And forthwith he came to Jesus , and said , Hail , master ; and kissed him .
text2: IcI win e ' kipie ' shiat e ' ciiInIt ni CisusIn , icI otI okinan , KtInmukon Ke ' knomakIn ; icI e ' kiwce ' mat .

text: And Jesus said unto him , Friend , wherefore art thou come ? Then came they , and laid hands on Jesus , and took him .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , Nikan , We ' kwnicI pie ' ocIshian ? Kipie ' shie ' k cI ki kipie ' m mackonawan ni CisusIn .

text: And , behold , one of them which were with Jesus stretched out his hand , and drew his sword , and struck a servant of the high priest ' s , and smote off his ear .
text2: IcI pInI , nkot kapmIwice ' wakIn ni CisusIn , kishipnuke ' no , icI , e ' kiwtapnuk okishkowun , icI e ' kiwe ' potwat opmitakaimInIn ni kcI - me ' matmot ; icI e ' kikishkitoke ' shwat .

text: Then said Jesus unto him , Put up again thy sword into his place : for all they that take the sword shall perish with the sword .
text2: OtI cI Cisus okinan , minI shiton i kishkowun kacIte ' k ki caye ' k ke ' otapnukuk kishkowun ; okupnacukwunawa i kishkowun .

text: Thinkest thou that I cannot now pray to my Father , and he shall presently give me more than twelve legions of angels ?
text2: KtIshte ' anI co ntakshkItosin e ' wi nume ' kituwuk Nos , kie ' nup e ' wi mishpI mtatso wusimI shItInish iaianke ' maoce ' tincIn mIshInwe ' n ?

text: But how then shall the scriptures be fulfilled , that thus it must be ?
text2: KishpIn otI oshIcke ' ian , tInicI ke ' ocI te ' pwe ' mkukipIn notI we ' npie ' kate ' k ? otI cI knomkIt .

text: In that same hour said Jesus to the multitudes , Are ye come out as against a thief with swords and staves for to take me ? I sat daily with you teaching in the temple , and ye laid no hold on me .
text2: Iwpic cI Cisus okiknonan , ni maoce ' tincIn kupie ' otIsumnI , ke ' cwa ke ' mockIt e ' pie ' ioie ' k kishkomwan , ipi kiaptuwInwIn e ' wiwtapne ' ie ' k . Nkicipitup ca ‘ wi , pIne ' ‘ e ' kInomonkon shi kcI - nume ' okumkok cocI kimackonsim .

text: But all this was done , that the scriptures of the prophets might be fulfilled . Then all the disciples forsook him , and fled .
text2: Caye ' k otI kishIckate ' pIn e ' te ' pwe ' mkuk nakanacimocuk kashupie ' ke ' wat . IcI ni caye ' k ke ' knomowacIn e ' ki nkItnIshmukot ;

text: And they that had laid hold on Jesus led him away to Caiaphas the high priest , where the scribes and the elders were assembled .
text2: IcI ki kamackonawat ni CisusIn , okishonawan e ' ciiInIt , Ke ' ie ' pusIn ni kcI - me ' matmot onInI we ' npie ' ke ' ncIn , ipi ke ' ctaosIncIn e ' she ' maoce ' tinIt .

text: But Peter followed him afar off unto the high priest ' s palace , and went in , and sat with the servants , to see the end .
text2: Pitu cI shkwe ' iak okipmInashkawan , shi kcI - me ' matmot onInI e ' tanIt ; icI e ' kipitike ' t okiwitpuman pmitakaiIn e ' wiwaptuk wakosanuk .

text: Now the chief priests , and elders , and all the council , sought false witness against Jesus , to put him to death ;
text2: KiwcI kcI - me ' matmocuk o nInwuk ipi ke ' ctaose ' cuk , ipi caye ' k kikitowun okipantawapmawan waknaoshke ' mawacIn ni CisusIn e ' wiwcInsawat cI .

text: But found none : yea , though many false witnesses came , yet found they none . At the last came two false witnesses ,
text2: CocI wIiI okimkawasiwan , e ' ki ianwI mane ' nIt waknoshkImawacIn kipie ' n , cocI okimkawasiwan , ici shkwe ' iak kipie ' k nish waknoshkImawacIn .

text: And said , This fellow said , I am able to destroy the temple of God , and to build it in three days .
text2: OtI cI kikItwuk , OtIsI otI kikIto , NtakshkIton e ' wipnactoian okIc nume ' okumuk Kshe ' mIne ' to , icI ntakishton nsokwnukuk .

text: And the high priest arose , and said unto him , Answerest thou nothing ? what is it which these witness against thee ?
text2: IcI kcI - me ' matot onInI , kipsukwi , otI cI okinan ; ConI ke ' ko kitIshnkwe ' take ' si ? we ' kwnicI , kotI e ' shmukon .

text: But Jesus held his peace . And the high priest answered and said unto him , I adjure thee by the living God , that thou tell us whether thou be the Christ , the Son of God .
text2: Cisus cI coke ' ko kikItsi . OcI kcI - me ' matwot onInI okinkwe ' twan otI okinan : OsI pe ' matsIt Ke ' she ' mIne ' to , ntInap e ' wiwitmoie ' k , tanak kin Knayst We ' kwIsmukwiIn Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: Jesus saith unto him , Thou hast said : nevertheless I say unto you , Hereafter shall ye see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power , and coming in the clouds of heaven .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan , KikishkItsu . OtI win Nin KtInum ; pama kuwapmawa We ' kwIsmukot NInwun e ' cipitupIt ote ' pniwnak , iw okIshke ' ‘ wsowun , ipi e ' piat shi ankwotok shpumuk .

text: Then the high priest rent his clothes , saying , He hath spoken blasphemy ; what further need have we of witnesses ? behold , now ye have heard his blasphemy .
text2: IcI o kcI - me ' matmot onInI , e ' kinanisikpe ' tot paskukIn : otI cI kikito , Pukon we ' takwsI ; we ' kwnicI wusimI ke ' ocI ntotwukon ki waiacimocuk pInI nawa kinotwawa e ' pkonwutakwsIt .

text: What think ye ? They answered and said , He is guilty of death .
text2: TInicI e ' shte ' aie ' k ? okinkwe ' twawancI otI cI kikItwuk ? Ne ' ntakwse ' ‘ sI e ' winpot .

text: Then did they spit in his face , and buffeted him ; and others smote him with the palms of their hands ,
text2: IcI e ' kiskowanawat w ‘ shkishkonuk , ipi okipkwakwnIcitwawan , ipi anIt okiwe ' potwawan , onIciwan .

text: Saying , Prophesy unto us , thou Christ , Who is he that smote thee ?
text2: OtI cI okinawan , nakanacimotwushnak , kin Knayst ; We ' nicI kawe ' potakwiIn ?

text: Now Peter sat without in the palace : and a damsel came unto him , saying , Thou also wast with Jesus of Galilee .
text2: OcI Pitu kicipitupI nkoci shi wikwamuk , icI she ' shksiIn kipie ' naskakon , otI cI okikon ; Kinsuke ' kipmI wice ' wa Cisus o Ke ' nIni onInI .

text: But he denied before them all , saying , I know not what thou sayest .
text2: Caye ' k cI e ' nasmukapwunIt kiakwne ' tum , otI cI , okinan ; Cokuke ' nmIsnon e ' kiton .

text: And when he was gone out into the porch , another maid saw him , and said unto them that were there , This fellow was also with Jesus of Nazareth .
text2: IcI kanmusakuk , icI kanmiIt te ' skanuk , pe ' kansIncIn she ' shksiIn okiwapmukon , otI cI okinan , shiw e ' inIncIn , otI sI ke ' win okipmI wice ' wan ni CisusIn ; Ne ' sIni onInI .

text: And again he denied with an oath , I do not know the man .
text2: IcI minI e ' ki iakwne ' take ' t e ' ki kie ' tnamtakwsIt , CosI nkuke ' nmasi onInI .

text: And after a while came unto him they that stood by , and said to Peter , Surely thou also art one of them ; for thy speech bewrayeth thee .
text2: IcI minI shkIc okipie ' naskakon pe ' mkapowIncIn , ipi okinawan ni PutuiIn , We ' we ' nI sI ke ' kin , kapme ' nashkuwut kuke ' ntakwIs e ' shumiIn knIstotakwIs .

text: Then began he to curse and to swear , saying , I know not the man . And immediately the cock crew .
text2: IcI e ' we ' p mIci kikitot , otI cI kikito , Cosu nkuke ' nmasi onInI ; IcI pic e ' notakwsIt pkuakwa .

text: And Peter remembered the word of Jesus , which said unto him , Before the cock crow , thou shalt deny me thrice . And he went out , and wept bitterly .
text2: Okimikwe ' ntancI Pitu kakot , ni CisusIn , e ' kikot e ' pwamshinotakwsIt pku ‘ akwa , nsuk , coin nin nkuke ' nmasi , kIshI . IcI e ' kisakuk e ' kiwukcumwut .

text: When the morning was come , all the chief priests and elders of the people took counsel against Jesus to put him to death :
text2: PIC cI kawapuk , caye ' k ki kcI - me ' matmocIk onInwuk , ipi oke ' ctaosiwmawan ki nIshInape ' k , okItshImawan ni CisusIn e ' winsawat .

text: And when they had bound him , they led him away , and delivered him to Pontius Pilate the governor .
text2: IcI katkopnawat okimacinawan , okipkItnumwawan , ni Pantus Payne ' tun okuma .

text: Then Judas , which had betrayed him , when he saw that he was condemned , repented himself , and brought again the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders ,
text2: OcI Cwte ' s kapkIt e ' nmat , kawapmat cI e ' winsIckasnIt ; kikisate ' ntum , icI e ' kipie ' tot ne ' iap i nswapituk tswapuk shonia okopie ' twan ni kcIme ' matmocuk onInwun , ipi ke ' ctaosIncIn .

text: Saying , I have sinned in that I have betrayed the innocent blood . And they said , What is that to us ? see thou to that .
text2: OtI cI okinan , Nkukie ' patIs e ' ki pkIte ' ntuman pwamiashtotumomkuk mskwI . OtI cI kItwuk , We ' kwnicI ninan i ? Kin sI i mtIno .

text: And he cast down the pieces of silver in the temple , and departed , and went and hanged himself .
text2: IcI mcIiukwan e ' kipukitot , i shonia shi kcIe ' nume ' okumkok , icI e ' ki macit e ' ki wukontIsot .

text: And the chief priests took the silver pieces , and said , It is not lawful for to put them into the treasury , because it is the price of blood .
text2: IcI ki kcI - me ' matmocIk onInwuk okiwtapnumwat i shonia , otI cI kItwuk , CotawunsInon , e ' witoikon maocIcke ' wunuk , osam otI kakshkIcke ' k mskwI .

text: And they took counsel , and bought with them the potter ' s field , to bury strangers in .
text2: Ki kikitokcI icI kitawe ' kcI ni shoniaiIn kikishpIne ' twawancI wapukIn naknukI onInI okshtkan , e ' winkowawat me ' mataosIncIn .

text: Wherefore that field was called , The field of blood , unto this day .
text2: Ie ' i we ' tshInkate ' k MskwI ktukan , otI e ' kishkiwuk .

text: Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremy the prophet , saying , And they took the thirty pieces of silver , the price of him that was valued , whom they of the children of Israel did value ;
text2: Ie ' i te ' pwe ' wunukuk kakitot CinImayi Nakanacimot otI kItwak , okiwtapnanawa i nswapituk nswapuk shonia , kapite ' ntakwsIt o kipInoce ' iuk Isniuk kapite ' nmawat .

text: And gave them for the potter ' s field , as the Lord appointed me .
text2: OkominawancI i onaknukI onInI ashkIot ce ' i okItkanI kanakwnIt Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And Jesus stood before the governor : and the governor asked him , saying , Art thou the King of the Jews ? And Jesus said unto him , Thou sayest .
text2: IcI Cisus e ' kinipwIt e ' nasmupnIt niw okuma , icI o okuma e ' natowat otI cI otInan , Kin , ni kitokumaomukok ki Cwiuk ? IcI Cisus , otI otInan kitukItsI .

text: And when he was accused of the chief priests and elders , he answered nothing .
text2: Pic cI kianmikakot ni kcI - me ' matmocuk onInwun , ipi ke ' ctaosIncIn ; coke ' ki okishInkwe ' ‘ twasin .

text: Then said Pilate unto him , Hearest thou not how many things they witness against thee ?
text2: OtI cI Payne ' t , okinan , conI kinotsin me ' kwe ' tso ke ' ko e ' shIi miane ' nmukon ?

text: And he answered him to never a word ; insomuch that the governor marvelled greatly .
text2: ConI tIna nkotuk okiknonasin ; kikcI mamkate ' ntum cI o okuma .

text: Now at that feast the governor was wont to release unto the people a prisoner , whom they would .
text2: IwcI e ' wikwtuk , okume ' kakuk okipkIte ' man nkote ' ie ' ke ' pakwukasnIt ke ' wawinanIt ni nIshInape ' n .

text: And they had then a notable prisoner , called Barabbas .
text2: Oki iu wawancI ke ' ke ' ntakwse ' nIt kie ' pakwukasnIt Pane ' pe ' s shInkaswun .

text: Therefore when they were gathered together , Pilate said unto them , Whom will ye that I release unto you ? Barabbas , or Jesus which is called Christ ?
text2: IcI pic kamaoce ' tiwat Payne ' t , otI okinan We ' ' nicI ne ' twe ' nme ' k e ' wipkItnumon kon ; Pe ' ne ' pe ' s tanake ' Cisus e ' shnukasot Knayst ?

text: For he knew that for envy they had delivered him .
text2: E ' ke ' nmat ni e ' kakiawe ' nmanIt kaocI pkItnumakot .

text: When he was set down on the judgment seat , his wife sent unto him , saying , Have thou nothing to do with that just man : for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him .
text2: Pic cI kacipitupIt shi tupaknukI pItie ' pwunuk , wiwun kipie ' mcIcimokie ' n otI cI kikItwun ; Ke ' ko nkot totwakIn one ' pwakatnInI ; kcImce ' sh ke ' ko win we ' cwitaiapituman nkom e ' kishkiwuk .

text: But the chief priests and elders persuaded the multitude that they should ask Barabbas , and destroy Jesus .
text2: KicI kcI - me ' matmocuk onInwuk , ipi ke ' ctaose ' cuk okiwishte ' pmawan ni maoce ' tincIn e ' wi ntotma ke ' nIt Pane ' pe ' sIn ; nicI e ' winshonacumIt CisusIn .

text: The governor answered and said unto them , Whether of the twain will ye that I release unto you ? They said , Barabbas .
text2: IcI okuma okinkwe ' twan , otI cI okinan , We ' nicI nkote ' ie ' ki kiIpkItnumonkon ; OtI cI kikItwuk , Pane ' pe ' s .

text: Pilate saith unto them , What shall I do then with Jesus which is called Christ ? They all say unto him , Let him be crucified .
text2: Payne ' t cI otI okinan . TInicI ke ' totwuk Cisus e ' shnukasot Knayst . OtI cI caye ' k okikon nocma win KIskakwukaso .

text: And the governor said , Why , what evil hath he done ? But they cried out the more , saying , Let him be crucified .
text2: IcI okuma kikIto , Taci ? We ' konicI kamcItotuk ? WusimI cI kiwishkowe ' k , otI cI kikItwuk , Nocma win KIskakwukaso .

text: When Pilate saw that he could prevail nothing , but that rather a tumult was made , he took water , and washed his hands before the multitude , saying , I am innocent of the blood of this just person : see ye to it .
text2: Pic cI Payne ' t e ' waptuk ke ' ko e ' wipwakshkItot , wusimI na ‘ wuc e ' nshkatsInIt , okiwtapinan mpish , icI e ' ki ksincat e ' nasmukapwunIt maoce ' tincIn , otI cI kikIto , Coin nin nsikwe ' pnumwasi ne ' pwakat omuskwim ; Kinwa wi ke ' shuwe ' psowe ' kwe ' n .

text: Then answered all the people , and said , His blood be on us , and on our children .
text2: Caye ' k cI ki nIshInape ' k okinkwe ' twawan , otI cI kikItwuk , Nocma ninan nkupukitakomIn iw mIskwim kIte ' nI , ipi nicanse ' nanuk .

text: Then released he Barabbas unto them : and when he had scourged Jesus , he delivered him to be crucified .
text2: IcI e ' kipkItnumwat ni Pane ' pe ' sIn , icI ni CisusIn , kapsItie ' wat okipkItnan e ' wiskakwukasnIt .

text: Then the soldiers of the governor took Jesus into the common hall , and gathered unto him the whole band of soldiers .
text2: IcI ni otI shumakunIshimIn okuma , okimacinawan ni CisusIn kikitokumkok , icI e ' kipie ' naskakot caye ' k shumakunIshIn e ' tshInIt .

text: And they stripped him , and put on him a scarlet robe .
text2: OkiskotnawancI icI e ' kipiskotnawat mskwe ' kIn kwawun .

text: And when they had platted a crown of thorns , they put it upon his head , and a reed in his right hand : and they bowed the knee before him , and mocked him , saying , Hail , King of the Jews !
text2: Pic cI kakate ' nmowat sisokwe ' psowun , cukunukaoshisun okitawawan otupik , ipi nasaknIshk okitawan ote ' pne ' cik , icI e ' kiw wucik kwuItwawat e ' nasmupkapwunIt , icI okinapitotwawan , , otI cI okinawan , We ' we ' nI ‘ we ' kuma omukwiIn Cwiuk .

text: And they spit upon him , and took the reed , and smote him on the head .
text2: IcI e ' ki skowanawat , ipi kiw tapnanawa i nasakunIshk , icI e ' kiwe ' potwawat otupik .

text: And after that they had mocked him , they took the robe off from him , and put his own raiment on him , and led him away to crucify him .
text2: KashkIc napitotwawat okikiskotnawan , icI win kapiskuk kipiskotnawan , icI e ' kishonawat e ' wiskakwawat .

text: And as they came out , they found a man of Cyrene , Simon by name : him they compelled to bear his cross .
text2: Kapie ' sakumwat cI ikiwapmawan , Se ' nini nInwun Sayiman e ' shInkaswun ; niw cI kitwe ' okinawan e ' wipmotonIt ni iashte ' iatkomnIn .

text: And when they were come unto a place called Golgotha , that is to say , a place of a skull ,
text2: Pic ci kanmupiawat e ' shnukate ' k , KanIkate ' , i e ' tmuk O Knatup e ' cite ' k .

text: They gave him vinegar to drink mingled with gall : and when he had tasted thereof , he would not drink .
text2: Okimanawan Siwapo , ipi wisup , katkostowat e ' wiminukwe ' nIt ; icI kakwucupituk , co ki mnukwe ' sin .

text: And they crucified him , and parted his garments , casting lots : that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet , They parted my garments among them , and upon my vesture did they cast lots .
text2: IcI e ' kiskakwawat , ipi okiswe ' nmowawan kapiskumnIt icI e ' kitatiwat e ' wite ' pwe ' wunukuk kakitot Nakanacimot , okiswe ' nawan paskamInIn e ' tshawat , ipi npiskumwakIn kaocI tatiwat .

text: And sitting down they watched him there ;
text2: Kicipitupwuk cI otukwapmawan cIshi .

text: And set up over his head his accusation written , THIS IS JESUS THE KING OF THE JEWS .
text2: IcI e ' kitowawat shiw otupik we ' npie ' kate ' nuk we ' cawat , OTI CISUS OTOKUMAMWAN KI CWIUK .

text: Then were there two thieves crucified with him , one on the right hand , and another on the left .
text2: Ipi cI nish kie ' motshke ' cuk , kitko Skakwukaswuk ; nkot ote ' pniwnak , nkot cI o onumciwnak .

text: And they that passed by reviled him , wagging their heads ,
text2: KicI kapmose ' cuk ikikuke ' cawan e ' mumukwe ' twawat .

text: And saying , Thou that destroyest the temple , and buildest it in three days , save thyself . If thou be the Son of God , come down from the cross .
text2: OtI cI otInawan , Kin , pe ' nactin kcInume ' okumuk , ipi kashIton e ' nsokwnukuk ke ' skontIson . KishpIn okwIsmukwiIn Kshe ' mIne ' to , pie ' nisasin shi kiashte ' iakwukinuk .

text: Likewise also the chief priests mocking him , with the scribes and elders , said ,
text2: Winwa ke ' ki kcIme ' matmocIk onInwuk okinatkoawan , kike ' onupie ' ke ' onInwuk , ipi ke ' ctaose ' cuk okinawan .

text: He saved others ; himself he cannot save . If he be the King of Israel , let him now come down from the cross , and we will believe him .
text2: Pe ' kansIncIn cI okike ' skonan , win cI co ke ' skontusi . KishpIn sI we ' tokmaomukwe ' n IsniIn , nocma win Kom kupie ' nisasi shi ashte ' atkok icI ke ' cI te ' pwe ' twukon .

text: He trusted in God ; let him deliver him now , if he will have him : for he said , I am the Son of God .
text2: Okipe ' nmonIn Kshe ' mIne ' ton , nocma win oka ‘ tapne ' kin , kishpIn waiaokokwe ' n , otI kakItot Nin NtokwIsmuk Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: The thieves also , which were crucified with him , cast the same in his teeth .
text2: KicI ke ' mockicuk katukwakwukascuk win wa ke ' i kanawat .

text: Now from the sixth hour there was darkness over all the land unto the ninth hour .
text2: Nawkwe ' k cI kikiskupkonia , e ' nkokwukumkiak ukI ; nash nsotupukIn e ' pite ' ntakwuk .

text: And about the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice , saying , Eli , Eli , lama sabachthani ? that is to say , My God , my God , why hast thou forsaken me ?
text2: Pic cI nso tupukInuk Cisus kikcInotakwse ' wak , otI cI kItwak , Inay , Inay , ne ' me ' se ' pe ' kte ' nay ? otI e ' kitok , Nkishe ' mIne ' tom Nkishe ' mIne ' tom , We ' kwnicI we ' c nkIshiun ?

text: Some of them that stood there , when they heard that , said , This man calleth for Elias .
text2: KicI anIt shikanipwoe ' cuk pic i kanotmowat , kikItwuk ; OtI nInI onItuman Inaisun .

text: And straightway one of them ran , and took a spunge , and filled it with vinegar , and put it on a reed , and gave him to drink .
text2: Kie ' nup cI nkot kimace ' pto , icI e ' kiw tapnuk Skuapowan , kiwumoshkIne ' tot siwapo , icI e ' kitot , e ' kinapsItot shi nasakunIshkok okiminancI , e ' wimnukwe ' nIt .

text: The rest said , Let be , let us see whether Elias will come to save him .
text2: KicI anIt otI kikItwuk , Ponuk , nocma wapmatan kI ‘ nwa ok ? pie ' skonkon ni Inaisun .

text: Jesus , when he had cried again with a loud voice , yielded up the ghost .
text2: Cisus cI kanotakwsIt minI e ' pic kotakuk , okipkItnan ocipamIn .

text: And , behold , the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom ; and the earth did quake , and the rocks rent ;
text2: PInI iwcI kaiakwukote ' k , pic iukwan kcInume ' okumkok , shpumuk kipie ' ocIpikw ‘ shke ' nashcI mtukumuk ; ipi kI ‘ kimacke ' mkIt ipi ni sInie ' n kipaskukie ' ton .

text: And the graves were opened ; and many bodies of the saints which slept arose ,
text2: Ipi kinsakshke ' ton ni cipe ' okumkwe ' n , mce ' sh cI kanpacuk kanumawakupIne ' n , kiwnIshke ' mkItnI wiwuwan ;

text: And came out of the graves after his resurrection , and went into the holy city , and appeared unto many .
text2: Kipie ' ocI sakumwuk shi cipe ' ‘ okumkok , kakishiapsinIt , kipitike ' kcI kcI - otanuk mce ' sh cI okiwaptuawan wiwuwan .

text: Now when the centurion , and they that were with him , watching Jesus , saw the earthquake , and those things that were done , they feared greatly , saying , Truly this was the Son of God .
text2: Pic cI Kapte ' n , ipi ni kapmI wice ' okocIn , kakowapmacIk CisusIn , e ' waptumwat kI e ' nanimshkanuk , ipi kanomkItInuk kikcIse ' ksik ; otI cI kikItwuk , We ' we ' ne ' sI otI okiwkwIsmukon Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And many women were there beholding afar off , which followed Jesus from Galilee , ministering unto him :
text2: Kimane ' k ke ' shi kwe ' k , pnoc e ' wsapmawat kapie ' pmnashkawacuk CisusIn kiw cupie ' k Ke ' nInIuk , e ' wipmitwawat .

text: Among which was Mary Magdalene , and Mary the mother of James and Joses , and the mother of Zebedee ' s children .
text2: Winke ' shi kitkoie ' Me ' ni Me ' kte ' ne ' n , ipi Me ' niIn , kaokie ' macIn Ce ' ms , ipi Cosus , ipi okie ' iwan Se ' piti onicansIn .

text: When the even was come , there came a rich man of Arimathaea , named Joseph , who also himself was Jesus ' disciple :
text2: Pic cI e ' nmupkonianuk kipie ' ocupie ' E ' nIme ' tiuk ke ' c tpe ' nwe ' osIt nInI , Cosip kishInkaso , win kie ' Cisus kaknomakot .

text: He went to Pilate , and begged the body of Jesus . Then Pilate commanded the body to be delivered .
text2: IcI tkishiat Paye ' ntIn , e ' kiwuntotmowat Cisus wiwuwIn . IcI Paye ' nt cI kikito , e ' wipkItumwut i wiia ‘ w .

text: And when Joseph had taken the body , he wrapped it in a clean linen cloth ,
text2: IcI Cosip kaotapnuk i wiia ‘ w okiwikwe ' ie ' kinan wapshkie ' kIn pukwoian , panakwtInuk .

text: And laid it in his own new tomb , which he had hewn out in the rock : and he rolled a great stone to the door of the sepulchre , and departed .
text2: OkiwusancI tpInwe ' otoshkicipe ' okumkok kawe ' napkaumatsokupIne ' n , shi sInik ; icI e ' ki tupce ' nuk kcI - sIn , e ' shkwate ' mwunuk , icipe ' okumkok , icI e ' kinke ' tuk .

text: And there was Mary Magdalene , and the other Mary , sitting over against the sepulchre .
text2: Kiie ' cI shi Me ' ni Me ' kte ' ne ' n , ipi o pe ' kansIt Me ' ni , kicipitukwuk cI ashowe ' iukwan shi cipe ' ‘ okumkok .

text: Now the next day , that followed the day of the preparation , the chief priests and Pharisees came together unto Pilate ,
text2: Ka WiiapukcI kakish oshIstowat i mkoshe ' wun ; ki kcI me ' matmocIk onInwuk , ipi Pe ' nisiuk kipie ' wice ' twuk , Payne ' tIn kipie ' shie ' k ;

text: Saying , Sir , we remember that that deceiver said , while he was yet alive , After three days I will rise again .
text2: OtI cI ikinawan Okuma , nmikwe ' ntamIn kakItpIt okawie ' shke ' mot me ' kwa e ' ie ' pmatsIt ; Kinsokwnukuk nkaonIshka minI .

text: Command therefore that the sepulchre be made sure until the third day , lest his disciples come by night , and steal him away , and say unto the people , He is risen from the dead : so the last error shall be worse than the first .
text2: KIton e ' wikawapcikate ' k nash i nsokishuk i cipe ' ‘ oknmuk ; tanupie ' n ke ' knomowacIn e ' ie ' pko nianuk e ' wikimocwunkot ; otI cI Otanawan ni nIshInape ' n , KipsukwiwaksI e ' npopI iwcI i ne ' tum .

text: Pilate said unto them , Ye have a watch : go your way , make it as sure as ye can .
text2: Paye ' nt cI otI okinan , anwusI KtIiwawak e ' kwapicuk ; ktashiamsI wawishkItok tso ke ' kshkItoie ' k .

text: So they went , and made the sepulchre sure , sealing the stone , and setting a watch .
text2: IcI e ' ki shiawat e ' ki wa ‘ wishkItowat i cipe ' okumuk , e ' ki tkwapkIstowat i sIn , ipi okisawan e ' kwapInIt .

text: In the end of the sabbath , as it began to dawn toward the first day of the week , came Mary Magdalene and the other Mary to see the sepulchre .
text2: KAPONUM e ' kishkuk e ' pie ' wasapuk i ne ' tum e ' kishkiwuk wik , kipie ' shiI Me ' ni Me ' ktIne ' n , ipi o pe ' kansIt Me ' ni , e ' pie ' waptumwat cipe ' ‘ okumuk .

text: And , behold , there was a great earthquake : for the angel of the Lord descended from heaven , and came and rolled back the stone from the door , and sat upon it .
text2: IcI pInI , e ' ki kcImackanuk kI ; Kshe ' mIne ' to omIshIne ' we ' mIn shpumuk kipie ' ocupie ' n , icI e ' kipiat nkoci cI okine ' nan i sIn kakpakwuke ' k shi shkwate ' muk icI e ' ki kwuctiie ' pIt .

text: His countenance was like lightning , and his raiment white as snow :
text2: E ' shnakwsItcI ke ' cwa e ' wawasmok , ipi paskuk kiwapshkianI ke ' cwakon .

text: And for fear of him the keepers did shake , and became as dead men .
text2: E ' pic kwsawat cI kikakowapcuk kinukshke ' k , ipi ne ' pkIn kishowe ' psik .

text: And the angel answered and said unto the women , Fear not ye : for I know that ye seek Jesus , which was crucified .
text2: OcI mshInwe ' okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan nikwe ' n ke ' ko kwtacke ' k ; kuke ' nme ' num Cisus e ' ntuwapme ' k , kaskakukwasot .

text: He is not here : for he is risen , as he said . Come , see the place where the Lord lay .
text2: Cowi shotI ie ' si ; kiw nIshke ' wak , kakItpIt , Piak pie ' waptumok kacIshkIshuk , Te ' pe ' nke ' t .

text: And go quickly , and tell his disciples that he is risen from the dead ; and , behold , he goeth before you into Galilee ; there shall ye see him : lo , I have told you .
text2: Kie ' nup shiak ipi kuitmowawak , ke ' knomowacIn e ' kiwnIshkanIt e ' npopIt ; pInI , nmInikani cawin ipI Ke ' ne ' niuk shiw ie ' shi ke ' cI wapme ' k , pInI , kikiwitmonum .

text: And they departed quickly from the sepulchre with fear and great joy ; and did run to bring his disciples word .
text2: IcI e ' kin mamaciwat e ' ki nkItmowat kie ' nup , i cipe ' ‘ okumuk kikwtacwuk , ipi kinciwe ' n - mok ; icI kipmupitok e ' wiwitmowawat ke ' knomowancIn .

text: And as they went to tell his disciples , behold , Jesus met them , saying , All hail . And they came and held him by the feet , and worshipped him .
text2: IcI e ' nmamaciwat e ' wuwitmowawat ni ke ' knomowancIn pInI , Cisus okinkwe ' shkwan otI cI okinan ; MnIwankosuk kinwa . IcI e ' ki pmumackonawat osItinuk , ipi okiwucikwnItwawan .

text: Then said Jesus unto them , Be not afraid : go tell my brethren that they go into Galilee , and there shall they see me .
text2: Cisus cI otI okinan ; Ke ' ko kwtacke ' k wuwitmowuk nikane ' iuk e ' wishiawat Ke ' nIniuk shiw ke ' cI wapmowat .

text: Now when they were going , behold , some of the watch came into the city , and shewed unto the chief priests all the things that were done .
text2: Me ' kwacI e ' nmIpiskawat , pInI anIt e ' kwapcIkipie ' shie ' k kcI otanuk , icI e ' kiwitmowawat kcI . me ' matmocIk onInwun , cake ' ko kashowe ' puk .

text: And when they were assembled with the elders , and had taken counsel , they gave large money unto the soldiers ,
text2: Pic cI kamaoce ' tiwat , ipi niw ke ' ctaose ' cIk ki - kikitot okiminawan mce ' sh shonia ni shumaknushIn ;

text: Saying , Say ye , His disciples came by night , and stole him away while we slept .
text2: OtI cI okinawan , otI kItok , ke ' knomowacIn kipie ' nme ' kwa e ' pkoniaiuk kipie ' kimocwunkon , e ' ie ' npaiak .

text: And if this come to the governor ' s ears , we will persuade him , and secure you .
text2: KishpIn cI otI , notuk okuma , nkuwishte ' pmamIn , icI ke ' cI pkIte ' nmukwie ' k .

text: So they took the money , and did as they were taught : and this saying is commonly reported among the Jews until this day .
text2: Okwtapnanawa cI i shonia kitotmokcI kanItwa ; icI ie ' i ke ' iapI e ' kitowat ki Cwiuk nash otI e ' kishciwuk .

text: Then the eleven disciples went away into Galilee , into a mountain where Jesus had appointed them .
text2: IcI ki mtatso shItnkot ke ' knomowacIn kishumacin shi Ke ' ne ' niuk kishie ' k e ' shpItnianuk kacI wawitmakwat ni CisusIn .

text: And when they saw him , they worshipped him : but some doubted .
text2: IcI kawapmawat okiw wucikwnItwawan , anIt cI kiianwe ' ntumwuk .

text: And Jesus came and spake unto them , saying , All power is given unto me in heaven and in earth .
text2: Cisus cI okipie ' knonan otIcI okinan , Caye ' k kshke ' ‘ e ' ‘ osuwun nminko , ipI shpumuk kishkok , ipi shotI kik .

text: Go ye therefore , and teach all nations , baptizing them in the name of the Father , and of the Son , and of the Holy Ghost :
text2: WimaciksI knomouk caye ' k e ' tso ikIswat nIshInape ' k ; kcItapie ' nuk otInoswunuk o We ' osmIt , ipi o We ' kwIsmIt ipi o KcI Ocipam .

text: Teaching them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you : and , lo , I am with you alway , even unto the end of the world . Amen .
text2: Ke ' nomouk e ' wi te ' pwe ' tmowat cak ke ' ko kashI ke ' kmInkon ; PInI kakuksI kowice ' wInum nash wishkwakiwuk . E ' me ' n .

text: The former treatise have I made , O Theophilus , of all that Jesus began both to do and teach ,
text2: NKIWSHITON ne ' tum msInukIn , O Tiapinus , caye ' k Cisus kaoshkawe ' pwshItot , ipi e ' ki kuknomake ' t .

text: Until the day in which he was taken up , after that he through the Holy Ghost had given commandments unto the apostles whom he had chosen :
text2: Nash i e ' kishkIwuk kaotapnukasot , shpumuk kakishminat okukie ' kwe ' wunIn shi PanakwsIt Cipam , ni nwakanacIn kaowe ' napmacIn ;

text: To whom also he shewed himself alive after his passion by many infallible proofs , being seen of them forty days , and speaking of the things pertaining to the kingdom of God :
text2: Nie ' ni ke ' iapI kawaptacIn wia ’ w e ' pmatsIt kakish kwtukitot shi mce ' sh we ' we ' nI te ' pwe ' tatwunIn e ' kiwapmukot nie ' waptuk tsokwun ipi e ' kiactuk cake ' ko Kshe ' mIne ' to otokumauwunuk :

text: And , being assembled together with them , commanded them that they should not depart from Jerusalem , but wait for the promise of the Father , which , saith he , ye have heard of me .
text2: Me ' kwacI e ' ie ' maosomat okiwitmowan e ' wipwa shi ocI macinIt Cinose ' ne ' muk e ' wi pwitowat Osma kowawituk , win kakitot nin kaocI notake ' ie ' k .

text: For John truly baptized with water ; but ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost not many days hence .
text2: Can we ' we ' nI ki kcItapie ' nwe ' , mpik nIshcI kinwa kukcItapie ' nkom , shi panakwsIt Cipam e ' pwamshI mce ' shkonkuk .

text: When they therefore were come together , they asked of him , saying , Lord , wilt thou at this time restore again the kingdom to Israel ?
text2: IcI kamaoce ' tiwat okinatawawan otI kikItwuk Te ' pe ' nke ' n ConI otI e ' picak minI kuminasi Isne ' iIn o kumauwun .

text: And he said unto them , It is not for you to know the times or the seasons , which the Father hath put in his own power .
text2: IcI otI okinan cosu wi kinwa e ' wi ke ' ntume ' k pic nikan wapiamkuk win osma katot shi owishkIswunuk .

text: But ye shall receive power , after that the Holy Ghost is come upon you : and ye shall be witnesses unto me both in Jerusalem , and in all Judaea , and in Samaria , and unto the uttermost part of the earth .
text2: KuotItnanawa wishkIswun ipi panakwsIt Cipam kikishotIskoie ' k , ipi nin kaocI witmake ' m caye ' k shi Cinose ' ne ' muk ipi caye ' k Cwtie ' uk , ipi shi Se ' me ' ne ' ok ipi shi mamwI pnocak shotI kik .

text: And when he had spoken these things , while they beheld , he was taken up ; and a cloud received him out of their sight .
text2: Pic cI kakish iactuk notI ke ' ko me ' kwa e ' ie ' wapmawat kiwcI otapnIkaso shpumuk ; ipi shi ankoton okipon wapmawan .

text: And while they looked stedfastly toward heaven as he went up , behold , two men stood by them in white apparel ;
text2: Me ' kwacI e ' ie ' kanapwat ipI shpumuk ; kanmIshianIt , pInI nish nInwun okiwicka pwutakwan kiwapshkianI kapiskumwacIn .

text: Which also said , Ye men of Galilee , why stand ye gazing up into heaven ? this same Jesus , which is taken up from you into heaven , shall so come in like manner as ye have seen him go into heaven .
text2: OtI cI ke ' iapI okikowan , Ke ' nIni tshI nInituk tacI we ' cnipwoie ' k shpumuk e ' napie ' k ? OtI nasap Cisus , kaocI otapnImakoie ' k shpumuk ; iw nasap ke ' shI piat kashu wapme ' k shpumuk kashu shiat .

text: Then returned they unto Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet , which is from Jerusalem a sabbath day ' s journey .
text2: IcI Cinose ' ne ' muk kishu kiwe ' k kiwcIpie ' k e ' pkotnianuk AnIpIt kishInkate ' e ' nume ' kishkuk e ' picak shi Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: And when they were come in , they went up into an upper room , where abode both Peter , and James , and John , and Andrew , Philip , and Thomas , Bartholomew , and Matthew , James the son of Alphaeus , and Simon Zelotes , and Judas the brother of James .
text2: Pic cI kapitke ' we ' t shpumuk kishie ' k wikwamuk kaci iuwat Pitu , ipi Ce ' ms , ipi can ipi E ' ntnu , Pinip , ipi Tame ' s , Pe ' toniu , ipi Me ' to ‘ Ce ' ms kaokwIsmukot E ' npiusIn , ipi Sayi mun Sinotus , ipi Cwte ' s , wikane ' iIn Ce ' ms .

text: These all continued with one accord in prayer and supplication , with the women , and Mary the mother of Jesus , and with his brethren .
text2: KotI caye ' k pIne ' kimsone ' ntumwuk akimimawat , ipi kimumatmok shi kiInkwe ' n , ipi Me ' ni kaokie ' imat o Cisus ipi niw wikane ' iIn

text: And in those days Peter stood up in the midst of the disciples , and said , ( the number of names together were about an hundred and twenty , )
text2: IwcI notI e ' kishkiwuk Pitu KinipwI na ‘ iukwan ni ke ' knomake ' cuk ( e ' tshuwat cukI tInoswunwa kansoiwat nkotwaktshik , ipi nishwaptuk ) otI cI kikIto ;

text: Men and brethren , this scripture must needs have been fulfilled , which the Holy Ghost by the mouth of David spake before concerning Judas , which was guide to them that took Jesus .
text2: NInituk , ipi nikane ' ituk , otI kikItowIn taocI nomkuk e ' wite ' pwe ' mkuk Te ' pIt kaocI kItot ni PanakwsIncIn CipamIn e ' kiiacimat nikan ni Cwte ' sIn , win kapmInikansIt e ' kiwtapnawat CisusIn .

text: For he was numbered with us , and had obtained part of this ministry .
text2: Win kiwictkokcIkaso ipi o kiwtItnan anIt otI pmitake ' wun

text: Now this man purchased a field with the reward of iniquity ; and falling headlong , he burst asunder in the midst , and all his bowels gushed out .
text2: OtI nInI okikishpIne ' ton ktukan iwtpu ‘ ukoswun miashuwe ' psiwun , ipi nikan kishI pmokocIn kitokce ' shInce ' na ‘ iukwan icI caye ' k picnI kisaktakwte ' nI .

text: And it was known unto all the dwellers at Jerusalem ; insomuch as that field is called in their proper tongue , Aceldama , that is to say , The field of blood .
text2: Ipi otI okikuke ' ntanawa , caye ' k ki katacuk shi Cinose ' ne ' muk kikuke ' ncIkate ' i ktukan , e ' shInkate ' kw winwa kwiuk e ' shumwat E ' sIntime ' e ' tmuk i ktukan mskwI .

text: For it is written in the book of Psalms , Let his habitation be desolate , and let no man dwell therein : and his bishoprick let another take .
text2: Osam onIpie ' kate ' shi msInukIn Nkumwunuk , Win e ' tat kupe ' pshukwsInI ipi cowIiI shi Ite ' si , ipi i otukwapke ' wun pe ' kansInIt okinapshkamakon .

text: Wherefore of these men which have companied with us all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us ,
text2: OtI cI ie ' i kotI nInwuk kapmuwice ' okonuk , pIne ' Tope ' nmukwiIkon Cisus e ' ki pitike ' t , ipi e ' kisakuk , shi e ' cIiIikon .

text: Beginning from the baptism of John , unto that same day that he was taken up from us , must one be ordained to be a witness with us of his resurrection .
text2: E ' we ' pkcItapie ' nwe ' t Can nash i e ' kishkiwuk kaotapnmakoikon nkot okInapshkawan e ' wi wicwitma ke ' ikon e ' ki iapsishnInIt .

text: And they appointed two , Joseph called Barsabas , who was surnamed Justus , and Matthias .
text2: Okiwe ' napmawan cI Nish Cosip kishInkaso Pe ' se ' pe ' s ipi ke ' iapI kashInkasot Custus , ipi Me ' taye ' s .

text: And they prayed , and said , Thou , Lord , which knowest the hearts of all men , shew whether of these two thou hast chosen ,
text2: IcI e ' kinumawat , ipi otI kikItwuk ; Kin Te ' pe ' nke ' n , kin ke ' ke ' ntumwutwa , caye ' k nInwuk ote ' ‘ iwan , knomoshInak we ' kwe ' nshutuk kote ' nkote ' iI kaowe ' napmItwa .

text: That he may take part of this ministry and apostleship , from which Judas by transgression fell , that he might go to his own place .
text2: Win e ' wi anIt pmitake ' t ipi NokantawIn win o Cwte ' s kaocI pmukocIk iw omaia tuwe ' psiwun , win e ' wishiat tpInowe ' e ' cIiIt .

text: And they gave forth their lots ; and the lot fell upon Matthias ; and he was numbered with the eleven apostles .
text2: IcI e ' kitatiwat wincI Me ' taye ' s kiw tapnuk aso ipi kitkokcIkaso ni mtatso shItnkot nwakanmIcIn .

text: And when the day of Pentecost was fully come , they were all with one accord in one place .
text2: Pic e ' kishkuk PIntikast wikwtowun kaocItsak , caye ' k kimsote ' e ' k kimaoce ' ‘ tik mamwInkoci .

text: And suddenly there came a sound from heaven as of a rushing mighty wind , and it filled all the house where they were sitting .
text2: IcI ka ‘ w kiwcI pie ' mkItnI notakwsIwun shpumuk ke ' cwa e ' ki cI wishkanmuk , ipi kimosh kIne ' se ' nI caye ' k shi wikwamuk kacI cipitupwat .

text: And there appeared unto them cloven tongues like as of fire , and it sat upon each of them .
text2: Owaptanawa se ' knInwaknIn ne ' swakwianuk ke ' cwa shkote ' , ipi nankot e ' tshowat kite ' nI wiwuwak .

text: And they were all filled with the Holy Ghost , and began to speak with other tongues , as the Spirit gave them utterance .
text2: Ipi caye ' k okimoshkIne ' shkakwan ni PankwsIt Cipam icI kiwe ' pkakikitok pkan kinowe ' k kashu minkowat OcipamIn .

text: And there were dwelling at Jerusalem Jews , devout men , out of every nation under heaven .
text2: Kite ' kcI ipI CInose ' ne ' muk Cwiuk me ' noshuwe ' pse ' cuk nInwuk e ' tsoshumowat shotI kik kiwcIpie ' k mtunmuk shpumuk .

text: Now when this was noised abroad , the multitude came together , and were confounded , because that every man heard them speak in his own language .
text2: IcI otI kanotmoat , pnoc kamaoce ' ticutk kipie ' maoke ' tik ? ipi kimamkate ' ntumwut os am e ' tshIt nInI okinotwawan e ' kikitonIte ' shumot .

text: And they were all amazed and marvelled , saying one to another , Behold , are not all these which speak Galilaeans ?
text2: Caye ' kcI kimamkate ' ntumwuk , ipi pkan okine ' mawan otIcI kishItwuk , PInI coe ' I kotI caye ' k kakitocuk Ke ' nIni nInwuk ?

text: And how hear we every man in our own tongue , wherein we were born ?
text2: TInicI e ' shnotwukon e ' tshIt nInI , e ' ki ie ' i nowe ' ikon kashu nikiiIkon .

text: Parthians , and Medes , and Elamites , and the dwellers in Mesopotamia , and in Judaea , and Cappadocia , in Pontus , and Asia ,
text2: Pe ' tie ' nuk , ipi Mitiuk , ine ' mituk ipi ki e ' tacuk shi MIsopote ' miuk , ipi shi Cwtie ' uk , Kpe ' toshie ' uk shi Pantusuk ipi E ' shie ' uuk ,

text: Phrygia , and Pamphylia , in Egypt , and in the parts of Libya about Cyrene , and strangers of Rome , Jews and proselytes ,
text2: Pnicie ' uk ipi shi e ' kiwuk Nipie ' uk ipi ipI Sinie ' nk ipi pwake ' ntakwse ' cuk kiw cupie ' k Nom ipi Cwiuk ipi te ' pwe ' twacIk .

text: Cretes and Arabians , we do hear them speak in our tongues the wonderful works of God .
text2: E ' nitniuk , ipi E ' ne ' pie ' niuk knotwamIn e ' kikitowat e ' shumie ' kon o oimamkate ' nta kwIwun Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And they were all amazed , and were in doubt , saying one to another , What meaneth this ?
text2: Ipi caye ' k ki mamkate ' ntumwuk ipi kikwinwune ' ntumwuk otIcI kishItwuk , we ' kwnicI otI we ' cnom Kuk ?

text: Others mocking said , These men are full of new wine .
text2: AnItcI okinaptotwawan kItwuk , kotIsI nInwuk Omoshkne ' shkakwnawa wshkI shomnapo .

text: But Peter , standing up with the eleven , lifted up his voice , and said unto them , Ye men of Judaea , and all ye that dwell at Jerusalem , be this known unto you , and hearken to my words :
text2: NIshcI Pitu akiwickapwutwan ni mtatso shItnkot okiknonan otI okinan ; kinwa e ' tshI nIniwie ' k Cwtie ' uk , ipi caye ' k kinwa , e ' taie ' k Cinose ' ne ' muk otI kuke ' ntmok , ipi psItumok notI nkikitoonIn ,

text: For these are not drunken , as ye suppose , seeing it is but the third hour of the day .
text2: Cowi kotI kiwIshkwe ' pie ' sik i e ' ne ' nme ' k o samkIni nsotpukIn e ' kwokishkiwuk .

text: But this is that which was spoken by the prophet Joel ;
text2: OtIsi ie ' i katuk nakanacimot Cowun ;

text: And it shall come to pass in the last days , saith God , I will pour out of my Spirit upon all flesh : and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy , and your young men shall see visions , and your old men shall dream dreams :
text2: OtI ke ' nomkuk pic wishkwakishkiwuk kItwak Kshe ' mIne ' to NkIsikna ncipam kwIciukwan caye ' k wias , ipi kokwIswak , ipi kitansu ’ wak knikanacimok , ipi ktoshInunwe ' mwak kukwsaptumwuk ipi ktukwe ' simawak oke ' iapwatanawa iapwe ' wunIn .

text: And on my servants and on my handmaidens I will pour out in those days of my Spirit ; and they shall prophesy :
text2: Ipi npumitakaimuk , ipi ntupa ’ nkwe ' imuk nkIsiknumwak ncipamIn niw e ' kishkiwuk icI knikanacimok .

text: And I will shew wonders in heaven above , and signs in the earth beneath ; blood , and fire , and vapour of smoke :
text2: Ipi nkuwaptuwe ' mamkate ' ntumwunIn shi shpumuk kishkok , ipi mataoshuwe ' psuwun shotI kik namiukwan , mskwI , ipi shkote ' , ipi ke ' c pkwe ' ne ' k .

text: The sun shall be turned into darkness , and the moon into blood , before that great and notable day of the Lord come :
text2: Ipi kisIs kukiskupkoniawapkIse ' , ipi tpukisIs kumskwiwe ' e ' pwamshupiamkuk i kcIkishIk , ipi omiuk kukishkom Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And it shall come to pass , that whosoever shall call on the name of the Lord shall be saved .
text2: KnomkItcI we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' wawitmowakwe ' n otInoswun Kshe ' mIne ' to kuke ' skona .

text: Ye men of Israel , hear these words ; Jesus of Nazareth , a man approved of God among you by miracles and wonders and signs , which God did by him in the midst of you , as ye yourselves also know :
text2: Isne ' iuk e ' tshI nIniwie ' k psItmok notI kikitonIn Cisus Ne ' sInI nInI kamnonwe ' kot Kshe ' mIne ' to kamataototuk , ipi mamkate ' ntumwunIn , ipi mataoshuwe ' psuwunIn win Kshe ' mIne ' to katotuk shi wiwunuk me ' kwe ' nawe ' nI kinwa ke ' iapI kuke ' ntanawa .

text: Him , being delivered by the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God , ye have taken , and by wicked hands have crucified and slain :
text2: Win kapkItnukasot kane ' nmat ipi nikan kashuke ' nmat Kshe ' mIne ' to , kinwa kautapne ' k ipi kmIconIciwan kiskakwawa ipi kinsawa .

text: Whom God hath raised up , having loosed the pains of death : because it was not possible that he should be holden of it .
text2: Win Kshe ' mIne ' to kapsukwitmat kaiapskopitot , i wis ke ' ntumwun shi upomuk , o samco otakshkumac konkosin shiw .

text: For David speaketh concerning him , I foresaw the Lord always before my face , for he is on my right hand , that I should not be moved :
text2: Osam Te ' pIt otI kItwak e ' ki iacimot , nikan nkiwapma Kshe ' mIne ' to pIne ' ’ e ' nasmupian shiuwak nte ' pniw nak , e ' wi pwamatpe ' ian .

text: Therefore did my heart rejoice , and my tongue was glad ; moreover also my flesh shall rest in hope :
text2: IwcI ie ' i nte ' ’ kimnowankosimkIt ipi nse ' knInwakIn kinciwe ' nmomkIt wusimI ke ' iapI ntuwiasum kInwashmomkIt shi pkose ' nmowunuk .

text: Because thou wilt not leave my soul in hell , neither wilt thou suffer thine Holy One to see corruption .
text2: Osam kin , cokInkinasi ncipam shi namkumuk , coke ' kin kIne ' nmasi panakwsIt Nkot e ' wiwaptuk mpIshknInwun .

text: Thou hast made known to me the ways of life ; thou shalt make me full of joy with thy countenance .
text2: KikInomowasha pmatse ' ian kin kumoshkIne ' sto ’ w papine ' nmowun shi ktIshnakwsiwunuk .

text: Men and brethren , let me freely speak unto you of the patriarch David , that he is both dead and buried , and his sepulchre is with us unto this day .
text2: NInituk ipi nikane ' ituk nocima we ' we ' nI kuknonum e ' witshumuk , o osma Te ' pIt iw e ' kinpot , ipi e ' kinkokasot , ipi i ocipe ' okumuk e ' ci iIikon te ' nI otI e ' kishkiwuk .

text: Therefore being a prophet , and knowing that God had sworn with an oath to him , that of the fruit of his loins , according to the flesh , he would raise up Christ to sit on his throne ;
text2: Osam win e ' iacimot ipi e ' ke ' ntuk Kshe ' mIne ' ton e ' kie ' tnamukot niw nicansun shiw otowiasmuk okaocI psukwitnan ni KnaystIn e ' wi cipitupnIt shiw cipitupwunuk .

text: He seeing this before spake of the resurrection of Christ , that his soul was not left in hell , neither his flesh did see corruption .
text2: Win nikane ' kiwaptuk okitshItomowan e ' wiapsishnInIt ni KnaystIn nike ' , ocipamIn , cokinkIc kasin shi namkumuk coke ' i otowiasum co kiwaptusin mpIshknInwun .

text: This Jesus hath God raised up , whereof we all are witnesses .
text2: OtI Cisus Kshe ' mIne ' to kapsukwitnat ie ' i kinan caye ' k watmake ' ikon .

text: Therefore being by the right hand of God exalted , and having received of the Father the promise of the Holy Ghost , he hath shed forth this , which ye now see and hear .
text2: Iw ie ' i ote ' pniwnanuk Kshe ' mIne ' ton kapsukwitnukot ipi kaminkoni osIn kawawitmakot ni panakwsIncIn CipamIn kanitawe ' t iw nkom waptume ' k ipi nwatme ' k .

text: For David is not ascended into the heavens : but he saith himself , The LORD said unto my Lord , Sit thou on my right hand ,
text2: Osam Te ' pIt comshu shpumuk shiIsi nIshcI . win tpInwe ' kIto , Te ' pe ' nke ' t okinan ni Te ' pe ' n mukwian , cipitupIn shotI nte ' pniwnak .

text: Until I make thy foes thy footstool .
text2: Nash kiw shu ukwa me ' iane ' nmukwiIn e ' wipIste ' piIn .

text: Therefore let all the house of Israel know assuredly , that God hath made that same Jesus , whom ye have crucified , both Lord and Christ .
text2: OtI cI ie ' i caye ' k otu wikwamwa Isne ' iIn we ' we ' nI okuke ' ntana Kshe ' mIne ' to okiwshuan oie ' o Cisus kinwa kaskakwoe ' k ne ' ne ' ish Te ' pe ' nke ' t ipi Knayst .

text: Now when they heard this , they were pricked in their heart , and said unto Peter and to the rest of the apostles , Men and brethren , what shall we do ?
text2: Pic cI otI kanotmoat kiptukte ' e ' shke ' k ipi otI okinawan ni PituIn , ipi ni anIt nwakanmIcIn NInituk ipi nikane ' ituk we ' kwnicI ke ' totmukon .

text: Then Peter said unto them , Repent , and be baptized every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ for the remission of sins , and ye shall receive the gift of the Holy Ghost .
text2: OtI cI Pitu okinan kisate ' ntmok , ipi kcItapie ' nkasok e ' tshIie ' k shiw tInoswunuk Cisus Knayst e ' wi we ' pnakoie ' k ni kmIiashuwe ' psiwnawan icI kuminkom i mikwe ' wun o panakwsIt Cipam .

text: For the promise is unto you , and to your children , and to all that are afar off , even as many as the Lord our God shall call .
text2: Osam i wawitmake ' wun , kuwawitmakom , ipi ki ktupInoce ' imowak ipi ki caye ' k pnoc e ' icIk ; ke ' iapI tso Te ' pe ' nke ' t Kshe ' mIne ' tomnan ke ' ntomakwe ' n .

text: And with many other words did he testify and exhort , saying , Save yourselves from this untoward generation .
text2: Ipi mce ' sh pe ' kankInkItwunIn , kiwitmake ' , ipi kikie ' kwe ' , otI kikIto , kiskontIsok , shiw ki me ' iashuwe ' pse ' cIk pmats cIk .

text: Then they that gladly received his word were baptized : and the same day there were added unto them about three thousand souls .
text2: Pic cI i kanciwe ' nmocuk e ' kiwtapnumwawat , iw kikitowun , kikcItapie ' nkaswuk icI i e ' kishkiwuk , nsuk mtatswak knIpIc kitshik .

text: And they continued stedfastly in the apostles ' doctrine and fellowship , and in breaking of bread , and in prayers .
text2: IcI kitotmok we ' we ' nI i nwakancuk ote ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwunwa , ipi tpantuwun , ipi e ' kipikupitowat pkwe ' shkIn ipi e ' numawat .

text: And fear came upon every soul : and many wonders and signs were done by the apostles .
text2: Ipi se ' ksowun , okiwtuskonawa e ' tshuwat cipamwan , ipi mce ' sh mamkate ' ntumwunIn , ipi mataototmonIn kitotmok ki nwakancuk .

text: And all that believed were together , and had all things common ;
text2: Ipi caye ' k ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk mamwI kiik ; otIpInoe ' wsiwnawa mamawI okitupe ' ne ' ntanawa .

text: And sold their possessions and goods , and parted them to all men , as every man had need .
text2: Ipi kitawe ' k otIpnoe ' usiwnawan , ipi otInkackInwan , icI e ' ki swe ' nmowawat , caye ' k nInwun kashumne ' snIt cak nInwun .

text: And they , continuing daily with one accord in the temple , and breaking bread from house to house , did eat their meat with gladness and singleness of heart ,
text2: Ipi pIne ' ‘ e ' tso kishkItnuk e ' kimsone ' ntumwuk shi kcI nume ' okumkok ipi okipikupitonawa pkwe ' shkIn , e ' tsunuk wikwame ' n ipi okimicnawa micum shi mnowankoswunuk , ipi kinkotnInI ote ' ‘ iwa .

text: Praising God , and having favour with all the people . And the Lord added to the church daily such as should be saved .
text2: E ' winwanawat Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi e ' mnonwe ' awat caye ' k nIshInape ' n , ipi Kshe ' mIne ' to okiianke ' san ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIcIn e ' tsokiskItnuk ; ki wake ' skonkascuk .

text: Now Peter and John went up together into the temple at the hour of prayer , being the ninth hour .
text2: IcI Pitu ipi Can , kiwice ' twuk shpumuk kcI - nume ' okumkok shaktso tpukIn e ' pite ' ntakwuk , pic wanumak .

text: And a certain man lame from his mother ' s womb was carried , whom they laid daily at the gate of the temple which is called Beautiful , to ask alms of them that entered into the temple ;
text2: IwcI ukot nInI e ' konikIt co kinupmose ' si kipmaocIkaso ; okisawan e ' tso kishkuk e ' cI shkwate ' mkate ' nuk kcI - nume ' okumuk e ' shnukate ' k Ke ' cwunuk ; e ' wintotmowawat mikwe ' wunIn nipatike ' nIt shi kcI - nume ' okumkok .

text: Who seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple asked an alms .
text2: E ' wapmatcI Pitu , ipi CanIn e ' nmupitike ' nut kcI - nume ' okumkok okintotmowan mikwe ' wun .

text: And Peter , fastening his eyes upon him with John , said , Look on us .
text2: Pitu cI okikanapman , ipi Can kItwak , WapmIshnak ;

text: And he gave heed unto them , expecting to receive something of them .
text2: IwcI okinaksowapman e ' pkose ' nmat ke ' koe ' wiminkot .

text: Then Peter said , Silver and gold have I none ; but such as I have give I thee : In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth rise up and walk .
text2: Pitu cI kIto ; Lonia ipi osaw shonia , cointe ' isin ; nIshcI e ' toian kuminIn , Otnoswunuk , Cisus Knayst , Ne ' se ' nIt nInI , psukwin , ipi pmose ' n .

text: And he took him by the right hand , and lifted him up : and immediately his feet and ancle bones received strength .
text2: IwcI e ' kiskInce ' nat ote ' pniciwnuk ipi okipsukwitnan iwcI papuk niwsIte ' n ipi okate ' n kiwishksimkItnI .

text: And he leaping up stood , and walked , and entered with them into the temple , walking , and leaping , and praising God .
text2: IwcI e ' kipsukwit kinipwI , ipi kipmose ' , ipi e ' nmowice ' wat shi kcI - nume ' okumkok , e ' nmupmose ' t , ipi e ' nmukwakwaskwse ' ot , ipi e ' uwinwanat Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And all the people saw him walking and praising God :
text2: Ipi caye ' k ki nIshInape ' k oki wapmawan e ' pmose ' nIt , ipi e ' uwinwananIt Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And they knew that it was he which sat for alms at the Beautiful gate of the temple : and they were filled with wonder and amazement at that which had happened unto him .
text2: Okikike ' nmawancI e ' ki cipitupnIt shi ke ' c wuntInuk shkwate ' muk kcI - nume ' okumkok icI kimoshkne ' shkakwnawa kimamkate ' ntumwun ipi okimamkate ' nmawan kashu shuwe ' ntakwsInIt .

text: And as the lame man which was healed held Peter and John , all the people ran together unto them in the porch that is called Solomon ' s , greatly wondering .
text2: IwcI o pwanupmose ' t nInI kane ' se ' e ' t okimackonan PituIn ipi CanIn , caye ' k ki cIshInape ' k ki pItok e ' ciInIt shkwate ' muk e ' shnukate ' k Sanuman , otIshkwate ' mwun kcImamkate ' ntumwan .

text: And when Peter saw it , he answered unto the people , Ye men of Israel , why marvel ye at this ? or why look ye so earnestly on us , as though by our own power or holiness we had made this man to walk ?
text2: IwcI pic Pitu kawaptuk , okiknonan ni nIshInape ' n , Kinwa isne ' iuk nInwuk , we ' kw nicI we ' cmamkate ' ntume ' k otI ipi we ' kwni , we ' ckanapmiak , ke ' cwa ninan te ' pinak nwishkIsiwnInan tanke ' , nmInoshuwe ' psiw nInan kaocIkshkukIt otI nInI e ' wipmose ' t .

text: The God of Abraham , and of Isaac , and of Jacob , the God of our fathers , hath glorified his Son Jesus ; whom ye delivered up , and denied him in the presence of Pilate , when he was determined to let him go .
text2: Okshe ' mIne ' tomIn . E ' pe ' ne ' e ' m , ipi Aysik , ipi Ce ' kap , ipi okshe ' mIne ' tomwan kosnanuk oki kcI pite ' nman okwIsIm CisusIn kinwa kapkIte ' n me ' k , ipi kaian we ' nme ' k e ' nasmupIt Payne ' t , pic kawishte ' pwe ' t e ' wipkItnat .

text: But ye denied the Holy One and the Just , and desired a murderer to be granted unto you ;
text2: NIshcI kianwe ' nmawa panakwsIt , Nkot ipi me ' noshuwe ' psIt , iwcI kintuwe ' nmawa e ' wipkIte ' ntmakoie ' k .

text: And killed the Prince of life , whom God hath raised from the dead ; whereof we are witnesses .
text2: Okanshuwe ' t kintonawa okuma pmatsowun Kshe ' mInato kapsukwItnuk shi npoonuk ninan iwe ' cwitmake ' iak

text: And his name through faith in his name hath made this man strong , whom ye see and know : yea , the faith which is by him hath given him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all .
text2: Ipi otInoswunuk , ote ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwIn shiw otInoswunuk , kaocI oshe ' It otI nInI e ' wishkIsIt kowapmawa ipi kuke ' ntanaw we ' we ' nI ote ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun shiw tInosunuk we ' cminIt otI kwiuk we ' cne ' se ' e ' t e ' nasmupie ' k kinwa caye ' k .

text: And now , brethren , I wot that through ignorance ye did it , as did also your rulers .
text2: Ipi nkom nikane ' ituk , Nin kuke ' ntan , ke ' ko e ' pwakuke ' ntume ' k iw , kaocItotme ' k katotmowat ke ' ki ktokmamwak .

text: But those things , which God before had shewed by the mouth of all his prophets , that Christ should suffer , he hath so fulfilled .
