text2: NIshcI notI cIie ' k Kshe ' mIne ' to nikan kashu knomowat ni caye ' k NakanacmoncIn , ni KnaystIn e ' wikwutuke ' ntumnIt , iwsI kanomkItnuk .

text: Repent ye therefore , and be converted , that your sins may be blotted out , when the times of refreshing shall come from the presence of the Lord ;
text2: Kisate ' ntumok , ipi kwe ' knoik tanakmIcshuwe ' psiwnawan ktakasipie ' makom , pic piamkuk e ' wshkinakwutot e ' nasmupIt Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And he shall send Jesus Christ , which before was preached unto you :
text2: Cisus KnaystIn , okupie ' nokanan ke ' isha kashupie ' wawitmakoie ' k .

text: Whom the heaven must receive until the times of restitution of all things , which God hath spoken by the mouth of all his holy prophets since the world began .
text2: Kishuk win , ke ' otapnukot nash kiwcItsunuk cake ' ko , win Kshe ' mIne ' to , kashI kikitot shiw toninuk caye ' k panakwsIncIn Nakan acimoncIn nash e ' kowe ' pkiwuk

text: For Moses truly said unto the fathers , A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren , like unto me ; him shall ye hear in all things whatsoever he shall say unto you .
text2: Mosis we ' we ' nI okinan nosnanIn Nakan acimot Kshe ' mIne ' to Se ' pe ' nmukwie ' k , kupsukwit namakwa kikane ' iwak ke ' cwa nin , winsu kupsItwawa cake ' ko , we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' koie ' k .

text: And it shall come to pass , that every soul , which will not hear that prophet , shall be destroyed from among the people .
text2: KnomkItcI we ' kwe ' ntuk cipam ke ' pwapsItwakwe ' n ni nakanacimocIn win kupinatsI me ' kwe ' nIshnape ' kI .

text: Yea , and all the prophets from Samuel and those that follow after , as many as have spoken , have likewise foretold of these days .
text2: Ipi caye ' k we ' piacimocuk Se ' mwInIn ipi ki ke ' naktone ' wacuk e ' tshowat kakItwat winwake ' okinikan iactanawa notI e ' kishkiwuk .

text: Ye are the children of the prophets , and of the covenant which God made with our fathers , saying unto Abraham , And in thy seed shall all the kindreds of the earth be blessed .
text2: KinwasI ktonicansumkowak Nakan acimocuk , ipi wawitmatwun , Kshe ' mIne ' to kawawitmowat kosnanIn okinan E ' pIne ' e ' mIn , ipi knicansuk caye ' k noe ' twun shotI kik kIshwe ' ntakwsik .

text: Unto you first God , having raised up his Son Jesus , sent him to bless you , in turning away every one of you from his iniquities .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to kapsukwitnat okwIsIn CisusIn , okinokanan kinwa ne ' tum e ' wishwe ' nmukwie ' k , e ' wiwe ' pnumakwie ' k kmiashuwe ' psiwnawan .

text: And as they spake unto the people , the priests , and the captain of the temple , and the Sadducees , came upon them ,
text2: Me ' kwe ' cI e ' ie ' knonawat ni nIshInape ' n me ' matmoncIn ipi Kapte ' n shi kcI - nume ' okumkok ipi Se ' cwsiuk , oki pie ' naskakwan .

text: Being grieved that they taught the people , and preached through Jesus the resurrection from the dead .
text2: Kikisate ' ntumwuk e ' ki knomowanIt ni nIshInape ' n , ipi e ' kie ' kwe ' nIt , i e ' wionIshkanIt , ni ne ' poncIn shi CisusIn .

text: And they laid hands on them , and put them in hold unto the next day : for it was now eventide .
text2: OkimshunawancI , ipi okikpakwawan nash wiapnInuk osam e ' nmupkonianuk .

text: Howbeit many of them which heard the word believed ; and the number of the men was about five thousand .
text2: NIshcI mce ' sh okite ' pwe ' takwan , kanotakwat nianuk mtatswak nInwuk kitshik kate ' pwe ' takwat .

text: And it came to pass on the morrow , that their rulers , and elders , and scribes ,
text2: KanomkukcI wiapuk kiw nakanse ' cuk , ipi otukwe ' simowan , ipi we ' npie ' makwcIn .

text: And Annas the high priest , and Caiaphas , and John , and Alexander , and as many as were of the kindred of the high priest , were gathered together at Jerusalem .
text2: Ipi E ' ne ' s ke ' cmatmot , ipi Ke ' Ipe ' s ipi Can , ipi E ' nukse ' ntu , ipi e ' tshowat e ' nwe ' mawacIn ni ke ' cmatmonIt kimaoce ' tik shi Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: And when they had set them in the midst , they asked , By what power , or by what name , have ye done this ?
text2: IwcI na ‘ wiukwan kacipitupawat okinatowawan . We ' kwnicI kshke ' osuwun tanakI we ' ni otInoswunuk otI kaocItotme ' k .

text: Then Peter , filled with the Holy Ghost , said unto them , Ye rulers of the people , and elders of Israel ,
text2: IwcI Pitu e ' moshkIne ' shkakot , PanakwsIncIn CipamIn , otI okinan , kinwa nakane ' nmukwie ' k nIshInape ' k , ipi e ' kwe ' simukwie ' k ki isne ' iun

text: If we this day be examined of the good deed done to the impotent man , by what means he is made whole ;
text2: KishpIn nkom e ' kishkiwuk natakoik , we ' cmnototwut , otI pwanu ‘ pmose ' t otI nInI , kaocI ne ' se ' t ?

text: Be it known unto you all , and to all the people of Israel , that by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth , whom ye crucified , whom God raised from the dead , even by him doth this man stand here before you whole .
text2: Kuke ' ntanawa kinwa caye ' k , ipi caye ' k nIshInape ' k shi isne ' iuk , shiw tInoswunuk Cisus Knayst Ne ' se ' ni nInI kaskakowe ' k Kshe ' mIne ' to kapsukwitnat e ' kinponIt , winsI otI nInI we ' cnipwIt e ' ne ' se ' t e ' nasmupie ' k .

text: This is the stone which was set at nought of you builders , which is become the head of the corner .
text2: OtIsI ie ' i sIn , kawe ' pne ' me ' k we ' ske ' ie ' k , iw sI ie ' i ne ' tmIsuk shi e ' wikwe ' ak .

text: Neither is there salvation in any other : for there is none other name under heaven given among men , whereby we must be saved .
text2: Coke ' pe ' kanuk ke ' skonwe ' wun otItosin cowi pe ' kanuk noswun namiukwun kishkok minasik ninwuk ke ' ocI ke ' skonkoikon .

text: Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John , and perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men , they marvelled ; and they took knowledge of them , that they had been with Jesus .
text2: IwcI kawaptumwawat i onikansiunawa ni PituIn ipi CanIn , e ' ke ' nmawat ke ' ko e ' pwake ' ntumnIt okimamkate ' nmawan ipi okinaktowe ' nmawan e ' kipmowice ' wanIt ni CisusIn .

text: And beholding the man which was healed standing with them , they could say nothing against it .
text2: Ipi e ' wapmawat , ni nInwun , kane ' se ' mIt e ' wickapwItakwat coke ' ko okinasiwan .

text: But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council , they conferred among themselves ,
text2: PicI kamace ' nashkawawat shi e ' tshI kikitowat okitshItanawa winwa .

text: Saying , What shall we do to these men ? for that indeed a notable miracle hath been done by them is manifest to all them that dwell in Jerusalem ; and we cannot deny it .
text2: OtI kItwuk , TInicI ke ' totwukon kotI nInwuk we ' we ' ne ' se ' mataonokie ' wun kitotmok ke ' iapI caye ' k waptanawa e ' tacuk shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , coce ' ktanIiakwne ' tsimIn .

text: But that it spread no further among the people , let us straitly threaten them , that they speak henceforth to no man in this name .
text2: E ' pwamshI cI kuke ' ntumwat nIshInape ' k kuikwamamIn , e ' wipwa kinonawat wIiI nInwun shi i noswunuk .

text: And they called them , and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach in the name of Jesus .
text2: IwcI e ' kintomawat ipi okinawan ke ' ko e ' wipwakItnIt , ipi e ' wipwakukinomake ' nIt shiw tInoswunuk CisusIn .

text: But Peter and John answered and said unto them , Whether it be right in the sight of God to hearken unto you more than unto God , judge ye .
text2: IwcI Pitu ipi Can , okinkwe ' twawan otI okinawan , Nakitowe ' ntmok kinwa wusIme ' nI kau ‘ wunIt e ' wiwaptuk Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' wipsItoukon kinwa wusimI icI Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: For we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard .
text2: CosI ntakshkItosimIn e ' wipwatshItmak notI ke ' ko kawaptmak ipi kanotmak .

text: So when they had further threatened them , they let them go , finding nothing how they might punish them , because of the people : for all men glorified God for that which was done .
text2: IwcI wusimI kaikwamawat okipkItnawan e ' pwamkumwat ke ' ko e ' wiwcI mcI totwawat osam e ' kwsawat ni nIshInape ' n , caye ' k nInwuk okiwinwanawan Kshe ' mIne ' to i katotmInIt .

text: For the man was above forty years old , on whom this miracle of healing was shewed .
text2: WusimI nie ' waptuk kitsoponkIsI onInI kamataone ' se ' It .

text: And being let go , they went to their own company , and reported all that the chief priests and elders had said unto them .
text2: IwcI kapkItnItwa kishie ' k e ' tnukie ' wat ipi kiactanawa caye ' k , kakowat , ni ke ' cmatmoncIn , ipi ke ' ctaose ' cuk .

text: And when they heard that , they lifted up their voice to God with one accord , and said , Lord , thou art God , which hast made heaven , and earth , and the sea , and all that in them is :
text2: IwcI i kanotmowat , mamawI okiwawinawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton , otI kItwuk Te ' pe ' nke ' n Kin Kshe ' mIne ' to , KawshIton kishuk , ipi kI , ipi kcIkum , ipi caye ' k pic iukwan e ' te ' k .

text: Who by the mouth of thy servant David hast said , Why did the heathen rage , and the people imagine vain things ?
text2: Kin kpumitakam Te ' pIt otonik kikIto , TacIki me ' ikIscIk , kaocInshkatsowat , ipi ki nIshInape ' k kaocI shIte ' awat ke ' ko me ' ante ' nuk ?

text: The kings of the earth stood up , and the rulers were gathered together against the Lord , and against his Christ .
text2: We ' kimaocIk shotI kik , kipsukwik ipi nakanse ' cuk kimaoce ' tik e ' nshke ' nmawat Te ' pe ' nke ' ncIn , ipi e ' nshke ' nmawat , Win KnaystIn .

text: For of a truth against thy holy child Jesus , whom thou hast anointed , both Herod , and Pontius Pilate , with the Gentiles , and the people of Israel , were gathered together ,
text2: We ' we ' ne ' te ' pwe ' wIn kinshke ' nmawan ni panakwsIncIn , knicansun CisusIn kin kawe ' napmIt , E ' nut ipi Pantus Payne ' t ipi ki Me ' ikIscIk , ipi ki nIshInape ' mIn isne ' iun kaocI maotoshnowat .

text: For to do whatsoever thy hand and thy counsel determined before to be done .
text2: E ' witotwe ' k we ' kwe ' ntuk knIciwan ipi ktIshte ' e ' wnowan , kane ' nme ' k e ' pwamshI i totwe ' k .

text: And now , Lord , behold their threatenings : and grant unto thy servants , that with all boldness they may speak thy word ,
text2: Ipi nkom Te ' pe ' nke ' n waptumo ‘ u kote ' ome ' iushtakwsonowa , ipi mish kupumitakaimuk , e ' wiwishkIte ' awat e ' witshItmowat i kukikitowIn .

text: By stretching forth thine hand to heal ; and that signs and wonders may be done by the name of thy holy child Jesus .
text2: E ' wishipnIce ' niIn , e ' wine ' se ' we ' n , ipi me ' matawiak , ipi mamkate ' ntumwunIn e ' wiwcI wshItok shiw , tInoswunuk panakwsIt knicanIs Cisus .

text: And when they had prayed , the place was shaken where they were assembled together ; and they were all filled with the Holy Ghost , and they spake the word of God with boldness .
text2: IwcI kakishnumawat shi cace ' iIwat , kiunukshke ' nI ; katshI maoce ' tiwat , ipi caye ' k , okimoshkIne ' shkakwan , panakwsIncIn cipam kiwishkItIe ' kcI e ' kitshItmowat okikitowun Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And the multitude of them that believed were of one heart and of one soul : neither said any of them that ought of the things which he possessed was his own ; but they had all things common .
text2: IwcI kimaoce ' ticuk cate ' pwe ' twacuk kin kot nInI ote ' ‘ iwa ipi kinkotwin cipamwan , coke ' wIiI ke ' ko okishItsin i te ' pe ' ntuk , win e ' iIt , okimsotpe ' ntanawa cake ' ko .

text: And with great power gave the apostles witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus : and great grace was upon them all .
text2: KcI wishkIswun cIki , nwakancIk , kikukInomake ' k i Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus kiwonIshke ' e ' npopIt ; icI kcI shuwe ' ncuke ' wun caye ' k okiInawa .

text: Neither was there any among them that lacked : for as many as were possessors of lands or houses sold them , and brought the prices of the things that were sold ,
text2: Coke ' wIiI e ' tshowat kintowe ' nkuke ' si e ' tshowat katpe ' ntukuk otukimwa tanake ' e ' tawacIn kitawe ' k , ipi , kipie ' tonawa kapite ' ntakwtunuk , ni katawe ' wacIn .

text: And laid them down at the apostles ' feet : and distribution was made unto every man according as he had need .
text2: IwcI mcIiakwan okitonawan e ' nasmup nIt ni nwakancIk osItiwak , icI e ' kimatu ‘ mwat e ' tshowat nInwuk , e ' shntawe ' ntumwat .

text: And Joses , who by the apostles was surnamed Barnabas , ( which is , being interpreted , The son of consolation , ) a Levite , and of the country of Cyprus ,
text2: Ipi Cosis ki nwakancIk kashuwawinItke ' Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , e ' iauke ' notmuk , We ' kwIsmukot mnowaukoswun , Nipayt nInI ipi e ' tnukie ' t Saypusuk . .

text: Having land , sold it , and brought the money , and laid it at the apostles ' feet .
text2: OkiIn , kI kitawe ' cI , ipi okipie ' ton i shonia , icI e ' kipie ' pkItnumwat ni nwakaucIk e ' tshIste ' pnIt .

text: But a certain man named Ananias , with Sapphira his wife , sold a possession ,
text2: NIshcI nkot nInI E ' ne ' naye ' s kishInkaso mamwI Se ' payne ' wiwun kitawe ' k otInpnowe ' wsiwnawa .

text: And kept back part of the price , his wife also being privy to it , and brought a certain part , and laid it at the apostles ' feet .
text2: IwcI i e ' kiiuwat i anIt kapite ' ntakwte ' nuk ke ' iapI ni wiwun okike ' ntan icI i anIt e ' kipie ' tot , ipi okipkItnumwan ni nwakancIk osItinuk .

text: But Peter said , Ananias , why hath Satan filled thine heart to lie to the Holy Ghost , and to keep back part of the price of the land ?
text2: OtI cI Pitu okinan E ' ne ' naye ' s , TacI mcImIne ' to kashI moshkIne ' sat kte ' ‘ ik e ' wikInwush ke ' nIt panakwsIt cipam , ipi e ' kiwtapnumIn , anIt i kapite ' ntakwuk i kI ?

text: Whiles it remained , was it not thine own ? and after it was sold , was it not in thine own power ? why hast thou conceived this thing in thine heart ? thou hast not lied unto men , but unto God .
text2: Shi e ' ie ' te ' k conI kin , kitpe ' ntusin , ipi katawe ' n conI ktakinI ‘ wishkInsin TacI otI kaocI shIte ' an shi kte ' ‘ ik cosuwi kuknosh kumasik nInwuk Kshe ' mIne ' toie ' k kuknoshkumu .

text: And Ananias hearing these words fell down , and gave up the ghost : and great fear came on all them that heard these things .
text2: IwcI E ' ne ' naye ' s e ' notuk notI kikitonIn kipmukocIn , ipi okipkItnan ocipamIn icI kik cIse ' ksik caye ' k ki kanotkuk notI .

text: And the young men arose , wound him up , and carried him out , and buried him .
text2: IwcI ki oshkInowe ' k e ' kipsukwiwat ipi okiwiwe ' knawan icI e ' kisakconawat icI e ' kinkowawat .

text: And it was about the space of three hours after , when his wife , not knowing what was done , came in .
text2: NsotpukIncI e ' pite ' ntakwuk wiwun e ' pwake ' n tuk kanomkItnuk kipie ' pitike ' .

text: And Peter answered unto her , Tell me whether ye sold the land for so much ? And she said , Yea , for so much .
text2: PitucI otI okinan WitmoshIn iwnItso kanukite ' k i kI ? otIcI okinan e ' ‘ iwsI kanukite ' k .

text: Then Peter said unto her , How is it that ye have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord ? behold , the feet of them which have buried thy husband are at the door , and shall carry thee out .
text2: Pitu cI otI okinan , TInicI e ' shwitokwtatie ' k e ' wikwcite ' pe ' nme ' k ocipamIn Te ' pe ' nke ' t PInI osItiwanki kawInkowacuk knape ' mIn cik shkwate ' muk ke ' iapI kin ksakconukok .

text: Then fell she down straightway at his feet , and yielded up the ghost : and the young men came in , and found her dead , and , carrying her forth , buried her by her husband .
text2: IwcI e ' kipmukocuk kie ' nup shiw osItik cI okipkItnan ocipamIn , icI ki oshkInowe ' k kipie ' pitike ' k , ipi okimkawawan e ' nponIt icI ke ' win e ' kisakconawat okiwunkowawan cik iukwan onape ' mun

text: And great fear came upon all the church , and upon as many as heard these things .
text2: KikcI saksikcI caye ' k ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk ipi e ' tshuwat kanotkuk notI .

text: And by the hands of the apostles were many signs and wonders wrought among the people ; ( and they were all with one accord in Solomon ' s porch .
text2: IwcI ki nwakancuk shi onIciwak kinInkie ' k mce ' sh mataototmowun ipi mamkate ' ntumwun me ' kwe ' nIshInape ' ke ' , ( ipi caye ' k mamawI kiikikshi sanamun otI shkwate ' muk . )

text: And of the rest durst no man join himself to them : but the people magnified them .
text2: KicI pe ' kanse ' cIk cowIiI nInI okiwitokwasiwan kicI nIshInape ' k okikcI winwankowan .

text: And believers were the more added to the Lord , multitudes both of men and women . )
text2: WusimIcI okite ' pwe ' twawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton patie ' n wucuik nInwuk ipi kwe ' k .

text: Insomuch that they brought forth the sick into the streets , and laid them on beds and couches , that at the least the shadow of Peter passing by might overshadow some of them .
text2: IwcI kaocI pie ' nawat iakwnokancIn shiw otan mie ' uwuk , ipi mpaknuk okishkIshmawan te ' pnak e ' wikIckakshkumakwat anIt ni PituIn e ' ie ' pmose ' nIt .

text: There came also a multitude out of the cities round about unto Jerusalem , bringing sick folks , and them which were vexed with unclean spirits : and they were healed every one .
text2: Kipie ' ocI sakumwuk maoce ' ticIk shi kcI otanIn , kiw tayiukwan Cinose ' ne ' muk e ' pie ' nawat iakwnokancIn , ipi ni McIme ' ton e ' kIshkwancIn , icI caye ' k kine ' se ' k .

text: Then the high priest rose up , and all they that were with him , ( which is the sect of the Sadducees , ) and were filled with indignation ,
text2: IwcI e ' kipsukwit kcI me ' matmot ipi ni caye ' k watokakwcIn Se ' cwsiIn kimoshkIne ' nshkatsikcI .

text: And laid their hands on the apostles , and put them in the common prison .
text2: IwcI e ' kimackonawat ni nwakancIn icI e ' kikpakwawat kpakwotiwkumkok .

text: But the angel of the Lord by night opened the prison doors , and brought them forth , and said ,
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to cI omIshIne ' we ' mIn e ' pkonianuk okipie ' n sakwnan kpakotiukumuk shkwate ' me ' n icI e ' kipie ' sakcowunat ipi otI okinan .

text: Go , stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life .
text2: Shiak ipi wunipwuk shi kcI - nume ' okumkok ipi witmouk ki nIshInape ' k i caye ' k kikitonIn otI pmatsowun .

text: And when they heard that , they entered into the temple early in the morning , and taught . But the high priest came , and they that were with him , and called the council together , and all the senate of the children of Israel and sent to the prison to have them brought .
text2: IwcI pic kanotmoat i kipitike ' k shi kcInume ' okumkok kukishie ' p , ipi kiknomake ' t kcI me ' matmot kipie ' ipi ni kapie ' wice ' okot okintoman e ' wikikitowat ipi caye ' k okIctaos simwan Isne ' iIn OnicansIn ipi kinokashwe ' shi kpakotiwkumkok e ' wi pie ' ckasnIt .

text: But when the officers came , and found them not in the prison , they returned , and told ,
text2: NIshcI okumuk kapiawat ipi kapwa mkuwawat shi kpakotiwkumkok kikiwe ' k ipi kiwitmake ' k .

text: Saying , The prison truly found we shut with all safety , and the keepers standing without before the doors : but when we had opened , we found no man within .
text2: OtI kItwuk we ' we ' nI nkimkamIn i kpakotiwkumuk e ' wike ' kpak wukate ' k ipi ki e ' kwapicuk sakciukwan shkwate ' muk e ' nipwowat nIshcI kansakwne ' mak cowIiI nInI nkimkawasimIn shi pituk .

text: Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple and the chief priests heard these things , they doubted of them whereunto this would grow .
text2: IwcI pic kanotmoat kcI me ' matmot ipi Kapte ' n shi kcI - nume ' okumkok , ipi me ' matmo cuk kikwInwune ' ntumwuk we ' kwe ' ntuk otI we ' cnomkItIkwe ' n .

text: Then came one and told them , saying , Behold , the men whom ye put in prison are standing in the temple , and teaching the people .
text2: IwcI nkot okipie ' witmakwe ' n otI kikIto PInI kiw nInwuk kakpakwe ' k shi kpakotiw kumkoki ni pwik shi kcI - nume ' okumkok ipi o kuknomowawan no nIshInape ' n .

text: Then went the captain with the officers , and brought them without violence : for they feared the people , lest they should have been stoned .
text2: IwcI e ' kishiawat Kapte ' n , ipi ki okumac tokumci okinanawan osam okikwsawan ni nIshInape ' n e ' wisInokwat .

text: And when they had brought them , they set them before the council : and the high priest asked them ,
text2: IwcI kapie ' nawat okicipitupawan e ' nasmupwat shi kikitonuk icI o kcI me ' matmot okinatawan .

text: Saying , Did not we straitly command you that ye should not teach in this name ? and , behold , ye have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine , and intend to bring this man ' s blood upon us .
text2: OtI okinan , ConI kiikwamIsnonmIn e ' wipwe ' knomake ' ie ' k shi noswunuk icI pInI kimoshkIne ' stonawa shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , i kukie ' kwe ' wunawa ktne ' ntanawacI e ' wipie ' twuiak o nInI muskwim .

text: Then Peter and the other apostles answered and said , We ought to obey God rather than men .
text2: IwcI Pitu , ipi kipe ' kanse ' cIk nwakancIk kinkwe ' twawan , otI okinawan Kshe ' mIne ' to sI wusimI nta ‘ te ' pwe ' twamIn , icI nInwuk .

text: The God of our fathers raised up Jesus , whom ye slew and hanged on a tree .
text2: Kosnanuk okshe ' mIne ' tomwan okipsukwitnan CisusIn kinwa kanse ' k ipi kakone ' k mtukok .

text: Him hath God exalted with his right hand to be a Prince and a Saviour , for to give repentance to Israel , and forgiveness of sins .
text2: Win Kshe ' mIne ' to , kapsukwitnat ote ' pnIciwnak e ' wi okumaonIt , ipi ke ' skonwe ' nIt e ' wiminat kisate ' ntumwun , ni Isne ' In ; ipi pone ' ntumwun miashuwe ' psiwnIn .

text: And we are his witnesses of these things ; and so is also the Holy Ghost , whom God hath given to them that obey him .
text2: Win sI ninan we ' c knomake ' iak notI ke ' ko , ipi winke ' PanakwsIt Cipam , Win Kshe ' mIne ' to kaminat ni te ' pwe ' takwcIn .

text: When they heard that , they were cut to the heart , and took counsel to slay them .
text2: IwcI i kanotmowat ki okiptukite ' e ' shkakwnawan ipi okitshImawan taocInsawat .

text: Then stood there up one in the council , a Pharisee , named Gamaliel , a doctor of the law , had in reputation among all the people , and commanded to put the apostles forth a little space ;
text2: IwcI nkot ki nipwI shi atshI kikitowat Pe ' ne ' si nInI shInkaso ke ' me ' niIn ke ' knomake ' t i tpakwnuke ' wun , okicInme ' nukon caye ' k ni nIshInape ' n , e ' wisakcocIkasnIt ni nwakancIk kishowe ' nomuk .

text: And said unto them , Ye men of Israel , take heed to yourselves what ye intend to do as touching these men .
text2: OtIcI okinan , kinwa isne ' iIn , nInwuk ikwame ' ntumok kiiwawa , otI watotwe ' k kotI nInwuk .

text: For before these days rose up Theudas , boasting himself to be somebody ; to whom a number of men , about four hundred , joined themselves : who was slain ; and all , as many as obeyed him , were scattered , and brought to nought .
text2: E ' pwamshI notI e ' kishkiwuk kipsukwiwak Tiwtie ' s kiwinwantIso e ' kcI pite ' ntakwsIt , nie ' waktso nInwun okiwitokwawan kansIckasnIt ipi caye ' k kikate ' pwe ' twacIk kiswe ' shke ' k cocI ke ' ko , kipite ' ntakwse ' sik .

text: After this man rose up Judas of Galilee in the days of the taxing , and drew away much people after him : he also perished ; and all , even as many as obeyed him , were dispersed .
text2: IwcI minI kipsukwi Cwte ' s Ke ' ne ' ni nInI , shi e ' kishkiwuk , i maocIcke ' wun , ipi mce ' sh nIshInape ' n kipmnashkakon winke ' ke ' iapI kipnatsI , ipi caye ' k , tso kate ' pwe ' takot kiswe ' shke ' n .

text: And now I say unto you , Refrain from these men , and let them alone : for if this counsel or this work be of men , it will come to nought :
text2: OtI nkom ktInum ponikwouk kotI nInwuk ipi ponmuk kipIn otI kiktowun tanake ' mikce ' wiwInInwuk , ocupiamkuk coke ' ko ke ' nomkIscon .

text: But if it be of God , ye cannot overthrow it ; lest haply ye be found even to fight against God .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' tok kishpIn ocupiamkuk cokitapinactosinawa kcumiuk ke ' iapI ktamkakom , e ' mikane ' k Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And to him they agreed : and when they had called the apostles , and beaten them , they commanded that they should not speak in the name of Jesus , and let them go .
text2: Kite ' pwe ' twawancI , icI kantomawat ni nwakancIk , icI kapsItie ' wawat okinawan e ' wipwa kikitowat shiw tInoswunuk CisusIn icI e ' kipkItnawat .

text: And they departed from the presence of the council , rejoicing that they were counted worthy to suffer shame for his name .
text2: IwcI shi kiw nmamacik shiw e ' tshi ki kitokiwnunuk , nmumnowankoswuk i e ' pite ' ntakwse ' wat , e ' wiwcI kwtukitowat , otInoswunuk CisusIn .

text: And daily in the temple , and in every house , they ceased not to teach and preach Jesus Christ .
text2: IwcI e ' tso kishkuk shiw kcI - nume ' okumkok ipi e ' tsuk wikwaman cokipon kInomake ' sik , ipi kipon kie ' kwe ' sik , shiw tInoswunuk Cisus KnaystIn .

text: And in those days , when the number of the disciples was multiplied , there arose a murmuring of the Grecians against the Hebrews , because their widows were neglected in the daily ministration .
text2: IwcI e ' kishkiwuk , pic , ki wusimI katshuwat kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , kipsukwimkItnI mcIkikitowun ki Knishie ' nuk okinawan ni ipiniwiIn osam ni oshikamwan , e ' kipwapame ' ntakwsInIt shi e ' tso kishkuk pmitake ' wun .

text: Then the twelve called the multitude of the disciples unto them , and said , It is not reason that we should leave the word of God , and serve tables .
text2: IcIki mtatsoshItnish , okintomawan ni maoce ' tincIn ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn e ' ciuwat otI cI okinawan , Co su wi wunsmon e ' winkItmokon Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun icI . e ' wipmitmukon , topwunIn .

text: Wherefore , brethren , look ye out among you seven men of honest report , full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom , whom we may appoint over this business .
text2: OtIcI ie ' i , nikane ' ituk , we ' napmuk kin mamawI nouktso nInwuk me ' nwacIkascIk moashkne ' shkakwcuk PanakwsIncIn Cipam , ipi npwakawun , e ' wi otI , miktumwat mikce ' wiwun .

text: But we will give ourselves continually to prayer , and to the ministry of the word .
text2: NIshcI win ninan nkumikwe ' mIn niwunanIn moshuk e ' winumaiak ipi e ' wipmitmak i kikitowun .

text: And the saying pleased the whole multitude : and they chose Stephen , a man full of faith and of the Holy Ghost , and Philip , and Prochorus , and Nicanor , and Timon , and Parmenas , and Nicolas a proselyte of Antioch :
text2: IcI i kItwun okimnwe ' ntanawa ki caye ' k maoce ' ticuk ipi e ' kiwe ' napmawat StipnIn , nInI moashkne ' sanuk te ' pwe ' intumwun , ipi ni PanakwsIucIn CipamIn , ipi PInip Pnokonus ipi Nayke ' na , ipi Taymun ipi Piminus ipi NIkone ' s te ' pwe ' ie ' ntuk shi E ' ntiakuk .

text: Whom they set before the apostles : and when they had prayed , they laid their hands on them .
text2: Ni wie ' ni kaciptupawacIn anasmupnIt ni nwakaumIcIn , pic kanumawat niw nIciwan okitonawan shi wiwunuk .

text: And the word of God increased ; and the number of the disciples multiplied in Jerusalem greatly ; and a great company of the priests were obedient to the faith .
text2: IcI i Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun wusimI kimaue ' nI , ipi katshawat , kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk wusimI kitshik , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi ke ' cmaoce ' ticuk kime ' matmocuk , kite ' pwe ' tanawa i te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun .

text: And Stephen , full of faith and power , did great wonders and miracles among the people .
text2: IcI StipnIn e ' moshkIne ' shkakot i te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun ipi wishkIswun kitotum , kcI - mas kate ' ntumwunIn , ipi mataonInkie ' onIn shi e ' kiiInIt ni nIshInape ' n .

text: Then there arose certain of the synagogue , which is called the synagogue of the Libertines , and Cyrenians , and Alexandrians , and of them of Cilicia and of Asia , disputing with Stephen .
text2: Pic , cI kipsukwik anIt shi nume ' okumkok , iw kashInkate ' k otInume ' okumkomwa ki , Nipintin nInwuk , ipi sayniniuk ipi E ' ne ' kse ' nte ' niuk , ipi ki kaie ' cuk Sinishie ' iuk , ipi E ' shie ' iuk okiakwne ' twawan ni StipnIn .

text: And they were not able to resist the wisdom and the spirit by which he spake .
text2: Cocu okikshkItosinawa , e ' winkwe ' tmoawat iw ne ' pwakawun , ipi i cipam iw kaocIkikitot .

text: Then they suborned men , which said , We have heard him speak blasphemous words against Moses , and against God .
text2: OkinokanawancI , nInwun e ' wikItnIt nkinotwamIn otI , e ' pcIknonat ni MosusIn , ipi ni Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And they stirred up the people , and the elders , and the scribes , and came upon him , and caught him , and brought him to the council ,
text2: IcI e ' ki opwe ' awat , ni nIshInape ' n ipi ni onikansimwan , ipi ki we ' npie ' ke ' cuk , icI e ' kipie ' naskawawat , ipi okimshInawan icI e ' kipitkInawat shi e ' tshu , kikitokiw nInwuk .

text: And set up false witnesses , which said , This man ceaseth not to speak blasphemous words against this holy place , and the law :
text2: Ipi okipie ' nawan , waknoshkacmacIk otI kikItwuk , otI nInI co ponkikitosi e ' pcItshItuk otI panakwuk nume ' okumuk , ipi i tpakwnuke ' wun .

text: For we have heard him say , that this Jesus of Nazareth shall destroy this place , and shall change the customs which Moses delivered us .
text2: Osam nkinotwamIn e ' kItot otI Cisus Ne ' se ' ni NIn nI okupnacton otI nume ' okumuk , ipi oke ' iacton iw otIshcIke ' wun Mosus kamiukoikon .

text: And all that sat in the council , looking stedfastly on him , saw his face as it had been the face of an angel .
text2: Ipi ki caye ' k , kacipitupcuk , shi e ' tshI kikitokiwuk kan okinapmawan , okiwapmawan shiw shkishkonuk e ' shInakwsInIt ke ' cwa , mshInwe ' n .

text: Then said the high priest , Are these things so ?
text2: IwcI otI kikito kcI me ' matmot , inI notI e ' nomkuk ?

text: And he said , Men , brethren , and fathers , hearken ; The God of glory appeared unto our father Abraham , when he was in Mesopotamia , before he dwelt in Charran ,
text2: OtIcI kikito NInituk ipi nikane ' ituk ipi nostuk psItwushuk Kshe ' mIne ' to ome ' nwankoswunuk ; okiwaptaan wi ‘ ow Kosnan E ' pe ' ne ' e ' mIn e ' ie ' iIt shi Misopote ' mi e ' pwamshe ' tat shi Ke ' ne ' nuk .

text: And said unto him , Get thee out of thy country , and from thy kindred , and come into the land which I shall shew thee .
text2: OtI cI okinan ocI macin shi e ' tnukie ' n , ipi e ' tshI nowe ' tasiIn , icI shian ke ' knomonan , ksh .

text: Then came he out of the land of the Chaldaeans , and dwelt in Charran : and from thence , when his father was dead , he removed him into this land , wherein ye now dwell .
text2: IwcI shi kapie ' ocI sakuk otukimwak shi Ke ' ntie ' nuk nIshInape ' n ipi kite ' wak shi Ke ' ne ' nk ici shi kanponIt ni osIn okipie ' shonan shotI nkom e ' cI tayie ' k .

text: And he gave him none inheritance in it , no , not so much as to set his foot on : yet he promised that he would give it to him for a possession , and to his seed after him , when as yet he had no child .
text2: Co cI ke ' ko kiminasin tpInwe ' osuwun cotIna wacI pInkit nIshcI kiwawitmowan e ' wiminat tpInwe ' osuwun ipi ni nicansIn wapie ' pmatsInIt e ' pwamshI onicansut .

text: And God spake on this wise , That his seed should sojourn in a strange land ; and that they should bring them into bondage , and entreat them evil four hundred years .
text2: OtIcI Kshe ' mIne ' to okishIknonan niw nicansIn e ' witanIt Me ' ikIsnIncIn otukimwak ipi e ' wi miashtotwumIt , ipi e ' wikwtukumIt nie ' wak tsopon .

text: And the nation to whom they shall be in bondage will I judge , said God : and after that shall they come forth , and serve me in this place .
text2: KicI nIshInape ' k ke ' otokianawat nkItpakwnak Kshe ' mIne ' to okinan icI kupie ' macik ipi nkupmitakok shotI e ' ciIuwat .

text: And he gave him the covenant of circumcision : and so Abraham begat Isaac , and circumcised him the eighth day ; and Isaac begat Jacob ; and Jacob begat the twelve patriarchs .
text2: OkiminancI wawitmatwun shiw tpakwn uke ' wunuk . Ipi E ' pne ' e ' m kiwosmukon ayse ' k icI kitpakwnan ka shwatsokwnuktunuk ipi ayse ' k kiw osmukon Ce ' kap ipi Ce ' kapIn kiwosmukon mtatso shItnish Osma .

text: And the patriarchs , moved with envy , sold Joseph into Egypt : but God was with him ,
text2: NIshcI osmak e ' nshke ' nmawat kitawe ' k CosipIn shi Iciptuk nIshcI Kshe ' mIne ' to okiwice ' wan ;

text: And delivered him out of all his afflictions , and gave him favour and wisdom in the sight of Pharaoh king of Egypt ; and he made him governor over Egypt and all his house .
text2: E ' kikwtukste ' nIt cI okike ' skonan , ipi okiminan mnoshuwe ' psuwun ipi mpwa kawun e ' nasmupnIt Pe ' noiIn okuma shi iciptuk , icI e ' kiwshuat e ' wi nikane ' ntakwse ' nIt caye ' k shi iciptuk ipi caye ' k i e ' tat .

text: Now there came a dearth over all the land of Egypt and Chanaan , and great affliction : and our fathers found no sustenance .
text2: IwcI kipie ' mkIt kcI - pkIte ' wun caye ' k e ' kiwuk iciptuk ipi Ke ' ne ' nine ' k ipi kcI kwtuke ' ntumwun , ipi kosnanuk cokimkIsinawa waocI pmatsowat .

text: But when Jacob heard that there was corn in Egypt , he sent out our fathers first .
text2: NIshcI Ce ' kap kanotake ' t e ' pInIt shi ntamnIn ipI Iciptuk okinokanan ne ' tum kosnanun .

text: And at the second time Joseph was made known to his brethren ; and Joseph ' s kindred was made known unto Pharaoh .
text2: IwcI nishuk kashiawat Cosip wikane ' iIn okikuke ' nmukon ipi Pe ' no okikuke ' nman Cosip e ' nwe ' mancIn .

text: Then sent Joseph , and called his father Jacob to him , and all his kindred , threescore and fifteen souls .
text2: Cosip cI kinokashwe ' ipi okintoman ni osIn Ce ' kapIn ipi caye ' k ni e ' nwe ' macIn nouksomtIne ' shItnianIn kitshik .

text: So Jacob went down into Egypt , and died , he , and our fathers ,
text2: IwcI Ce ' kap kishie ' wak Iciptuk ipi shi kitpIne ' ’ kosnanuke ' .

text: And were carried over into Sychem , and laid in the sepulchre that Abraham bought for a sum of money of the sons of Emmor the father of Sychem .
text2: IpI cI kishocukaswuk shi Saykumuk ipi shi kinkokaswuk cipe ' okumkok E ' pne ' e ' m kakishpnItwacIn e ' kiminat shonia ni We ' kwIsmukwacIn E ' maiIn kaosmat SaykumIn .

text: But when the time of the promise drew nigh , which God had sworn to Abraham , the people grew and multiplied in Egypt ,
text2: IwcI pic ci kiukwan e ' piamkuk Kshe ' mIne ' to kawawitmowat ni E ' pne ' e ' mIn ki mnokwuk , ipi kimane ' k nIshInape ' k shi Iciptuk .

text: Till another king arose , which knew not Joseph .
text2: Nash pe ' kansIt kapsukwit kcI - okuma kapwake ' nmat ni CosipIn .

text: The same dealt subtilly with our kindred , and evil entreated our fathers , so that they cast out their young children , to the end they might not live .
text2: Win okiwie ' shan e ' nwe ' nkonuk ipi okim iashtotwan kosnanIn iwkaocI we ' pnawat otoshknicansowan e ' wipwa pmatsInIt .

text: In which time Moses was born , and was exceeding fair , and nourished up in his father ' s house three months :
text2: Iwpic Mosus kinikwakak cowunsut ipi kitshI ka ‘ owe ' pcIkaso shi osIn e ' tanIt nso kisIs .

text: And when he was cast out , Pharaoh ' s daughter took him up , and nourished him for her own son .
text2: Pic cI kasakcowe ' pnukasot , Pe ' no otansIn okiwtapnan ipi kikishkInmatso e ' wi okwIsmat .

text: And Moses was learned in all the wisdom of the Egyptians , and was mighty in words and in deeds .
text2: Mosus caye ' k okike ' ntumwan onupwa kawunInIn . Ini Iciptuk nInwun ipi kiwish kIsI shi okikitonuk , ipi otInkumkIswunuk .

text: And when he was full forty years old , it came into his heart to visit his brethren the children of Israel .
text2: PicI kwiiIn nie ' waptuk katsoponkIsIt kishIte ' ‘ e ' e ' wiwI mpwacat ; ni wikane ' iIn kaonicansumkowacIn ni Isne ' iIn .

text: And seeing one of them suffer wrong , he defended him , and avenged him that was oppressed , and smote the Egyptian :
text2: IwcI nkot e ' wapmat e ' miashtotwumIt ipi okiwickapwItwan ke ' ko e ' wipwato twumIt ni me ' iashtotwumIt icI e ' kinsat ni Iciptuk nInI .

text: For he supposed his brethren would have understood how that God by his hand would deliver them : but they understood not .
text2: Okine ' nmancI ni wikane ' iIn e ' ke ' nmanIt ni Kshe ' mIne ' ton win one ' cik e ' wi ocI pkItnukasasat cocI okike ' ntusInawa .

text: And the next day he shewed himself unto them as they strove , and would have set them at one again , saying , Sirs , ye are brethren ; why do ye wrong one to another ?
text2: WiiapnInuk cI okiwaptan wiiow ‘ me ' kwa e ' kikatwat , icI okine ' nman e ' wi mnototatnIt minI otIcI okinan PInI ktowikane ' itum We ' kwnicI we ' c miashtotatie ' k .

text: But he that did his neighbour wrong thrust him away , saying , Who made thee a ruler and a judge over us ?
text2: IwcI o kamiashtotwat ni nkot okikatokon otIcI okinan We ' nicI kaoshuuk e ' wikawapme ' iak ipi e ' witpakwne ' iak .

text: Wilt thou kill me , as thou diddest the Egyptian yesterday ?
text2: KInshInI ke ' cwa katotwIt o iciptuk nInI onako ?

text: Then fled Moses at this saying , and was a stranger in the land of Madian , where he begat two sons .
text2: Pic cI otI kanotuk Mosus kiwshumo cocI kike ' ntakwse ' si shi Mitie ' nuk e ' kiwuk shi katshI osmukot nish okwIsun .

text: And when forty years were expired , there appeared to him in the wilderness of mount Sina an angel of the Lord in a flame of fire in a bush .
text2: IwcI nie ' waptuk tsopon katpIsak Kshe ' mIne ' ton omIshIne ' we ' mIn okiwaptu ‘ ukon wiiow ‘ shi na ‘ wmtukwakik e ' pkotniak Sayne ' e ' iuk shi e ' pskone ' nuk mtukosuk .

text: When Moses saw it , he wondered at the sight : and as he drew near to behold it , the voice of the Lord came unto him ,
text2: PicI Mosus kawaptuk okimamkasaptan kawapituk icI pe ' shoc e ' pie ' naskuk e ' wiwapituk okiwtuskon Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun .

text: Saying , I am the God of thy fathers , the God of Abrham , and the God of Isaac , and the God of Jacob . Then Moses trembled , and durst not behold .
text2: OtI kikitwun Nin koswak okshe ' mIne ' tomwan ipi E ' pIne ' e ' m okshe ' mIne ' tomIn , ipi ayse ' k okshe ' mIne ' tomIn ipi Ce ' kap okshe ' mIne ' tomIn ; icI Mosus kinukshke ' ipi okikwtan e ' wiwaptuk .

text: Then said the Lord to him , Put off thy shoes from thy feet : for the place where thou standest is holy ground .
text2: IwcI Kshe ' mIne ' to otI okinan we ' pnIn ni kmuksInIn osam shi e ' ci nipwin pinakwut , ne ' kwuk kI .

text: I have seen , I have seen the affliction of my people which is in Egypt , and I have heard their groaning , and am come down to deliver them . And now come , I will send thee into Egypt .
text2: Nkiwapitan , Nkiwapitan okwutke ' ntumwwnwa ntInIshInape ' muk e ' icuk shi Iciptuk ipi nkinotmowak omumatwe ' onuwa , i we ' c pie ' ni sasiian e ' wi pkItnukwa piancI ke ' nokanIn shi Iciptuk .

text: This Moses whom they refused , saying , Who made thee a ruler and a judge ? the same did God send to be a ruler and a deliverer by the hand of the angel which appeared to him in the bush .
text2: OtI ie ' o Mosus kaiakwne ' twacIn okinawan We ' nici kaoshauk e ' wikawapme ' ie ' k , ipi e ' wi shpakwne ' iak otI ie ' o Kshe ' mIne ' to kanokanacIn e ' wikowapmat , ipi e ' wisakconawe ' nIt onIcinuk ni mIshInwe ' n kawotuskocIn shi e ' pskone ' nuk mtukosuk .

text: He brought them out , after that he had shewed wonders and signs in the land of Egypt , and in the Red sea , and in the wilderness forty years .
text2: Kakish waptaat mamkate ' ntumwunIn ipi kInwatIntumwunIn shi Iciptuk ipi shi msko kcukumik ipi no ‘ umtukwakik nie ' waptuk tsopon oki sakicawunan .

text: This is that Moses , which said unto the children of Israel , A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren , like unto me ; him shall ye hear .
text2: OtI ie ' o Mosus kanat nicansIn isne ' iIn kikane ' iwak Kshe ' mIne ' to Te ' pe ' nmukwuie ' k okuocI psukwitnamakwa Nakan acimot ke ' cwa nin WinsI kupsItwawa .

text: This is he , that was in the church in the wilderness with the angel which spake to him in the mount Sina , and with our fathers : who received the lively oracles to give unto us :
text2: OtIsI ie ' o kawitokwacIn te ' pwe ' take ' ncIn shi no ‘ wmtukwakik ke ' iapwke ' ni mshInwe ' n kaknonkocIn , shi e ' pkotnianuk Saynie ' uk ipi ke ' iapI kosnanuk kaotapnukuk , kakuk kikitowun e ' wi min koikon .

text: To whom our fathers would not obey , but thrust him from them , and in their hearts turned back again into Egypt ,
text2: Niwie ' ni kosnanuk kapwa te ' pwe ' twawacIn nkociie ' k ikishI katwawan ipi shi kishIte ' ‘ e ' k ote ' ‘ iwak e ' wi kiwe ' wat minI Iciptuk .

text: Saying unto Aaron , Make us gods to go before us : for as for this Moses , which brought us out of the land of Egypt , we wot not what is become of him .
text2: Okinawan ni E ' nunIn oshItwushnak Me ' ntokascIk e ' winmInikaniwat , Win otI Mosus kapie ' ocI sakconIimIt shi e ' kiwuk Iciptuk coukuke ' nmasimIn e ' ciIt .

text: And they made a calf in those days , and offered sacrifice unto the idol , and rejoiced in the works of their own hands .
text2: IwcI ni e ' kishkiwuk okiwshaawan pshukisun icI e ' kiciknumwawat mikwe ' wun ni me ' ntokasnIncIn kimnawankoswukcI kashI mikce ' wiwat tpInwe ' winwa onIciwan .

text: Then God turned , and gave them up to worship the host of heaven ; as it is written in the book of the prophets , O ye house of Israel , have ye offered to me slain beasts and sacrifices by the space of forty years in the wilderness ?
text2: IwcI Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' kinkInat ipi okipkIte ' nman e ' winume ' ktuwanIt ni maoce ' tincIn shpumuk e ' npie ' kate ' k shiw omusnIkInwak ki Nakanacimocuk , O kinwa wikwamuk isne ' iIn kipie ' tnumwumnI ne ' scIk we ' siuk ipi mikwe ' wunIn niawapituk tsopon shi no ‘ wmtukwa kik ?

text: Yea , ye took up the tabernacle of Moloch , and the star of your god Remphan , figures which ye made to worship them : and I will carry you away beyond Babylon .
text2: We ' we ' nI kiwtapnanawa pukwoian wikwam i Monak ipi otInukomIn kmIntomwa Nimpin me ' ntokas cuk kaoshIe ' k e ' wi nume ' kitawe ' k , ipi kumacinum wushinowuc Pe ' pe ' nunak ;

text: Our fathers had the tabernacle of witness in the wilderness , as he had appointed , speaking unto Moses , that he should make it according to the fashion that he had seen .
text2: Kosnanuk okiiI nawa i pukwoian wikwam ke ' ke ' ncukate ' nuk shi no ‘ wmtukwakik kashukumowat kiwitmoan MosusIn i e ' wishI oshItonIt kashuwapitukupIn ,

text: Which also our fathers that came after brought in with Jesus into the possession of the Gentiles , whom God drave out before the face of our fathers , unto the days of David ;
text2: Ke ' iapI ki Kosnanuk shkwe ' iak kapiacuk okipie ' nawan CisusIn shi otukimnInuk Me ' ikIscIk niwie ' ni Kshe ' mIne ' to kamace ' nashkawacIn masmukapwunIt kosnanIn nash otukishki muk Te ' pIt .

text: Who found favour before God , and desired to find a tabernacle for the God of Jacob .
text2: Winwa kamnototakwat Kshe ' mIne ' ton ipi okinuwe ' ntanawa wikwam e ' wimkumwawat Ce ' kap okshe ' mIne ' tomIn .

text: But Solomon built him an house .
text2: NIshcI Sane ' mun okiwshItwan wikwam .

text: Howbeit the most High dwelleth not in temples made with hands ; as saith the prophet ,
text2: NIshcI Mamoshpe ' ntakwsIt wikwamuk we ' shcIkate ' nuk cote ' si e ' shkItot Nakanacimot .

text: Heaven is my throne , and earth is my footstool : what house will ye build me ? saith the Lord : or what is the place of my rest ?
text2: Spumuk sI i ; Ntuptie ' pwun , ipi kI ntupsIt e ' pwun , TInicI e ' shnakwuk wikwam ke ' oshItwin ? KItwak Kshe ' mIne ' to tanake ' tInipi tatshI nwashmoian ?

text: Hath not my hand made all these things ?
text2: ConI nIce ' n nkiiosinIn notI caye ' k e ' kiwshItoian ?

text: Ye stiffnecked and uncircumcised in heart and ears , ye do always resist the Holy Ghost : as your fathers did , so do ye .
text2: Kinwa capcukwiiuwaie ' k ipi washkIte ' aie ' k ipi kito ‘ kawan kinwa pIne ' , knIshke ' nmawa o PanakwsIt Cipam koswakatotmowapItiw ke ' kinwa e ' totme ' k .

text: Which of the prophets have not your fathers persecuted ? and they have slain them which shewed before of the coming of the Just One ; of whom ye have been now the betrayers and murderers :
text2: TIninukcIki Nakanacimocuk kapwa kwtukawat kikoswak ? ipi okinsawan ni kaknoma kwacIn nikan e ' pwamshupianIt ni Nkot Ne ' pwakat kinwa kawie ' she ' k , ipi kanshuwe ' ie ' k .

text: Who have received the law by the disposition of angels , and have not kept it .
text2: MishInwe ' k kiminkowak i tpakwnuke ' wun cocu kiwtapnIsinawa .

text: When they heard these things , they were cut to the heart , and they gnashed on him with their teeth .
text2: Pic cI otI kanotmoat notI kiptIkte ' e ' shke ' k ipi okiwmtwe ' iapte ' twawan .

text: But he , being full of the Holy Ghost , looked up stedfastly into heaven , and saw the glory of God , and Jesus standing on the right hand of God ,
text2: NIshcI win e ' moshkIne ' shkakot ni PanakwsIncIn CipamIn ; shpumuk kankinapI okiwaptan Kshe ' mIne ' to ome ' nwankoswun , ipi CisusIn e ' nipwunIt shi ote ' pnIciwnak Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And said , Behold , I see the heavens opened , and the Son of man standing on the right hand of God .
text2: Ipi otI kikito PInI nowapitan shpumuk e ' nsakshkak , ipi We ' kwIsmIt NInwun e ' nipwut ote ' pnIciwnak Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: Then they cried out with a loud voice , and stopped their ears , and ran upon him with one accord ,
text2: IwcI kiwishkowe ' k , ipi oki kpakwanawan ota ‘ wkawan okimsomwunawan .

text: And cast him out of the city , and stoned him : and the witnesses laid down their clothes at a young man ' s feet , whose name was Saul .
text2: Ipi kisakciwe ' pnawan shi kcI otanuk icI e ' kisInwawat kicI kapatamacuk okikiskanawan paskumwacIn , ipi okitonawan e ' tshIste ' pnIt nkot shkInowe ' San , kishInkaso .

text: And they stoned Stephen , calling upon God , and saying , Lord Jesus , receive my spirit .
text2: IwcI e ' kisInwawat ni StipnIn okiwawinan Kshe ' mIne ' ton ipi otI kItwak , Te ' pe ' nke ' n Cisus otapIn ncipam .

text: And he kneeled down , and cried with a loud voice , Lord , lay not this sin to their charge . And when he had said this , he fell asleep .
text2: IwcI e ' kiowucikwnIkapwut , ipi kiwishkowe ' e ' kinumat Te ' pe ' ke ' nke ' n ke ' ko nkot ne ' nmakIn otI e ' shmiashtotmoat icI kakishkItot , iw kashukwoukw ‘ shuk .

text: And Saul was consenting unto his death . And at that time there was a great persecution against the church which was at Jerusalem ; and they were all scattered abroad throughout the regions of Judaea and Samaria , except the apostles .
text2: Ipi San kiwitokaso e ' nsumut . IwcI pic kikcI miashtotwak ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk kaie ' cuk shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi caye ' k kiswe ' shke ' k caye ' k e ' nkokwkwkumkiak Cwtie ' uk , ipi Se ' me ' ne ' iuk , mtInoie ' ki e ' nkacuk .

text: And devout men carried Stephen to his burial , and made great lamentation over him .
text2: IwcI ke ' cmno shuwe ' pse ' cIk nInwuk okimacinawan StipInIn e ' winkowawat , ipi okikcImao ‘ mawan .

text: As for Saul , he made havock of the church , entering into every house , and haling men and women committed them to prison .
text2: San cI , okinshonacan , ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIcIn , e ' pmupitke ' t , e ' tsunuk wikwame ' n , e ' saktItacmat nInwun ipi kwe ' n , e ' pitke ' we ' pnat , kupakwotiwkumkok .

text: Therefore they that were scattered abroad went every where preaching the word .
text2: Osam cI otI kaswe ' shkawat kishie ' k , cak nkoci e ' pmukie ' kwe ' wat .

text: Then Philip went down to the city of Samaria , and preached Christ unto them .
text2: IwcI pic Pinip , kiniscowe ' , kcI otanuk shi Se ' me ' ne ' uk , ipi okimnwactumwan KnaystIn .

text: And the people with one accord gave heed unto those things which Philip spake , hearing and seeing the miracles which he did .
text2: Ipi ki nIshInape ' k oki mamwe ' te ' pwe ' twawan ni PinipIn , kakItnIt e ' psItwawat ipi e ' wapmawat , kashumataototmInIt .

text: For unclean spirits , crying with loud voice , came out of many that were possessed with them : and many taken with palsies , and that were lame , were healed .
text2: WansIncIn mIne ' ton kakukIshkwanIt , kiwishkowe ' n e ' pie ' sakumnIt ipi mce ' sh kaie ' cuk nie ' psowun ipi kapwanIupmose ' cuk , okine ' se ' an .

text: And there was great joy in that city .
text2: KikcI pakine ' nmok , shi kcI - otanuk .

text: But there was a certain man , called Simon , which beforetime in the same city used sorcery , and bewitched the people of Samaria , giving out that himself was some great one :
text2: NIshcI nkot nInI Sayiman kishInkaso , pic i e ' pwamshI piamkItnuk , shi otanuk , okikie ' patsian ni nIshInape ' n shi Se ' me ' niuk e ' witmowat win e ' kcIpite ' ntakwsIt .

text: To whom they all gave heed , from the least to the greatest , saying , This man is the great power of God .
text2: Caype ' ksI okipsItwawan cak wIiI otI kikItwuk otIsI nInI , ote ' ion , owishkIswun Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And to him they had regard , because that of long time he had bewitched them with sorceries .
text2: WinsI okipsItwawan osam kInowe ' i okikie ' patsian , i mIne ' to si kaswunIn .

text: But when they believed Philip preaching the things concerning the kingdom of God , and the name of Jesus Christ , they were baptized , both men and women .
text2: Pic cI , te ' pwe ' twawat ni PinipIn e ' mnwactumnIt i ke ' ko otokumauwun Kshe ' mIne ' to ipi shi otInoswunuk Cisus Knayst , oki kcItapie ' nan nInwun ipi kwe ' n .

text: Then Simon himself believed also : and when he was baptized , he continued with Philip , and wondered , beholding the miracles and signs which were done .
text2: Winke ' Sayman okite ' pwe ' twan picI kakcItapie ' nIt kiiuwak shi e ' cIiInIt PinipIn ipi okimamkate ' ntum e ' waptuk ni mataototmonIn ipi kInwace ' ke ' onIn katotmInIt .

text: Now when the apostles which were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of God , they sent unto them Peter and John :
text2: Nwakancuk kikaie ' cuk Cinose ' ne ' muk , kanotake ' wat e ' psItmowat okiktowIn Kshe ' mIan ne ' to shi Same ' niuk okishInokanawan shi PituIn ipi CanIn .

text: Who , when they were come down , prayed for them , that they might receive the Holy Ghost :
text2: Winwa kapiawat okinume ' kItumwatwan e ' wi ke ' win wa minmIt PanakwsIncIn CipamIn .

text: ( For as yet he was fallen upon none of them : only they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus . )
text2: E ' pwamshIcI pkIshnotakwat , mtInoki ka kcItapie ' ntwa shiw tInoswunuk Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus .

text: Then laid they their hands on them , and they received the Holy Ghost .
text2: IwcI wiuwawak okitaknIcamawan iwcI winwa kashuotuskowat ni PanokwsIncIn CipamIn .

text: And when Simon saw that through laying on of the apostles ' hands the Holy Ghost was given , he offered them money ,
text2: Pic cI Sayme ' n kawapmat ni nwakancIn te ' pnak e ' taknuwe ' nIt i e ' otIskowat panakwsIncIn Cipam okiwawitmowan shonia .

text: Saying , Give me also this power , that on whomsoever I lay hands , he may receive the Holy Ghost .
text2: OtIcI okinan mishuke ' nin otI kshkI - e ' osuwun , ninke ' we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' taknuk , win kaotIskon PanakwsIt Cipam .

text: But Peter said unto him , Thy money perish with thee , because thou hast thought that the gift of God may be purchased with money .
text2: NIshcI Pitu okinan , Nocma i kshoniaium kukInshonatIs , osam kine ' ntum Kshe ' mIne ' to omikwe ' wun kuocI kshkItom shonia .

text: Thou hast neither part nor lot in this matter : for thy heart is not right in the sight of God .
text2: Cosukin , ktpe ' ntusin , otI mikce ' wiwun osam i kte ' ’ comnosInon e ' waptuk Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: Repent therefore of this thy wickedness , and pray God , if perhaps the thought of thine heart may be forgiven thee .
text2: Kisate ' ntum otI kmIiashuwe ' psiwun , ipi nume ' kito ’ w Kshe ' mIne ' to kIne ' pIc e ' shte ' an shi kte ' ’ ik kitapone ' ntumako .

text: For I perceive that thou art in the gall of bitterness , and in the bond of iniquity .
text2: Nowapitan kine ' in shi wisup ke ' iwiskuk ipi shi tkopcukunuk miashwe ' psiwunuk .

text: Then answered Simon , and said , Pray ye to the Lord for me , that none of these things which ye have spoken come upon me .
text2: IwcI Sayiman e ' kinkwe ' twat ipi otI okinan , Kin ne ' me ' kito ’ w moshIn ; Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' wipwa ke ' ko nomkuk notI ke ' ko kashu wawitmoiIn .

text: And they , when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord , returned to Jerusalem , and preached the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans .
text2: IwcI winwa kakish mnowactumwawat okikitowun Kshe ' mIne ' to kikiwe ' k Cinose ' nInuk icI okimnwactanawa i mnowacimowIn shi otane ' sun ki Se ' me ' ne ' nInwuk .

text: And the angel of the Lord spake unto Philip , saying , Arise , and go toward the south unto the way that goeth down from Jerusalem unto Gaza , which is desert .
text2: IcI Kshe ' mIne ' to mIshIne ' we ' mIn , okiknonan PinipIn otI okinan , Psukwin ipi shian we ' c shawunu ‘ uk iw mie ' w ’ we ' tsuk Cinose ' ne ' muk ipi Ke ' se ' uk now ’ mtukwakik .

text: And he arose and went : and , behold , a man of Ethiopia , an eunuch of great authority under Candace queen of the Ethiopians , who had the charge of all her treasure , and had come to Jerusalem for to worship ,
text2: IwcI e ' kipsukwit ipi e ' kimacit icI pInI , Itiopi nInI nkot iwnuk , ke ' cpite ' ntakwsIt katpe ' nmukot Ke ' nte ' se ' n otokumakwe ' mwan , Itiopi nIuwuk , win kakuwaptumwacIn caye ' k otIpInoe ' wsiwnInIn , ipi kishiakpIn Cinose ' ne ' muk e ' kiwunumat .

text: Was returning , and sitting in his chariot read Esaias the prophet .
text2: E ' pie ' kiwe ' t kipie ' ciptupI , shiw ototapianuk , owuptanomusnukIn Ise ' usIn Nakanacimot .

text: Then the Spirit said unto Philip , Go near , and join thyself to this chariot .
text2: IwcI cipam okinan ni pinipIn , Shian pe ' shoc ipi wice ' o oaI otapian .

text: And Philip ran thither to him , and heard him read the prophet Esaias , and said , Understandest thou what thou readest ?
text2: IcI Pinip e ' kipItot ipI , ipi okipsItwan e ' waptumnIt i musInukIn , Ise ' us Nakanacimot otI cI okinan , kinIstotanI otI waptumIn ?

text: And he said , How can I , except some man should guide me ? And he desired Philip that he would come up and sit with him .
text2: OtI cI okinan , TInicI ke ' shI kuke ' ntuman , kishpIn wIiI nInI , pwake ' noomowat , icI e ' kintomat ni PinipIn , e ' wipie ' kwutasinIt , ipi e ' wiwitpumkot .

text: The place of the scripture which he read was this , He was led as a sheep to the slaughter ; and like a lamb dumb before his shearer , so opened he not his mouth :
text2: ShiwcI kacuwaptuk i msInukIn otI ie ' i kiskapie ' na ke ' cwa mantane ' sh , watshInsIc kasat , ipi ke ' cwa mantanshe ' s , co okInonasin mowashkocIn iwsI kashupwapakitone ' not .

text: In his humiliation his judgment was taken away : and who shall declare his generation ? for his life is taken from the earth .
text2: E ' ie ' tpIse ' nmIt cokipkIte ' ntumwasi mnototatwun , We ' nicI ke ' wawitmakot iw iaianke ' pmatsowun osam iw opmatsowun kiw cIotapnukate ' nI shotI kik .

text: And the eunuch answered Philip , and said , I pray thee , of whom speaketh the prophet this ? of himself , or of some other man ?
text2: IwcI o iwnuk kinkwe ' twan , ipi okinan , ni ni PinipIn , WitmoshIn We ' nicI , e ' nacIn o Nakanacimot ? WinI tpInwe ' tanake ' pe ' kansIt nInI ?

text: Then Philip opened his mouth , and began at the same scripture , and preached unto him Jesus .
text2: IwcI Pinip e ' kinsakwunuk i oton , ipi okiwe ' pkukinomowan i musInukIn ipi ikimnwactumwan ni CisusIn .

text: And as they went on their way , they came unto a certain water : and the eunuch said , See , here is water ; what doth hinder me to be baptized ?
text2: IwcI e ' ie ' nme ' ie ' wat shi mie ' wuk , okiwtItanawa mpish , icI o iw ’ nuk kikIto WapitIn otIsI mpish , We ' kwnicI ke ' pwaocI kIcitapie ' nkasian .

text: And Philip said , If thou believest with all thine heart , thou mayest . And he answered and said , I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God .
text2: Pinip cI otI okinan , Caye ' ksI kte ' ik , kishpIn te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumIn iwsI ke ' nomkuk , icI e ' kinkwe ' twat ipi otI kikIto . Nin te ' pwe ' ie ' ntum Cisus Knayst , otokwIsmukon Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And he commanded the chariot to stand still : and they went down both into the water , both Philip and the eunuch ; and he baptized him .
text2: IwcI tokum ikinipwaat ni otapianIn , icI e ' kiniscowe ' wat ne ' ne ' ish e ' kipkopie ' wat shi mpik , Pinip ipi Iwnuk icI e ' kikcItapie ' nat .

text: And when they were come up out of the water , the Spirit of the Lord caught away Philip , that the eunuch saw him no more : and he went on his way rejoicing .
text2: IwcI kakish pie ' kwashnowat shi mpik , Kshe ' mIne ' to CipamIn , okiwtapnan ni PinipIn , icI o iwnuk cominI okiwapmasin , icI e ' kinmumacit kinmI mInowankosI .

text: But Philip was found at Azotus : and passing through he preached in all the cities , till he came to Caesarea .
text2: Pinip cI kimkukaso , shi E ' sotusuk icI e ' nmIshapshkuk , kinImI kie ' kwe ' caye ' k shi kcI otanuk , nashkapiat shi sisne ' iuk .

text: And Saul , yet breathing out threatenings and slaughter against the disciples of the Lord , went unto the high priest ,
text2: IwcI San me ' kwa moshuk mcIkikito e ' nshke ' nmat ni ke ' knomowacIn Te ' pe ' nke ' t kishie ' wak ni kcI me ' matmonIt .

text: And desired of him letters to Damascus to the synagogues , that if he found any of this way , whether they were men or women , he might bring them bound unto Jerusalem .
text2: IwcI e ' kintotmowat musInukInIn , shi nume ' okumkok , ipi Te ' me ' skusuk , kishpIn wIiI mkuwat i e ' shwe ' psIncIn , tanak nInwun tanake ' kwe ' n , e ' wipie ' nat ipi e ' witkopnat shi Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: And as he journeyed , he came near Damascus : and suddenly there shined round about him a light from heaven :
text2: E ' nmupiskat kipie ' wak ci kiiIkwan , Te ' me ' skIsuk kukaw ’ wiiwuk kiwtayiukwan kiwawasnote ' nI wase ' anuk , kiwcIpie ' mkItnI shpumuk

text: And he fell to the earth , and heard a voice saying unto him , Saul , Saul , why persecutest thou me ?
text2: IwcI kipmukocIn kik ipi kinotan kiki towun , otI kikItomkIt San , San , We ' kwnicI we ' c kwtuk , in ?

text: And he said , Who art thou , Lord ? And the Lord said , I am Jesus whom thou persecutest : it is hard for thee to kick against the pricks .
text2: OtI cI okinan We ' nicI kin , Te ' pe ' nke ' n ? Te ' pe ' nke ' t cI otI okinan . Nin sI Cisus , kin me ' iashtotwin kcIsnukIt sn kin e ' witkIshkwutwa kakawshiiuk .

text: And he trembling and astonished said , Lord , what wilt thou have me to do ? And the Lord said unto him , Arise , and go into the city , and it shall be told thee what thou must do .
text2: IwcI e ' ie ' nukshkat ipi e ' ‘ ie ' nmamkate ' ntuk , otI kikito , Te ' pe ' nke ' n , We ' kwnicI e ' ne ' nmin e ' wishowe ' pse ' an ? Te ' pe ' nke ' t cI otI okinan , Psukwin ipi shian kcI otanuk , shiw cI kuwitmako watotmIn .

text: And the men which journeyed with him stood speechless , hearing a voice , but seeing no man .
text2: Kiw cI nInwuk kap mI wice ' wacuk kinipwik co kinI kikitosik e ' notmowat i kikitowun wIiIcI kInwun e ' pwawapmawat .

text: And Saul arose from the earth ; and when his eyes were opened , he saw no man : but they led him by the hand , and brought him into Damascus .
text2: San cI shi kiwcI psukwi shi kik , icI kantuwapIt co wIiI nInwun , okiwapmasin , okipmIskInke ' nawan icI e ' kishonawat shi Te ' me ' skusuk

text: And he was three days without sight , and neither did eat nor drink .
text2: Nsokishuk cI co kine ' ntuwapsi , coke ' , kiwisnIsi , ipi co kimnukwe ' si .

text: And there was a certain disciple at Damascus , named Ananias ; and to him said the Lord in a vision , Ananias . And he said , Behold , I am here , Lord .
text2: . Si Te ' me ' skusuk nkot kiuwak ke ' knomowut E ' ne ' naye ' s , kishInkaso , Kshe ' mIne ' to otI okinan , kinaptum E ' ne ' nayus , otIcI kikito , PInI Te ' pe ' nke ' n shotI ntIi ’ I .

text: And the Lord said unto him , Arise , and go into the street which is called Straight , and inquire in the house of Judas for one called Saul , of Tarsus : for , behold , he prayeth ,
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to cI otI , okinan , Psukwin ipi shian , shi otanmie ' wuk TapasI e ' shnukate ' k , ipi natake ' n shiw Cwte ' s e ' tat nkot e ' shmnukasot San , Tasus nInI , PInI win nume ' wak !

text: And hath seen in a vision a man named Ananias coming in , and putting his hand on him , that he might receive his sight .
text2: Win kinaptum e ' wapmat , nkot nInI E ' ne ' naye ' s . , e ' shnukasot , e ' pie ' pitike ' nIt , ipi okituwan onIce ' n shi wiIuwuk e ' wintawapnIt .

text: Then Ananias answered , Lord , I have heard by many of this man , how much evil he hath done to thy saints at Jerusalem :
text2: IwcI E ' ne ' naye ' s okinan , Te ' pe ' nke ' n nkinotwak mce ' sh , otI nInI mce ' sh me ' iante ' nuk , e ' kiwat tapwe ' ie ' ntukuk shi Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: And here he hath authority from the chief priests to bind all that call on thy name .
text2: Ipi shotI kshke ' osuwun minkon ni kcIme ' matmoncIn , e ' wi tkopnat caye ' t ke ' wawitkuk ktInoswunuk .

text: But the Lord said unto him , Go thy way : for he is a chosen vessel unto me , to bear my name before the Gentiles , and kings , and the children of Israel :
text2: NIshcI Te ' pe ' nke ' t otI okinan , Mumacin , Win kawe ' uapmuk , e ' wi pe ' naotot , ntInoswIn e ' nasmupnIt ni Me ' ikIscIk ipi kcI okumak ipi Isne ' iIn nicansIn .

text: For I will shew him how great things he must suffer for my name ' s sake .
text2: Nkawapta ’ a , tso ke ' ko ke ' ocI wiske ' ntuk i ntInoswun .

text: And Ananias went his way , and entered into the house ; and putting his hands on him said , Brother Saul , the Lord , even Jesus , that appeared unto thee in the way as thou camest , hath sent me , that thou mightest receive thy sight , and be filled with the Holy Ghost .
text2: IwcI E ' ne ' naye ' s kin mumacit kinmupitike ' shi wikwamuk icI e ' kitot , one ' ce ' n shi wiiwInuk otIcI okinan , Nikane ' San Te ' pe ' nke ' t ie ' i ipite ' ntakwsIt Cisus , kawaptu ’ kon wia ’ w e ' pic pie ' shian shotI , nokanuk , e ' wiocI ntawapian , ipi e ' wi moshkIne ' shkakwiIn PanakwsIt Cipam .

text: And immediately there fell from his eyes as it had been scales : and he received sight forthwith , and arose , and was baptized .
text2: Kie ' nup kipmukote ' ne ' shiw shkishkok ke ' cwa onu ’ ke ' iuk icI e ' ki ntawapit kie ' nup , ipi kipsukwi icI e ' kikcItapie ' nIt .

text: And when he had received meat , he was strengthened . Then was Saul certain days with the disciples which were at Damascus .
text2: IwcI kawisnIt , kiwishkukine ' icI San , okiwitokwan , ke ' knomoncIn onatsokwIn , shi kaie ' ncIn Te ' me ' skusuk .

text: And straightway he preached Christ in the synagogues , that he is the Son of God .
text2: Ipi kie ' nup okimInwaciman KnaystIn shiw nume ' okumkok win e ' okwIsmukot Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: But all that heard him were amazed , and said ; Is not this he that destroyed them which called on this name in Jerusalem , and came hither for that intent , that he might bring them bound unto the chief priests ?
text2: KicI caye ' k kanotwacuk kimamkate ' ntumwuk , ipi otI kikItwuk , ConI wi otI kanshonacat ni kawawitmInIt otI Noswun , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi shotI we ' c piat e ' witkopnat ipi e ' wisha ’ otuwat ni kcI me ' matmoncIn ?

text: But Saul increased the more in strength , and confounded the Jews which dwelt at Damascus , proving that this is very Christ .
text2: NIshcI San wusimI kiwishkIsI ipi , kimamkate ' nmukon ni CiwiIn shiw Te ' me ' skusuk kaie ' ncIn kie ' tnam kikIto owiie ' o Knayst .

text: And after that many days were fulfilled , the Jews took counsel to kill him :
text2: IwcI kakish mce ' ish tsokwnuktInuk katpIsanuk ki Ciwiuk okitshumawan e ' winsawat .

text: But their laying await was known of Saul . And they watched the gates day and night to kill him .
text2: IwcI e ' kuwapmukot , okikInman o San Ipi okikuwaptanawa ni shkwatame ' n e ' kishkiwuk , ipi e ' pkoniak , e ' winsawat .

text: Then the disciples took him by night , and let him down by the wall in a basket .
text2: IwcIci te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk okimacinawan e ' ie ' pkonianuk ipi kokpInaknuk okisawan icI osakiiukwan e ' ki pkIsapie ' nawat .

text: And when Saul was come to Jerusalem , he assayed to join himself to the disciples : but they were all afraid of him , and believed not that he was a disciple .
text2: IwcI San kapiat , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , okiwikwcIton , e ' wiwitokwat ni te ' pwaie ' ntumnIt nIshkI caye ' k okikwsawan ipi co kite ' pwe ' twasiwan winke ' e ' te ' pwie ' ntuk .

text: But Barnabas took him , and brought him to the apostles , and declared unto them how he had seen the Lord in the way , and that he had spoken to him , and how he had preached boldly at Damascus in the name of Jesus .
text2: NIshcI Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , kimacinan , ipi okisha ’ onan iciiInIt ni nwakancIk , ipi kiwitmowan kashu wapmat ni Kshe ' mIne ' ton kanmupiskat ; ipi e ' kiknonat ipi kashu kie ' kwe ' nIt shi Te ' me ' skusuk otInoswunuk CisusIn .

text: And he was with them coming in and going out at Jerusalem .
text2: Ipi shiw okiwican e ' pitke ' wat , ipi e ' sakumwat , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: And he spake boldly in the name of the Lord Jesus , and disputed against the Grecians : but they went about to slay him .
text2: KiwishkItakwsI e ' kie ' kwe ' t shiw tInoswunuk Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus , okiwikwce ' an ni Knik nInwun nIshcI okikwce ' nsukon .

text: Which when the brethren knew , they brought him down to Caesarea , and sent him forth to Tarsus .
text2: IwcI ni wikane ' iIn kake ' ntumnIt okipie ' nawan shi SisInie ' uk , ipi okinokanawan ipI Tasusuk .

text: Then had the churches rest throughout all Judaea and Galilee and Samaria , and were edified ; and walking in the fear of the Lord , and in the comfort of the Holy Ghost , were multiplied .
text2: Pic cI ki maoce ' ticuk te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , kinwashmok , caye ' k Cwtie ' uk ipi Ke ' nIniuk , ipi Se ' me ' ne ' iuk , ipi kiknomowak , ipi pmose ' k shi okwutacwunuk , Te ' pe ' nke ' t , ipi shi omInwankoswunuk PanakwsIt ocipam wusimI cI kitshik .

text: And it came to pass , as Peter passed throughout all quarters , he came down also to the saints which dwelt at Lydda .
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk , Pitu kapmIshiat cak onukumuk , okipie ' naskawan , ke ' ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk katacuk shi NItie ' uk .

text: And there he found a certain man named Aeneas , which had kept his bed eight years , and was sick of the palsy .
text2: Shi okimkawan nkot nInwun Inie ' s kishInke ' so , nouktso pon kishkIshIn onupaknuk kiakwnoke ' i nie ' psowun .

text: And Peter said unto him , Aeneas , Jesus Christ maketh thee whole : arise , and make thy bed . And he arose immediately .
text2: Pitu cI okinan Inie ' s Cisus Knayst , ktosh ‘ uk e ' wine ' se ' n , Psukwin mnoston knupakIn , icI e ' kipsukwit kie ' nup .

text: And all that dwelt at Lydda and Saron saw him , and turned to the Lord .
text2: KicI caye ' k katacuk shi NItie ' uk , ipi Se ' nunuk kiwapmawan icI e ' kikwe ' knoitwawat Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: Now there was at Joppa a certain disciple named Tabitha , which by interpretation is called Dorcas : this woman was full of good works and almsdeeds which she did .
text2: Cape ' uk cI kite ' wak nkot te ' pwe ' ie ' ntuk kishInkaso Te ' payte ' i e ' anke ' notmuk , Takus , e ' ktok otI kwe ' kimoshkne ' se ' nI we ' onItnuk mikce ' wiwun ipi katotuk mnototake ' onIn .

text: And it came to pass in those days , that she was sick , and died : whom when they had washed , they laid her in an upper chamber .
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk shiw e ' kishkiwuk kiakwnoke ' icI e ' kinpot kakishksipie ' nawat okishkIshmawan , shpumuk wikwamuk .

text: And forasmuch as Lydda was nigh to Joppa , and the disciples had heard that Peter was there , they sent unto him two men , desiring him that he would not delay to come to them .
text2: Osam cI NItie ' ki pe ' shocaiIn shi Capiuk icI ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk kanotake ' wat ni PituIn shi e ' iInIt okinokanawan nish nInwun e ' ntomawat kie ' nup shi e ' wipie ' shianIt .

text: Then Peter arose and went with them . When he was come , they brought him into the upper chamber : and all the widows stood by him weeping , and shewing the coats and garments which Dorcas made , while she was with them .
text2: IwcI Pitu e ' kipsukit e ' kiwice ' wat pic cI kapiawat okisho ‘ nawan shi shpumuk wikwamuk ipi caye ' k , ki shakaocIk okiwickapwutakon e ' mwuwat , ipi e ' wapitu ‘ kot ni piskumwaknIn , ipi kwawo ‘ nIn Takus kaoshItot me ' kwa e ' ie ' pmatsIt .

text: But Peter put them all forth , and kneeled down , and prayed ; and turning him to the body said , Tabitha , arise . And she opened her eyes : and when she saw Peter , she sat up .
text2: NIshcI Pitu caye ' k okisaktInan icI e ' ki owucikwnukapowIt , ipi kinume ' ‘ ipi okikwe ' knoi shi wiwunuk , otI kikIto , Te ' payte ' , Psukwin , icI e ' kipaknuk , niw oshkishkwe ' n , icI kawapmat ni PituIn , kicipitupI .

text: And he gave her his hand , and lifted her up , and when he had called the saints and widows , presented her alive .
text2: IwcI e ' ki minat niw nIce ' n icI e ' ki psukwitnat pic cI kantomat ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn ipi shakaocIk kiminan e ' pmatsInIt .

text: And it was known throughout all Joppa ; and many believed in the Lord .
text2: Caye ' k cI shi kikuke ' ncukate ' shi Cape ' uk mce ' sh cI kite ' pwe ' twawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And it came to pass , that he tarried many days in Joppa with one Simon a tanner .
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk , okiwican me ' kwe ' tsokwun , shi Cape ' uk , nkot Sayimun we ' she ' knIke ' t . .

text: There was a certain man in Caesarea called Cornelius , a centurion of the band called the Italian band ,
text2: Nkot nInI kiuwak Sisine ' uk , Kuninius kishInkaso , Kapte ' nmowan ki shuma knIshuk , e ' shnukascuk Ayte ' niun nkotwe ' nI .

text: A devout man , and one that feared God with all his house , which gave much alms to the people , and prayed to God alway .
text2: Ke ' cnumat nInI , ipi nkot , kakwsat Kshe ' mIne ' to , ipi caye ' k , e ' tsoke ' t , kaminat mce ' sh , mikwe ' onIn ni nIshInape ' n ; ipi pIne ' , e ' nume ' ktawat Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: He saw in a vision evidently about the ninth hour of the day an angel of God coming in to him , and saying unto him , Cornelius .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to , omIshIne ' we ' mIn owaptuan , kinap tum , we ' we ' ne ' , shaktso tpukIn , shi e ' kishkiwuk , e ' pie ' naskakot , ipi otI otukon , Kuninius .

text: And when he looked on him , he was afraid , and said , What is it , Lord ? And he said unto him , Thy prayers and thine alms are come up for a memorial before God .
text2: IcI kantowapIt , kikwtacI , ipI otI kikIto , We ' konicI Te ' pe ' nke ' n ? OtIcI okikon , ni ktInume ' onIn , ipi kimikwe ' onIn shpumuk , pie ' mkIt e ' winaktIwe ' nmukwiIn e ' nasmupIt Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And now send men to Joppa , and call for one Simon , whose surname is Peter :
text2: Nkom nokash nInwuk e ' wishiawat Capie ' uk ipi ntom nkot Sayimun ke ' iapI e ' shnukasot Pitu ;

text: He lodgeth with one Simon a tanner , whose house is by the sea side : he shall tell thee what thou oughtest to do .
text2: Witke ' man nkot Sayimun we ' she ' knIke ' t ci kcukimik , e ' tat e ' te ' nuk , win kawitmak , wanukmuksin .

text: And when the angel which spake unto Cornelius was departed , he called two of his household servants , and a devout soldier of them that waited on him continually ;
text2: IcI o mshInwe ' , kakinonat KuninusIn , kan mamacit , nish okintoman , nish opmitakaimIn , ipi te ' pwe ' ie ' ntuk shumakunIsh , ni pIne ' kapmitakwcIn .

text: And when he had declared all these things unto them , he sent them to Joppa .
text2: IwcI pic caye ' k kakish witmoat , okinokanan ipI Cape ' uk .

text: On the morrow , as they went on their journey , and drew nigh unto the city , Peter went up upon the housetop to pray about the sixth hour :
text2: IwcI , wiapuk pe ' shoc e ' nmIiuwat shi kcI otanuk , nkotwatso tpukIn e ' pite ' ntakwute ' nuk Pitu , kishie ' kwItpuk e ' winumat .

text: And he became very hungry , and would have eaten : but while they made ready , he fell into a trance ,
text2: KikcI pkIte ' , ipi takiwisnI , me ' kwace ' e ' iI oshIstowat , kiapwe ' .

text: And saw heaven opened , and a certain vessel descending unto him , as it had been a great sheet knit at the four corners , and let down to the earth :
text2: IcI e ' kiwapituk kishIk , e ' nsakshkanuk , ipi nkot tnacke ' wun , e ' piamkItnuk e ' ciIt ke ' cwa , kcI wapoian e ' tkopte ' nuk shi nie ' wuk , e ' shkwe ' ie ' knuwuk , e ' pie ' nisnukate ' nuk shotI kik .

text: Wherein were all manner of fourfooted beasts of the earth , and wild beasts , and creeping things , and fowls of the air .
text2: Shi cI pic iukwan , caye ' k e ' shnakwsawat nie ' okata cuk , we ' siuk , shotI kik , ipi pkocwe ' siuk , ipi pe ' pa mote ' shkuk , ipi pe ' pamsacuk .

text: And there came a voice to him , Rise , Peter ; kill , and eat .
text2: IcI notakwsuwun okiwtuskon Psukwin Pitu ; nta ‘ we ' n , ipi wisnIn .

text: But Peter said , Not so , Lord ; for I have never eaten any thing that is common or unclean .
text2: Pitu , cI otI kikito , Coin Te ' pe ' nke ' n Cowi wika ke ' ko nkimitsin , ke ' ko me ' anuk tanake ' wanakwuk .

text: And the voice spake unto him again the second time , What God hath cleansed , that call not thou common .
text2: OnotwancI minI owIiI e ' kikitonIt , iwni nishuk , Iw Kshe ' mIne ' to , kapinakwtot , ke ' ko winakwut , kItkIn .

text: This was done thrice : and the vessel was received up again into heaven .
text2: Nsuk otI kitotam , tnacke ' wuncI ne ' iap , minI kiwtapnukate ' shiw shpumuk .

text: Now while Peter doubted in himself what this vision which he had seen should mean , behold , the men which were sent from Cornelius had made inquiry for Simon ' s house , and stood before the gate ,
text2: Me ' kwacI Pitu e ' ie ' kwinwune ' ntuk i wio ‘ w we ' kwe ' ntuk otI napitumwun , i kanaptuk , ke ' nomkuk , pInI ki nInwuk Kuninius , kanokanacIn kinatake ' k Sayimun e ' tat ipi kinipwik shkwate ' muk .

text: And called , and asked whether Simon , which was surnamed Peter , were lodged there .
text2: Ipi kinatake ' k tanak shi Sayimun e ' shwawinIt Pitu shi e ' wiiInIt .

text: While Peter thought on the vision , the Spirit said unto him , Behold , three men seek thee .
text2: Me ' kwacI Pitu e ' ie ' nakituwe ' ntuk Cipam , otI okikon , pInI nswI nInwuk knItwapmukok .

text: Arise therefore , and get thee down , and go with them , doubting nothing : for I have sent them .
text2: Psukwin ipi nisasin , icI kowice ' wak , ke ' kokwinwune ' ntukIn , nin kwshI ntInkanak .

text: Then Peter went down to the men which were sent unto him from Cornelius ; and said , Behold , I am he whom ye seek : what is the cause wherefore ye are come ?
text2: IcI Pitu e ' kishiat ni nInwun , Kuninius kanokanacIn otI cI okinan , pInI , NinkwshI ne ' twapmIie ' k , We ' kwnicI otI we ' cpiaie ' k .

text: And they said , Cornelius the centurion , a just man , and one that feareth God , and of good report among all the nation of the Jews , was warned from God by an holy angel to send for thee into his house , and to hear words of thee .
text2: OtI cI kikItwuk , Kuninius nkot kapte ' n ne ' pwakat nInI , ipi , kwe ' sat , Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi me ' notshumkot caye ' k ni CwiIn , Kshe ' mIne ' to , okinokanan panakwsIncIn omIshInwe ' n okikan e ' wintomkon , e ' wishian e ' tat e ' wipsItuk kikitounIn .

text: Then called he them in , and lodged them . And on the morrow Peter went away with them , and certain brethren from Joppa accompanied him .
text2: IwcI e ' kintomat e ' wipitke ' nIt shinI kiik icI wiapnInuk , Pitu okinmawice ' wan , ipi anIt wikane ' iIn , kiwcIpie ' k , Cape ' uk okinmI wice ' o kon .

text: And the morrow after they entered into Caesarea . And Cornelius waited for them , and had called together his kinsmen and near friends .
text2: IwcI owiapnInuk , kanmIiuwat shi SIsinie ' uk , Kuninus okipwian , kakish maosomat ni e ' nwe ' macIn , ipi te ' panacIn wikanIn .

text: And as Peter was coming in , Cornelius met him , and fell down at his feet , and worshipped him .
text2: IcI Pitu e ' ie ' pi e ' pitke ' t , Kuninus okinkwe ' shkwan ipi kipmukocIn mcIiukwan asItinuk , ipi okinume ' ktuwan .

text: But Peter took him up , saying , Stand up ; I myself also am a man .
text2: NIshce ' Pitu okipsukwitnan , otI cI okinan , Nipwun , ninkwshIke ' , nInI , ke ' iapI .

text: And as he talked with him , he went in , and found many that were come together .
text2: IwcI e ' pic kInonat , kinmupitke ' , icI okimkawan shi mce ' sh , e ' maoce ' tinIt .

text: And he said unto them , Ye know how that it is an unlawful thing for a man that is a Jew to keep company , or come unto one of another nation ; but God hath shewed me that I should not call any man common or unclean .
text2: OtIcI okinan kuke ' ntanawasI , cowunsInon nInI e ' Cwiwut , e ' wiwitokwat tanake ' e ' wipie ' shiat ni pkan , e ' shumnIncIn , nIshcI Kshe ' mIne ' to nkiwapitu ’ uk e ' wipwa , wIiI nInI shInkanuk me ' anuk , tanake ' wanakwuk .

text: Therefore came I unto you without gainsaying , as soon as I was sent for : I ask therefore for what intent ye have sent for me ?
text2: IwcI ie ' i , we ' cpie ' naskonan , co ke ' ko ukikItsi pic kantomiIn knatoncI nkom , We ' kwnicIwe ' c ntomiIn ?

text: And Cornelius said , Four days ago I was fasting until this hour ; and at the ninth hour I prayed in my house , and , behold , a man stood before me in bright clothing ,
text2: IwcI Kuninus otI kikIto , shiI nie ' okonkIt , coin nkiwisnIsi nash otI tpukIn , icI shaktso tpukIn e ' pite ' ntakwuk , nkinuma shi e ' taian , ipi pInI , nInI , e ' nasmupian kinipwI kiwaste ' ne ' , paskukIn .

text: And said , Cornelius , thy prayer is heard , and thine alms are had in remembrance in the sight of God .
text2: OtI cI kikIto Kuninius kitInume ' owun kinotam ipi kmikwe ' onIn omikwe ' ncIkate ' , e ' nasmupIt Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: Send therefore to Joppa , and call hither Simon , whose surname is Peter ; he is lodged in the house of one Simon a tanner by the sea side : who , when he cometh , shall speak unto thee .
text2: Nokashwe ' n ipI Cape ' uk , ipi ntom , Sayimun e ' shnukasat Pitu shiw iuwak owikwamuk nkot Saymun we ' she ' knIke ' t , cikcukumik , win kipiat kawitmak .

text: Immediately therefore I sent to thee ; and thou hast well done that thou art come . Now therefore are we all here present before God , to hear all things that are commanded thee of God .
text2: Kie ' nup , nkinokashwe ' e ' wi ntomkon , kimnototum cI e ' pian , nkom shotI caye ' k nte ' imIn , e ' nasmupIt Kshe ' mIne ' to , e ' wipsItumak , cake ' ko kashu wamitmakwiIn Kshe ' mIne ' to .
