text: Then Peter opened his mouth , and said , Of a truth I perceive that God is no respecter of persons :
text2: IwcI Pitu kapaktone ' not , ipi otI kikIto , We ' we ' ne ' nkuke ' nma Kshe ' mIne ' to , co wIiI wusimI , otupite ' nmasi .

text: But in every nation he that feareth him , and worketh righteousness , is accepted with him .
text2: E ' tsoshumowat win kwe ' sat , ipi mnototuk , nie ' ni we ' tapnacIn .

text: The word which God sent unto the children of Israel , preaching peace by Jesus Christ : ( he is Lord of all : )
text2: Kikitowun , Kshe ' mIne ' to kanitaat , ni Isniun nicansun , omInwacimowun , o Cisus Knayst ; Win mamwI Te ' pe ' nke ' t .

text: That word , I say , ye know , which was published throughout all Judaea , and began from Galilee , after the baptism which John preached ;
text2: I kikitowun kuke ' ntanawa kawawickate ' k , cak iukwanuk Cwtie ' uk , ipi kiw cupie ' mkIt Ke ' ne ' niuk , iw Can kakie ' kwe ' t , kakishcI tapie ' n we ' t .

text: How God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Ghost and with power : who went about doing good , and healing all that were oppressed of the devil ; for God was with him .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to kashu siknumwat ni CisusIn Ne ' se ' ni nInI , ni PanakwsIncIn , OcipamIn ipi i kshke ' osuwun , winkipashie ' we ' onItnuk , e ' kipmInukmuksIt , ipi e ' kine ' se ' at caye ' k ni kaktukukwacIn ni mcImIne ' ton ; osam Kshe ' mIne ' to kipmawice ' wan .

text: And we are witnesses of all things which he did both in the land of the Jews , and in Jerusalem ; whom they slew and hanged on a tree :
text2: Ninan nkuke ' ntamIn , caye ' k notI ke ' ko katotuk , shotI otukiwak Ciwiuk , ipi shi Cinose ' ne ' muk ni wie ' ni kansawacIn ipi kakonawat , mtukok .

text: Him God raised up the third day , and shewed him openly ;
text2: Win Kshe ' mIne ' to kansokwnuktunuk kapsukwitnat , ipi kiwaptu ‘ we ' wiwunuk ;

text: Not to all the people , but unto witnesses chosen before of God , even to us , who did eat and drink with him after he rose from the dead .
text2: Coin nish caye ' k nIshInape ' n , mtIno ki ke ' ke ' nmacIk kauwe ' napmacIn , Kshe ' mIne ' to ninan , kawitopmukIt , ipi kawicmnukwe ' mkIt kakish psukwit e ' kinpopIt .

text: And he commanded us to preach unto the people , and to testify that it is he which was ordained of God to be the Judge of quick and dead .
text2: Ninanki nkikatonkonan , e ' wikie ' kmukIt , ipi e ' wiwitmokIt ki nIshInape ' k , win e ' ki we ' napmukot Kshe ' mIne ' ton e ' witpakwnat , ni pe ' matsIncIn , ipi ne ' poncIn .

text: To him give all the prophets witness , that through his name whosoever believeth in him shall receive remission of sins .
text2: Win kaminat caye ' k iacimoncIn , e ' wi iacimonIt , shiw tInoswunuk we ' kwe ' ntuk ke ' twe ' pwe ' ie ' ntuk kupone ' ntumwa ni muiashuwe ' psiwnIn .

text: While Peter yet spake these words , the Holy Ghost fell on all them which heard the word .
text2: Me ' kwacI Pitu e ' ie ' kakikitot , PanakwsIt Ocipam okipkIshnotakwan caye ' k , ki kapsItkuk i kikitowun .

text: And they of the circumcision which believed were astonished , as many as came with Peter , because that on the Gentiles also was poured out the gift of the Holy Ghost .
text2: KiwcI winwakaka ‘ otashmocuk kate ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk kimamkate ' ntumwuk , tso kapie ' wice ' wacuk , ni PituIn osam kie ' winwa ki Me ' ikIscIk , ke ' iapI , kisiknumwak i mikwe ' wun PanakwsInIt Cipam .

text: For they heard them speak with tongues , and magnify God . Then answered Peter ,
text2: Osam kinotwawan , e ' miukshumnIt ipi e ' winwanawat Kshe ' mIne ' ton , PitucI otI kikito .

text: Can any man forbid water , that these should not be baptized , which have received the Holy Ghost as well as we ?
text2: WIiInI nInI takIto compish , ke ' iosImIn kote ' e ' wi kcItapie ' ntwa , kamincuk ni PanakwsInIt Cipam ke ' cwa ninan .

text: And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of the Lord . Then prayed they him to tarry certain days .
text2: OkukatonancI e ' wi kcItapie ' nkasnIt shiw tInoswunuk Kshe ' mIne ' to ; okiwishte ' pmawancI e ' wi iInIt o nat sokwun .

text: And the apostles and brethren that were in Judaea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word of God .
text2: IwcI ki nwakancuk , ipi wikane ' iIn kaicuk shi Cwtie ' uk kanotake ' wat , ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn winwake ' e ' kipsItmowat Kshe ' mIne ' to kikitowun .

text: And when Peter was come up to Jerusalem , they that were of the circumcision contended with him ,
text2: IwcI Pitu kapiat shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , kiw cI kate ' pwe ' tkuk , ( CiwiIn winwa ka kaotashmocuk ) otupakwnuke ' owunwa okinshkuknonawan -

text: Saying , Thou wentest in to men uncircumcised , and didst eat with them .
text2: OtI cI okinawan ; kipitikawak , ki nInwuk ( me ' ikIscIk ) pwa kaotashcuk ipi kiwitopmak .

text: But Peter rehearsed the matter from the beginning , and expounded it by order unto them , saying ,
text2: Pitu cI we ' we ' ni okiwitmowan e ' wshkuwe ' p nomkItnuk , ipi oki iactumwan , otI okinan .

text: I was in the city of Joppa praying : and in a trance I saw a vision , A certain vessel descend , as it had been a great sheet , let down from heaven by four corners ; and it came even to me :
text2: Shi nkiiI kcIotanuk Cape ' uk , nkinuma icI nkiapwa nkiwapitancI , kanaptman nkot tnacke ' wun kipie ' nisashke ' mkIt ke ' cwa kcI wapoian kiwcI nisnukate ' shi shpumuk nie ' wuk , e ' wikwe ' ie ' knIwuk icI nkipie ' naskakon .

text: Upon the which when I had fastened mine eyes , I considered , and saw fourfooted beasts of the earth , and wild beasts , and creeping things , and fowls of the air .
text2: IcI kawaptuman nkinaktowe ' ntan , ipi nkiwapmak ne ' ie ' ostacuk we ' siuk , ipi pkoc we ' siuk shotI kik , ipi pe ' pamote ' shkuk ipi pe ' pamsacuk .

text: And I heard a voice saying unto me , Arise , Peter ; slay and eat .
text2: Ipi nkinotan notakwsuwun otI ktomkIt Psukwin Pitu , nta ‘ we ' n , ipi wisnIn .

text: But I said , Not so , Lord : for nothing common or unclean hath at any time entered into my mouth .
text2: NIshcI otI nkikIt , Coin Te ' pe ' nke ' n ; coin ke ' ko me ' anuk tanake ' , wanakwuk wika ntIshkumosi .

text: But the voice answered me again from heaven , What God hath cleansed , that call not thou common .
text2: NIshcI minI notakwsuwun , nkiwcI , nkwe ' takon shiw shpumuk iw Kshe ' mIne ' to kapinakwtot ke ' ko wanakwuk shInkatkIn .

text: And this was done three times : and all were drawn up again into heaven .
text2: IwcI otI nsuk kinomkIt icI caye ' k , minI ki opashke ' mkIt ipI shpumuk .

text: And , behold , immediately there were three men already come unto the house where I was , sent from Caesarea unto me .
text2: IwcI pInI kie ' nup shi kiik nswI nInwuk , kishashikiik , wIkwamuk , kaciiian e ' kipie ' icI ntomwat , shi Sisine ' uk .

text: And the spirit bade me go with them , nothing doubting . Moreover these six brethren accompanied me , and we entered into the man ' s house :
text2: IwcI o Cipam , nkiwitmak e ' wiwice ' okwa e ' wipwa ianwe ' ntuman ; wusimI kI nkotwatso nikane ' uk , nkiwice ' okok , icI e ' kinmupitike ' iak o nInI e ' tat .

text: And he shewed us how he had seen an angel in his house , which stood and said unto him , Send men to Joppa , and call for Simon , whose surname is Peter ;
text2: Ipi nkiwitmaknan kashuwapmat mshInwe ' n shi e ' tat e ' nipwunIt , ipi otI kikItwun nokashI nInwuk , ipI Cape ' uk , ipi ntom Sayimun , e ' shnuk asot ke ' Pitu ;

text: Who shall tell thee words , whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved .
text2: Win kuwitmak kikitonIn ke ' ocI , ke ' skonkoie ' k kin , ipi caye ' k ktowikwamuk , e ' icuk ;

text: And as I began to speak , the Holy Ghost fell on them , as on us at the beginning .
text2: Pic cI e ' we ' pkInonkwa PanakwsIt Cipam okipkIshnotakwan ke ' cwa kinan , e ' wshkI shuwe ' pse ' ikon .

text: Then remembered I the word of the Lord , how that he said , John indeed baptized with water ; but ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost .
text2: IwcI pic kimikwe ' ntan okikitowun , Kshe ' mIne ' to iw e ' kikItpIt Can we ' we ' ni kikcItapie ' nwe ' shi mpishuk , nIshcI kinwa kukcItapie ' nkasom shi PanakwsIt Cipam .

text: Forasmuch then as God gave them the like gift as he did unto us , who believed on the Lord Jesus Christ ; what was I , that I could withstand God ?
text2: Osam win Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' kiminat i kashu minkoikon , kinan , kate ' pwe ' twukon , Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus Knayst , we ' kwnicI nin , takshkItoian , e ' wiwtumu ‘ k Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: When they heard these things , they held their peace , and glorified God , saying , Then hath God also to the Gentiles granted repentance unto life .
text2: IcI otI kanotmoat , coke ' kokikItsik , ipi o kiwinwanawan , Kshe ' mIne ' ton , otI kikItwuk , Kshe ' mIne ' to nukwuke ' ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn , okiminan kisate ' ntumwun shi pmatsowunuk .

text: Now they which were scattered abroad upon the persecution that arose about Stephen travelled as far as Phenice , and Cyprus , and Antioch , preaching the word to none but unto the Jews only .
text2: Kiw cI kaswe ' shkacuk , onukmuk , osam e ' kimiashtotwut StipIn , kipmI shishie ' k shi Pinusuk , ipi Saypusuk ipi E ' ntiakuk , e ' pmumnwactumwat i kikitowun ; cowi wIiI mtIno ni CwiIn .

text: And some of them were men of Cyprus and Cyrene , which , when they were come to Antioch , spake unto the Grecians , preaching the Lord Jesus .
text2: IwcI anIt Saypusuk nInwuk , ipi Saynin nInwuk , kapiawat shi E ' ntiakuk okikinonawan Kniksh nInwuk , Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus kukie ' kwe ' wun .

text: And the hand of the Lord was with them : and a great number believed , and turned unto the Lord .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to cI okshke ' osuwun , okiwice ' okonawa , mce ' shcI okite ' pwe ' twawan , ipi okikwe ' knIwitwawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: Then tidings of these things came unto the ears of the church which was in Jerusalem : and they sent forth Barnabas , that he should go as far as Antioch .
text2: KicI te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk kanotmoat notI ke ' ko , okinokanawan Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , e ' wishianIt , shi E ' ntiakuk .

text: Who , when he came , and had seen the grace of God , was glad , and exhorted them all , that with purpose of heart they would cleave unto the Lord .
text2: Win kapiat , ipi kawaptuk , oshuwe ' ncuke ' wun Kshe ' mIne ' to , kinciwe ' nmo , ipi okiakwaman caye ' k , e ' wiwishkIte ' anIt ipi , e ' wiwickapwutwawot ni Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: For he was a good man , and full of the Holy Ghost and of faith : and much people was added unto the Lord .
text2: Osam kimnoshuwe ' pse ' nInI , ipi okimoshkIne ' shkakon ni PanakwsIn Cipam , ipi te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun , mce ' sh cI nIshInape ' k kitkwaknoik Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: Then departed Barnabas to Tarsus , for to seek Saul :
text2: IcI kinmamaci Pe ' ne ' pe ' s e ' shiat Tasusuk , e ' wuntuwapmat Sanun ;

text: And when he had found him , he brought him unto Antioch . And it came to pass , that a whole year they assembled themselves with the church , and taught much people . And the disciples were called Christians first in Antioch .
text2: IwcI kamkawat okipie ' nan shi , E ' ntiakuk otI kanomkuk , nkot pon , kimaoce ' tik ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , ipi okiknomowawan mce ' sh nIshInape ' n , ipi ki ke ' knomocuk , Knayst nIshInape ' k kishInkasok , ne ' tum shi E ' ntiakuk .

text: And in these days came prophets from Jerusalem unto Antioch .
text2: IwcI notI e ' kishkiwuk Nakan acimocuk kiw cupie ' k , Cinose ' ne ' muk , kipie ' shie ' k E ' ntiakuk .

text: And there stood up one of them named Agabus , and signified by the spirit that there should be great dearth throughout all the world : which came to pass in the days of Claudius Caesar .
text2: Nkot cI ki nipwI E ' kipus , kishInkaso , kiwitmake ' shi cipamuk , e ' wikcI , pkIte ' kiwnunuk , caye ' k , shotI kik , iw kashuwe ' puk , otukishkimuk Knatius Sise ' .

text: Then the disciples , every man according to his ability , determined to send relief unto the brethren which dwelt in Judaea :
text2: Pic cI ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , e ' tshowat washukshkItIt kine ' ntumwuk , e ' wi nishokomowawat ni wikane ' iwan , katanIt Cwtie ' uk .

text: Which also they did , and sent it to the elders by the hands of Barnabas and Saul .
text2: Iw katotmowat , ipi okinitaawan ni nakane ' ntakwsIncIn , Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , ipi San , onIcinuk .

text: Now about that time Herod the king stretched forth his hands to vex certain of the church .
text2: Pic cI otI , E ' nat kcI okuma , kishipnuke ' no e ' wi miashtotwat anIt te ' pwe ' ie ' ntIncIn .

text: And he killed James the brother of John with the sword .
text2: Ce ' msIncI okinsan wikane ' iIn Can okion i kishkowun .

text: And because he saw it pleased the Jews , he proceeded further to take Peter also . ( Then were the days of unleavened bread . )
text2: OsamcI e ' wapmat ni CwiIn i e ' mnwe ' ntumnIt kishIte ' ’ e ' ’ , ke ' ni e ' wiwtapnat ni PituIn pic cI ni e ' kishkiwuk , pwaopce ' te ' k pkwe ' shkIn .

text: And when he had apprehended him , he put him in prison , and delivered him to four quaternions of soldiers to keep him ; intending after Easter to bring him forth to the people .
text2: IwcI kaotapnat okikpakwoan , okikuwaptumoan ni mtotsoshItInkotwatso , shumaknIshIn , e ' wikawapmanIt , kine ' ntumwak kikishkwe ' pmose ' mkuk wikwtowun , e ' wi sakcowunat , e ' nasmupnIt ni nIshInape ' n .

text: Peter therefore was kept in prison : but prayer was made without ceasing of the church unto God for him .
text2: IwcI Pitu kaocI kpakot , kiwcI te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , pIne ' , okinume ' ktuwawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton win , i kaocI shuwe ' psInIt .

text: And when Herod would have brought him forth , the same night Peter was sleeping between two soldiers , bound with two chains : and the keepers before the door kept the prison .
text2: IwcI i e ' pkonianuk , E ' nut , wasakconapIt Pitu kinpe ' wak , na ’ iukwan nish shumaknIshIn , nish cI piwapikwe ' n tkopso ipi ki e ' kwapcIk cikshkwate ' m oki kowaptanawa i kpakwotiwkumuk .

text: And , behold , the angel of the Lord came upon him , and a light shined in the prison : and he smote Peter on the side , and raised him up , saying , Arise up quickly . And his chains fell off from his hands .
text2: PInI , Kshe ' mIne ' to omIshInwe ' mIn , kipie ' n e ' ciiIt ipi kiwasnote ' ne ' shi kpakwotiwkumkok , ipi okipkuman ni PituiIn wiwunuk , ipi okipsukwitnan , ipi otI okinan Psukwin , icI ni piwapkwe ' n kipmukote ' ne ' , katkopsot shiw onIcik .

text: And the angel said unto him , Gird thyself , and bind on thy sandals . And so he did . And he saith unto him , Cast thy garment about thee , and follow me .
text2: IwcI omIshwe ' n otI okinan , kicipnItson ipi tkopton kmuksInIn , iwcI katotuk ; ipi otI okinan , piskIn kpiskumwakIn , ipi pmnashkoshIn .

text: And he went out , and followed him ; and wist not that it was true which was done by the angel ; but thought he saw a vision .
text2: IwcI e ' kisakuk , ipi kipmnashkawan , cokike ' ntusin e ' te ' pwe ' wunuk katotmInIt , ni mIshInwe ' n , nIsh niapwa kishIte ' ’ e ' ’ ;

text: When they were past the first and the second ward , they came unto the iron gate that leadeth unto the city ; which opened to them of his own accord : and they went out , and passed on through one street ; and forthwith the angel departed from him .
text2: IwcI kakwe ' pmosanawat , ni ne ' tum , e ' kwapnIt ipi ni ianke ' kowapnIt ; kipie ' kshi piwapko shkwate ' muk e ' suk , shi kcI otanuk , nIshcI nshukI kinsakwshke ' ne ' icI e ' kinmIsakumwat , icI kakwe ' pmosatmowat , nkot otan mie ' o , ipi kie ' nupcI omshInwe ' okinkInan .

text: And when Peter was come to himself , he said , Now I know of a surety , that the Lord hath sent his angel , and hath delivered me out of the hand of Herod , and from all the expectation of the people of the Jews .
text2: Pic cI Pitu kake ' ntuk , otI kikIto , Nkom nkuke ' ntan , we ' we ' nI Kshe ' mIne ' to omIshIne ' we ' mIn e ' kinokanat , ipi nia ’ w okiktusknIce ' pnan ni E ' nutIn , ipi ki caye ' k Cwiuk , kane ' nmawat .

text: And when he had considered the thing , he came to the house of Mary the mother of John , whose surname was Mark ; where many were gathered together praying .
text2: IwcI kakishnaktawe ' ntuk iw kipie ' wak e ' tanIt Me ' niIn , okie ' iIn Can , e ' shnukasotke ' Mak , shi mce ' I kimaoce ' tik e ' numawat .

text: And as Peter knocked at the door of the gate , a damsel came to hearken , named Rhoda .
text2: Me ' kwacI Pitu e ' ie ' papakakwuk , shi shkwate ' muk , kikiak , kipie ' psIcto , kishInkaso Note ' .

text: And when she knew Peter ' s voice , she opened not the gate for gladness , but ran in , and told how Peter stood before the gate .
text2: IwcI kansItowat ni PituiIn , cokin nsakwnIsin i shkwate ' m , , e ' pic nciwe ' nmot , kipitke ' pto ipi kiwitmake ' PituiIn , sakci ukwan e ' nipwunIt shkwate ' muk .

text: And they said unto her , Thou art mad . But she constantly affirmed that it was even so . Then said they , It is his angel .
text2: OtI cI okinawan , kawawunum ; kiwish te ' pwe ' cI , i e ' nomkItnuk . OtI cI kikItwuk omIshInwe ' mIn sIni .

text: But Peter continued knocking : and when they had opened the door , and saw him , they were astonished .
text2: NIshcI Pitu pIne ' , Kipapakakwu ’ uke ' , icI kakishnsakwnumwat i shkwate ' m , ipi kawapmawat kimamkate ' ntumwuk .

text: But he , beckoning unto them with the hand to hold their peace , declared unto them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison . And he said , Go shew these things unto James , and to the brethren . And he departed , and went into another place .
text2: Oki iaine ' nkawan e ' wipwa ke ' ko kItnIt okiwitmowan kashu sakcowunukot ni Kshe ' mIne ' ton shi kpakwotiwkumkok ipi otI okinan wuwitmo otI , Ce ' ms ipi ki kikane ' nanuk . IwcI e ' kinmamacit pkan koci kishie ' .

text: Now as soon as it was day , there was no small stir among the soldiers , what was become of Peter .
text2: IwcI kawapnInuk , kinatatwuk kishumaknIshuk e ' ciiInIt PutuiIn .

text: And when Herod had sought for him , and found him not , he examined the keepers , and commanded that they should be put to death . And he went down from Judaea to Caesarea , and there abode .
text2: Pic cI E ' nut , kantowapmat ipi kakwintawapmat okitpakwnan ni e ' kwapnIncIn ipi kishowe ' e ' wi nsIckasnIt . KiwcI nmamaci shi Cwtie ' uk , e ' kishiat isinie ' uk ; icI shi e ' kiIt .

text: And Herod was highly displeased with them of Tyre and Sidon : but they came with one accord to him , and , having made Blastus the king ' s chamberlain their friend , desired peace ; because their country was nourished by the king ' s country .
text2: E ' nut okikcInshke ' nman , ni kaiInIt ipI Tayniuk ipi Saytunuk , nIshcI kipie ' msou ’ tik e ' ciiInIt icI kawikanmawat Pne ' stiIn kcI okuma , opumitakaimIn , okintotanawa , noe ' twun osam iw otukimwa , kiw tInke ' k shi kcI okuma otukimuk .

text: And upon a set day Herod , arrayed in royal apparel , sat upon his throne , and made an oration unto them .
text2: E ' nut cI e ' kikito kishkItnuk , okipiskanIn kcI okuma otikwame ' iIn , ipi shi kicipitupI ocipitupwunuk , icI kika kikito .

text: And the people gave a shout , saying , It is the voice of a god , and not of a man .
text2: IwcI ki nIshInape ' k kinotakwsik , otI kikItwuk , Kshe ' mIne ' to otI okikitowun , cowi nInI .

text: And immediately the angel of the Lord smote him , because he gave not God the glory : and he was eaten of worms , and gave up the ghost .
text2: Ipi kie ' nup cI , Kshe ' mIne ' to omIshInowe ' mIn , okiwe ' potwan osam co , okiminasin Kshe ' mIne ' to winwacke ' wun ; mIne ' tose ' iIn cI okimokon , icI e ' kipkItnat ocipamIn .

text: But the word of God grew and multiplied .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to cI kikitowun , kikishkInI , ipi kimane ' nI .

text: And Barnabas and Saul returned from Jerusalem , when they had fulfilled their ministry , and took with them John , whose surname was Mark .
text2: IwcI Pane ' pas , spi San , kiwcI kiwe ' k shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , kakish knomake ' wat , okinmumacinawan , CanIn ; kashInkasotke ' , Mak .

text: Now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain prophets and teachers ; as Barnabas , and Simeon that was called Niger , and Lucius of Cyrene , and Manaen , which had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch , and Saul .
text2: Te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk cIshi , anIt kiik , E ' ntiakuk nakanacimocuk , ipi ke ' knomake ' cuk Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , ipi Simiun kashInkasotke ' Nayku , ipi Nwsius , Saynin , nInI , ipi Me ' ne ' in kapie ' wic , kishkIcIn ni E ' nutIn , okumas , ipi San .

text: As they ministered to the Lord , and fasted , the Holy Ghost said , Separate me Barnabas and Saul for the work whereunto I have called them .
text2: E ' ie ' cI pmitwawat , ni Te ' pe ' nke ' ncIn ipi e ' pwawisnawat , PanakwsIt Cipam otI okikowan , papke ' ptoshuk , Pe ' ne ' pe ' s ipi San , i mikice ' wiwum kaocI ntomkwa .

text: And when they had fasted and prayed , and laid their hands on them , they sent them away .
text2: IwcI pic kapwa wisnawat , ipi kakishnumawat , ipi katawawat niw nIciwan shi wiwunuk , okinokanawan .

text: So they , being sent forth by the Holy Ghost , departed unto Seleucia ; and from thence they sailed to Cyprus .
text2: PanakwsIt Cipam , okinokankowan kishie ' k , shi Sinwshiuk icI shi kiwcI macik kinashwuk shi Saypnusuk .

text: And when they were at Salamis , they preached the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews : and they had also John to their minister .
text2: Ipi shi kaiIwat Sine ' musuk , okimnwactanawa okikitowun Kshe ' mIne ' to , otInume ' o kumkomwak ki Cwiuk . CanIn kie ' ni , ke ' iapI okinishokmakwan .

text: And when they had gone through the isle unto Paphos , they found a certain sorcerer , a false prophet , a Jew , whose name was Bar - jesus :
text2: IwcI kanmIt kumshkumwat i mnIshI kishie ' k Pe ' posuk okimkawawan nkot me ' ntokasnIt , iacimokasot , Cwi nInI , pacisus kishInkaso .

text: Which was with the deputy of the country , Sergius Paulus , a prudent man ; who called for Barnabas and Saul , and desired to hear the word of God .
text2: Win okiwitokwan , okinasIn , shi e ' tnukie ' wat Sinicius , Panus , ne ' pwakat nInI , okintoman Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , ipi SanIn , e ' ntowe ' ntuk e ' wipsItuk i okikitowun Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: But Elymas the sorcerer ( for so is his name by interpretation ) withstood them , seeking to turn away the deputy from the faith .
text2: NIshcI Inimus , mIntosikasot , ( i ie ' i e ' shnukasot e ' ianke ' notmuk ) okiwikwce ' an , e ' wi te ' pwe ' takot ni okumasIn , i te ' pwe ' tatwun .

text: Then Saul , ( who also is called Paul , ) filled with the Holy Ghost , set his eyes on him ,
text2: IwcI San , ke ' iapukI e ' shnukasot Pan , e ' moshkIne ' shkakot , PanakwsIncIn , Cipam , kancI okinapman ;

text: And said , O full of all subtilty and all mischief , thou child of the devil , thou enemy of all righteousness , wilt thou not cease to pervert the right ways of the Lord ?
text2: IcI otI okinan , O ! moashkIne ' shkakwiIn caye ' k , wie ' shtowun ipi caye ' k , me ' anuk , we ' nicansumkon mIcImIne ' to , me ' iane ' ntumIn caye ' k me ' noshuwe ' psowun , ConI kuponiksim Kshe ' mIne ' to omInoshuwe ' psiwun ?

text: And now , behold , the hand of the Lord is upon thee , and thou shalt be blind , not seeing the sun for a season . And immediately there fell on him a mist and a darkness ; and he went about seeking some to lead him by the hand .
text2: Ipi nkom pInI ; one ' ce ' n Kshe ' mIne ' to oshIton shi kiiwuk , ipi ku ’ kie ' pikwa , co kuwapmasi kisIs nomuk . IiI kie ' nup kipuksInI shiw shkishkok wunsiwu ’ n , ipi kiskupkoniawapwun , icI e ' ki pantawapmat owIiI wapmIskIncInkot .

text: Then the deputy , when he saw what was done , believed , being astonished at the doctrine of the Lord .
text2: IwcI okumas pic kawapituk kashotwumIt kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntum osam , okimamkate ' ntum , okuknomake ' wun Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: Now when Paul and his company loosed from Paphos , they came to Perga in Pamphylia : and John departing from them returned to Jerusalem .
text2: Pic cI Pan , ipi ni kapmIwice ' wacIn kawe ' pshkawat shi Pe ' posuk , kipie ' shie ' k PInke ' uk , shi Pe ' mpinie ' uk , icI Can , shi kacInkInat kikiwe ' Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: But when they departed from Perga , they came to Antioch in Pisidia , and went into the synagogue on the sabbath day , and sat down .
text2: PInke ' uk , cI kaocI maciwat , kishie ' k E ' ntiakuk shi Psitie ' uk , ipi kipitike ' k shi nume ' okumkok , icI e ' kicipitupwat ; e ' nume ' kishkItnuk .

text: And after the reading of the law and the prophets the rulers of the synagogue sent unto them , saying , Ye men and brethren , if ye have any word of exhortation for the people , say on .
text2: IcI i tpakwnuke ' wun , ipi nakanacimocuk , kakish wapcIkate ' k , shi msInukInuk , e ' kwaptukuk i nume ' okumuk okintomawan , ipi otI okinawan , NInituk , ipi nikane ' ituk , KishpIn ke ' ko kikitowun , wikie ' kme ' k , kotI nIshInape ' k , ktakikitom .

text: Then Paul stood up , and beckoning with his hand said , Men of Israel , and ye that fear God , give audience .
text2: IcI pan , e ' kipsukwit , ipi okiiaine ' nkowan , otI okinan , NInwuk shi IsniIn , ipi kinwa , kwe ' se ' k Kshe ' mIne ' to ; psItmok .

text: The God of this people of Israel chose our fathers , and exalted the people when they dwelt as strangers in the land of Egypt , and with an high arm brought he them out of it .
text2: O Kshe ' mIne ' tomwan kotI nIshInape ' k , shi IsniIn , okiwe ' napman kosnanIn , ipi okipsukwitnan ni nIshInape ' n , winwa cokike ' ntakwsusik , e ' kitawat shi e ' kiwuk Iciptuk , ipi wishkInkaonuk shiw o kipie ' ocusakcowunan .

text: And about the time of forty years suffered he their manners in the wilderness .
text2: Pic cI nie ' wapituk tsopon ; okipkIte ' ntumwan iw tIshwe ' psiwnawan shi na ’ wmtukwakik .

text: And when he had destroyed seven nations in the land of Chanaan , he divided their land to them by lot .
text2: IwcI kakish pnacat , nouktso e ' shnmnIn e ' kiwuk shi Ke ' ne ' e ' n , okimatan iw tukimnInIn e ' ki tatiwat .

text: And after that he gave unto them judges about the space of four hundred and fifty years , until Samuel the prophet .
text2: IcI kakish , icI showe ' psIt okiminan tpakwnuke ' onInwun nie ' wak , ipi niano mtInI tso pon nash Se ' mnwIn nakanacimot .

text: And afterward they desired a king : and God gave unto them Saul the son of Cis , a man of the tribe of Benjamin , by the space of forty years .
text2: IcI i kakish , showe ' psIt , okintuwe ' nmawan okuman , ocI Kshe ' mIne ' to okiminan SanIn we ' kwIsmukot , E ' Ish Pe ' nce ' mIn kashIcmot nInI nie ' wapituk tsopon ;

text: And when he had removed him , he raised up unto them David to be their king ; to whom also he gave testimony , and said , I have found David the son of Jesse , a man after mine own heart , which shall fulfil all my will .
text2: IcI ni kaotapnat minI nkot okipsukwitnumwan , Te ' pItIn e ' wi otokumamwat , win Kshe ' mIne ' to kaiacimat otI kikIto , Nkimkowa Te ' pIt we ' kwIsmukot Ce ' siIn , nInI tpInwe ' nin nte ' ’ we ' te ' it win , ke ' kshkItot , kaye ' k , ntIne ' ntumwun .

text: Of this man ' s seed hath God according to his promise raised unto Israel a Saviour , Jesus :
text2: OtI nInI onicansIn , Kshe ' mIne ' to win kashowawitmake ' t e ' wipsukwitnumwat ni Isni In ke ' skonwe ' ncIn CisusIn .

text: When John had first preached before his coming the baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel .
text2: Pic Can , kawe ' pkie ' kwe ' t e ' pwamshI pianIt ; kcItapie ' nwe ' wun i kisate ' ntumwun ; kicaye ' k nIshInape ' k ; Isne ' iIn .

text: And as John fulfilled his course , he said , Whom think ye that I am ? I am not he . But , behold , there cometh one after me , whose shoes of his feet I am not worthy to loose .
text2: IcI me ' kwa Can , e ' ie ' , kie ' kwe ' t , otI okinan we ' nicI nin e ' ne ' nmie ' k ? coin win nte ' isi , nIshcI , pInI , nkot pe ' kanksIt shkwe ' iak , pie ' tne ' sI win omuksInIn , shiw osItik cointupite ' ntakwsIsi , e ' wiapskoptuwuk .

text: Men and brethren , children of the stock of Abraham , and whosoever among you feareth God , to you is the word of this salvation sent .
text2: NInituk , ipi nikane ' ituk we ' nican sunkoie ' k , E ' pe ' ne ' e ' m , ipi we ' kwe ' ntuk kwe ' sakwe ' n , Kshe ' mIne ' ton , kinwasI i kikitowIn otI ke ' skonwe ' wun knitakom .

text: For they that dwell at Jerusalem , and their rulers , because they knew him not , nor yet the voices of the prophets which are read every sabbath day , they have fulfilled them in condemning him .
text2: Kikatacuk shi Cinose ' ne ' muk ; ipi onikansimwan , osam cokike ' nmasiwan , coke ' okinsItowasiwan ni NakanacimoncIn e ' tso nume ' kishkuk , kaiactmuk okite ' pwe ' tonawa i e ' ki pkIte ' nmawak .

text: And though they found no cause of death in him , yet desired they Pilate that he should be slain .
text2: Pic cI kapwamkumwat , ke ' ko e ' wiwcIne ' nIt , ke ' iapI okintuwe ' nmawan Payne ' tIn e ' winsIc kasnIt .

text: And when they had fulfilled all that was written of him , they took him down from the tree , and laid him in a sepulchre .
text2: Pic cI kacaktpIse ' stowat , caye ' k i e ' shonupie ' kasot shi msInuknuk okiwcI nisnawan , shi mtukok icI e ' kishkIshmawst shi cipe ' ’ okumkok .

text: But God raised him from the dead :
text2: NIshcI Kshe ' mIne ' to minI okipsukwitnan e ' nponpIt .

text: And he was seen many days of them which came up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem , who are his witnesses unto the people .
text2: Mce ' sh kon kiwapmukon kapie ' ocI wice ' kocIn shi Ke ' nIniuk , kipie ' shie ' k Cinose ' ne ' muk , winwaki ke ' iacimukot ni nIshInape ' n .

text: And we declare unto you glad tidings , how that the promise which was made unto the fathers ,
text2: KuwitmonmIn mciwe ' nmowun i witmatwun , kashIwawitmotwa kikosnanuk .

text: God hath fulfilled the same unto us their children , in that he hath raised up Jesus again ; as it is also written in the second psalm , Thou art my Son , this day have I begotten thee .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to sI win nasap , okitpIstaknan kinan we ' nicansumkoikom iw e ' ki psukwit nat , minI ni CisusIn , iwke ' shI e ' npie ' kate ' k , shi nish Nkumwunuk Kin we ' kwIsme ' nan , otI e ' kishkiwuk , kiw , osum .

text: And as concerning that he raised him up from the dead , now no more to return to corruption , he said on this wise , I will give you the sure mercies of David .
text2: Ipi i e ' kipsukwitnat i e ' nponpIt , cowi minI e ' wipkIshkIne ' not , otI kikIto kuminIn we ' we ' ne ' oshuwe ' ncuke ' wun Te ' pIt .

text: Wherefore he saith also in another psalm , Thou shalt not suffer thine Holy One to see corruption .
text2: I ie ' i otI osam , minI we ' ckito mkuk pe ' kanuk nkumwIn , co minI kne ' nmasi pan nakwsIt Nkot e ' wiwaptuk pkIshknInwun .

text: For David , after he had served his own generation by the will of God , fell on sleep , and was laid unto his fathers , and saw corruption :
text2: Te ' pIt cI kakish pmitwat niw wicpmatsiIn kane ' nmukot Kshe ' mIne ' to , kinpe ' , ki wic nkokaso niosIn , ipi kinpIsh kinpIshknIno .

text: But he , whom God raised again , saw no corruption .
text2: Wincie ' ko , Kshe ' mIne ' to kapisukwitnat minI co okiwaptusin mpIshknInwun .

text: Be it known unto you therefore , men and brethren , that through this man is preached unto you the forgiveness of sins :
text2: I ie ' i ke ' ocI kuke ' ntusme ' k nInituk , ipi nikane ' itnk , Win otI nInI we ' c kie ' kmukoie ' k , i e ' wi we ' pnukate ' k miashuwe ' psiwnIn

text: And by him all that believe are justified from all things , from which ye could not be justified by the law of Moses .
text2: Ipi win caye ' k ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , pkIte ' ntumwak cake ' ko ; iw tpakwnuke ' wun Mosus tapwa pkIte ' ntumake ' t .

text: Beware therefore , lest that come upon you , which is spoken of in the prophets ;
text2: Naktuwe ' ntmok , osam otI ktanI otIskonawa kashu kikitowat ki Nakanacimocuk .

text: Behold , ye despisers , and wonder , and perish : for I work a work in your days , a work which ye shall in no wise believe , though a man declare it unto you .
text2: PInI , shake ' nke ' ie ' k , ipi mamkate ' nkie ' k , ipi knIshnatsum ; osam nin nmikce ' wi mikice ' wiwun , shi ktuki , shkimwak mikce ' wiwun , co kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntusinawa ; nInI ianwI witmakwie ' k .

text: And when the Jews were gone out of the synagogue , the Gentiles besought that these words might be preached to them the next sabbath .
text2: KicI Cwiuk , kanmI sakumwat , shi nume ' okumkok , ki me ' mataose ' cIk , okiwishte ' pmawan e ' wi kie ' kmukwat ni kikitonIn , minI nume ' kishkItnuk .

text: Now when the congregation was broken up , many of the Jews and religious proselytes followed Paul and Barnabas : who , speaking to them , persuaded them to continue in the grace of God .
text2: IcI ki pic maoce ' ticIk , kanmumaciwat Cwiuk , kimane ' k ipi e ' nmaa cuk , kakwe ' knoicuk , okipmInashkawawan PanIn , ipi Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , e ' knonkowat , oki ikwamukwan , e ' wi ikwamtonIt Kshe ' mIne ' to oshuwe ' ncke ' wun .

text: And the next sabbath day came almost the whole city together to hear the word of God .
text2: IcI minI e ' nume ' kishkuk kaka , caye ' k e ' icIk shi kcI otanuk ; kimaoce ' tik e ' wip sItmowat , Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun .

text: But when the Jews saw the multitudes , they were filled with envy , and spake against those things which were spoken by Paul , contradicting and blaspheming .
text2: NIshcI pic Kawapmawat ki Cwiuk ni maoce ' tincIn , kimoshkIne ' se ' nI miane ' ncke ' wun , ipi okipapshItanawa notI kaiactuk Pan , okiakwne ' twawan ipi pcI - kikitok .

text: Then Paul and Barnabas waxed bold , and said , It was necessary that the word of God should first have been spoken to you : but seeing ye put it from you , and judge yourselves unworthy of everlasting life , lo , we turn to the Gentiles .
text2: IcI Pan , ipi Pe ' ne ' pe ' s kiwishkukwuk , ipi otI kikItwuk , kiw wunItsI Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun , kinwa ne ' tum ; e ' wi iactumakoie ' k , osamcI nkoci e ' ne ' nme ' k , ipi e ' waptuwuie ' k kiiuwawa e ' pwa pite ' ntakwsie ' k e ' wiiIiIie ' k kakuke ' pmatsowun pInI naskawa mIn , ki Me ' i kIs cIk .

text: For so hath the Lord commanded us , saying , I have set thee to be a light of the Gentiles , that thou shouldest be for salvation unto the ends of the earth .
text2: OtIsI ie ' i Kshe ' mIne ' to nkikatonkonan , otI kikIto ; kukicipitupe ' num e ' wiwase ' shkmoe ' k ki me ' mataose ' cIk , kinwa kuke ' skontuwe ' wun e ' wishiamkuk e ' kokiwuk .

text: And when the Gentiles heard this , they were glad , and glorified the word of the Lord : and as many as were ordained to eternal life believed .
text2: IcI ki Me ' ikiscIk , kanotmoat otI kinciwe ' nmok , ipi okiwin watanawa Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun ipi cI tso kawe ' napme ' cIk , ika kukie ' pmatsowun kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwuk .

text: And the word of the Lord was published throughout all the region .
text2: Ipi i Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun , kimnwacIkate ' caye ' k shi katnukie ' wat .

text: But the Jews stirred up the devout and honourable women , and the chief men of the city , and raised persecution against Paul and Barnabas , and expelled them out of their coasts .
text2: NIshcI ki Cwiuk , otopwe ' mawan ni e ' nmaancIn , nakansIncIn kwe ' n ipi ni nakansincIn nInwun , shi kcI - otanuk , ipi oki miash totwawan PanIn , ipi Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , ipi oki miwnashkawawan , shi e ' tnukie ' wat .

text: But they shook off the dust of their feet against them , and came unto Iconium .
text2: Oki papiwshkumakwan , i ne ' kwukI , shiw osItiwak icI kipie ' k shi Ikoniumuk .

text: And the disciples were filled with joy , and with the Holy Ghost .
text2: Ipi ki ke ' knomocuk ; kimoshkIne ' shkaknawa mciwe ' nmowun , ipi ni PanakwsIncIn Cipam .

text: And it came to pass in Iconium , that they went both together into the synagogue of the Jews , and so spake , that a great multitude both of the Jews and also of the Greeks believed .
text2: IcI kanomkuk shi Ikoniumuk , ne ' ne ' ish kin mIwice ' twuk e ' kipitike ' wat , shiwtIn une ' okum komwak ki Cwiuk ipi kikitok , icI ki ke ' cmaoce ' ticuk ne ' ne ' ish ki Cwiuk , ipi ki ke ' iapI Knik nIshInape ' k , ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwuk .

text: But the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles , and made their minds evil affected against the brethren .
text2: NishcI ki kapwa te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk Cwiuk oki wpwe ' mawan ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn icI okimiane ' nmawan ni wikane ' iwan .

text: Long time therefore abode they speaking boldly in the Lord , which gave testimony unto the word of his grace , and granted signs and wonders to be done by their hands .
text2: IwcI ie ' i shi kInwe ' sh kaocIiuwat kiwish kI kikitok shi Kshe ' mIne ' to otImoswunuk kimikwe ' cI shkIe ' osuwun iw kikitowun oshuwe ' ncIke ' wun , okiminankI kInwacIke ' onIn , ipi mamkate ' ntumwunIn e ' winuk kmuksInIt .

text: But the multitude of the city was divided : and part held with the Jews , and part with the apostles .
text2: NIshcI kimaoce ' ticIk shi kcI otanuk okipapkantonawa wiwa ’ wa ’ , anIt okiwitokwawan , ni CwiIn , anIt cI ki okiwitokwawan ni nwakanme ' cIn .

text: And when there was an assault made both of the Gentiles , and also of the Jews with their rulers , to use them despitefully , and to stone them ,
text2: Pic cI ki Me ' ikIscIk , ipi ki Cwiuk , ipi niw onikansimwan , pic e ' wi miashtotwawat , ipi e ' wi sInwawat .

text: They were ware of it , and fled unto Lystra and Derbe , cities of Lycaonia , and unto the region that lieth round about :
text2: Okike ' ntanawa icI e ' ki nInshumwat shi Nayste ' uk ipi Te ' piuk , kcI otanuk shi Ne ' koniumuk , ipi shi e ' kiwuk kiw tayiukwan .

text: And there they preached the gospel .
text2: Shi cI kikie ' kwe ' k i mnoacimowun .

text: And there sat a certain man at Lystra , impotent in his feet , being a cripple from his mother ' s womb , who never had walked :
text2: ShicI nkot nkot nInI kicipitupI , shi Nayste ' uk kimiakikate ' , co kinI pmose ' si e ' konikIt .

text: The same heard Paul speak : who stedfastly beholding him , and perceiving that he had faith to be healed ,
text2: Win okinotwan PanIn e ' kikitonIt , win kan okinapman , ipi e ' ke ' nmat e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIt e ' wine ' se ' nIt ;

text: Said with a loud voice , Stand upright on thy feet . And he leaped and walked .
text2: OtI kikIto kiwishkowe ' , Nipokapwun shi ksItik . IcI e ' kikwasksoot , ipi e ' kipmose ' t .

text: And when the people saw what Paul had done , they lifted up their voices , saying in the speech of Lycaonia , The gods are come down to us in the likeness of men .
text2: Pic cI ki nIshInape ' k kawaptumwat Pan katotmInIt , Kiwishkwe ' we ' ksik , e ' shumnIt ni Naykonie ' nInwuk , ipi otI kikItwuk , Te ' pe ' nke ' cuk , pie ' nisasitakwnanuk e ' shnakwsawat nInwuk .

text: And they called Barnabas , Jupiter ; and Paul , Mercurius , because he was the chief speaker .
text2: OkishInkanawan cI Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn CwpitI , ipi PanIn , Me ' kwnius , osam win nakan kakitot .

text: Then the priest of Jupiter , which was before their city , brought oxen and garlands unto the gates , and would have done sacrifice with the people .
text2: IcI CwpitI omumatke ' mcIn , win e ' nasmupIt shiw okIcotanwak , okipie ' nawan psukwun , ipi wawaskone ' toiIn , shi shkwate ' muk , ipi otaki wic pitakimiman mikwe ' wunIn ni nIshInape ' n .

text: Which when the apostles , Barnabas and Paul , heard of , they rent their clothes , and ran in among the people , crying out ,
text2: IcI ki nwakancIk , Pe ' ne ' pe ' s ipi Pan , kanotmowat i okinanisikpItonawa ni paskumwacIn , ipi kipItok me ' kwe ' nIshInape ' kI , kinotakwsik .

text: And saying , Sirs , why do ye these things ? We also are men of like passions with you , and preach unto you that ye should turn from these vanities unto the living God , which made heaven , and earth , and the sea , and all things that are therein :
text2: Ipi otI kikItwuk , We ' kwnicI otI we ' ctotme ' k , NinansIke ' ntIniwmIn e ' shwe ' psie ' k kinwa ipi kukie ' kmInmIn otI e ' wi ponikme ' k otI pe ' shkwacak , icI e ' wi kwe ' knoitwe ' k kakuke ' pmatsIt Kshe ' mIne ' to kaoshItot kishuk , ipi kI ipi kcIkum , ipi cake ' ko piciukwane ' te ' k .

text: Who in times past suffered all nations to walk in their own ways .
text2: Winke ' isha kapkIte ' nmat caye ' k e ' shumnIt e ' shte ' anIt e ' wishowe ' psInIt .

text: Nevertheless he left not himself without witness , in that he did good , and gave us rain from heaven , and fruitful seasons , filling our hearts with food and gladness .
text2: Ke ' iapI cI otI kiwapitu konan pIne ' ’ kimnototakwnan , ipi , kiwcI minkonan kmowIn shpumuk , ipi e ' wi minokuk ke ' ko e ' tso mnokmuk , kmoshkIne ' stakwnan kte ' ’ inanIn i micum , ipi nciwe ' nmo wun .

text: And with these sayings scarce restrained they the people , that they had not done sacrifice unto them .
text2: OtI cI i e ' kianwInawat , kawa okikshkawan ni nIshInape ' n e ' ipwa minawat mikwe ' wunIn .

text: And there came thither certain Jews from Antioch and Iconium , who persuaded the people , and , having stoned Paul , drew him out of the city , supposing he had been dead .
text2: Kipie ' kcI shi anIt Cwiuk , kiw cupie ' k E ' ntiakuk ipi Ikoniumuk , okiwishte ' pmawan ni nIshInape ' n , ipi kasInwawat ni PanIn , okisakcowe ' pnawan shiw kcI otanuk , kinpoak e ' ne ' nmawat .

text: Howbeit , as the disciples stood round about him , he rose up , and came into the city : and the next day he departed with Barnabas to Derbe .
text2: NIshcI ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , kinipwik e ' ciiInIt , kipsukwiwak , ipi kishie ' shi kcIotanuk , icI wiapnInuk Te ' piuk , kishI macik okiwice ' wan Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn .

text: And when they had preached the gospel to that city , and had taught many , they returned again to Lystra , and to Iconium , and Antioch ,
text2: IcI pic , kakishkie ' kwe ' wat i mnoacimowun shi kcI otanuk , ipi mce ' sh kaknomowawat minI kishIkiwe ' k , Nayste ' uk ipi Ikoniumuk , ipi shi E ' ntiakuk .

text: Confirming the souls of the disciples , and exhorting them to continue in the faith , and that we must through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God .
text2: E ' wi shke ' ntumoawat nite ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn ocipamnInIn , ipi e ' ikwamawat e ' wi nishkI te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIt , kuwaptamI nmce ' sh ianmIswun , winmI pitike ' ikon Kshe ' mIne ' te ' otokumauwunuk .

text: And when they had ordained them elders in every church , and had prayed with fasting , they commended them to the Lord , on whom they believed .
text2: IcI kakishonakwnawat Ke ' kie ' kwe ' ncIn , ki caye ' k te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , onukmuk , ipi kakishnumawat e ' ki pwawisnawat okinume ' kitumwawan ni Kshe ' mIne ' ton , kate ' pwe ' ie ' nmawacIn .

text: And after they had passed throughout Pisidia , they came to Pamphylia .
text2: IcI kakish cakshkumwat , shi Psitie ' uk kipie ' shie ' k Pe ' mpinie ' uk .

text: And when they had preached the word in Perga , they went down into Attalia :
text2: IcI kakish mnoactumwat i kikitowun shi Pinke ' uk , kipie ' shie ' k shi E ' te ' nie ' uk :

text: And thence sailed to Antioch , from whence they had been recommended to the grace of God for the work which they fulfilled .
text2: Shiw cI kiwcI nashwuk , ipI E ' ntiakuk , shiw ie ' shi , katshI nume ' kitotwa , Kshe ' mIne ' to oshuwe ' ncIke ' wun , osam , i mikce ' wiwun katpIse ' stowat .

text: And when they were come , and had gathered the church together , they rehearsed all that God had done with them , and how he had opened the door of faith unto the Gentiles .
text2: Pic cI kapie ' wat , ipi kakish maotIna wat ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn , okiwitmowawan cake ' ko Kshe ' mIne ' ton kaocI kshIe ' osuwat ; ipi kashI te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIt ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn .

text: And there they abode long time with the disciples .
text2: ShiwcI kInwe ' sh okiwicawan ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn .

text: And certain men which came down from Judaea taught the brethren , and said , Except ye be circumcised after the manner of Moses , ye cannot be saved .
text2: AnIt cI , nInwuk , kaocI piacuk Cwtie ' uk , okiknomowawan , ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn , otI kikItwuk , KishpIn , i pwashI tpakwnIkoie ' k , kashI we ' psIt Mosus , coktake ' skwisim .

text: When therefore Paul and Barnabas had no small dissension and disputation with them , they determined that Paul and Barnabas , and certain other of them , should go up to Jerusalem unto the apostles and elders about this question .
text2: IcI Pan , ipi Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , mce ' sh okiInawa iakwne ' tatwun okine ' nmawan ni PanIn ipi Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , ipi niw anIt pe ' kansIn cIn , winwa , e ' wishiawat shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , e ' win natawawat ni nwakancIk , ipi nakanse ' cIk ; i natatwun .

text: And being brought on their way by the church , they passed through Phenice and Samaria , declaring the conversion of the Gentiles : and they caused great joy unto all the brethren .
text2: Kanmupitse ' wat cI oki , ni shokumakwan , ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIcIn , okinmIshapshkanawa Pinisuk ipi Se ' me ' niuk , e ' witmake ' wat e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIt , ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn icI kikcI papine ' ntumwun ni caye ' k wikane ' iwan .

text: And when they were come to Jerusalem , they were received of the church , and of the apostles and elders , and they declared all things that God had done with them .
text2: IwcI kapiawat shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , oki pitkInkowan ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn ipi ni nwakancuk , ipi ni nakansIncIn , icI okiwitmowawan , cak ke ' ko Kshe ' mIne ' to , kaocukshke ' osowat .

text: But there rose up certain of the sect of the Pharisees which believed , saying , That it was needful to circumcise them , and to command them to keep the law of Moses .
text2: AnIt cI ki Pe ' nisiuk , kate ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk kipsukwik , ipi otI kikItwuk , o wunItsI e ' wi tpakwnItwa , ipi e ' winakitawe ' ntumwat i Mosus otpakwnuke ' wun .

text: And the apostles and elders came together for to consider of this matter .
text2: IcI ki nwakancIk , ipi koe ' siuk kimaoce ' tik e ' winaktuwe ' ntumwat otI wanomkuk .

text: And when there had been much disputing , Peter rose up , and said unto them , Men and brethren , ye know how that a good while ago God made choice among us , that the Gentiles by my mouth should hear the word of the gospel , and believe .
text2: Pic , cI mce ' shuk kaiakwne ' tatwat , Pitu kipsukwi ipi otI okinan , NInituk , ipi nikane ' ituk , kukuke ' ntanawa pnowi , Kshe ' mIne ' to kiwwe ' napmukonan nin , e ' wi iactumwukwa i mnoacimowun ki Me ' ikIscIk , ipi e ' wite ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwat .

text: And God , which knoweth the hearts , bare them witness , giving them the Holy Ghost , even as he did unto us ;
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to ke ' ke ' ke ' ntuk , ote ' ‘ iman , win witokowan , ipi okiminan , ni PanakwsIn cIn CipamIn , kinan kashuminkoikon .

text: And put no difference between us and them , purifying their hearts by faith .
text2: Ipi co pkan okine ' nmasin , ipi kinan , okipinakwtowan ni ote ' ‘ inIn , i e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwat .

text: Now therefore why tempt ye God , to put a yoke upon the neck of the disciples , which neither our fathers nor we were able to bear ?
text2: We ' kwnicI we ' c kwcItIpe ' nme ' k Kshe ' mIne ' to , e ' wipiskotne ' k napkumwakIn shiw kwe ' knawak , ki te ' pwe ' ie ' n tukuk , co ninan nkote ' iI nosnanuk tanake ' ninan e ' wi kshkItoiak e ' wipmo ‘ wtoiak .

text: But we believe that through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ we shall be saved , even as they .
text2: NIshcI nte ' pwe ' ie ' ntamIn , oshuwe ' ncuke ' wun , Te ' pe ' nke ' t , Cisus Knayst ninanke ' nkuke ' skonkomIn ke ' cwa winwa .

text: Then all the multitude kept silence , and gave audience to Barnabas and Paul , declaring what miracles and wonders God had wrought among the Gentiles by them .
text2: IcI ki caye ' k maoce ' ticIk tokumkiik ipi okipsItwawan ni Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , ipi PanIn , e ' witmakwat , mataototmonIn ipi mamkate ' ntumwunIn , Kshe ' mIne ' to kashI nishokmakwat , e ' ciiInIt ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn .

text: And after they had held their peace , James answered , saying , Men and brethren , hearken unto me :
text2: IcI kakish pwa ke ' ko kItnIt Ce ' ms okinkwe ' twan , ipi otI kikIto , NInituk ipi nikane ' ituk PsItwushuk .

text: Simeon hath declared how God at the first did visit the Gentiles , to take out of them a people for his name .
text2: SImiun kishwitmaknan , Kshe ' mIne ' to ne ' tum kashI otIsat ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn e ' wi otI otapnat nIshInape ' n iw tInoswunuk .

text: And to this agree the words of the prophets ; as it is written ,
text2: OtIsI ie ' i nasap okikitonawa ki NakanacimocIk e ' shpie ' kate ' k ;

text: After this I will return , and will build again the tabernacle of David , which is fallen down ; and I will build again the ruins thereof , and I will set it up :
text2: Kikish otI nomkuk minI nkupie ' kiwe ' ipi nkaoshIton minI e ' tat Te ' pIt , kapmukote ' k ; ipi nkukishton i kanshonacak , ipi nku ‘ onakwsIton .

text: That the residue of men might seek after the Lord , and all the Gentiles , upon whom my name is called , saith the Lord , who doeth all these things .
text2: Ipi ki anIt nInwuk , e ' wintone ' wawat ni Kshe ' mIne ' to , ipi ki caye ' k , Me ' ikIscIk ntInoswun wawitkuk kItwak Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' totkuk caye ' k notI ke ' ko .

text: Known unto God are all his works from the beginning of the world .
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to okike ' ntan caye ' k niw omikce ' wiwnIn e ' kowe ' pkiwuk .

text: Wherefore my sentence is , that we trouble not them , which from among the Gentiles are turned to God :
text2: Osam cI otI we ' cshIte ' aian , e ' wipwam mkoshkacikwukon , ki Me ' ikIscIk kakwe ' knoitwacIk Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: But that we write unto them , that they abstain from pollutions of idols , and from fornication , and from things strangled , and from blood .
text2: NIshcI ktaonupie ' mowamIn , e ' wi pwa shiawat wansincIn , ni me ' ntokasnIncIn ipi , waonIshkawun , ipi , Ke ' pne ' we ' shkamkuk ipi mskwI .

text: For Moses of old time hath in every city them that preach him , being read in the synagogues every sabbath day .
text2: Mosus ke ' isha e ' tsInuk kcI otanIn kiw anIt okimnwactmakon iw otpakwnuke ' wun , wapcIkate ' shi msInukInuk , nume ' okumkok e ' tso nume ' kishkuk .

text: Then pleased it the apostles and elders , with the whole church , to send chosen men of their own company to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas ; namely , Judas surnamed Barsabas , and Silas , chief men among the brethren :
text2: IcI ki nwakancIk , ipi nakanse ' cIk , ipi caye ' k ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk okimnwe ' ntumwuk e ' winokanawat we ' napcIkasnIt ni nInwun winwa mamwI , e ' wishianIt E ' ntiakuk , e ' wiwice ' wanIt , PanIn , ipi Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , kotI , Cwte ' s , ke ' iapI kashInkasot Pe ' se ' pe ' s , ipi Sayne ' s , kanikanse ' cIk , nInwuk , shi mamwI wikane ' iwan .

text: And they wrote letters by them after this manner ; The apostles and elders and brethren send greeting unto the brethren which are of the Gentiles in Antioch and Syria and Cilicia :
text2: Okiw nIpie ' anawan cI mIsInuknIn , otI kinIpie ' ke ' k , NwakancIk , ipi nakanse ' cIk , ipi , wikane ' iwan , onitaawan numkatwun ni wikane ' iwan Me ' ikIscIk shi e ' icIk , E ' ntiakuk ipi shi Sinie ' uk , ipi Sinishie ' uk ;

text: Forasmuch as we have heard , that certain which went out from us have troubled you with words , subverting your souls , saying , Ye must be circumcised , and keep the law : to whom we gave no such commandment :
text2: Osam nkinotake ' mIn , anIt ninan shotI kaocI maciwat kimkoshkasmukwak niw kikitonIn , kiwie ' shtmakwak cipamwak otI e ' kItwat , kinwa kItpakwnukom ipi kInaktIwe ' ntawa i tpakwnuke ' wun , coninan , i nkishI kie ' kmasimIn .

text: It seemed good unto us , being assembled with one accord , to send chosen men unto you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul ,
text2: We ' we ' nI nkine ' ntamIn e ' maoce ' tiak , e ' nkotuk , ntIshte ' onInan , e ' wi ipI kinwa shIn nokankIt , we ' napcIkascuk , nInwuk , e ' ciiIie ' k , e ' wiwice ' wawat te ' pankon Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , ipi Pan :

text: Men that have hazarded their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ .
text2: NInwuk , kaianmItowat opumatsiw nowan , otInoswunuk , Te ' pe ' nmukwie ' kon Cisus Knayst , kaocI ishowe ' psowat .

text: We have sent therefore Judas and Silas , who shall also tell you the same things by mouth .
text2: OtI ie ' i we ' c nokankIt Cwte ' s , ipi Sayne ' s , winwa , ke ' ke ' iapI kuwitmakwak nasap notI ke ' ko shiw otoniwak .

text: For it seemed good to the Holy Ghost , and to us , to lay upon you no greater burden than these necessary things ;
text2: We ' we ' nI , kine ' ntum PanakwsIt Cipam ipi ninan , e ' witotme ' k notI ke ' ko , tashI owunuk e ' witomuk .

text: That ye abstain from meats offered to idols , and from blood , and from things strangled , and from fornication : from which if ye keep yourselves , ye shall do well . Fare ye well .
text2: E ' wi pwamicie ' k , wias , kamintwa me ' ntokascuk , ipi mskwiik ipi ke ' ko kakpe ' ne ' we ' shkamkuk , ipi pshukwat sowun , kishpIn notI pwatotme ' k kumnototam We ' we ' nI ktIne ' nmInmIn .

text: So when they were dismissed , they came to Antioch : and when they had gathered the multitude together , they delivered the epistle :
text2: Pic , cI kapkItnItwa , kishie ' k , shi E ' ntiakuk , icI pic kamaosomawat ni maoce ' tincIn ki mikwe ' k , o mIsInukIn .

text: Which when they had read , they rejoiced for the consolation .
text2: IcI kakishwaptumwat i mIsInukIn kimnowankoswuk , i kashu mnoacimonIt .

text: And Judas and Silas , being prophets also themselves , exhorted the brethren with many words , and confirmed them .
text2: Osam cI , Cwte ' s , ipi Sayne ' s , nakanacimocuk winwa , okiakwamawan ni wikane ' iwan , mce ' sh kikitonIn , ipi okiwishkumawan .

text: And after they had tarried there a space , they were let go in peace from the brethren unto the apostles .
text2: IcI shi kakishiIwat , nomuk , we ' we ' nI okip kIte ' nmukwan ni wikane ' iwan , icI e ' kishiawat ni nwakancuk .

text: Notwithstanding it pleased Silas to abide there still .
text2: Ki ianwI mnwe ' ntuk Sayne ' s , shie ' witat .

text: Paul also and Barnabas continued in Antioch , teaching and preaching the word of the Lord , with many others also .
text2: Pan ke ' iapI , ipi Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , kiik shi E ' ntiakuk e ' kInomake ' wat , ipi e ' mnwactumwat okikitowun Kshe ' mIne ' to , ipi ki anIt pe ' kanse ' cIk , ke ' winwa .

text: And some days after Paul said unto Barnabas , Let us go again and visit our brethren in every city where we have preached the word of the Lord , and see how they do .
text2: IcI kaonatsokwnuktInuk , Pan , otI okinan , Pe ' ne ' pe ' sIn , Shi atan minI , ipi owawapmatan kikane ' nanuk , shi e ' tsuk , kcI otanIn , katshI , mInwactumwukon okikitowun Kshe ' mIne ' to ; ipi e ' wiwapmukon e ' shwe ' psuwat .

text: And Barnabas determined to take with them John , whose surname was Mark .
text2: Pe ' ne ' pe ' s cI kine ' ntum e ' wi wice ' wawat CanIn ke ' iapI e ' shnukasot Mak .

text: But Paul thought not good to take him with them , who departed from them from Pamphylia , and went not with them to the work .
text2: NIshcI Pan , cowunse ' non kine ' ntum e ' wi wice ' wawat , okinknancI shi Pe ' mpinie ' uk cocI okiwice ' wasin , e ' wi mikce ' winIt .

text: And the contention was so sharp between them , that they departed asunder one from the other : and so Barnabas took Mark , and sailed unto Cyprus ;
text2: CocI kimnwe ' ntusik iwcI , kaocI papke ' wat , icI Pe ' ne ' pe ' s , okiw i ce ' wan MakIn SaypnIsuk cI ki kinashwuk .

text: And Paul chose Silas , and departed , being recommended by the brethren unto the grace of God .
text2: IcI Pan , okiwe ' napman , Sayne ' sIn , icI kakish matmowawat , Kshe ' mIne ' to oshuwe ' ncIke ' wIn , ni wikane ' iwan , kin mumacik .

text: And he went through Syria and Cilicia , confirming the churches .
text2: IcI e ' kishiat Sinie ' uk , ipi Sinishie ' uk , e ' wishke ' e ' ntumoat ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn .

text: Then came he to Derbe and Lystra : and , behold , a certain disciple was there , named Timotheus , the son of a certain woman , which was a Jewess , and believed ; but his father was a Greek :
text2: IwcI kapiat shi Te ' piuk , ipi Ne ' stiuk ipi pInI , nkot te ' pwe ' ie ' ntuk shi kiiI Timotius kishInkaso , okiw okwIsmukon , nkot , Cwkwe ' , kate ' pwe ' ie ' ntuk , nicI osIn Knik nInI .

text: Which was well reported of by the brethren that were at Lystra and Iconium .
text2: We ' we ' nI okishumkon ni we ' wikane ' itIncIn ipI kaie ' cuk Ne ' stiuk , ipi Ikoniumuk .

text: Him would Paul have to go forth with him ; and took and circumcised him because of the Jews which were in those quarters : for they knew all that his father was a Greek .
text2: Win , Pan , kine ' ntum , e ' wiwice ' okot , ipi oki tpakwnan osam ni CwiIn shi kaiIncIn , osam , okike ' nmawan caye ' k , ni isIn e ' Knik nInwunIt .

text: And as they went through the cities , they delivered them the decrees for to keep , that were ordained of the apostles and elders which were at Jerusalem .
text2: IwcI kanmIshiawat shi kcI otanIn okiminawan i tpakwnuke ' wun e ' wikowaptumwat , kaoshItowat ki nwakancIk ipi nakanse ' cIk , shi e ' icIk Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: And so were the churches established in the faith , and increased in number daily .
text2: OtI cI kashI we ' psuwat kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , kiwishkIckate ' ne ' , ote ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwunwa wusimI cI , kimane ' k , e ' tso kishkuk .

text: Now when they had gone throughout Phrygia and the region of Galatia , and were forbidden of the Holy Ghost to preach the word in Asia ,
text2: Pic cI kacakshkumwat shi Pniciuk ipi shi e ' kiwuk , Ke ' ne ' shiuk , okiknImakowan ni PanakwsIncIn CipamIn , e ' wi mnwactumwat i kikitowIn shi E ' shie ' uk .

text: After they were come to Mysia , they assayed to go into Bithynia : but the Spirit suffered them not .
text2: Kapiawat cI shi Maysiuk , Kine ' ntumwuk , e ' wishiawat , ipI Piti niuk , cocI okine ' nmukwsiwan , ni CipamIn .

text: And they passing by Mysia came down to Troas .
text2: IwcI okikwe ' pmosatanawa Maysiuk , icI kipie ' shie ' k , shi Tno e ' suk .

text: And a vision appeared to Paul in the night ; There stood a man of Macedonia , and prayed him , saying , Come over into Macedonia , and help us .
text2: Pan cI e ' pkonianuk , kiapwI , nkot , e ' nipwunIt Me ' sitonie ' nInwun , e ' wish te ' pmukot otI kikItwun ; Me ' sitonie ' uk pie ' shian ; ipi pie ' nishokmoshInak .

text: And after he had seen the vision , immediately we endeavored to go into Macedonia , assuredly gathering that the Lord had called us for to preach the gospel unto them .
text2: Kakish i napituk , kie ' nup , ipI ki kwcI shie ' k Me ' sitonie ' uk , we ' we ' nI e ' ne ' ntuk Kshe ' mIne ' to kintomkonan , e ' wiiac tumwukon , i mnoacmowun .

text: Therefore loosing from Troas , we came with a straight course to Samothracia , and the next day to Neapolis ;
text2: IcI kawe ' pshkaiak shi , Tnoe ' suk , nkipie ' shiamIn tpasI shi Samotne ' shie ' uk , icI wiapuk , shi NiapnIsuk .

text: And from thence to Philippi , which is the chief city of that part of Macedonia , and a colony : and we were in that city abiding certain days .
text2: NkiwcI shiamIn shi Pinipayuk , iw ie ' i mamwI kcI otan shi Me ' sitonie ' kik , KaocI tpe ' ncIkate ' k shi cI nkiImIn shi kcI otanuk , onatsokwun .

text: And on the sabbath we went out of the city by a river side , where prayer was wont to be made ; and we sat down , and spake unto the women which resorted thither .
text2: IcI e ' nume ' kishkuk , nkisakamIn shi kcI otanuk , nkishiamIn , ciksIpik , katshI ntanumawat , icI nkicipitupmIn , ipi nki knonamIn kwe ' k , shi kacipie ' n tashiawat .

text: And a certain woman named Lydia , a seller of purple , of the city of Thyatira , which worshipped God , heard us : whose heart the Lord opened , that she attended unto the things which were spoken of Paul .
text2: IwcI nkot kwe ' Nite ' kishInkaso tawe ' t mskwe ' kIn kcI otanuk Taye ' tayniuk kanume ' kItowat Kshe ' mIne ' ton , nkipsItakwnan , Kshe ' mIne ' to kapaknumwat ote ' ’ inIn iwcI kaocI psItuk , kakItnIt ni PanIn .

text: And when she was baptized , and her household , she besought us , saying , If ye have judged me to be faithful to the Lord , come into my house , and abide there . And she constrained us .
text2: IwcI kakish kcI - tapie ' nIt , ipi ni kawitke ' macIn ; nkiwishte ' pmukwunan otI kikIto , kishpIn ne ' nImIie ' k e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' nmuk Kshe ' mIne ' to , pie ' pitike ' k , e ' taian , ipi shiiuk ; icI nkiwishte ' pmukwunan .

text: And it came to pass , as we went to prayer , a certain damsel possessed with a spirit of divination met us , which brought her masters much gain by soothsaying :
text2: IcI otI kanomkuk , e ' wi we ' pnumaiak nkot kikiak , packakwcIn mIne ' tonakanacmonIt nkinkwe ' shkakwnan , mce ' sh ke ' ko okikshkItwan te ' pe ' nmukwocIn iw onikanacimonIn .

text: The same followed Paul and us , and cried , saying , These men are the servants of the most high God , which shew unto us the way of salvation .
text2: Win okipmnashkawan PanIn ipi ninan , ipi kiwishkwe ' we ' kse ' otI kikIto . KotI nInwuk MamwI shpumuk Kshe ' mIne ' to , opmitakaimIn , waptukoikon washu ke ' skonkoikon .

text: And this did she many days . But Paul , being grieved , turned and said to the spirit , I command thee in the name of Jesus Christ to come out of her . And he came out the same hour .
text2: IwcI mce ' shkon katotuk , NIshcI Pan kikwinwune ' ntum kikwe ' knoi , ipi otI okinan , ni mIne ' ton , Nin ktInIn shiw tInoswunuk Cisus Knayst , e ' wi pie ' sakumIn . IcI e ' ki pie ' sakuk , shi ie ' i pic tpukIn .

text: And when her masters saw that the hope of their gains was gone , they caught Paul and Silas , and drew them into the marketplace unto the rulers ,
text2: IwcI ni pic , te ' pe ' nmukwocIn kawap tumwat kashI nkItowat , iw , ie ' shkIcke ' wat , okimshInawan ni PanIn ipi Sayne ' sIn ipi okishonawan shi e ' tshItatuk ni nakansIncIn .

text: And brought them to the magistrates , saying , These men , being Jews , do exceedingly trouble our city ,
text2: Ipi oki shonawan e ' ciiInIt tpakwnuke ' onInwun otI kikItwuk , kotI nInwuk , e ' ianwe ' Cwiwawat , okIc , mkoshkacikanawa kIc otanan .

text: And teach customs , which are not lawful for us to receive , neither to observe , being Romans .
text2: Ipi kuknomake ' k watotmuk cokinan wunsInon e ' wiwtapnumkon , tanake ' e ' winaktIwe ' ntumkon , osam kinam NomIn nInwuk .

text: And the multitude rose up together against them : and the magistrates rent off their clothes , and commanded to beat them .
text2: IwcI ki maoce ' ticIk kipsukwik mamawI ipi ki tpakwnuke ' nInwuk , oki na ni sikpIto nawan paskumwacIn ipi kishuwe ' k e ' wi we ' we ' pockasnIt ;

text: And when they had laid many stripes upon them , they cast them into prison , charging the jailor to keep them safely :
text2: IcI kakish we ' we ' potwawat mce ' shuk , okipitike ' , wapnawan shi cupakotiw kumkok ipi okiwitmowawan ni e ' kwapicuk , e ' wi wike ' kawapmanIt .

text: Who , having received such a charge , thrust them into the inner prison , and made their feet fast in the stocks .
text2: Iw winwa kakish witmotwa okikatwawan shi ianke ' piciukwan , kupakotiwkumkok , ipi okiktapkuwawan shiw osItinuk .

text: And at midnight Paul and Silas prayed , and sang praises unto God : and the prisoners heard them .
text2: IcI e ' iaptI tpukuk Pan , ipi Sayne ' s ki nume ' k , ipi kinkumwuk okiwinwanawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi ki shi kakpakwukasnIt , okinotakwan .

text: And suddenly there was a great earthquake , so that the foundations of the prison were shaken : and immediately all the doors were opened , and every one ' s bands were loosed .
text2: IcI kie ' nup kikcI macshke ' , kI , ipi i ne ' tmuskIn shi kpakwo tiw kumkok kinukshke ' , icI papuk , caye ' k ni shkwate ' me ' n kinsakwshke ' ton , ipi e ' tshuwat otukpIckInwan kiapskoke ' ne ' .

text: And the keeper of the prison awaking out of his sleep , and seeing the prison doors open , he drew out his sword , and would have killed himself , supposing that the prisoners had been fled .
text2: IcI o e ' kwapituk i kpakotiwkumuk e ' tokit , ipi e ' waptuk kpakotiw shkwate ' mIn e ' nsakwsInuk , okikicpIton i okishkowun , ipi takinsIto e ' kine ' nmat ni kie ' pakwuukasnIncIn e ' kiw shumnIt .

text: But Paul cried with a loud voice , saying , Do thyself no harm : for we are all here .
text2: NIshcI Pan kiwishkowe ' otI okinan , Ke ' ko na ’ w totatsokIn ; anwukshI caye ' k shotI ntIimIn .

text: Then he called for a light , and sprang in , and came trembling , and fell down before Paul and Silas ,
text2: IcI e ' kintotuk waskone ' ncukIn , ipi kipie ' pitike ' se ' , ipi kinukshke ' kipmukocIn e ' nasmupnIt PanIn , ipi Sayne ' sIn .

text: And brought them out , and said , Sirs , what must I do to be saved ?
text2: IcI e ' ki pie ' sakconat , ipi otI okinan Ke ' knomake ' ik , We ' kwnonicI ke ' totman e ' wi ke ' skwian ?

text: And they said , Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ , and thou shalt be saved , and thy house .
text2: OtI cI okinawan , Te ' pwe ' ie ' num Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus Knayst , icI ke ' cI ke ' skwin , ipi ki e ' icuk , e ' tan .

text: And they spake unto him the word of the Lord , and to all that were in his house .
text2: IwcI e ' kiiactumwawat iw kikitowun Kshe ' mIne ' to , ipi ni caye ' k , kaie ' ncIn shi e ' tanIt .

text: And he took them the same hour of the night , and washed their stripes ; and was baptized , he and all his , straightway .
text2: IwcI e ' kiw otapnat iw pic tpukIn e ' pkonianuk , ipI e ' kiksipie ' nmoat kanuk inackasnIt , icI e ' kikcItapie ' nIt , ipi caye ' k shi kaice ' n , e ' tat , kie ' nup .

text: And when he had brought them into his house , he set meat before them , and rejoiced , believing in God with all his house .
text2: IwcI kapitike ' nat shi e ' tat , otituwan wamicnIt , e ' nasmupnIt , ipi kimnowankose ' e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' nmat Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi ni caye ' k kaie ' ncIn e ' tat .

text: And when it was day , the magistrates sent the serjeants , saying , Let those men go .
text2: IwcI kawapne ' nuk , tpakwnuke ' , nInwuk , okinokanawan ni okumasIn , otI kikItwuk ; PkItnuk , kotI nInwuk .

text: And the keeper of the prison told this saying to Paul , The magistrates have sent to let you go : now therefore depart , and go in peace .
text2: IkI o e ' kwaptuk , i kpakotiwkumuk , okiwitmowan ni PanIn , tpakwnuke ' nInwuk , nokashwe ' t , e ' wi pkItnukasie ' k , Macik , ipi we ' we ' nI shiak .

text: But Paul said unto them , They have beaten us openly uncondemned , being Romans , and have cast us into prison ; and now do they thrust us out privily ? nay verily ; but let them come themselves and fetch us out .
text2: Pan cI otI okinan , Ninan sI Nome ' n nInwuk , ipi NkipsItie ' konanukIni , e ' cowapcIkate ' k , e ' pwa tpakwnuke ' wat , ipi nki pitikwe ' pe ' nukinanuk , kpakotiwkumkok , nkom nIcI kimoc nwisakcI , katokwnanuk ? we ' we ' nI coIn , winwa tpInwI kupie ' k ipi nkIsakconukwinanuk .

text: And the serjeants told these words unto the magistrates : and they feared , when they heard that they were Romans .
text2: IwcI kiw okumasuk , kawitmowawat ni tpakwnuke ' onInwun , kakItnIt , kise ' ksik kanotake ' wat winwae ' , Nome ' n wInwunIt .

text: And they came and besought them , and brought them out , and desired them to depart out of the city .
text2: IwcI e ' kipiawat , ipi okiwishte ' pmawan icI e ' ki sakcocawat , ipi okinatowawan e ' wi sakumnIt shi kcI otanuk .

text: And they went out of the prison , and entered into the house of Lydia and when they had seen the brethren , they comforted them , and departed .
text2: IwcI e ' kisakumwat shi kpakotiwkumkok , icI e ' kipitike ' wat shi e ' tanIt Nitie ' iIn icI kawapmawat ni wikane ' iwan okinciwe ' nmoawan , icI e ' ki maciwat .

text: Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia , they came to Thessalonica , where was a synagogue of the Jews :
text2: IwcI kanmI kwe ' pmosatmowat E ' mpoponisuk , ipi E ' pononie ' uk , kipie ' shie ' k shi Te ' sinonie ' uk shi kite ' nI otInume ' okumkomwa ki Cwiuk .

text: And Paul , as his manner was , went in unto them , and three sabbath days reasoned with them out of the scriptures ,
text2: IwcI Pan , e ' shcIke ' t okipitike ' ntawan shi , ipi nsuk e ' nume ' kishkuk , okiwishte ' pman shi Kshe ' mIne ' to ikikitonuk .

text: Opening and alleging , that Christ must needs have suffered , and risen again from the dead ; and that this Jesus , whom I preach unto you , is Christ .
text2: E ' witmowat ipi we ' we ' nI e ' iactumwat , nomkItne ' Knayst e ' wi kwtukitot , ipi , minI e ' wipsukwit , e ' kinpot , otI cI ie ' o Cisus nin me ' nwactumonkon oie ' o Knayst .

text: And some of them believed , and consorted with Paul and Silas ; and of the devout Greeks a great multitude , and of the chief women not a few .
text2: IwcI anIt kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwuk , ipi okiwitokwawan ni PanIn , ipi Sayne ' sIn , ipi ke ' cmaoce ' ticIn , e ' nmuancIn Knik nIshInape ' k , ipi co kipke ' ci shIiwusik , nakanse ' cIk kwe ' k .

text: But the Jews which believed not , moved with envy , took unto them certain lewd fellows of the baser sort , and gathered a company , and set all the city on an uproar , and assaulted the house of Jason , and sought to bring them out to the people .
text2: KicI Cwiuk , kapwate ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , kikshawe ' ncuke ' k , ipi okiwtapnawan anIt ke ' kie ' patsIncIn nInwun , mamwI kie ' patsIncIn , ipi okimaotanawan , maoce ' tincIn , ipi caye ' k shi kcI - otanuk kiwishkwe ' we ' ksik , ipi okimikatmoawan e ' tanIt Ce ' sInIn , e ' wi kwcIsakcoonawat e ' wisho ’ tuwawat ni nIshInape ' n .

text: And when they found them not , they drew Jason and certain brethren unto the rulers of the city , crying , These that have turned the world upside down are come hither also ;
text2: IwcI shi kapwa mkuwawat , okiwtapnawan Ce ' sInIn , ipi anIt wikane ' inInIn , okisho ’ tuwawan , ni nakansIncIn shi kcI - otanuk otI kikItwuk , kotI , kakwe ' npawe ' pnukuk kI , win wake ' shotI pie ' k .

text: Whom Jason hath received : and these all do contrary to the decrees of Caesar , saying that there is another king , one Jesus .
text2: KotI Ce ' sIn kapitike ' nacIn , caye ' k cI cototsik otpakwnuke ' wun SIse ' iIn , otI kItwuk , nkot , pkansI kcI okuma , nkot Cisus .

text: And they troubled the people and the rulers of the city , when they heard these things .
text2: Ipi kimkoshkate ' ntumwuk , ki nIshInape ' k ipi nikansimwan shi kcI - otanuk , pic kanotmoat notI ke ' ko .

text: And when they had taken security of Jason , and of the other , they let them go .
text2: IwcI kataswat , o Ce ' sun ipi ki anIt , kipkItnukaswuk .

text: And the brethren immediately sent away Paul and Silas by night unto Berea : who coming thither went into the synagogue of the Jews .
text2: IwcI ni wikane ' iwan , kie ' nup , kinokana wan ni PanIn , ip Sayne ' sIn kapkonianuk ipI Pinie ' uk kapiawat kipitike ' k shi otInume ' okumkomwa ki Cwiuk .

text: These were more noble than those in Thessalonica , in that they received the word with all readiness of mind , and searched the scriptures daily , whether those things were so .
text2: KotI cI wusimI kipite ' ntakwsik icI kikaicuk ipI Te ' sinonike ' uk , osam winwa kipsItanawa i kikitowIn , caye ' k , anwaci ne ' ntumwun , ipi okintowapitanawa Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun e ' tso kishkuk , e ' wike ' ntumwat tanak notI ke ' ko , e ' wite ' pwe ' mkItnuk .

text: Therefore many of them believed ; also of honourable women which were Greeks , and of men , not a few .
text2: IwcI ie ' i mce ' sh kaocI te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwat ke ' iapI nakanse ' cIk knik kwe ' k , ipi nInwuk co kipke ' cishIiwusik .

text: But when the Jews of Thessalonica had knowledge that the word of God was preached of Paul at Berea , they came thither also , and stirred up the people .
text2: Pic cI ki Cwiuk kaie ' cuk Te ' sinonike ' uk kake ' ntumwat Pan , e ' mnwactuk Kshe ' mIne ' to kikitowIn , ipI Pinie ' uk , kipie ' k shi ke ' iapI , ipi okiopwe ' awan ni nIshInape ' n .

text: And then immediately the brethren sent away Paul to go as it were to the sea : but Silas and Timotheus abode there still .
text2: IwcI kie ' nup ni wikane ' iwan okinokanawan PanIn , ke ' cwa e ' ki shiakasot shi kcu kamik , Sayne ' s cI ipi Timotius shi me ' kwa kiik .

text: And they that conducted Paul brought him unto Athens : and receiving a commandment unto Silas and Timotheus for to come to him with all speed , they departed .
text2: KiwcI kapmonacuk ni PanIn , kipie ' na wan shi E ' tinsuk , icI kakish witmakwat e ' wiwitmowawat Sayne ' sIn , ipi TimotiusIn kie ' nup e ' wipianIt shi e ' ciIt , kinmamacik .

text: Now while Paul waited for them at Athens , his spirit was stirred in him , when he saw the city wholly given to idolatry .
text2: Me ' kwacI Pan e ' ie ' pwi iat shi E ' tinsuk ocipamIn okim mackakon , pic waptuk i kcI otan , caye ' k e ' pkItnItsowat me ' nIto kat nIncIn .

text: Therefore disputed he in the synagogue with the Jews , and with the devout persons , and in the market daily with them that met with him .
text2: IwcI otI , kaocI iakwne ' twat , ni CwiIn shi otInume ' okumkonmnuk , ipi ni e ' nmaancIn , ipi shi e ' tshItatuk e ' tso kishkuk shiw kankwe ' shkakwcIn .

text: Then certain philosophers of the Epicureans , and of the Stoicks , encountered him . And some said , What will this babbler say ? other some , He seemeth to be a setter forth of strange gods : because he preached unto them Jesus , and the resurrection .
text2: IwcI anIt ne ' pwakacIk nInwuk , kiw Ipkwnie ' n ipi stoik nInwuk okiiakwne ' takon . Ipi anIt , otI kikItwuk , WikwnicI otI ke ' c , ntakakikitot , ke ' kItot ? anIt ke ' pe ' kanse ' cIk , kikItwuk , ne ' ntakwsI , we ' ckie ' kwe ' t ni me ' matao sIncIn MIne ' ton , osam kaocI kie ' kwe ' t ni CisusIn , ipi psukwiwun kanpok .

text: And they took him , and brought him unto Areopagus , saying , May we know what this new doctrine , whereof thou speakest , is ?
text2: IwcI e ' kiw otapnawat , ipi okishonawan shi E ' niopike ' suk , otI cI kikItwuk ; ConI otI ntake ' ntusimIn , oshke ' shIcke ' wun , otI kin iactumIn .

text: For thou bringest certain strange things to our ears : we would know therefore what these things mean .
text2: Osam kin kpie ' ton me ' matawiak ke ' ko ntokananuk ; ie ' i ntIne ' ntamIn e ' wike ' ntumak notI ke ' ko we ' cnomkuk .

text: ( For all the Athenians and strangers which were there spent their time in nothing else , but either to tell , or to hear some new thing . )
text2: Osam caye ' k ki E ' tinsuk nInwuk , ipi pwake ' ncIkascuk , shi kaie ' cuk , coke ' ko oki miktIsinawa , mtIno , e ' wi witmake ' wat tanake ' e ' wi psItmowat we ' shkianuk , ke ' ko .

text: Then Paul stood in the midst of Mars ' hill , and said , Ye men of Athens , I perceive that in all things ye are too superstitious .
text2: IwcI Pan e ' kinipwIt , shi na ’ wiukwan Me ' s kwutakik , , ipi otI kikito ; E ' tinsuktI nIn ituk , nmukan kinwa cake ' ko , ktosam te ' pwe ' tanawa .

text: For as I passed by , and beheld your devotions , I found an altar with this inscription , TO THE UNKNOWN GOD . Whom therefore ye ignorantly worship , him declare I unto you .
text2: E ' pmose ' ian kiwapmInum , e ' numaie ' k , nkimkawa , e ' tshI sku ’ umatuk , otI e ' shuonIpie ' kate ' k , WIN KSHE ' MINE ' TO PWAKE ' NTAKWSIT ; otI ie ' i e ' pwa ke ' ntume ' k , ktInume ' kitowawat , Win ke ' iactmonum .

text: God that made the world and all things therein , seeing that he is Lord of heaven and earth , dwelleth not in temples made with hands ;
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to , kaoshItot kI , ipi cake ' ko pic iukwan e ' te ' nuk , osam win o Te ' pe ' n tan shpumuk , ipi kI cowi te ' si , wikwamuk , onIcima kaoshIcke ' k .

text: Neither is worshipped with men ' s hands , as though he needed any thing , seeing he giveth to all life , and breath , and all things ;
text2: Cowike ' , nInwuk onIciwan ocI nume ' ktowasi , ke ' cwa e ' ntuwe ' ntuk ke ' ko , osam cak wIiI ominan pmatsuwun , ipi ne ' mwun , ipi cake ' ko .

text: And hath made of one blood all nations of men for to dwell on all the face of the earth , and hath determined the times before appointed , and the bounds of their habitation ;
text2: Okowshian cak e ' shumnIt nInwun , e ' nkot nInwuk mskwI , shotI e ' icIk caye ' k kik , ipi kisha , kishne ' ntum e ' pwamshu piamkIt nuk pic , ipi wakopmatsInIt .

text: That they should seek the Lord , if haply they might feel after him , and find him , though he be not far from every one of us :
text2: E ' wi ntone ' wawat Kshe ' mIne ' ton tanak , kinaktawe ' nmawat ipi mkawawat ; co anwI pnociIsi e ' tshIikon .

text: For in him we live , and move , and have our being ; as certain also of your own poets have said , For we are also his offspring .
text2: Osam win we ' cpmatse ' ikon , ipi we ' cmacnuwiIkon , ipi we ' ciIikon kpmatsiwnunanIn , ke ' cwa anIt kinwa ne ' kumocIk kakItwat , ke ' iapI ninan ntonicansumkonan .

text: Forasmuch then as we are the offspring of God , we ought not to think that the Godhead is like unto gold , or silver , or stone , graven by art and man ' s device .
text2: OsomcI kinan e ' wi nicansumkoikon Kshe ' mIne ' to , cosuktashite ' asimIn , Kshe ' mIne ' to shInakwsI , ke ' cwa osaw ’ shonia , tanake ' shonia , tanake ' , SIn , kamiuk , u ’ koshuk , nInI , e ' shkuke ' ntuk .

text: And the times of this ignorance God winked at ; but now commandeth all men every where to repent :
text2: Pic cI otI , pwake ' ntumuk Kshe ' mIne ' to okicipikwe ' tan , nIshcI nkom , otInan caye ' k nInwun e ' wikisate ' ntusnIt .

text: Because he hath appointed a day , in the which he will judge the world in righteousness by that man whom he hath ordained ; whereof he hath given assurance unto all men , in that he hath raised him from the dead .
text2: Osam okishwshIston e ' kishkiwuk shiw ke ' ci tpakwnuk otI kI , shi npwakawunuk , niw nInwun , kawe ' napmacIn , kashu witmoat , caye ' k nIiwun , i e ' kipsukwitnat , e ' nponpIt .

text: And when they heard of the resurrection of the dead , some mocked : and others said , We will hear thee again of this matter .
text2: IwcI kanotmoat i psukwiwun , e ' npok anIt okinapto takon , ipi anIt otI ki kItwuk , minI kupsItonmIn otI katshItmIn .

text: So Paul departed from among them .
text2: IwcI Pan e ' kinkInat e ' kinmumacit .

text: Howbeit certain men clave unto him , and believed : among the which was Dionysius the Areopagite , and a woman named Damaris , and others with them .
text2: NIshcI anIt nInwuk , okiwice ' okon ipi kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwuk , nkot - cI Tayonius E ' niapikayt , nInI , ipi nkot kwe ' , Te ' me ' nIs , kishInkaso , ipi anIt pe ' kanse ' cIk .

text: After these things Paul departed from Athens , and came to Corinth ;
text2: IcI kakish otI nomkuk Pan kiwcI maci , shi E ' tinsuk , ipi kipie ' wak Kone ' ntuk .
