text: And found a certain Jew named Aquila , born in Pontus , lately come from Italy , with his wife Priscilla ; ( because that Claudius had commanded all Jews to depart from Rome : ) and came unto them .
text2: IwcI shi okimkawan nkot CwiIn E ' kwine ' kishInkaso katshInikIt shi Pantusuk mcupshuk kiwcupie ' Ite ' niuk , kipie ' wice ' wan wiwun , Pe ' se ' nie ' n , osam Knatius kishowe ' caye ' k CwiIn e ' wiwcImacinIt shi Nom ; icI e ' kipie ' naskakwat .

text: And because he was of the same craft , he abode with them , and wrought : for by their occupation they were tentmakers .
text2: OsamcI ke ' win kiie ' inInkie ' , shiw okiwitke ' man , ipi kimikce ' win , pukwoian wikwame ' n e ' oshItowat i kanInkie ' wat .

text: And he reasoned in the synagogue every sabbath , and persuaded the Jews and the Greeks .
text2: Ipi kiknomake ' shi nume ' okumkok e ' tso nume ' kishkuk ; okikie ' kman , ni CwiIn ipi Knik nInwun .

text: And when Silas and Timotheus were come from Macedonia , Paul was pressed in the spirit , and testified to the Jews that Jesus was Christ .
text2: Pic Sayne ' s ipi Timotius kaocupiawat Me ' sitonie ' uk , Pan cipamIn okiw pwe ' shkakon , ipi we ' we ' nI okiwitmowan ni CwiIn o Cisus , win Knayst .

text: And when they opposed themselves , and blasphemed , he shook his raiment , and said unto them , Your blood be upon your own heads ; I am clean : from henceforth I will go unto the Gentiles .
text2: IwcI kanshke ' nmawat , ipi kapicIkikitowat , okipapiwnanIn niw paskukIn ipi otI okinan , kinwa kmIskwimwa kupuksIn ktupiwak , nincI mpinakwIs nkom , cI nkIshia e ' ci iIwat , Me ' ikIscIk .

text: And he departed thence , and entered into a certain man ' s house , named Justus , one that worshipped God , whose house joined hard to the synagogue .
text2: IwcI kanmumacit kinmupitike ' nkot nInI wikwamnInIn , Custus , kishInkaso , win kanume ' kitowat Kshe ' mIne ' ton , e ' tat , pe ' shoc kite ' nI shi nume ' okumkok .

text: And Crispus , the chief ruler of the synagogue , believed on the Lord with all his house ; and many of the Corinthians hearing believed , and were baptized .
text2: IwcI KnIspus ke ' k nikansIt shi nume ' okumkok , kite ' pwe ' ie ' nman Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi caye ' k kaiInIt shi e ' tat ipi mce ' sh ki Kone ' ntie ' n nIshInape ' k kspsItake ' wat kite ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwuk ipi ki kcItapie ' nkaswuk .

text: Then spake the Lord to Paul in the night by a vision , Be not afraid , but speak , and hold not thy peace :
text2: IwcI Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' pkonianuk okiknonan ni PanIn , otI kinaptum , Ke ' ko kwtackIn , kikiton , ke ' kowi co kikitokIn .

text: For I am with thee , and no man shall set on thee to hurt thee : for I have much people in this city .
text2: Nin ke ' ce ' in kuiI ipi cowIiI nInI ke ' ko ktotakwsi , na ’ w e ' wi totakwiIn osam mce ' sh ntInIshInape ' muk shotI ik kcI otanuk .

text: And he continued there a year and six months , teaching the word of God among them .
text2: IwcI shi e ' kiiIt nkot pon ipi nkot watso kisIs , e ' kiknomowat , i Kshe ' mIne ' to kikitowun .

text: And when Gallio was the deputy of Achaia , the Jews made insurrection with one accord against Paul , and brought him to the judgment seat ,
text2: Pic Ke ' nio e ' ie ' okumawut shi E ' kie ' uk icI ki Cwiuk , ki mamwI ne ' ntumwuk kipie ' msou ’ tik e ' kiw otapnawat , ni PanIn , ipi okipie ' nawan shi tpakwnuke ' cipitupwunuk .

text: Saying , This fellow persuadeth men to worship God contrary to the law .
text2: OtI kikItwuk otI nInI wishte ' pman nInwun , e ' winume ' kitowanIt , Kshe ' mIne ' ton , e ' shpwa tpakwnuke ' ikon .

text: And when Paul was now about to open his mouth , Gallio said unto the Jews , If it were a matter of wrong or wicked lewdness , O ye Jews , reason would that I should bear with you :
text2: Pic cI Pan , wawe ' pkakitot Ke ' nio , otI okinan ni CwiIn , kishpIn otI ke ' ko mianuk , tanake ' , kie ' patsowun , O kinwa Cwituk , taowunIt , e ' wpsItonkon .

text: But if it be a question of words and names , and of your law , look ye to it ; for I will be no judge of such matters .
text2: NIshcI tanak ki kitonIn ipi noswunIn , ipi shi ktpakwnuke ' onuwa , kinwa naktu we ' ntumok , CoIn nin nkItpakwnIsin notI ke ' ko .

text: And he drave them from the judgment seat .
text2: IwcI e ' kimiwnashkawat shi tpakwnuke ' cipitupwunuk .

text: Then all the Greeks took Sosthenes , the chief ruler of the synagogue , and beat him before the judgment seat . And Gallio cared for none of those things .
text2: IwcI ki caye ' k , Knikuk nInwuk kiwtapnawan Sostinis , ke ' c nikansIt shi nume ' okumkok , ipi okipsItie ' wawan , shi tpakwnuke ' cipitupwunuk , Ke ' nio cI co oki tpate ' n tusin notI ke ' ko .

text: And Paul after this tarried there yet a good while , and then took his leave of the brethren , and sailed thence into Syria , and with him Priscilla and Aquila ; having shorn his head in Cenchrea : for he had a vow .
text2: Pan cI , otI kashkish otI nomkItnuk kInwe ' shi kiw , icI e ' kinumkawat ni wikane ' iIn , iwcI e ' ki ocIposIt shiw e ' kinashIt Sinie ' uk , ipi okiwice ' okon Pisinie ' , ipi E ' kwine ' , okimoshwan otupinuk , shi SInkniuk , okiwawitma ke ' .

text: And he came to Ephesus , and left them there : but he himself entered into the synagogue , and reasoned with the Jews .
text2: Ipi kipie ' wak shi Ipisus shi cI oki nkInan wincIie ' k , kipitike ' wak shi nume ' okumkok , ipi okikie ' kman ni CwiIn .

text: When they desired him to tarry longer time with them , he consented not ;
text2: IcI shi e ' wiiInIt , e ' kinawat wusimI co okite ' pwe ' twasin .

text: But bade them farewell , saying , I must by all means keep this feast that cometh in Jerusalem : but I will return again unto you , if God will . And he sailed from Ephesus .
text2: OkinumkawancI otI okinan , ninsI we ' we ' nI , nkumicIn wikwtowun ipI waiuk , Cinose ' ne ' muk , nIshcI minI ne ' iap kupie ' naskonum kishpIn Kshe ' mIne ' to ne ' ntuk IwcI shi e ' kiwcI posIt , Ipisuswk .

text: And when he had landed at Caesarea , and gone up , and saluted the church , he went down to Antioch .
text2: IcI kakupat , shi Sisune ' uk , ipi kawu kuke ' nonat ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn , kishie ' wak , E ' ntiakuk .

text: And after he had spent some time there , he departed , and went over all the country of Galatia and Phrygia in order , strengthening all the disciples .
text2: IwcI shi kInwe ' shishI kaiIt , kinmumaci , ipi kishie ' cak , e ' kiwuk , Kne ' shiuk , ipi Pnicie ' uk , iaianke ' , e ' wishke ' ntumoat caye ' k ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn .

text: And a certain Jew named Apollos , born at Alexandria , an eloquent man , and mighty in the scriptures , came to Ephesus .
text2: Ipi nkot Cu E ' panus kishInkaso katshinikIt , shi E ' ne ' kse ' nte ' ne ' uk ke ' ckikitot nInI , ipi kawishkisIt shiw kikitonuk Kshe ' mIne ' to , kipie ' shie ' shi Ipisusuk .

text: This man was instructed in the way of the Lord ; and being fervent in the spirit , he spake and taught diligently the things of the Lord , knowing only the baptism of John .
text2: OtI nInI kiknomowa shi otIne ' ntumwunuk , Kshe ' mIne ' to ; kiminwe ' ose ' shi ocipamuk , oki iactan , ipi kikInomake ' pIne ' , e ' ne ' ntumnIt Kshe ' mIne ' ton , mtIno okike ' ntan , CanIn okIctapie ' nwe ' wun .

text: And he began to speak boldly in the synagogue : whom when Aquila and Priscilla had heard , they took him unto them , and expounded unto him the way of God more perfectly .
text2: IwcI e ' we ' p wishkuknonat shi nume ' okumkok pic E ' kwini ipi Pisine ' kanotwawat okiw tapnawan ipi okikInomowawan , wusimI we ' we ' nI , e ' ne ' ntumnIt Kshe ' mIne ' ton .

text: And when he was disposed to pass into Achaia , the brethren wrote , exhorting the disciples to receive him : who , when he was come , helped them much which had believed through grace :
text2: IwcI e ' kine ' ntuk e ' wishiat shi E ' ke ' ie ' uk , wikane ' iIn kiwnIpie ' ke ' k , e ' wishte ' pmanIt , ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn , e ' wi mnototwanIt , pic ipI pianIt , okikcI nishokmowan ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIt , shuwe ' ncIke ' wun .

text: For he mightily convinced the Jews , and that publickly , shewing by the scriptures that Jesus was Christ .
text2: Ipi okiwishkukie ' kman ni CwiIn , ipi e ' wapituat mIsInukInuk o Cisus oie ' o Knayst .

text: And it came to pass , that , while Apollos was at Corinth , Paul having passed through the upper coasts came to Ephesus : and finding certain disciples ,
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk , E ' panus , e ' ie ' iIt shi Koue ' ntiuk , Pan kapmIcakshkuk , mpIne ' iukwan shiw otukimwak kipie ' wak shi Ipisusuk , okimkawan anIt shi te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn .

text: He said unto them , Have ye received the Holy Ghost since ye believed ? And they said unto him , We have not so much as heard whether there be any Holy Ghost .
text2: OtI cI okinan , KiwtuskowanI o PanakwsIt Cipam , e ' ko te ' pwe ' ie ' ntume ' k ? OtI cI okinawan co su tInankinotake ' simIn e ' wiiIt PanakwsIt Cipam .

text: And he said unto them , Unto what then were ye baptized ? And they said , Unto John ' s baptism .
text2: IwcI otI okinan , We ' kwni nukwe ' , kaocI cItapie ' nkoie ' k ? OtI cI okinawan , CansI okIctapie ' nwe ' onuk ;

text: Then said Paul , John verily baptized with the baptism of repentance , saying unto the people , that they should believe on him which should come after him , that is , on Christ Jesus .
text2: OtI cI kikIto Pan , Can , we ' we ' nI kikcI tapie ' nkowa shi kcItapie ' nwe ' onuk , e ' kisate ' ntumuk otI okinan , ni nIshInape ' n , e ' wi te ' pwe ' ie ' nmanIt ni shkwe ' iak wapie ' tnIsnIncIn niw cI ie ' ni Knayst CisusIn .

text: When they heard this , they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus .
text2: Pic cI kanotmoat otI , kikcItapie ' nkaswuk shiw tInoswunuk Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus .

text: And when Paul had laid his hands upon them , the Holy Ghost came on them ; and they spake with tongues , and prophesied .
text2: Pic cI Pan ka ’ tot niw onIce ' n shi wiwunuk , PanakwsIt Cipam okipkIshnotakwan , ipi papkankishu kikitok , e ' iacimoat .

text: And all the men were about twelve .
text2: MtatsoshItInish , ki caye ' k nInwuk , kitshik .

text: And he went into the synagogue , and spake boldly for the space of three months , disputing and persuading the things concerning the kingdom of God .
text2: IwcI e ' kipitike ' t shi nume ' okumkok , nso kisIs kiwishkukie ' kwe ' , e ' wishte ' pmat , ipi e ' tshItuk ni ke ' ko shi otokumauwunuk Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: But when divers were hardened , and believed not , but spake evil of that way before the multitude , he departed from them , and separated the disciples , disputing daily in the school of one Tyrannus .
text2: Pic cI anIt kawishkite ' awat , ipi kapwa te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIt , nIshcI e ' ki mcI tshItmoat iw ni maoce ' tincIn , shiw kiwcImaci e ' kinkInat , ipi e ' kipapke ' pnat ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn , ipi e ' ki iakwne ' twat e ' tso kishkuk , shi Tayne ' nusIn , e ' tshI kno make ' nIt .

text: And this continued by the space of two years ; so that all they which dwelt in Asia heard the word of the Lord Jesus , both Jews and Greeks .
text2: IwsI otI pIne ' , katotuk nishpon , icI ki caye ' k kaie ' cuk shi E ' shiuk , okinotanawa okikitowun Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus , ne ' ne ' ish Cwiuk ipi knikuk , nIshInape ' k .

text: And God wrought special miracles by the hands of Paul :
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to cI kimataonInkie ' , shiw onIcinuk ni PanIn .

text: So that from his body were brought unto the sick handkerchiefs or aprons , and the diseases departed from them , and the evil spirits went out of them .
text2: Shi cI owiiwuk otocmacitwawan , ni iakwnokancIn moshwe ' iIn , tanake ' , pe ' kanuk kwu ’ wun , icI i otInapne ' onawa ke ' imacimkItnuk , ipi ni mIcImIne ' nton kisakumwun shi wiuwuwak .

text: Then certain of the vagabond Jews , exorcists , took upon them to call over them which had evil spirits the name of the Lord Jesus , saying , We adjure you by Jesus whom Paul preacheth .
text2: IcI anIt ki ke ' ko pwapite ' ntakwsIcIk Cwiuk , caskie ' cuk , kine ' ntumwuk , e ' wintomawat , kakIshkwanIt , ni mIcIme ' ton , e ' wiwawinawat ni Te ' pe ' nke ' ne ' t CisusIn , otI kikItwuk , ku WitmonmIn shi Cisusuk o Pan we ' ckie ' kwe ' t .

text: And there were seven sons of one Sceva , a Jew , and chief of the priests , which did so .
text2: NonkcI kitshin okwIsIn Sipe ' i , Cwi nInInI , ipi kanikansIt ni me ' matmoncIn iw kanukmuksInIt .

text: And the evil spirit answered and said , Jesus I know , and Paul I know ; but who are ye ?
text2: IwcI o mIcIme ' to okinkwe ' twan ipi otI okinan Cisus sIie ' k nkuke ' nma , ipi Pan , nkuke ' nma , nIshcI we ' ninukcIkinwa ?

text: And the man in whom the evil spirit was leaped on them , and overcame them , and prevailed against them , so that they fled out of that house naked and wounded .
text2: IcI o nInI kakIshkwat , ni mIcIme ' ton okikwashknotwan , ipi okinshiwuan , ipi okiwe ' ctIn shiwan , icI shi kisakitInshumwuk shi wikwamuk , shashakIt , ipi kimiaksik .

text: And this was known to all the Jews and Greeks also dwelling at Ephesus ; and fear fell on them all , and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified .
text2: OtI cI okike ' ntanawa caye ' k , ki Cwiuk ipi Knik , nIshInape ' k , ke ' iapu , katacuk shi Ipisusuk ; ipi caye ' k , kise ' ksik icI otInoswun Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus , kiwinwackate ' ne ' .

text: And many that believed came , and confessed , and shewed their deeds .
text2: Ipi mce ' sh ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk kipie ' k , ipi oki iactanawa , ipi kiwaptawe ' k , kanukmuksowat .

text: Many of them also which used curious arts brought their books together , and burned them before all men : and they counted the price of them , and found it fifty thousand pieces of silver .
text2: Mce ' sh ke ' iapI kiw mataototkuk , okipie ' tonawan , mIsnukInwan , e ' ki msocaksumwat e ' nasmupnIt nInwun ; ipi okiki tanawa e ' pite ' ntakwtInuk , nianomtInI tsuk mtatswak shonia .

text: So mightily grew the word of God and prevailed .
text2: Iw kashu kcI mace ' knInuk Kshe ' mIne ' to okikitowun , ipi kinshiw awe ' mkItnI .

text: After these things were ended , Paul purposed in the spirit , when he had passed through Macedonia and Achaia , to go to Jerusalem , saying , After I have been there , I must also see Rome .
text2: IcI kakish nomkItnuk , Pan kishIte ' ’ e ' ’ shiw Cipamuk , kakish kwe ' pmosatuk Me ' sitonie ' uk , ipi E ' ke ' iuk e ' wshiat shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , otI kikIto shi kishie ' ian ke ' iapI nkowaptan Nom .

text: So he sent into Macedonia two of them that ministered unto him , Timotheus and Erastus ; but he himself stayed in Asia for a season .
text2: Okinokanan cI , ipI Me ' sitoniuk , nish ni kapmitakwcIn , Timotius , ipi Ine ' stus , nIshcI win shi kiuwak , nomuk ; shi E ' shie ' uk .

text: And the same time there arose no small stir about that way .
text2: IwcI i pic ; okik cI cshItanawa i totmowun .

text: For a certain man named Demetrius , a silversmith , which made silver shrines for Diana , brought no small gain unto the craftsmen ;
text2: Osam nkot nInI KishInkaso Timitinus shwaniake ' t , kaoshItwat shonia mkukwe ' n , ni Taye ' niIn , okikshkIton mce ' sh e ' ki pie ' twat ni , shonia mikce ' winInwun .

text: Whom he called together with the workmen of like occupation , and said , Sirs , ye know that by this craft we have our wealth .
text2: Okimaosoman ni , shwaniake ' ncIn , kashu ie ' i mikce ' winIt , otI okinan , Nikantuk , kuke ' ntanawa , otI e ' shmikce ' wikon we ' c tpInwe ' ose ' ikon .

text: Moreover ye see and hear , that not alone at Ephesus , but almost throughout all Asia , this Paul hath persuaded and turned away much people , saying that they be no gods , which are made with hands :
text2: Ke ' iapukI kinwa kowaptanawa , ipi kinotanawa , comtIno , ipI Ipisusuk , kakake ' shi caye ' k E ' shiie ' uk , otI Pan , okiwishte ' pman , ipi okikwe ' knan mce ' sh nIshInape ' n , otI okinan Cowi ki Kshe ' mIne ' tok , winwa kaoshIckascuk onIcimak - e ' iok .

text: So that not only this our craft is in danger to be set at nought ; but also that the temple of the great goddess Diana should be despised , and her magnificence should be destroyed , whom all Asia and the world worshippeth .
text2: Coike ' otI mtIno , kmikce ' wiwunInan , nie ' sansInon , e ' wi we ' pnukate ' k , iwkwshu ke ' ke ' iapI otInume ' okumkom , kcImIne ' to Taye ' ne ' , e ' wi shi ke ' ncIkate ' k , ipi i okIcne ' ntakwsuwun , kupinacIkate ' caye ' k E ' shie ' uk , ipi kik , e ' nume ' kitakwcIn .

text: And when they heard these sayings , they were full of wrath , and cried out , saying , Great is Diana of the Ephesians .
text2: Pic cI otI kanotmowat ; notI kItwunIn , kimoshkIne ' nshkatsik , ipi kinotakwsik , otI kikItwuk , Ke ' cpite ' ntakwsIt , Taye ' ne ' , te ' pe ' n mukot IpisusIn nIshInape ' n .

text: And the whole city was filled with confusion : and having caught Gaius and Aristarchus , men of Macedonia , Paul ' s companions in travel , they rushed with one accord into the theatre .
text2: Ipi i caye ' k kcI otan , kimoshkIne ' wishkwe ' we ' kIt , ipi kamIshInawat Ke ' usIn , ipi , E ' nistakusIn , Me ' sitoni nInwuk , Pan kapmIwice ' wacIn e ' pamatsIt , kimso pitike ' ptok shi ke ' ko e ' tshI waptuwe ' k .

text: And when Paul would have entered in unto the people , the disciples suffered him not .
text2: Pic cI Pan , e ' wipitike ' ntuwat , ni nIshInape ' n ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn cokipkItnukwsin ;

text: And certain of the chief of Asia , which were his friends , sent unto him , desiring him that he would not adventure himself into the theatre .
text2: Ipi anIt kiwokumak , shiw E ' shie ' uk , ka wikanmacIn , kinokashwe ' k , e ' nawat e ' wipwa kwcI pitike ' nIt shi e ' tshI ke ' ko wapituwe ' k .

text: Some therefore cried one thing , and some another : for the assembly was confused ; and the more part knew not wherefore they were come together .
text2: AnIt ke ' aiapIn kishInotakwsik , anIt ke ' papkan , osam ki maoce ' ticIk kiwishkwe ' we ' ksik , wusimI kimane ' k , ki kapwa kuke ' ntukuk kaocI maotoshnowat .

text: And they drew Alexander out of the multitude , the Jews putting him forward . And Alexander beckoned with the hand , and would have made his defence unto the people .
text2: KicI Cwiuk , kipie ' sakconawan E ' nikse ' nte ' In , shi e ' tshI maoce ' tiwat , E ' nikse ' nte ' , cI okiiainInkawan , ni nIshInape ' n ipi takiknotmatso .

text: But when they knew that he was a Jew , all with one voice about the space of two hours cried out , Great is Diana of the Ephesians .
text2: IcI kake ' nmawat , e ' Cwi nInwunIt , caye ' k kimsonotaksik , e ' pite ' ntakwuk nish tpukIn , KcIpite ' ntakwsI Taye ' ne ' , Te ' pe ' nmukot IpisusIn nIshInape ' n .

text: And when the townclerk had appeased the people , he said , Ye men of Ephesus , what man is there that knoweth not how that the city of the Ephesians is a worshipper of the great goddess Diana , and of the image which fell down from Jupiter ?
text2: Pic cI o we ' npie ' ke ' t shi otanuk katokmupat ni nIshInape ' n , otI okinan tshI nInituk Ipisus , We ' nice ' nInI pwake ' ntuk okIc otanmowa , ki IpsisusIn nIshInape ' k , e ' nume ' kituwat ni kcI Taye ' ne ' In , ipi i we ' npie ' kate ' k , kaocI pmukocuk , shi Cwpite ' uk .

text: Seeing then that these things cannot be spoken against , ye ought to be quiet , and to do nothing rashly .
text2: Osam cI notI , ke ' ko co ke ' ko tanIshIckate ' snon tokum ktaium , ipi kie ' nup ke ' ko e ' wi pwatotme ' k .

text: For ye have brought hither these men , which are neither robbers of churches , nor yet blasphemers of your goddess .
text2: Osam kote ' kipie ' nawak nInwuk , ktInie ' me ' okumkomwak , pwakmocuk , coke ' otumcIcshumasiwan ni kimintomwan .

text: Wherefore if Demetrius , and the craftsmen which are with him , have a matter against any man , the law is open , and there are deputies : let them implead one another .
text2: IwsI ie ' i otI , kishpIn Timitius ipi ki mikce ' winInwuk , ni pe ' mwice ' kocIn , ke ' konInmawat wIiI nInwun , tpakwnuke ' wun nsakwsun , ipi ik tpakwnuke ' nInwuk , nocma winwa ke ' tpakwnItwuk .

text: But if ye inquire any thing concerning other matters , it shall be determined in a lawful assembly .
text2: KishpIn cI e ' k , ke ' ko pe ' kanuk witshItme ' k , kiac cI kate ' , shi tpakwnuke ' wunuk .

text: For we are in danger to be called in question for this day ' s uproar , there being no cause whereby we may give an account of this concourse .
text2: Osam knInie ' sansImIn , e ' witpakwnukoikon otI nkom e ' kishkiwuk e ' kiwishkwe ' we ' kuk co ke ' ko kukItsimIn otI we ' cmaoce ' tikon .

text: And when he had thus spoken , he dismissed the assembly .
text2: IcI otI kakishkItot , okisakitInan ni maoce ' tincIn .

text: And after the uproar was ceased , Paul called unto him the disciples , and embraced them , and departed for to go into Macedonia .
text2: IcI kakish wishkwe ' we ' kuk Pan okintoman ni te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn , ipi okinumkowan , icI e ' kinmumacit e ' wishiat Me ' sitoniuk .

text: And when he had gone over those parts , and had given them much exhortation , he came into Greece ,
text2: IcI kakish pe ' nIcakshkuk , shi , ipi kapmI kcIwishte ' pmat , kipie ' shie ' Knisuk ;

text: And there abode three months . And when the Jews laid wait for him , as he was about to sail into Syria , he purposed to return through Macedonia .
text2: ShicI kiiI nso kisIs . IcI ki Cwiuk e ' kuwapmawat pic wanashnIt , shi Sinie ' uk , kie ' ntum e ' wi shukiwe ' t , e ' winmIshiat Me ' sitoniuk .

text: And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea ; and of the Thessalonians , Aristarchus and Secundus ; and Gaius of Derbe , and Timotheus ; and of Asia , Tychicus and Trophimus .
text2: IcI okishIwice ' okon shi E ' shie ' uk , Sope ' te ' Pinie ' nInI , ipi E ' nIstakus ipi Sikuntus Te ' sinoni nInwuk , ipi Ke ' us ipi Timotius , Te ' pie ' nInwuk , ipi TaycIkus Topimus E ' shie ' nInwuk .

text: These going before tarried for us at Troas .
text2: KotIcI kinmInikanik , nkipwikonanuk , shi Toe ' suk .

text: And we sailed away from Philippi after the days of unleavened bread , and came unto them to Troas in five days ; where we abode seven days .
text2: Nkiw cI mace ' iashmIn shi Pinipayuk kakishkishkiwuk , pwaopce ' te ' k pkwe ' shkIn , icI kanianokwnukuk nkipie ' otIsamIn shi Toe ' suk shicI nkiiImIn nouktsokwun .

text: And upon the first day of the week , when the disciples came together to break bread , Paul preached unto them , ready to depart on the morrow ; and continued his speech until midnight .
text2: IcI ine ' tum e ' kishkwuk shi wik , pic ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , kamaoce ' tiwat e ' wi pikuptowat pkwe ' shkIn , Pan , okikie ' kman e ' wshInwit , wapuk e ' wimacit , icI oki knonan nash apitI tpukitInuk .

text: And there were many lights in the upper chamber , where they were gathered together .
text2: Ipi shi kimane ' nI waskone ' ncukInIn shi shpumuk wikwamuk , katshI maoce ' tiwat .

text: And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus , being fallen into a deep sleep : and as Paul was long preaching , he sunk down with sleep , and fell down from the third loft , and was taken up dead .
text2: IcI shi nkot , kicipitupI , e ' cI wase ' ckIn kate ' nuk , oshkInwe ' Iwtaykus kishInkaso kikcIn pe ' , icI Pan kInwe ' sh e ' kie ' kwe ' t kipmukocIn e ' ie ' npat , nsuk e ' pitokInIkate ' k shi shpumuk kiwtukocIn , ipi kiw tapInukaso e ' upot .

text: And Paul went down , and fell on him , and embracing him said , Trouble not yourselves ; for his life is in him .
text2: IcI Pan e ' kinisasit , ipi wiwunuk kipukshIn , icI e ' ki iakce ' nat , otI cI kikIto ; ke ' ka mkoshkate ' ntuke ' k , opmatsiwun shi me ' kwate ' nI .

text: When he therefore was come up again , and had broken bread , and eaten , and talked a long while , even till break of day , so he departed .
text2: IcI minI kapie ' kwutasit , ipi kapikupitot i pkwe ' shkIn , ipi kawisnIt , ipi kIn we ' sh kakakikitot nash e ' wase ' apnInuk , icI e ' ki macit .

text: And they brought the young man alive , and were not a little comforted .
text2: IcI okipie ' nawan niw oshkInwe ' n e ' pmatsInIt , kikcI mciwe ' nmokcI .

text: And we went before to ship , and sailed unto Assos , there intending to take in Paul : for so had he appointed , minding himself to go afoot .
text2: IcI ninan nkinikanimIn , e ' ki shiaiak , napkwanuk , ipi nkinashmIn E ' susuk , nkine ' ntamIn shi e ' wi otapnukIt , Pan iw kashumiImIt , kine ' ntum win swipmose ' t .

text: And when he met with us at Assos , we took him in , and came to Mitylene .
text2: IcI kankwe ' shkwukIt , shi E ' susuk nkipo samIn , ipi nkipiamIn shi Maytiniuk ;

text: And we sailed thence , and came the next day over against Chios ; and the next day we arrived at Samos , and tarried at Trogyllium ; and the next day we came to Miletus .
text2: ShicI nkiwcI macimIn , nki nashmIn icI wiapuk nkikpamIn shi Kayasuk , icI minI wiapuk nkipiamIn shi Se ' masuk nkiiImIn cI shi Tnociniumuk , icI minI iapuk nkipiamIn shi Minitiusuk .

text: For Paul had determined to sail by Ephesus , because he would not spend the time in Asia : for he hasted , if it were possible for him , to be at Jerusalem the day of Pentecost .
text2: Pan kine ' ntum e ' winashIt cikiiIkwan Ipisusuk , osam co kine ' ntusi shi e ' wiIt E ' shie ' uk , kiwe ' witpIshke ' , shi e ' wi te ' piat shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , pic e ' wiwikwtowut .

text: And from Miletus he sent to Ephesus , and called the elders of the church .
text2: Minitusuk cI nokashwe ' e ' wishianIt ipI Ipisusuk , e ' ntomat ni onikansimwan ki te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk .

text: And when they were come to him , he said unto them , Ye know , from the first day that I came into Asia , after what manner I have been with you at all seasons ,
text2: IcI kapiawat otI okinan , Kuke ' ntanawa , pic e ' wshkukishkuk , kapie ' naskonkon shi E ' shie ' uk , kashuwe ' psian , pIne ' , e ' kowicInkon .

text: Serving the Lord with all humility of mind , and with many tears , and temptations , which befell me by the lying in wait of the Jews :
text2: E ' shpmitwuk Kshe ' mIne ' to e ' pwakcIne ' ntuman miia ’ w , ipi mce ' sh moawun , ipi kwcItupe ' ntuwun iw kaocI showe ' psian e ' kikawapmIwat ki Cwiuk .

text: And how I kept back nothing that was profitable unto you , but have shewed you , and have taught you publickly , and from house to house ,
text2: Ipi kapwashu , ke ' ko kiatmonkon , tao cI ke ' koie ' ie ' k ; kiwaptInum , ipi kiknomonum e ' cI wapcIkate ' k iaianke ' wikwamuk .

text: Testifying both to the Jews , and also to the Greeks , repentance toward God , and faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ .
text2: E ' kie ' kmukwa ki Cwiuk , ipi ke ' iapI ki Knik nIshInape ' k , kisate ' ntumwun e ' wi ne ' nmukon Kshe ' mIne ' to ipi e ' wi te ' pwe ' ie ' nmukon Te ' pe ' nmukwiukon Cisus Knayst .

text: And now , behold , I go bound in the spirit unto Jerusalem , not knowing the things that shall befall me there :
text2: Ipi nkom pInI , ntusha , tkopso ncipam shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , co nkuke ' ntusin ke ' shu we ' psowane ' n shi :

text: Save that the Holy Ghost witnesseth in every city , saying that bonds and afflictions abide me .
text2: NIshcie ' k PanakwsIt Cipam , witmake ' , shi e ' tso kcI otanwuk , tkopsowunIn , ipi kwtukitowunIn ntupwiikon .

text: But none of these things move me , neither count I my life dear unto myself , so that I might finish my course with joy , and the ministry , which I have received of the Lord Jesus , to testify the gospel of the grace of God .
text2: NIshcI co ke ' ko notI mpupame ' ntusin , coke ' ke ' ko npumatsuwun ntupite ' ntusin , iw mtIno e ' wipon mikce ' wian mnowan kosian , ipi i pmitake ' wun kamishIt , Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus e ' wiwitmake ' ian , omIn wacmonuk iw shuwe ' ncIke ' wun Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: And now , behold , I know that ye all , among whom I have gone preaching the kingdom of God , shall see my face no more .
text2: Ipi nkom pInI , nkuke ' ntan kinwa caye ' k kapmImnwactumonkon iw otoku mauwun Kshe ' mIne ' to , co minI kawapmIsim .

text: Wherefore I take you to record this day , that I am pure from the blood of all men .
text2: OtI cI ie ' i , we ' cotapinInkon , otI e ' kishkiwuk e ' wi ke ' ntme ' k , e ' pinakwse ' ian nInwuk omuskwimwan .

text: For I have not shunned to declare unto you all the counsel of God .
text2: Co nkipontosin e ' witmonkon caye ' k Kshe ' mIne ' to otIne ' ntumwun .

text: Take heed therefore unto yourselves , and to all the flock , over the which the Holy Ghost hath made you overseers , to feed the church of God , which he hath purchased with his own blood .
text2: Ikwame ' ntumok , kiiwuwa , ipi caye ' k ki kumsawe ' , o PanakwsIt Cipam , kaoshukoie ' k e ' wikuwapme ' k ; e ' wipmIshIme ' k , te ' pwe ' ie ' nmacuk , Kshe ' mIne ' ton win tpInwe ' omIskwim kaocI kshkaacIn .

text: For I know this , that after my departing shall grievous wolves enter in among you , not sparing the flock .
text2: Osam otI nkuke ' ntan , kikish mumacian , shake ' ntakse ' cIk moe ' k , okupitike ' ntawawan , cokuponikwasiwawan ni me ' ’ sotincin .

text: Also of your own selves shall men arise , speaking perverse things , to draw away disciples after them .
text2: Ke ' iapI ke ' kinwa tpInwe ' nInwuk kupsukwik ; kumcIkikitok , e ' wi wikpInawat te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumnIncIn .

text: Therefore watch , and remember , that by the space of three years I ceased not to warn every one night and day with tears .
text2: IwsI ie ' i otI , kuwapuk , ipi nakutuwe ' n tmok , e ' konsoponkuk , conki ponwitmoasik e ' tshuwat e ' tso pkoniak , ipi e ' tso kishkuk , e ' mwoian .

text: And now , brethren , I commend you to God , and to the word of his grace , which is able to build you up , and to give you an inheritance among all them which are sanctified .
text2: Ipi nkom nikane ' ituk , nminakiiIwuwa Kshe ' mIne ' to , shi ntInume ' onuk . ipi shi okikitonuk oshuwe ' ncuke ' onuk , ie ' i takshkukoie ' k , e ' wipsukwitnukwie ' k ipi e ' wiminkoiak te ' pe ' ntukuk , e ' ciiuwat ki caye ' k panakwcIkascuk .

text: I have coveted no man ' s silver , or gold , or apparel .
text2: Co nItwe ' ntumwasi wIiI nInI oshoniaum , tanake ' osaw shoniaiIm tanake ' otukwIn .

text: Yea , ye yourselves know , that these hands have ministered unto my necessities , and to them that were with me .
text2: Kinwa , tpInwe ' , kuke ' ntanawa , notI nIce ' n , ne ' twe ' ntuman nkipmitakwnIn , ipi kiw kapmI wice ' ocuk .

text: I have shewed you all things , how that so labouring ye ought to support the weak , and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus , how he said , It is more blessed to give than to receive .
text2: Cake ' ko , kiwapte ' ’ num , otI e ' shu mikce ' wik , washu nishokmoe ' k ki ne ' ninwuscuk , ipi e ' wi naktIwe ' ntumwe ' k okikitonIn Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus , e ' kikItot . wusimI shuwe ' ntakwsowun , i e ' wimikwak icI e ' wiwtapnmuk .

text: And when he had thus spoken , he kneeled down , and prayed with them all .
text2: Pic cI i kakish kItot kiIwucikwnIshIn ipi caye ' k kiwic nume ' ’ k .

text: And they all wept sore , and fell on Paul ' s neck , and kissed him ,
text2: IcI caye ' k kikcumwik ; ipi kipmukocnok , shiw kwe ' knanuk , ni PanIn , ipi okiwce ' mawan .

text: Sorrowing most of all for the words which he spake , that they should see his face no more . And they accompanied him unto the ship .
text2: WusimI i kaocI kisate ' ntumwat , i e ' kikitnIt cominI kawapmIsim . IcI ipI napkwanuk e ' kishuwic wawat .

text: And it came to pass , that after we were gotten from them , and had launched , we came with a straight course unto Coos , and the day following unto Rhodes , and from thence unto Patara :
text2: OtIcI , kanomkuk , icI kankInkIt , ipi kawe ' pshkaiak , tpasu nkishiamIn shi Ko - osuk icI wiapuk nkipiamIn Nots - uk , icI shi nkiwcI macimIn icI nkipiamIncI shi Pe ' te ' ne ' uk .

text: And finding a ship sailing over unto Phenicia , we went aboard , and set forth .
text2: IcI kamkumak napkwan , e ' nasuk , ipI Pinisie ' uk , nkiposmIn , ipi nkinmacimIn .

text: Now when we had discovered Cyprus , we left it on the left hand , and sailed into Syria , and landed at Tyre : for there the ship was to unlade her burden .
text2: IcI kawaptumak , Saypnusuk , onum ciwnak nkishInkItamIn , ipi nkinashmIn shi Sinie ' uk , ipi nkikpamIn shi Tayniuk , shi wie ' shi wacukwasnaswat i napkwan .

text: And finding disciples , we tarried there seven days : who said to Paul through the Spirit , that he should not go up to Jerusalem .
text2: NkimkowamIncIshi te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , nkiiImIn shi nouktsokwun , okinawan shiw Cipamwak ni PanIn , e ' wipwa shi auIt shi Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: And when we had accomplished those days , we departed and went our way ; and they all brought us on our way , with wives and children , till we were out of the city : and we kneeled down on the shore , and prayed .
text2: Pic cI kate ' psak notI e ' kishkiwuk nkinmacimIn , ipi caye ' k , nkiwice ' okonanuk nike ' owiuwan , ipi otupnoce ' imowan , nash kanmIsakumak , shi kcI - otanuk , icI nkiuwucikwnIshnImIn shi cik kcukumik , ipi nkinumamIn .

text: And when we had taken our leave one of another , we took ship ; and they returned home again .
text2: Pic cI kakishnumkokIt , nkiposmIn shi napkwanuk , icI ke ' winwa minI kikiwe ' k .

text: And when we had finished our course from Tyre , we came to Ptolemais , and saluted the brethren , and abode with them one day .
text2: KaocIpiaiak , cI shi Tayniuk nkipie ' shiamIn shi Ptonimiusuk ipi nkinumkuwamIn kiwnikane ' inanuk , ipi shi nkotkon nkiiImIn .

text: And the next day we that were of Paul ' s company departed , and came unto Caesarea : and we entered into the house of Philip the evangelist , which was one of the seven ; and abode with him .
text2: IcI iwiapuk ninan kapmI wice ' okIt Pan , nkimacimIn , ipi nkipaimIk shi Sisinie ' uk nkipitike ' mIn e ' tat Pinip , ke ' kie ' kwe ' t , win o nkot nouk ke ' tshIcuk , ipi nkiwicamIn .

text: And the same man had four daughters , virgins , which did prophesy .
text2: WincI o nInI kinie ' win ote ' nsIn ki kikiak win , kiiacimok .

text: And as we tarried there many days , there came down from Judaea a certain prophet , named Agabus .
text2: Shice ' nkiwmIn onatsokwIn kiwcI pie ' wak Cwtie ' uk , nkot Nakanacimot , E ' ke ' pus kishInkaso .

text: And when he was come unto us , he took Paul ' s girdle , and bound his own hands and feet , and said , Thus saith the Holy Ghost , So shall the Jews at Jerusalem bind the man that owneth this girdle , and shall deliver him into the hands of the Gentiles .
text2: Pic kaotIsiImIt okiwtapnumwan okIcipsownInIn PanIn , icI e ' kitkop tot , niw onIce ' n ipi osIte ' n , otI cI kikito ; otIsI e ' kitot , PanakwsIt Cipam i ke ' totwawat ki Cwiuk okItkopnawan ni nInwun te ' pe ' ntumnIt otI kcipsowun , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi okupkItnumwawan wia ’ w shiw onIc inuk , ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn .

text: And when we heard these things , both we , and they of that place , besought him not to go up to Jerusalem .
text2: Pic cI otI kanotmak notI , ne ' ne ' ish ninan , ipi ki shi kaie ' cuk ; nkiwishte ' pmamIn e ' wi pwashiat sho Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: Then Paul answered , What mean ye to weep and to break mine heart ? for I am ready not to be bound only , but also to die at Jerusalem for the name of the Lord Jesus .
text2: Pe ' n cI otI okinan , TacI we ' cmwoie ' k ipi e ' wi pkIshke ' ntumo ’ ie ' k ? CoIn mtIno nkishe ' wisi e ' wi tkopsoian mtIno ke ' iapIsuke ' e ' wi npoian ipI Cinose ' ne ' muk , win shiw otIuoswunuk Te ' pe ' nke ' t Cisus .

text: And when he would not be persuaded , we ceased , saying , The will of the Lord be done .
text2: Pic cI kapwak shkumkIt nkiponmamIn otI nkikItmIn , OtIne ' n tumwun Kshe ' mIne ' to knomkItne ' .

text: And after those days we took up our carriages , and went up to Jerusalem .
text2: IcI notI kakish kishkiwuk nkimacinamIn ntotapiananuk icI e ' kishiaiak Ii Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: There went with us also certain of the disciples of Caesarea , and brought with them one Mnason of Cyprus , an old disciple , with whom we should lodge .
text2: Ipi anIt nkiwice ' okonanuk , te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , shi sisine ' uk , ipi nkot kipie ' nawan , Me ' nsun , Saypnus nInI , kowe ' si te ' pwe ' ie ' ntuk , win o e ' wiwicukIt .

text: And when we were come to Jerusalem , the brethren received us gladly .
text2: Pic cI kapiaiak shi Cinose ' ne ' muk nikane ' inanuk , kinciwe ' nmok e ' kiwapme ' ie ' nIt .

text: And the day following Paul went in with us unto James ; and all the elders were present .
text2: IcI i wiapuk Pan , nkiwice ' okonan , Ce ' ms e ' ciIt , ipi caye ' k ki nakanse ' cIk shi kiik .

text: And when he had saluted them , he declared particularly what things God had wrought among the Gentiles by his ministry .
text2: IcI kakish numkaokIt , nkiwike ' witmaknan , Kshe ' mIne ' ton kashu mwuntmakot , shi e ' ciiInIt Me ' ikIsnIncIn shiw okukie ' kwe ' wunuk .

text: And when they heard it , they glorified the Lord , and said unto him , Thou seest , brother , how many thousands of Jews there are which believe ; and they are all zealous of the law :
text2: Pic cI otI kanotmowat , okowinwanawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi otI , okinawan Kowapitan , nikane ' , tsuk mtatswak Cwiuk , te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , ipi caye ' k pupame ' ntanawa i tpakwnuke ' wun .

text: And they are informed of thee , that thou teachest all the Jews which are among the Gentiles to forsake Moses , saying that they ought not to circumcise their children , neither to walk after the customs .
text2: Kinotake ' ksI kin e ' knomotwa , caye ' k ki Cwiuk , wawiakshkuwacuk , ki me ' ikIscIk , awinkInawat MosusIn otI kikIt awipwa tpakwnawat niw nicansawan e ' wipwake ' naksuwapitumwat ni ototmonuwan .

text: What is it therefore ? the multitude must needs come together : for they will hear that thou art come .
text2: We ' kwnicI otI , taocI nomkuk ? ki nIshInape ' k , kumaotoshnok , osam kInotake ' k e ' kipian .

text: Do therefore this that we say to thee : We have four men which have a vow on them ;
text2: OtI cI ie ' i , ke ' ocI totmIn , nie ' w nInwuk shotI ntIiwamIn , kawawitmake ' cuk .

text: Them take , and purify thyself with them , and be at charges with them , that they may shave their heads : and all may know that those things , whereof they were informed concerning thee , are nothing ; but that thou thyself also walkest orderly , and keepest the law .
text2: OtapIn ki , ipi pinakwton kia ' w ipi winwa , ipi tpI ’ In anIt ke ' pite ' n takwuk , iw ke ' ocI moshmowat niw otupi wan , ipi caye ' k e ' wike ' n . tumwat kashu notake ' wat , i e ' kikon coke ' ko pite ' ntakwsInon iw kaocI ke ' ntumwat kwiuk e ' shuwe ' psin , ipi e ' naktuwe ' ntumIn , i tpakwnuke ' wun .

text: As touching the Gentiles which believe , we have written and concluded that they observe no such thing , save only that they keep themselves from things offered to idols , and from blood , and from strangled , and from fornication .
text2: Kiw cI wi Me ' ikIscIk , te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk nkiwnIpie ' mowamIn ipi nkine ' ntamIn e ' wi pwa naktowe ' ntumwat notI ke ' ko , mtInoie ' k , e ' wikokatowat wiuwawa kamontwa ki mIntokasnIncIn , ipi mskwI , ipi ke ' ko ke ' pne ' we ' shkanuk , ipi pshukwatsowun .

text: Then Paul took the men , and the next day purifying himself with them entered into the temple , to signify the accomplishment of the days of purifcation , until that an offering should be offered for every one of them .
text2: IwcI Pan ki e ' kiwtapnat ni nInwun icI wiapuk e ' ki pinakwtot i wiia ’ w ipi ni icI e ' kipitike ' wat shi nume ' okumkok , e ' wiwaptowe ' wat e ' caksanuk nie ' kishkiwuk shi pinakwItsowunuk , nashcI mikwe ' wun , e ' tshowat e ' wimintwa .

text: And when the seven days were almost ended , the Jews which were of Asia , when they saw him in the temple , stirred up all the people , and laid hands on him ,
text2: Pic cI kaka e ' nouk tsokwnuke ' tInuk Ki Cwiuk , kaocI piacuk , E ' shie ' uk , kawapmawat shi nume ' okumkok , okiwpwe ' mawan ni nIshInape ' n , icI e ' kiw tapnawat .

text: Crying out , Men of Israel , help : This is the man , that teacheth all men every where against the people , and the law , and this place : and further brought Greeks also into the temple , and hath polluted this holy place .
text2: Kinotakwsik , IsniIn tshI nInituk nishokmoshInak . OtI ie ' i nInI , ke ' knomowat caye ' k nInwun , caknkoci e ' winshke ' nmanIt ni nIshInape ' n ipi i tpakwnuke ' wun , ipi otI nume ' okumuk , ipi wusimI okipie ' nan Knik , nIshInape ' n ke ' iapI shotI nume ' okumkok , ipi okiw winakwton otI panakwuk nume ' okumuk .

text: ( For they had seen before with him in the city Trophimus an Ephesian , whom they supposed that Paul had brought into the temple . )
text2: Osam kiwapmawan oshkIca , e ' pmowice ' wanIt shi kcI otanuk , TopimusIn , Ipisusuk nInI , okine ' nmawan ni PanIn , e ' kipitike ' nanIt shi nume ' okumkok .

text: And all the city was moved , and the people ran together : and they took Paul , and drew him out of the temple : and forthwith the doors were shut .
text2: IcI caye ' kshi kcI otanuk , kimatIn , icI ki nIshInape ' k , kimsowe ' pik , ipi okiw tapnawan PanIn , ipi oki sakite ' nawan shi nume ' okumkok . IcI kie ' nup e ' ki kpakw ’ umwat ni shkwate ' me ' n .

text: And as they went about to kill him , tidings came unto the chief captain of the band , that all Jerusalem was in an uproar .
text2: Me ' kwacI e ' ie ' tnInkowat e ' winsawat kikitowun , kipie ' twa okcI Kapte ' nmowan ki shumaknIshuk , shi caye ' k Cinose ' ne ' muk e ' wishkwe ' we ' ktInuk .

text: Who immediately took soldiers and centurions , and ran down unto them : and when they saw the chief captain and the soldiers , they left beating of Paul .
text2: Win kie ' nup kimacinan , shumaknIshIn ipi kapte ' nIn , icI ipI e ' kipItowat . Pic cI ki kawapmawat ni kcI Kapte ' nIn , ipi shumaknIshIn okipon psItie ' wawan ni PanIn .

text: Then the chief captain came near , and took him , and commanded him to be bound with two chains ; and demanded who he was , and what he had done .
text2: IcI o kcI Kapte ' n pe ' shoc kipie ' , ipi okiwtapnan kishuwe ' e ' witkopcIkasnIt nish piwapkwe ' n , ipi kinatake ' , We ' kwe ' ntuk ni , ipi we ' kwe ' nshutuk katotmokwe ' n .

text: And some cried one thing , some another , among the multitude : and when he could not know the certainty for the tumult , he commanded him to be carried into the castle .
text2: AnIt cI , kako kikItwuk , anIt kI pkan kikItwuk , kiw maoce ' ticIk , picI we ' we ' nI , e ' pwake ' ntuk , osam i e ' wishkwe ' we ' ksInIt kishuwe ' , e ' wishao ’ cukasnIt shi wakakInuk .

text: And when he came upon the stairs , so it was , that he was borne of the soldiers for the violence of the people .
text2: IcI kapiawat shi e ' kwkwItasiwunukate ' nuk okipmanukon ni shumakInIshIn osam e ' puksukwtatwat ki nIshInape ' k .

text: For the multitude of the people followed after , crying , Away with him .
text2: Osamki maoce ' ticIk nIshInape ' k oki pmnashkakon kinanotakwsik ; Maciwnuk .

text: And as Paul was to be led into the castle , he said unto the chief captain , May I speak unto thee ? Who said , Canst thou speak Greek ?
text2: Pan cI o Wapitike ' nIt shi wakakInuk , otI oki nan ni kcI Kapte ' nIn , Kta pkIte ' numnI e ' wiknonan ? wincI otI okinan , ktanI ’ kikItnI Knikuk e ' shumwat ?

text: Art not thou that Egyptian , which before these days madest an uproar , and leddest out into the wilderness four thousand men that were murderers ?
text2: ConI kin o Iciptuk nInI , otI e ' pwamshu picak , kawishkwe ' we ' kitot , ipi nie ' wuk mtat swak nInwun kashuonat shi na ’ wmtukwakik kanshowe ' cuk .

text: But Paul said , I am a man which am a Jew of Tarsus , a city in Cilicia , a citizen of no mean city : and , I beseech thee , suffer me to speak unto the people .
text2: Pan cI otI kikito ; Nin sI Cwi nInI nkitshInik shi Tasusuk , kcI otanuk shi Sinishie ' uk , e ' kiwuk , ntoc pia e ' cI pwa na ’ wne ' ntakwuk kcI otan , kumumatmIn e ' wipkIte ' nmin e ' wiknonkwa kotI nIshInape ' k .

text: And when he had given him licence , Paul stood on the stairs , and beckoned with the hand unto the people . And when there was made a great silence , he spake unto them in the Hebrew tongue , saying ,
text2: Pic cI kapkIte ' ‘ nmat , Pan kinipwI shi e ' kwtasiwnukate ' nuk , ipi okiaine ' nkowan ni nIshInape ' n , pic cI kakcItokmIte ' nuk , okiknonan , Ipnoiun , e ' shumnIt , OtI kikItwak .

text: Men , brethren , and fathers , hear ye my defence which I make now unto you .
text2: NInituk , nikane ' ituk , ipi Nose ' ituk ; psItumok , wanInkon e ' winatmatsoian .

text: ( And when they heard that he spake in the Hebrew tongue to them , they kept the more silence : and he saith , )
text2: ( Pic cI kanotwawat e ' kikitonIt , e ' shumnIt ni Ipnoiun , wusimI tokum kiik icI otI okinan ; )

text: I am verily a man which am a Jew , born in Tarsus , a city in Cilicia , yet brought up in this city at the feet of Gamaliel , and taught according to the perfect manner of the law of the fathers , and was zealous toward God , as ye all are this day .
text2: We ' we ' nI nin , Cw nInI , nkitshInik shi Tasusuk , kcI otanuk , shi Sinishie ' uk e ' kiwuk , nIshcI nkit shIkishuk , shotI kcI - otanuk , e ' tIste ' pIt Ke ' me ' niIn , ipi nkiknomako , omIno tpakwnuke ' onuwa , kikosnanuk , ipi nkipmitwa Kshe ' mIne ' to ke ' cwa kinwa e ' totme ' k nkom e ' kishkiwuk .

text: And I persecuted this way unto the death , binding and delivering into prisons both men and women .
text2: Nkimiashtotwak , ipi nkinsak otI kashu te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk , nkitkopInak , ipi nkipitike ' nak kpakotiwkumkok nInwuk , ipi kwe ' k .

text: As also the high priest doth bear me witness , and all the estate of the elders : from whom also I received letters unto the brethren , and went to Damascus , to bring them which were there bound unto Jerusalem , for to be punished .
text2: Ipi ke ' iapI ke ' cme ' matmot , nkuke ' nmuk , ipi caye ' k , kakitocIk , kinakanse ' cIk , winwa ke ' iapI , nkiminkok , ni msInukInIn e ' wimacitwukwa ki nikane ' iuk , ipi nkishia ipI Te ' me ' ske ' suk e ' wipie ' nkwa , shi te ' kopsocuk , Cinose ' ne ' muk e ' wipsItie ' kaswat .

text: And it came to pass , that , as I made my journey , and was come nigh unto Damascus about noon , suddenly there shone from heaven a great light round about me .
text2: OtIcI kanomkuk , me ' kwa e ' ie ' ipI shiaian , ipi pe ' shoc kanImItnIsian shi Te ' me ' skusuk , e ' na ‘ wkwe ' k , kie ' nup kikcIwase ' ia ociiukwan shpumuk nkiwa wase ' shkmakon kiwtayiukwan .

text: And I fell unto the ground , and heard a voice saying unto me , Saul , Saul , why persecutest thou me ?
text2: Ipi nkipmukocIn shi ne ' kwukik ; ipi nkinotan notakwsuwun , otIki kitomkIt , San , San , We ' kwnicI we ' cmiashtotwun ?

text: And I answered , Who art thou , Lord ? And he said unto me , I am Jesus of Nazareth , whom thou persecutest .
text2: OtI cI nkishInkwe ' twa , We ' nicI kin , Te ' pe ' nke ' n ? otI cI nkinuk , ninsI Cisus Ne ' se ' ni nInI , kin me ' ashtotwin .

text: And they that were with me saw indeed the light , and were afraid ; but they heard not the voice of him that spake to me .
text2: KicI kapmowice ' okuk , we ' we ' nI okiw aptanawa e ' wase ' anuk , ipi kise ' ksik , nIshcI cokinotwasiwawan nikaki noshcIn .

text: And I said , What shall I do , Lord ? And the Lord said unto me , Arise , and go into Damascus ; and there it shall be told thee of all things which are appointed for thee to do .
text2: OtI cI nkikIt , We ' kwnicI ke ' totman Te ' pe ' nke ' n , icI o Te ' pe ' nke ' t otI nkinuk Psukwin ipi shian Te ' me ' skusuk , shiw kwshI kuwitmako , cake ' ko e ' ne ' nmukon waoshIton .

text: And when I could not see for the glory of that light , being led by the hand of them that were with me , I came into Damascus .
text2: Pic cI kapwan apian e ' pic iasikwe ' sian i e ' wase ' iak , nkipmIskInkInkok , ki kapmowice ' ocuk , nkipie ' shia Te ' me ' skusuk .

text: And one Ananias , a devout man according to the law , having a good report of all the Jews which dwelt there ,
text2: Nkot E ' ne ' naye ' s , kwiuk nInI , shi tpakwnuk e ' wunuk , caye ' k ni CwiIn kamnotshumkot shi katancIn ;

text: Came unto me , and stood , and said unto me , Brother Saul , receive thy sight . And the same hour I looked up upon him .
text2: Nkipie ' naskak , kinipwawak , ipi otI nkinuk , Nikane ' San , n ‘ I ntuwapIn icI pic i tpukIn , nkiwapma .

text: And he said , The God of our fathers hath chosen thee , that thou shouldest know his will , and see that Just One , and shouldest hear the voice of his mouth .
text2: OtI cI nkinuk , O Kshe ' mIne ' tomwan ki kosnanuk , kiwe ' napmuk e ' wike ' n tumIn iw tIne ' ntumwun , ipi e ' wi wapmIt o Nkot Kwiuk ; ipi e ' winotmIn iw kikitowun shiw tonik .

text: For thou shalt be his witness unto all men of what thou hast seen and heard .
text2: Kin ke ' ocI kuke ' ntumwat caye ' knInwuk , caye ' k , i kawaptumIn , ipi kanotmIn .

text: And now why tarriest thou ? arise , and be baptized , and wash away thy sins , calling on the name of the Lord .
text2: We ' kwnicI nkom e ' pwiton ? Psukwin ipi kcItapie ' nkason , e ' wiksIiapawe ' k kmiashsuwe ' psiwnIn , nume ' ki to ‘ w Kshe ' mIne ' to shi tInoswunuk .

text: And it came to pass , that , when I was come again to Jerusalem , even while I prayed in the temple , I was in a trance ;
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk , minI shi kapiaian Cinose ' ne ' muk e ' ie ' numaian shi nume ' okumkok nkiapwa ;

text: And saw him saying unto me , Make haste , and get thee quickly out of Jerusalem : for they will not receive thy testimony concerning me .
text2: Ipi nkiwapma , otI nkinuk , Ke ' npIsIn , ipi kie ' nup sak - In shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , osamco , okIte ' pwe ' tsinawa , kukie ' kwe ' wun , e ' shmiIn .

text: And I said , Lord , they know that I imprisoned and beat in every synagogue them that believed on thee :
text2: OtIcI nkikIt , Te ' pe ' nke ' n , nkw ke ' nmukok , e ' kikpakwokwa , ipi e ' ki psItie ' kwa shi e ' tsuk nume ' okum kwe ' n ki kate ' pwe ' ie ' nmukwiIn .

text: And when the blood of thy martyr Stephen was shed , I also was standing by , and consenting unto his death , and kept the raiment of them that slew him .
text2: Pic cI omuskwim kupmitakaiIm StipIn , kasikwe ' pnukate ' nuk , ninke ' iapI shi nkinipow ; ipi e ' te ' pwe ' tman , iw o nupwun ; ipi nkiknInmowak paskumwacIn kikansacuk .

text: And he said unto me , Depart : for I will send thee far hence unto the Gentiles .
text2: OcI cI nkinuk , Nmumacin ; knokanIn ; pnoc , shi e ' ce ' iuwat ki Me ' ikIscIk .

text: And they gave him audience unto this word , and then lifted up their voices , and said , Away with such a fellow from the earth : for it is not fit that he should live .
text2: OkipsItwawancI , nashcI otI kakItnIt . kiwishkwe ' we ' ksik , ipi otI kikItwuk , Macinuk , otI e ' shwe ' psIt nInI , shotI kik ; cosupite ' ntakwsIsi e ' wi pmatsIt .

text: And as they cried out , and cast off their clothes , and threw dust into the air ,
text2: E ' ie ' wishkwe ' we ' ksuwat ipi e ' kiskonie ' wat , ipi ne ' kwukI shpumuk e ' ie ' puk itowat ;

text: The chief captain commanded him to be brought into the castle , and bade that he should be examined by scourging ; that he might know wherefore they cried so against him .
text2: KcI kapte ' n kishuwe ' e ' wipitikIckas nIt shi wakakInuk , ipi kishuwe ' e ' wipsItie ' kasnIt , e ' wiocIke ' nmawat we ' c i shumkot ni nIshInape ' n .

text: And as they bound him with thongs , Paul said unto the centurion that stood by , Is it lawful for you to scourge a man that is a Roman , and uncondemned ?
text2: Me ' kwacI , e ' ie ' tkopnawat ni mishakIn tkopcIkInIn Pan ; okinan , niw okuman cikiwukwan kanipwunIt inI ktIne ' ntakwsum shi tpakwnuke ' wunuk e ' wipsItie ' we ' k , Nome ' n , nInI e ' pwamshI tpakwnIt .

text: When the centurion heard that , he went and told the chief captain , saying , Take heed what thou doest : for this man is a Roman .
text2: Pic cI kanotwat o okuma kishie ' wak ipi okiwitmowan ni kcI kapte ' nIn otI okinan , ikwamsuk otI e ' totme ' k osam Nome ' n nInI otI .

text: Then the chief captain came , and said unto him , Tell me , art thou a Roman ? He said , Yea .
text2: IcI kcI kapte ' n kipie ' ipi otI , okinan , WitmoshIn kinI Nome ' nInI ? OtI cI kikito e ' ‘ .

text: And the chief captain answered , With a great sum obtained I this freedom . And Paul said , But I was free born .
text2: IcI o kcI kapte ' n , okinkwe ' twan , mce ' sh shonia nkimikwe ' - e ' ki - kikishpIne ' toian te ' pe ' ntuswun ; Pan cI otI ki kIto ninkinik , e ' tupe ' ntusian .

text: Then straightway they departed from him which should have examined him : and the chief captain also was afraid , after he knew that he was a Roman , and because he had bound him .
text2: Kie ' nupcI okinknawan , kiw wak e ' nmapninuk , ipi ke ' o kcI kapte ' n kise ' kse ' , kake ' nmat , win Nome ' n nInwunIt , osam win okitkopnan .

text: On the morrow , because he would have known the certainty wherefore he was accused of the Jews , he loosed him from his bands , and commanded the chief priests and all their council to appear , and brought Paul down , and set him before them .
text2: IcI wiapnIwuk , e ' wike ' ntuk i e ' nomkItnuk , e ' mcItshumkot ni CwiIn , okiiapwan shi nIcinuk , ipi okinan ni ke ' cmatmoncIn , ipi caye ' k okikitonawan e ' wipianIt , ipi okipie ' niswunan , ni panIn , ipi okicipitupan e ' nasmup wat .

text: And Paul , earnestly beholding the council , said , Men and brethren , I have lived in all good conscience before God until this day .
text2: IcI Pan kane ' napmat , kikito nInwun , otI kikIto , NInituk , ipi nikane ' ituk , e ' kopie ' pmatse ' ian , pie ' mnone ' ntum , e ' nasm upIt Kshe ' mIne ' to , nash otI e ' kishkiwuk .

text: And the high priest Ananias commanded them that stood by him to smite him on the mouth .
text2: IcI o kcI me ' matmot E ' ne ' naye ' s , okinan , nI kanipwunIt shi cikiiukwan , e ' wiwe ' pokwanIt shiw otoninuk .

text: Then said Paul unto him , God shall smite thee , thou whited wall : for sittest thou to judge me after the law , and commandest me to be smitten contrary to the law ?
text2: PancI otI , okinan , Kshe ' mIne ' to kuwe ' potak , kin , wapshkukasiIn , shinI we ' c cipitupiIn , e ' wi tpakwnin , shi tpakwnuke ' wunuk ipi e ' towe ' n e ' wi we ' potakoian shi tpakwnuke ' wunuk ? e ' shupwacIcke ' k ?

text: And they that stood by said , Revilest thou God ' s high priest ?
text2: KicI kanipwucuk cikiiukwan , otI kikItwuk , kumiashknonanI Kshe ' mIne ' to , ke ' cmatmukwocIn ?

text: Then said Paul , I wist not , brethren , that he was the high priest : for it is written , Thou shalt not speak evil of the ruler of thy people .
text2: IcI Pan , otI kikIto , Conkuke ' nmasi nikane ' ituk win e ' kcIme ' matmot ; osam otI nIpie ' kate ' , Ke ' ko , mcItshumakIn otokumamwan ki ktInIshInape ' muk .

text: But when Paul perceived that the one part were Sadducees , and the other Pharisees , he cried out in the council , Men and brethren , I am a Pharisee , the son of a Pharisee : of the hope and resurrection of the dead I am called in question .
text2: Pic cI Pan , kake ' nmat ni anIt e ' Se ' cwsiwunIt ipi ni anIt e ' Pe ' ne ' siwunIt , kikItwak shi e ' kikitokiwnInuk , NInituk ipi nikane ' ituk , NinsI Pe ' ne ' si , ipi Pe ' ne ' si ntokwIsmuk ; pkose ' ncIke ' n , shi ipi minI psukwiwun kanpok , ie ' i we ' cntom koian , e ' wishpakwnukoian .

text: And when he had so said , there arose a dissension between the Pharisees and the Sadducees : and the multitude was divided .
text2: Pic cI i kakItot , kipie ' mkIt kikatwun ki Pe ' ne ' siuk , ipi Se ' cwsiuk , ipi ki mas ce ' ticIk , kipapkItik .

text: For the Sadducees say that there is no resurrection , neither angel , nor spirit : but the Pharisees confess both .
text2: Osam ki Se ' cwsiuk , kItwuk , Coin minI ke ' ko psukwiwun kanpok , coi ki mshInwe ' k , tanake ' , cipam , kicI ie ' k Pe ' nisiuk , te ' pwe ' tanawa ne ' ne ' ish .

text: And there arose a great cry : and the scribes that were of the Pharisees ' part arose , and strove , saying , We find no evil in this man : but if a spirit or an angel hath spoken to him , let us not fight against God .
text2: IcI kikcI notakwsik , ipi ni we ' npie ' mowacuk ni Pe ' nisiIn kipsukwik , ipi kikikatwat , otI kikItwuk , coke ' ko nmukumoasimIn miashowe ' psuwun , otI nInI , kishpInie ' k mIne ' to , tanake ' , mshInwe ' , kaknonkokwe ' n , cokumikanasimIn Kshe ' mIne ' to ;

text: And when there arose a great dissension , the chief captain , fearing lest Paul should have been pulled in pieces of them , commanded the soldiers to go down , and to take him by force from among them , and to bring him into the castle .
text2: IcI kapiamkuk , kcI kikatwun kcIkapte ' n , e ' kwsat ni PanIn , e ' wipikupcIkasnIt ; okinan ni shumaknIshIn , e ' winisasinIt , ipi kitwe ' e ' wi otapna nIt , ipi e ' wipie ' nanIt shi wakakInuk .

text: And the night following the Lord stood by him , and said , Be of good cheer , Paul : for as thou hast testified of me in Jerusalem , so must thou bear witness also at Rome .
text2: WiapukcIs e ' pkoniak , Kshe ' mIne ' to , okiwic kapwutwan , otI cI okinan , MInowankosIn Pan , osam nin kimnwacum , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , iwke ' ke ' shu mnwacmin ke ' iapI shi Nom .

text: And when it was day , certain of the Jews banded together , and bound themselves under a curse , saying that they would neither eat nor drink till they had killed Paul .
text2: Pic cI kakishkiw nInuk anIt ki Cwiuk kimsomaotoshnok ; otI kikItwuk , ‘ pnats iwnuk , nkIshiamIn , kishpIn pwansukIt Pan , e ' pwamshu wisne ' ak tanake ' , e ' pwanshu mnukwe ' iak .

text: And they were more than forty which had made this conspiracy .
text2: WusimI cI nie ' waptuk kitshik , otI kashuwitokwtatwat .

text: And they came to the chief priests and elders , and said , We have bound ourselves under a great curse , that we will eat nothing until we have slain Paul .
text2: IcI okipie ' naskawawan nkcI me ' matmoncIn , ipi nakanse ' cIk , kikItwuk , otI nkikItmIn , pnatsiwnunuk nkIshiamIn , kishpIn pwansukIt Pan , e ' pwamshu wisne ' iak ,

text: Now therefore ye with the council signify to the chief captain that he bring him down unto you to morrow , as though ye would inquire something more perfectly concerning him : and we , or ever he come near , are ready to kill him .
text2: IcI ie ' i kin ipi i kikitowun , nokashwe ' n e ' wiwitmowIt kcI kapton , e ' wipie ' nawat wapuk , ke ' cwa ke ' ko e ' wi ocInatowut , wusimI kwiuk e ' wi iactukwia ‘ w ; icI ninan pe ' shoc e ' pwamshu piaiak , nkukishkumkIsmIn e ' winsukIt .

text: And when Paul ' s sister ' s son heard of their lying in wait , he went and entered into the castle , and told Paul .
text2: Pi cI Pan , omIse ' iIn okwIsnInIn , kanotwat e ' wikuwapmanIt , kishie ' wak , ipi kipitike ' shi wakakInuk , icI e ' kiwitmowat ni PanIn .

text: Then Paul called one of the centurions unto him , and said , Bring this young man unto the chief captain : for he hath a certain thing to tell him .
text2: IcI Pan e ' kintomat , nkot ni okuman ipi otI okinan , sha ‘ onuk otI oshkInowe ' e ' ciwnIt ni kcI kapte ' nIn ; osam ke ' ko wiwitmowan .

text: So he took him , and brought him to the chief captain , and said , Paul the prisoner called me unto him , and prayed me to bring this young man unto thee , who hath something to say unto thee .
text2: IcI e ' kiwtapnat . ipi e ' ki sha ‘ onat , e ' ciiInIt kcI kapte ' nIn , ipi otI okinan , Pan ke ' pa kwukasot , nkintomuk , ipi nkiwishte ' pmuk e ' wi pie ' tonan otI oshkInwe ' , winke ' ko kwishukunonuk .

text: Then the chief captain took him by the hand , and went with him aside privately , and asked him , What is that thou hast to tell me ?
text2: IcI o kcI kapte ' n okiskInke ' nan , ipi cIciukwan kishie ' kimoc , icI e ' kinatawat We ' kwnicI otI wawitmoiIn ?

text: And he said , The Jews have agreed to desire thee that thou wouldest bring down Paul to morrow into the council , as though they would inquire somewhat of him more perfectly .
text2: OtI cI kikIto , kisI Cwiuk , kikItwuk , e ' winatakwiIn e ' wipie ' nIt Pan , wapuk , shi watshu kikitok , ke ' cwa e ' wi natawawat wusimI kwie ' k ke ' ko .

text: But do not thou yield unto them : for there lie in wait for him of them more than forty men , which have bound themselves with an oath , that they will neither eat nor drink till they have killed him : and now are they ready , looking for a promise from thee .
text2: NIshkI ke ' ko pamtawakIn , wusimI nie ' waptuk tshik ki nInwuk e ' kwapmacuk kIkakIcuk , pnatsowunuk nkishiamIn , kishpIn , pwansukIt conkuwisnIsimIn coke ' nkumnukwe ' simIn , ipi nkom otupwitonawa , e ' wi wawitmotwa .

text: So the chief captain then let the young man depart , and charged him , See thou tell no man that thou hast shewed these things to me .
text2: IcI o kcI Kapte ' n okipkItnan , niw shkInwe ' n e ' wimacinIt ; ipi okiikwaman ke ' ko wIiI nInI witmowakIn , otI kapie ' witmoiIn .

text: And he called unto him two centurions , saying , Make ready two hundred soldiers to go to Caesarea , and horsemen threescore and ten , and spearmen two hundred , at the third hour of the night ;
text2: IcI e ' kintomat nish kapte ' nIn otIcI okinan oshInwiuk nishwak shumaknIshuk , e ' wishiawat Sisine ' uk , ipi nouksomtInI pe ' momkocIk , ipi nishwak , shumakinIn me ' mackonkuk , nsotpukIn kish iaptu tpukuk .

text: And provide them beasts , that they may set Paul on , and bring him safe unto Felix the governor .
text2: Ipi minuk ne ' ktoshkshayIn , Pan , e ' winumomkot , ipi mnopie ' nuk e ' ciiIt Piniks , NakansIncIn .

text: And he wrote a letter after this manner :
text2: IcI e ' kiwnIpie ' uk msInukIn , otI cI kanIpie ' uk ;

text: Claudius Lysias unto the most excellent governor Felix sendeth greeting .
text2: Knatius Naysie ' s , okImonan , o ke ' c , mIno NakansIt Piniks ; otIne ' nman mInowankoswan ;

text: This man was taken of the Jews , and should have been killed of them : then came I with an army , and rescued him , having understood that he was a Roman .
text2: OtI nInI okiwtapnukon ni CwiIn , ipi otakinsukon , shumakInIshuk cI nkipie ' wice ' wak , icI nkike ' skona mIn , kanotake ' ian win Nome ' n nIniwut .

text: And when I would have known the cause wherefore they accused him , I brought him forth into their council :
text2: OsamcI e ' wike ' ntuman , i kaocI mcItshumawat , nkisha ‘ onashi e ' tI kikitowat .

text: Whom I perceived to be accused of questions of their law , but to have nothing laid to his charge worthy of death or of bonds .
text2: NIshcI nkimkan okimiashtshamawan , shiw tpakwnuke ' onawak , cocowi ke ' ko otInasiwan , taocI pite ' ntakwtunuk onupwun , tanake ' waocI kpakot .

text: And when it was told me how that the Jews laid wait for the man , I sent straightway to thee , and gave commandment to his accusers also to say before thee what they had against him . Farewell .
text2: Pic cI kawitmakoian ki Cwiuk , kashu kawapmawat ni nInwun , nkinokashwe ' kie ' nup , e ' ciin , ipi nkiwitmoIsk ni kamiasht shumkocIn ipi e ' wikItwat we ' kwe ' ntuk i we ' cmiane ' n mawage ' n e ' nasmupie ' n . We ' we ' nI ktInkwunmIn .

text: Then the soldiers , as it was commanded them , took Paul , and brought him by night to Antipatris .
text2: IcI ki shumakInIshuk kishowe ' psik kashumtwa e ' kimacinawan PanIn , ipi oki pie ' nawan , kapkonianuk shi E ' ntipe ' tnIsuk ,

text: On the morrow they left the horsemen to go with him , and returned to the castle :
text2: IcI kawapnInuk okinkInawan ni ne ' nomkoncIn e ' wiwice ' wanIt icI , e ' kikiwe ' wat shi wakakInuk .

text: Who , when they came to Caesarea , and delivered the epistle to the governor , presented Paul also before him .
text2: Winwa kapiawat shi Sisinie ' uk ipi kami nawat msInukIn , ni NakansIncIn , okipie ' nawan ke ' iapI ni PanIn , e ' nasmupnIt .

text: And when the governor had read the letter , he asked of what province he was . And when he understood that he was of Cilicia ;
text2: Pic cI o NakansIt , kawaptuk i msInukIn okinatawan , e ' tnukie ' nIt , pic kake ' nmat , e ' Sinishie ' nInwunIt ;

text: I will hear thee , said he , when thine accusers are also come . And he commanded him to be kept in Herod ' s judgment hall .
text2: KupsIton okinan , pic piawat ke ' winwa ki me ' iashtshumkoinuk , icI kishowe ' e ' wikuwapcIkasnIt shi E ' nut otpakwnuke ' okumkomuk .

text: And after five days Ananias the high priest descended with the elders , and with a certain orator named Tertullus , who informed the governor against Paul .
text2: Kakish nianokwnuktInuk , E ' ne ' naye ' s , ke ' cme ' matmot okiwice ' wan ni nakansIncIn , ipi nkot , kakikitot . TitunIs kishInkaso , kamcIcshumat PanIn e ' nasmupnIt , ni NakansIncIn .

text: And when he was called forth , Tertullus began to accuse him , saying , Seeing that by thee we enjoy great quietness , and that very worthy deeds are done unto this nation by thy providence ,
text2: Pic cI kantomIt TitunIs , o kiwe ' p mcIcshuman otI okinan , osam , kin , we ' ckcI tokumie ' iak , ipi , kIcmnototwak kote ' nIshInape ' k , e ' mno kowapmItwa ;

text: We accept it always , and in all places , most noble Felix , with all thankfulness .
text2: Nto tapnamIn pIne ' , ipi caye ' k , nkoci ke ' cmnoshuwe ' psin Piniks , cak nmI noshIte ' ‘ e ' ‘ onInanIn .

text: Notwithstanding , that I be not further tedious unto thee , I pray thee that thou wouldest hear us of thy clemency a few words .
text2: Cowike ' otI wusimI kInwe ' sh e ' wiknonan , kumumatmIn , e ' wipsItwe ' iak shi kmnoshuwe ' psiwnuk o natso nkikitonInanIn .

text: For we have found this man a pestilent fellow , and a mover of sedition among all the Jews throughout the world , and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes :
text2: Osam otI ukimkawamIn , pe ' pamkoshkaswe ' t , nInI , ipi okimacan caye ' k ni CwiIn , caye ' k shotIkik , e ' wi mkoshkacikwtat nIt , ipi pe ' mnikansIt , shi Ne ' se ' ni nInwun .

text: Who also hath gone about to profane the temple : whom we took , and would have judged according to our law .
text2: Win ke ' iapI kawinakwtot , i nume ' okumuk nkiwtapnamIn , ipi ntaki tpakwnamIn shi ntpakwnuke ' onunanuk ;

text: But the chief captain Lysias came upon us , and with great violence took him away out of our hands ,
text2: NIshcI kcI kapte ' n Naysius kipie ' wak ipi nkimne ' ukonan , shi nIcinanuk .

text: Commanding his accusers to come unto thee : by examining of whom thyself mayest take knowledge of all these things , whereof we accuse him .
text2: E ' kikatonan , ni kamcIcshumkocIn e ' wi pie ' naskakwiIn , kin e ' winInatowut ipi e ' wi ke ' ntumIn cak otI ke ' ko we ' cmcIc shumkIt .

text: And the Jews also assented , saying that these things were so .
text2: Ipi ki Cwiuk ke ' iapI kite ' pwe ' tatwuk otI kikIt - wuk otI we ' we ' nI e ' nomkuk .

text: Then Paul , after that the governor had beckoned unto him to speak , answered , Forasmuch as I know that thou hast been of many years a judge unto this nation , I do the more cheerfully answer for myself :
text2: Pic cI kcI NakansIt kaianInkowat ni PanIn , e ' wikikitonIt , o kinkwe ' twan osam kuke ' ntan , me ' kwe ' tsopon , kin ktupakwnak , kotI nIshInape ' k , ie ' i wusimI we ' cmnwe ' ntuman e ' wi kikitotatsoian .

text: Because that thou mayest understand , that there are yet but twelve days since I went up to Jerusalem for to worship .
text2: Osam otI ke ' ocI nsItmIn mtatsoshItInish tsokwunukIt kakoshiaian shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , e ' ki wunumaian .

text: And they neither found me in the temple disputing with any man , neither raising up the people , neither in the synagogues , nor in the city :
text2: Coke ' nkimkakwsik shi nume ' okumkok , e ' wi e ' iaiakwne ' twuk wIiI nInI ; coke ' nkimacasik ki nIshInape ' k , coke ' shi nume ' okumkok coke ' shi kcI otanuk .

text: Neither can they prove the things whereof they now accuse me .
text2: Coke ' wIiI otamkawasiwawan e ' wite ' pwe ' ta kwuat , i e ' wi kItnIt , i kashuwe ' pse ' ian .

text: But this I confess unto thee , that after the way which they call heresy , so worship I the God of my fathers , believing all things which are written in the law and in the prophets :
text2: OtIcI , ie ' k niactan winwa e ' tmowat , ie ' i mcItotmowun , iwsI e ' shnume ' kitowuk Okshe ' mInitomwan , kinosuk , e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' ntuman cake ' ko e ' shunIpie ' kate ' k shi tpakwnuke ' wunuk ipi ki Nakan acimocuk .

text: And have hope toward God , which they themselves also allow , that there shall be a resurrection of the dead , both of the just and unjust .
text2: Nte ' pwe ' ie ' nma Kshe ' mIne ' to , winwake ' ke ' iapI ote ' pwe ' ie ' nmawan , e ' wipsukwinIt kanponIt , ne ' ne ' ish ni ne ' pwakancIn , ipi ke ' kie ' patsIncIm ;

text: And herein do I exercise myself , to have always a conscience void of offence toward God , and toward men .
text2: Iw otI pIne ' e ' shkwcIpmatse ' ian , e ' wipwamIcitotwuk , Kshe ' mIne ' to , e ' nasmupIt , ipi nInwuk e ' nasmupwat .

text: Now after many years I came to bring alms to my nation , and offerings .
text2: KakishcI mce ' shtsoponkuk , nkipia e ' wipie ' twukwa , mnototatwun , ipi mikwe ' wu nIn , ki , nicie ' ishIshmoiuk .

text: Whereupon certain Jews from Asia found me purified in the temple , neither with multitude , nor with tumult .
text2: Iw pic anIt Cwiuk nkimkat kaocI piacuk E ' shie ' uk ‘ nkimkakok e ' pinakwse ' ian , shi nume ' okumkok ; coke ' nkiwice ' wasik , maoce ' ticIk , coke ' nkiopwe ' asik .

text: Who ought to have been here before thee , and object , if they had ought against me .
text2: Winwake ' shotI takiik , e ' nasmupiIn , ipi awikItwat , kishpIn ke ' kone ' n mawapIt .

text: Or else let these same here say , if they have found any evil doing in me , while I stood before the council ,
text2: Tanake ' shotI e ' icIk kuktwuk , kishpIn ke ' ko mkumwowat nmIctotmowun e ' ie ' nipwoian e ' nasmupwat okikito onuwak .

text: Except it be for this one voice , that I cried standing among them , Touching the resurrection of the dead I am called in question by you this day .
text2: Iwie ' k , mtIno nkot kikitowun , kakItian me ' kwa e ' wickapwutwukwa , E ' kitshItuman i psukwiwun i kanpok , iw we ' c tpakwnin otI e ' kishkiwuk .

text: And when Felix heard these things , having more perfect knowledge of that way , he deferred them , and said , When Lysias the chief captain shall come down , I will know the uttermost of your matter .
text2: IcI kik Piniks kanotuk notI ke ' ko , ipi wusimI e ' nsItup e ' nomkItnuk e ' wipwikot , otI cI okinan , pama piat kcI kapte ' n Naysius nkuke ' ntan , wusimI e ' nomkuk .

text: And he commanded a centurion to keep Paul , and to let him have liberty , and that he should forbid none of his acquaintance to minister or come unto him .
text2: Okikatonan nkot Kapte ' nIn e ' wikuwapmanIt ni PanIn , e ' ne ' ntumnIt e ' wishuwe ' psunIt , ipi e ' wipwaknaomowanIt ni e ' nwe ' manIt e ' wipmitakot tanake ' , e ' wipitkakot .

text: And after certain days , when Felix came with his wife Drusilla , which was a Jewess , he sent for Paul , and heard him concerning the faith in Christ .
text2: Ipi kakish onatso kwnukItInuk Piniks , okipie ' wice ' wan wiwun TnwsIne ' In Cwkwe ' ; okintoman ni PanIn , ipi okipsItwan e ' kim nwactumnIt , i te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun shi KnaystIn .

text: And as he reasoned of righteousness , temperance , and judgment to come Felix trembled , and answered , Go thy way for this time ; when I have a convenient season , I will call for thee .
text2: Me ' kwacI e ' ie ' knomowat i mnoshuwe ' psiwun , kwiuk , pmatsowun , ipi tpakwnuke ' kishuk piamkItnuk , Piniks kinukshke ' , ipi okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan , Winmacin , nkom pama minI , we ' npInuk , kIntomIn .

text: He hoped also that money should have been given him of Paul , that he might loose him : wherefore he sent for him the oftener , and communed with him .
text2: Kine ' ntum ke ' iapI shonia , e ' wiminkot , ni PanIn , e ' wiwcIpkItInat , iwcI ie ' i kaocI ntomat nanakIc , e ' wikInonat .

text: But after two years Porcius Festus came into Felix ' room : and Felix , willing to shew the Jews a pleasure , left Paul bound .
text2: NIshcI kakish nishponkItnuk Posius Pe ' stus okinapshkawan , PiniksIn , icI Pniks e ' wi mnwe ' ntumnIt , ni CwiIn , okinkInan ni PanIn , e ' kupkasnIt .

text: Now when Festus was come into the province , after three days he ascended from Caesarea to Jerusalem .
text2: Pic cI Pe ' stus kapiat shi e ' kiwuk ; kansokwnuktInuk , kiwcI maci shi Sisine ' uk e ' kishiat Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: Then the high priest and the chief of the Jews informed him against Paul , and besought him ,
text2: IcI o ke ' cmatmot , ipi otokmamwan ki Cwiuk , okiwitmowawan , e ' kimia nacimawan ni PanIn ipi okima tmawan ;

text: And desired favour against him , that he would send for him to Jerusalem , laying wait in the way to kill him .
text2: OkintawancI e ' winokanat shi Cinose ' ne ' muk ; e ' kuwapmawat shi wapmIshianIt , e ' winsawat .

text: But Festus answered , that Paul should be kept at Caesarea , and that he himself would depart shortly thither .
text2: NIshcI Pe ' stus okinkwe ' twan , otI okinan , Pan shi e ' wikuwapcIkasnIt , Sisine ' uk ipi win tpInwe ' kie ' nup ipI e ' wishiat .

text: Let them therefore , said he , which among you are able , go down with me , and accuse this man , if there be any wickedness in him .
text2: OtI cI kikIto nocima ki ke ' kshkItocuk e ' wishiawat , nkuwice ' okok , ipi mIcIcshume ' k otI nInI ; kishpIn ke ' ko shumiashuwe ' psIt .

text: And when he had tarried among them more than ten days , he went down unto Caesarea ; and the next day sitting on the judgment seat commanded Paul to be brought .
text2: IcI kakishiIt shi wusimI mtatsokwun kishie ' wak , shi Sisinie ' uk , icI wiapuk kacipitupIt shi tpakwnuke ' cipitupwunuk kishuwe ' PanIn e ' wipie ' ckasnIt .

text: And when he was come , the Jews which came down from Jerusalem stood round about , and laid many and grievous complaints against Paul , which they could not prove .
text2: PcI kapiat ki Cwiuk kaocI piacuk shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , kinipwik kiwtayiukwan mce ' shcI ke ' ko kamcI kItwuk e ' wipatamawat ni PanIn cocu okikshkupatama siwan ;

text: While he answered for himself , Neither against the law of the Jews , neither against the temple , nor yet against Caesar , have I offended any thing at all .
text2: Kinkwe ' tmatso , otI kikIto , Cowika , me ' iashto tmoasik , ki Cwiuk , otupakwnuke ' onuwa coke ' wi kashi , nume ' okumkok , coke ' wika me ' iashtotwasi Sise ' .

text: But Festus , willing to do the Jews a pleasure , answered Paul , and said , Wilt thou go up to Jerusalem , and there be judged of these things before me ?
text2: NIshcI Pe ' stus , e ' wimnwe ' ntumnIt , ni CwiIn okinkwe ' twan , PanIn ipi otI okinan , kIshianI , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi shi e ' witpakwnukon , notI ke ' ko e ' nasmupian ?

text: Then said Paul , I stand at Caesar ' s judgment seat , where I ought to be judged : to the Jews have I done no wrong , as thou very well knowest .
text2: Pan cI otI ikinan , Nipo ’ w , shotI Sise ' otupakwnuke ' ocipitupwunuk shotI tatshI tpakwnukoian , , kicI Cwiuk , coke ' ko nkishI , miashtotwasik kin we ' we ' nI anwI kuke ' ntan .

text: For if I be an offender , or have committed any thing worthy of death , I refuse not to die : but if there be none of these things whereof these accuse me , no man may deliver me unto them . I appeal unto Caesar .
text2: KishpIn kamIcitotmoanIn , tanake ' ke ' ko katotmoanIn pite ' ntakwuk npowIn , coin nshakwe ' nimosi e ' winpoian , KishpIn cI ke ' ko otI pwanomkuk , we ' c patamkoian , cowIiI nInI ntapkItinuk kwsi Sise ' nkItIpakwnuk .

text: Then Festus , when he had conferred with the council , answered , Hast thou appealed unto Caesar ? unto Caesar shalt thou go .
text2: Pic cI Pe ' stus , kakishknonat shi kikitonuk , okinkwe ' twan , ipi otI okinan , KnItwe ' nt anI Sise ' e ' witpakwnukwiIn ’ kishiasI Sise ' .

text: And after certain days king Agrippa and Bernice came unto Caesarea to salute Festus .
text2: IcI kakish onat sokwnuktInuk , kcI okuma , E ' kIpe ' , ipi Pe ' nIs , kipie ' shie ' k Sisine ' uk , e ' winumkawawat Pe ' ste ' sIn .

text: And when they had been there many days , Festus declared Paul ' s cause unto the king , saying , There is a certain man left in bonds by Felix :
text2: Shi cI kakishiuwat mce ' shkon , Pe ' ste ' s okiwitmoan ni kcI okuman , PanIn e ' shwe ' psInIt , otI nI okinan , ShotI nkot nInI Piniks okinkInan okik pakwan .

text: About whom , when I was at Jerusalem , the chief priests and the elders of the Jews informed me , desiring to have judgment against him .
text2: E ' kiianshi Cinose ' ne ' muk ki kcI - me ' matmocuk , ipi onikansimwan , ki Cwiuk , okimcIcshumawan ipi nkinatakok , ipi i tpakwnuke ' wun e ' wipatakonIt .

text: To whom I answered , It is not the manner of the Romans to deliver any man to die , before that he which is accused have the accusers face to face , and have licence to answer for himself concerning the crime laid against him .
text2: OtI cI nkinak , Cosuwi otI e ' witotmowat ki Nome ' n nInwuk , e ' wipkIte ' nma wat , wIiI nInwun e ' winponIt , e ' pwamshu win o me ' cIcshnmIt , ni patamkocIn , e ' witshItmoat , ipi e ' wipkItnukasot e ' wikikitotmatsot , i we ' c mcIcshumIt .

text: Therefore , when they were come hither , without any delay on the morrow I sat on the judgment seat , and commanded the man to be brought forth .
text2: IwsIie ' i , shotI kapiawat , e ' swapwitoian e ' wiwapuk , nkicipitup shi tpakwnuke ' cipitupwunuk , ipi nkinokashwe ' o nInI e ' wipie ' nIt .

text: Against whom when the accusers stood up , they brought none accusation of such things as I supposed :
text2: KapatamacIk kapsukwiwat coke ' ko okishu patamasiwan , e ' ne ' nmukwapIn .

text: But had certain questions against him of their own superstition , and of one Jesus , which was dead , whom Paul affirmed to be alive .
text2: NIshcI kaocI miane ' nmawat , mtIno winwa okukie ' patsiwnuwa ipi nkot okitshumawan CisusIn , kanpopIt , win Pan we ' we ' nI kakitot ; e ' pmatsInIt .

text: And because I doubted of such manner of questions , I asked him whether he would go to Jerusalem , and there be judged of these matters .
text2: Osam cI nkikwinwune ' ntanIn notI natatwunIn , Nkinat tawa , tanak e ' wi shiat , shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi shi e ' wi tshIt pakwnIt .

text: But when Paul had appealed to be reserved unto the hearing of Augustus , I commanded him to be kept till I might send him to Caesar .
text2: Pic cI Pan kakItot , AkustusIn , e ' witpa kwnukot ; nkishuwe ' e ' wi kuwapcIkasot nash e ' wi sho ’ wcIkasot e ' ciIt Sise ' .

text: Then Agrippa said unto Festus , I would also hear the man myself . To morrow , said he , thou shalt hear him .
text2: IcI E ' knIpe ' otI okinan ni Pe ' ste ' sIn Ninsuke ' ke ' iapI , ntapsItwa otI nInI . OtI cI okinan , WapuksI kupsItwa .

text: And on the morrow , when Agrippa was come , and Bernice , with great pomp , and was entered into the place of hearing , with the chief captains , and principal men of the city , at Festus ' commandment Paul was brought forth .
