text2: IcI kawapinInuk , pic E ' knIpe ' ipi Pe ' nIs , kapiawat wickcImishatsonuwa , ipi kakish pitike ' we ' t watshu psItake ' wat okiwice ' okowan ni kcI kapte ' nIn , ipi nakanse ' cIk nInwun shi kcI otanuk , Pe ' ste ' scI kashawe ' t , Pan kipie ' ckaso .

text: And Festus said , King Agrippa , and all men which are here present with us , ye see this man , about whom all the multitude of the Jews have dealt with me , both at Jerusalem , and also here , crying that he ought not to live any longer .
text2: IcI Pe ' stus otI kikito , kcI okuma E ' knIpe ' , ipi caye ' k nInituk , shotI e ' ie ' k kuwapmawa ; otI nInI caye ' k ki maoce ' ticuk Cwiuk , kaocI mkoshkacawat ipI Cinose ' ne ' muk , ipi ke ' iapI shotI e ' kItwat , cowunsInon wusimI e ' wipmatsIt .

text: But when I found that he had committed nothing worthy of death , and that he himself hath appealed to Augustus , I have determined to send him .
text2: NIshcI pic ke ' ko kapwamkumwuk , e ' pite ' ntakwuk npowun , ipi win onItwe ' nman e ' witpakwnukot ni AkustusIn , nkine ' ntan , ipI e ' wishaocIkasot .

text: Of whom I have no certain thing to write unto my lord . Wherefore I have brought him forth before you , and specially before thee , O king Agrippa , that , after examination had , I might have somewhat to write .
text2: Win coke ' ko , e ' pwe ' mkItnuk , nmukmoasi taocI onupie ' omouk , Te ' pe ' nmIt iwce ' ie ' i we ' cpie ' nuk , e ' nasmupie ' k ipi we ' we ' nI e ' nasmupiIn kin okcI okuma E ' knIpe ' ipi kish tpakwnukasot ; ke ' ko ntaotnIn e ' wiw onIpie ' ke ' ian .

text: For it seemeth to me unreasonable to send a prisoner , and not withal to signify the crimes laid against him .
text2: CowunsInon ntIne ' ntum , e ' winitawe ' k ke ' pakwukasot , ipi e ' pawitmatuk we ' cmcItshumIt ,

text: Then Agrippa said unto Paul , Thou art permitted to speak for thyself . Then Paul stretched forth the hand , and answered for himself :
text2: IcI E ' knIpe ' otI okinan , ni PanIn kpuki tIwkas e ' wikikitotatson , icI Pan , e ' ki shipnuke ' not ipi e ' kinkwe ' tmatsot .

text: I think myself happy , king Agrippa , because I shall answer for myself this day before thee touching all the things whereof I am accused of the Jews :
text2: We ' we ' nI nte ' ne ' ntan nia ‘ w kcI okuma E ' knIpe ' , osam e ' wi kikitotmatsoian otI e ' kishkiwuk , e ' nasmupiIn , e ' witshItman cake ' ko we ' c mcItshumwat ki Cwiuk .

text: Especially because I know thee to be expert in all customs and questions which are among the Jews : wherefore I beseech thee to hear me patiently .
text2: We ' we ' nI kin osam e ' ke ' nme ' nan , kin e ' ke ' ntumIn caye ' k , otIshcIke ' onawa ipi nInatatwunwan , Winwaki Cwiuk , owsIie ' i , kumumatmIn , we ' we ' nI e ' wipsItwin .

text: My manner of life from my youth , which was at the first among mine own nation at Jerusalem , know all the Jews ;
text2: Caye ' k ki Cwiuk , nkuke ' nmukok , e ' shpmatse ' ian , e ' kopnoce ' iuwe ' ian , e ' kiwitike ' mkwa nic ie ' ishIsmoiuk shi Cinose ' ne ' muk .

text: Which knew me from the beginning , if they would testify , that after the most straitest sect of our religion I lived a Pharisee .
text2: Kake ' nmIcuk oshkIca , kishpIn witmaka wat , iw kakish we ' we ' nI , kwiuk e ' tomuk shi ntInume ' onunanuk , nkishu pmatIs Pe ' nIsiuk .

text: And now I stand and am judged for the hope of the promise made of God unto our fathers :
text2: IcI nkom nipo ‘ w , ipi we ' ctpakwnukasian osam e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' ntuman kawawitmoat Kshe ' mIne ' to KosnanIn .

text: Unto which promise our twelve tribes , instantly serving God day and night , hope to come . For which hope ' s sake , king Agrippa , I am accused of the Jews .
text2: Kinan mtatso shItInish , e ' shumcuk , pIne ' pmitwawan Kshe ' mIne ' ton , kakpe ' kishIk ipi kakpe ' tpuk , ne ' ntumwuk e ' wipiawat ; osamce ' i te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumwun kcI okuma E ' knIpe ' i we ' cpatamwat ki Cwiuk .

text: Why should it be thought a thing incredible with you , that God should raise the dead ?
text2: TacI shIna we ' tshIte ' an e ' wipwakshkItot , Kshe ' mIne ' to , e ' wipsukwitnat kanponcIn .

text: I verily thought with myself , that I ought to do many things contrary to the name of Jesus of Nazareth .
text2: We ' we ' nI , nkine ' ntus , e ' witotman ke ' komce ' sh e ' wimcItotmowuk otInoswun Cisus Ne ' se ' ni nInI .

text: Which thing I also did in Jerusalem : and many of the saints did I shut up in prison , having received authority from the chief priests ; and when they were put to death , I gave my voice against them .
text2: Iw katotman ke ' iapI shi Cinose ' ne ' muk ipi mce ' sh te ' pwe ' ie ' ntukuk nkikpakwak shi kpakotiwkumkok , kamishwat kshke ' e ' osuwun ki ke ' cme ' matmocuk , ipi pic kan sIckaswat , nkimcItshImak ;

text: And I punished them oft in every synagogue , and compelled them to blaspheme ; and being exceedingly mad against them , I persecuted them even unto strange cities .
text2: NkipsItie ' wak , nanakIc e ' tsuk nume ' o kumkok , ipi nkiwishte ' pmak e ' wipcI ‘ kikitowat , ipi e ' kcInshke ' nmukwa , nkikwtukak shi pwake ' ntakwkIn kcI otanIn .

text: Whereupon as I went to Damascus with authority and commission from the chief priests ,
text2: IwcI ie ' i e ' shiaian Te ' me ' skusuk ; nkiiun kshke ' e ' osuwun ipi msInukInIn , nkiminkok kike ' c me ' matonocuk .

text: At midday , O king , I saw in the way a light from heaven , above the brightness of the sun , shining round about me and them which journeyed with me .
text2: E ' na ‘ wkwe ' kcI O kcI Okuma , e ' ie ' shiaian nkiwaptan wase ' iak , kiwcIpie ' mkIt shpumuk , wusimI kishu wase ' ia icI o kisIs nkiwawase ' shkmak kiwtayiukwan ipi ki kapmIwice ' ocuk .

text: And when we were all fallen to the earth , I heard a voice speaking unto me , and saying in the Hebrew tongue , Saul , Saul , why persecutest thou me ? it is hard for thee to kick against the pricks .
text2: Pic cI caye ' k kapmukocnak shi kik , nkinotan notakwsuwun e ' knonkoian ipi otI kikitomkIt , shi Ipnwuk e ' shumwat , San , San , We ' kwnicI we ' c mIcItotwin ? SInukIt kin e ' witkIshkwutwa kakaoshiuk .

text: And I said , Who art thou , Lord ? And he said , I am Jesus whom thou persecutest .
text2: IcI otI nkikIt We ' nicI kin Te ' pe ' nke ' n ? IcI otI kikIto , NinsI Cisus me ' iashtotwin .

text: But rise , and stand upon thy feet : for I have appeared unto thee for this purpose , to make thee a minister and a witness both of these things which thou hast seen , and of those things in the which I will appear unto thee ;
text2: NIshcI Psukwin , ipi , nipwun , osam otI we ' cwapitue ' nan otI nia ‘ w e ' wiwshe ' nan e ' wipmitwin , ipi e ' wiwitmake ' n notI ke ' ko , kawaptImiInIn , ipi notI ke ' ko ke ' wapte ' nan shi niiwuk .

text: Delivering thee from the people , and from the Gentiles , unto whom now I send thee ,
text2: Shi ktocke ' skonIn ki nIshInape ' k , ipi Me ' ikIscIk shiwie ' shi , nkom , e ' shnokanan .

text: To open their eyes , and to turn them from darkness to light , and from the power of Satan unto God , that they may receive forgiveness of sins , and inheritance among them which are sanctified by faith that is in me .
text2: E ' winsakwnumwutwa ni oshkishkowan ipi me ' kwe ' kiskupkonia , e ' wikwe ' knItwa shi e ' wase ' iak , ipi e ' wimiwnumwutwa MIcImIne ' to O wishkIswun , e ' wimintwacI Kshe ' mIne ' to o wishkIswun , e ' wimintwa e ' wiwe ' pnumwutwan i miashuwe ' psiwnun , ipi kuminak , tpInwe ' osuwun e ' ciiInIt kaocI pinakwsowat e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' nmowat .

text: Whereupon , O king Agrippa , I was not disobedient unto the heavenly vision :
text2: Kie ' nupcI O kcI Okuma E ' knIpe ' , nkite ' pwe ' tan wawaptuman , kaocIpiamkuk , shpumuk .

text: But shewed first unto them of Damascus , and at Jerusalem , and throughout all the coasts of Judaea , and then to the Gentiles , that they should repent and turn to God , and do works meet for repentance .
text2: Ne ' tum nkikikie ' kumak kaie ' cuk Te ' me ' skusuk , ipi shi Cinose ' ne ' ‘ muk , ipi shi caye ' k , Cwtie ' uk , ipi pic ki Me ' ikIscIk ; e ' wikisate ' ntumwat , ipi e ' wi kwe ' knoitwawat Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi e ' wishI mikce ' wiwat e ' wiwapitowe ' wat , kisate ' ntumwunwa .

text: For these causes the Jews caught me in the temple , and went about to kill me .
text2: OtI cI ie ' i ki Cwiuk kaocI mshInwat shi nume ' okumkok , ipi waocIn shuwapIt ,

text: Having therefore obtained help of God , I continue unto this day , witnessing both to small and great , saying none other things than those which the prophets and Moses did say should come :
text2: Kshe ' mIne ' to cI nkinishokmak , ntIi nash otI e ' kishkiwuk , e ' witmokwa , ne ' ne ' nish ke ' c pite ' ntakwse ' cIk , ipi pwapite ' ntakwse ' cIk , nkikIt coike ' ko , mtIno i Mosus , ipi Nakanacimocuk , kakItwat , e ' ipiamkItnuk .

text: That Christ should suffer , and that he should be the first that should rise from the dead , and should shew light unto the people , and to the Gentiles .
text2: I Knayst , e ' wikwtukitot , ipi win , ne ' tum kie ' psukwit , e ' npopIt , ipi e ' wiwapitaat wase ' anuk ni nIshInape ' n , ipi ni Me ' ikIsnIncIn .

text: And as he thus spake for himself , Festus said with a loud voice , Paul , thou art beside thyself ; much learning doth make thee mad .
text2: Me ' kwacI ie ' ie ' knotmatsot , Pe ' stus , kiwishkowe ' , ipi otI kikito , Pan , kowawunum , mce ' sh ke ' ko e ' ke ' ntumIn , we ' conate ' n tumIn .

text: But he said , I am not mad , most noble Festus ; but speak forth the words of truth and soberness .
text2: NIshcI otI okinan , cosuwi ntonate ' ntusi wusimI ke ' cpite ' ntakwsin Pe ' stus , nIshcI e ' kikitoian we ' we ' nI nkikIt ipi mnone ' ntumwun .

text: For the king knoweth of these things , before whom also I speak freely : for I am persuaded that none of these things are hidden from him ; for this thing was not done in a corner .
text2: Osam kcI okuma win okuke ' ntanIn otI ke ' ko , win e ' nasmupIt ke ' iapI we ' c we ' we ' nI kikitoian , osam tIne ' n tum , coi notI ke ' ko kukItwasi co otI kitotsim e ' wikwe ' ak .

text: King Agrippa , believest thou the prophets ? I know that thou believest .
text2: KcI o kuma E ' knIpe ' kte ' pwe ' twaknI ki Nakanacimocuk ? Kuke ' nmIn , e ' te ' pwe ' ie ' ntumIn ,

text: Then Agrippa said unto Paul , Almost thou persuadest me to be a Christian .
text2: IcI E ' knIpe ' otI okinan , ni PanIn , kaka kowishte ' pum , e ' wi KnaystnIniwian .

text: And Paul said , I would to God , that not only thou , but also all that hear me this day , were both almost , and altogether such as I am , except these bonds .
text2: Pan cI otI kikIto , ape ' ntIne ' nma Kshe ' mIne ' to , co i kin mtIno , ke ' iapI cpe ' k noatuwuwat otI e ' kishkiwuk , cowi kaka e ' shwe ' psoian , kwiuksI e ' shwe ' pse ' ian , mtInoie ' k notI tkopcIkInIn .

text: And when he had thus spoken , the king rose up , and the governor , and Bernice , and they that sat with them :
text2: IwcI pic kakishkikitot kcI okuma kipsukwik , ipi o NakansIt , ipi Pe ' nIs , ipi ki kawitpmacuk ,

text: And when they were gone aside , they talked between themselves , saying , This man doeth nothing worthy of death or of bonds .
text2: Pic cI nkoci kashIawat ki kInontok , otI kikItwuk , OtI nInI coke ' ko , kitotsi taocI pite ' ntakwte ' nuk , npowun ; tanake ' we ' c tkopsot .

text: Then said Agrippa unto Festus , This man might have been set at liberty , if he had not appealed unto Caesar .
text2: IcI E ' knIpe ' , otI okinan , ni Pe ' ste ' sIn OtI nInI taki pkItna , kishpIn , pwakItIpIt e ' wi tpakwnukot Sase ' In .

text: And when it was determined that we should sail into Italy , they delivered Paul and certain other prisoners unto one named Julius , a centurion of Augustus ' band .
text2: Pic cI katpowe ' wat e ' winashiak Ite ' niuk okipkItnawan PanIn , ipi anIt pe ' kansIncIn kie ' pakwukascIk kiminawan nkot Cwnius , kishInkaso , kapte ' n Akustus o shumakInIshimIn .

text: And entering into a ship of Adramyttium , we launched , meaning to sail by the coasts of Asia ; one Aristarchus , a Macedonian of Thessalonica , being with us .
text2: IcI kaposiakshi E ' tne ' maytium tshI napkwan , nkiwe ' pshkamIn , nkine ' ntamIn e ' winashiak ci kiiukwan e ' kokmukiak E ' shie ' uk nkot E ' nIstakus Me ' sitoni nInI kiw cupie ' , Te ' sinonIke ' uk nkipmI wice ' okonan .

text: And the next day we touched at Sidon . And Julius courteously entreated Paul , and gave him liberty to go unto his friends to refresh himself .
text2: IcI wiapuk ukikpamIn , Saytunuk , icI Cwnius we ' we ' nI okitotwan ni PanIn , ipi okipkIte ' nman , e ' wi shi anIt , ni wikanIn , e ' winwashmonIt ,

text: And when we had launched from thence , we sailed under Cyprus , because the winds were contrary .
text2: Pic cI shi kaocI we ' pshkaiak , ci kiiukwan Saypnusuk , nkipmInashmIn , Osam kimiananmIt .

text: And when we had sailed over the sea of Cilicia and Pamphylia , we came to Myra , a city of Lycia .
text2: Pic cI Katkumashiak shi kcIkumik Sinishiuk ipi Pe ' mpinie ' uk , nkipiamIn shi Mayniuk , kcI otanuk , Naysiuk .

text: And there the centurion found a ship of Alexandria sailing into Italy ; and he put us therein .
text2: Shi cI o kapte ' n , E ' nikse ' nte ' ne ' tshI napkwan okimkan , Itinie ' uk e ' winasuk icI shi e ' kipose ' imIt .

text: And when we had sailed slowly many days , and scarce were come over against Cnidus , the wind not suffering us , we sailed under Crete , over against Salmone ;
text2: Pic cI u ‘ e ' kapmashiak o natsokwun , kawantotamIn Snaytusuk , osam cI e ' miananmuk nkinashmIn , ci kiuikwan Knituk e ' nasmIte ' k , Se ' nmoniuk .

text: And , hardly passing it , came unto a place which is called The fair havens ; nigh whereunto was the city of Lasea .
text2: E ' pwamshI kwe ' pmosatmak nkiwtItamIn Mnokpe ' onIn ; e ' shnukate ' k , pe ' shoc shi kcI otanuk Ne ' sie ' uk ;

text: Now when much time was spent , and when sailing was now dangerous , because the fast was now already past , Paul admonished them ,
text2: Pic cI kInwe ' sh kaotumkumkIsuk , ipi pmashwun e ' ni e ' saniak , osami kikwe ' pocItse ' e ' pwawisuuk , Pan oki ikwaman ;

text: And said unto them , Sirs , I perceive that this voyage will be with hurt and much damage , not only of the lading and ship , but also of our lives .
text2: OtI okinan NInituk nIstowe ' ntan , otI pmashwun , kInie ' sania , ipi mce ' sh pnactaswun , coi mtIno i postaswun ipi napkwan , kupumatsiwnInanIn ke ' iapI .

text: Nevertheless the centurion believed the master and the owner of the ship , more than those things which were spoken by Paul .
text2: Ke ' iapI o kapte ' n , okite ' pwe ' twan ni okiman ipi ni Te ' pe ' ntumnIt i napkwan , wusimI , ni icI kakItnIt ni PanIn .

text: And because the haven was not commodious to winter in , the more part advised to depart thence also , if by any means they might attain to Phenice , and there to winter ; which is an haven of Crete , and lieth toward the south west and north west .
text2: Osam cI i kpe ' wun , cowunsInon shi e ' wiponshuk , kaka caye ' k kine ' ntumwuk shi e ' wiwcI maciwat , tanakshkItowat , e ' wishiawat Pinusuk , e ' wishi ponshawat kpe ' wunuk shi Knituk , e ' cIte ' k we ' cpkIshmok .

text: And when the south wind blew softly , supposing that they had obtained their purpose , loosing thence , they sailed close by Crete .
text2: Pic cI we ' csha ‘ onuuk n ‘ e ' ke ' wtanumuk , kine ' ntumwuk , e ' wtItnumwat , kashu ntIwe ' ntumwat kiwe ' pshke ' k , ipi ci kiiukwan Knituk kinashwuk ;

text: But not long after there arose against it a tempestuous wind , called Euroclydon .
text2: NIshcI co kInwe ' sh kikcInotIn e ' kikwe ' kanmuk Iwnoknaytun e ' shnukate ' k ;

text: And when the ship was caught , and could not bear up into the wind , we let her drive .
text2: Pic cI i napikwan , we ' pasuk , ipi e ' pwa nipwimkuk ie ' notuk ; nkipkItnamIn ;

text: And running under a certain island which is called Clauda , we had much work to come by the boat :
text2: Ci kiiukwan cI kapmie ' iak mnIshe ' iuk , Knatie ' , shInkate ' , nkikcI mikce ' wimIn e ' wi postoiak i ciman .

text: Which when they had taken up , they used helps , undergirding the ship ; and , fearing lest they should fall into the quicksands , strake sail , and so were driven .
text2: Pic cI kapostowat , e ' wi nishokmotowat cI namiiukwan okitkopitonawa inapikwan , ipi e ' kwutumwat , e ' wipe ' kwshInwat , pInItaokokik oki nispItonawan pmashwun , ipi nkiwe ' pashmIn .

text: And we being exceedingly tossed with a tempest , the next day they lightened the ship ;
text2: IkI e ' kcI we ' pokwiak , iw e ' miananmuk ; icI wiapuk , nkipukiatomIn i napikwan .

text: And the third day we cast out with our own hands the tackling of the ship .
text2: Kansokwnukuk , cI nki sakcowe ' pnamIn e ' iok , shi napikwanuk , tpInwe ' nIcinanIn .

text: And when neither sun nor stars in many days appeared , and no small tempest lay on us , all hope that we should be saved was then taken away .
text2: Pic cI onatsokwun e ' pwanakwsIt kisIs , ke ' iapukI nukok , ipi pIne ' e ' kcI notuk , caye ' k nkine ' ntamIn , e ' wipnatse ' ak .

text: But after long abstinence Paul stood forth in the midst of them , and said , Sirs , ye should have hearkened unto me , and not have loosed from Crete , and to have gained this harm and loss .
text2: NIshcI kInwe ' sh e ' pwawisnIwat ki nipwI Pan , me ' kwe ' nawe ' nI , otI cI kikIto NInituk , kitakipsItwumsI , ipi co kitakiwce ' we ' pshkasim shi Knituk , cocu kitaki pinatsIsimIn , ipi ktaki nkIt ‘ asimIn

text: And now I exhort you to be of good cheer : for there shall be no loss of any man ' s life among you , but of the ship .
text2: Ipi nkom nkumumatmInum , e ' wi mInwankosie ' k , cowi wIiI nInI opmatsiwun kupnacasnInI , mtInoie ' k i napikwan .

text: For there stood by me this night the angel of God , whose I am , and whom I serve ,
text2: Osam nkom otI e ' pkoniak , Kshe ' mIne ' to omIshIne ' we ' mIn , e ' ciian kinipwI Win te ' pe ' nmIt , ipi win , pe ' mitwuk .

text: Saying , Fear not , Paul ; thou must be brought before Caesar : and , lo , God hath given thee all them that sail with thee .
text2: OtI cI kikIto , ke ' kokwtackIn Pan , kIsho ‘ ocIkas , e ' nasmupIt Sise ' , ipi pInI , Kshe ' mIne ' to kiminuk caye ' k ki pe ' mwitomcuk ;

text: Wherefore , sirs , be of good cheer : for I believe God , that it shall be even as it was told me .
text2: OtI cI ie ' i NInituk mInowankosuk , nte ' pwe ' twa Kshe ' mIne ' to , iw ke ' nomkuk kashu witmakoian .

text: Howbeit we must be cast upon a certain island .
text2: NIshcI mInIshe ' iuk kupukcIkasmIn .

text: But when the fourteenth night was come , as we were driven up and down in Adria , about midnight the shipmen deemed that they drew near to some country ;
text2: Pic cI mtatso shItInie ' w katsotpukuk ; e ' ie ' onukumuk nInashiak shi E ' tniuk , e ' iaptI tpukitInuk , ki napikwan nInwuk , kine ' ntumwuk , pe ' shoc e ' pie ' tnIswat nkoci e ' kiwnunuk .

text: And sounded , and found it twenty fathoms : and when they had gone a little further , they sounded again , and found it fifteen fathoms .
text2: IcI kikwtukie ' ke ' k ; okimkanawacI nishwaptuktsonuk e ' kwitmianuk ; nakIcI kapmashwat okikwtukie ' anawa minI okimkanawacI mtatso ctInianIn tsonuk e ' kwitmianuk .

text: Then fearing lest we should have fallen upon rocks , they cast four anchors out of the stern , and wished for the day .
text2: E ' kwtumwacI tane ' nashwuk me ' kwe ' sInik mpik okipukitonawan nie ' w Piwapkwe ' n , otakanuk ociiukwan , e ' pwi towat e ' wiwapnInuk ;

text: And as the shipmen were about to flee out of the ship , when they had let down the boat into the sea , under colour as though they would have cast anchors out of the foreship ,
text2: IcI ki napkwan nInwuk e ' pitkumkIswat e ' winkItnIshtumwat , i napikwan , katowat i ciman , shi kcIkumik , e ' wine ' nmItwa e ' wipu . kitowat , Piwapkwe ' n shi nikan mukanuk ,

text: Paul said to the centurion and to the soldiers , Except these abide in the ship , ye cannot be saved .
text2: Pan , cI otI okinan , ni kapte ' nIn , ipi ni shumaknIshIn ; KishpIn kotI pwaiuwat shi napikwanuk , coki take ' skwisim .

text: Then the soldiers cut off the ropes of the boat , and let her fall off .
text2: IcI ki shumaknIshuk , oki kishkshanawan ni kate ' apiIn , shi cimanuk , icI e ' kiwe ' pote ' nuk .

text: And while the day was coming on , Paul besought them all to take meat , saying , This day is the fourteenth day that ye have tarried and continued fasting , having taken nothing .
text2: IcI pic e ' pie ' tapuk , Pan oki mumatuman caye ' k , e ' wiwisnInIt , otI kikIto , otI e ' ki shkiwuk mtatso shItnie ' w tsokwun , e ' ko pwitoie ' k , ipi moshuk e ' pwawisne ' ie ' k ; ipi coke ' ko kimitsinawa .

text: Wherefore I pray you to take some meat : for this is for your health : for there shall not an hair fall from the head of any of you .
text2: IwsI , ie ' i , we ' cmatmInkon , e ' wiwisnIie ' k , e ' wiwcI mnopmatse ' ie ' k ; co tIna nkot kinsIsiwa kuocI pmukote ' snon , nkote ' iI ktupiwak .

text: And when he had thus spoken , he took bread , and gave thanks to God in presence of them all : and when he had broken it , he began to eat .
text2: Pic cI i kakishkItot , okiwtapnan pkwe ' shkIn , ipi okinume ' kitowan Kshe ' mIne ' ton , e ' nasmupnIt caye ' k , icI kakish pikupitot kiwe ' pwisnI .

text: Then were they all of good cheer , and they also took some meat .
text2: IcI caye ' k kimnowankoswuk , ipi wInwa ke ' iapI , okiwtapnanawa anIt , micum .

text: And we were in all in the ship two hundred threescore and sixteen souls .
text2: ShicI caye ' k kaie ' iak shi napikwanuk , nishwak , ipi nouksomtInI shItInkotwatso , cipamuk ;

text: And when they had eaten enough , they lightened the ship , and cast out the wheat into the sea .
text2: IcI kakish te ' psInie ' wat , okipukiatonawa i napkwan , okipukitonawa i pkwe ' shkIn , e ' wpukomnanwuk shi kcIkumik .

text: And when it was day , they knew not the land : but they discovered a certain creek with a shore , into the which they were minded , if it were possible , to thrust in the ship .
text2: Pic cI kawapnInuk , co kike ' ntusinawa , i e ' kiwnunuk , nIshcI okiwaptanawa nkot sipiwe ' , e ' cikumkianuk , shi kine ' ntumwuk , kishpInkshkItowat shi e ' wikwitowat , i napikwan .

text: And when they had taken up the anchors , they committed themselves unto the sea , and loosed the rudder bands , and hoised up the mainsail to the wind , and made toward shore .
text2: Pic cI kaotapnumwat ni Piwapkwe ' n , okipkIte ' ntanawa , wiuwawa , shi kcIkumik , ipi , okiapanawa i powI shiw otakanuk ipi okiw nakakwnanawa , kcI katasmowe ' kIn shi we ' c notnInuk , ipi kinashwuk cikpIe ' k .

text: And falling into a place where two seas met , they ran the ship aground ; and the forepart stuck fast , and remained unmoveable , but the hinder part was broken with the violence of the waves .
text2: KipukitashwukcI shi nish kcukimiIn , e ' matasuk , kipe ' kwsun i napkwan , icI nikanmukan kimcImosIn ipi ke ' iapcI wishkIsIn , icIie ' k , otakanuk , kipikwIn e ' kcImakashkak .

text: And the soldiers ' counsel was to kill the prisoners , lest any of them should swim out , and escape .
text2: IwcI ki shumakInIshuk kine ' ntumwuk e ' winsawat ni kie ' pakwu - ukasnIncIn , e ' kwtumwat , e ' wipmatkanIt , ipi e ' wikiInkowat .

text: But the centurion , willing to save Paul , kept them from their purpose ; and commanded that they which could swim should cast themselves first into the sea , and get to land :
text2: NIshcI o kapte ' n , e ' wishte ' psIt e ' wike ' skonat ni PanIn , co okipkIte ' nmasin i kane ' ntumnIt , kishuwe ' cI , ni ne ' atkanIt , e ' wipuksowat , shi kcukumik ne ' tum , ipi e ' wikwashnInIt :

text: And the rest , some on boards , and some on broken pieces of the ship . And so it came to pass , that they escaped all safe to land .
text2: Ipi kipe ' kanse ' cIk , AnIt cI ki psukakok , ipi anIt kaocI pikwshkanuk , i napikwan . IwcI kanomkuk , caye ' k kikiItmok shi e ' kiwnInuk .

text: And when they were escaped , then they knew that the island was called Melita .
text2: IwcI kakiItmowat okike ' ntanawa i mnIshe ' e ' shInkate ' nuk Minayte ' .

text: And the barbarous people shewed us no little kindness : for they kindled a fire , and received us every one , because of the present rain , and because of the cold .
text2: Ipi ki pkoc nIshInape ' k , co pike ' ci nkishI mnototakwsinanuk ; okiwtItonaua , shkote ' , ipi e ' tshIiak nkipitkInkonanuk , osam e ' kmowuk , ipi e ' ksIniak .

text: And when Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks , and laid them on the fire , there came a viper out of the heat , and fastened on his hand .
text2: IwcI pic Pan kakish mamkInsukwe ' t , ipi kapkItnuk shi shkote ' k kipie ' ocI soikitota pwatacke ' t mIne ' to shi shkote ' k ipi okimcumnukon shiw one ' cik .

text: And when the barbarians saw the venomous beast hang on his hand , they said among themselves , No doubt this man is a murderer , whom , though he hath escaped the sea , yet vengeance suffereth not to live .
text2: IwcI pic ki pkoc nIshInape ' k , kawapmawat ni mIcIpwatacke ' ncIn , e ' we ' we ' pkocnInIt , shiw onIcinIn ; otI kikItwuk , we ' we ' nIsI otI nInI ne ' shwe ' t , win , e ' kiianwu kie ' tuk shi kcIkumik , kwiukmnoshuwe ' psowun co ne ' ntakwsIsi e ' wipmatsIt .

text: And he shook off the beast into the fire , and felt no harm .
text2: IwcI e ' kipapiwe ' pnat ni mIcIpwatacke ' ncIn , shi shkote ' k cocu ke ' ko kitsi .

text: Howbeit they looked when he should have swollen , or fallen down dead suddenly : but after they had looked a great while , and saw no harm come to him , they changed their minds , and said that he was a god .
text2: IwcI okiwapmawan , pic i e ' wi mkwitmInIt , tanake ' e ' wipmukocnInIt , kie ' nup e ' winponIt , nIshcI kakish kInwe ' sh wapmawat , ipi ke ' ko e ' pwa shuwe ' psInIt , pkan okine ' nmawan otI kikItwuk , Win sI o Kshe ' mIne ' to .

text: In the same quarters were possessions of the chief man of the island , whose name was Publius ; who received us , and lodged us three days courteously .
text2: Shiw cI kitkomkIt tpInwe ' osoonIn , katpe ' ntuk , nakansIt nInI , shimnIshIiuk kashInkasot Pupnius nkiitp kInkonan , ipi shi nkiImIn nsokwun nki mnototakwnan .

text: And it came to pass , that the father of Publius lay sick of a fever and of a bloody flux : to whom Paul entered in , and prayed , and laid his hands on him , and healed him .
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk , Pupnius osIn shkIshIn e ' iakwnokat e ' psIsot , ipi e ' mskwapiat , Pan okipitkawan , ipi kinume ' ’ ipi okipkItnanIn , niw nIce ' n shiwiwunuk , icI e ' kine ' se ' at .

text: So when this was done , others also , which had diseases in the island , came , and were healed :
text2: IwcI kakish itotuk pe ' kanse ' cuk ke ' iapI , na ' w kanapne ' cuk , shi mnIshe ' iuk kipie ' naskawawan , icI e ' kine ' se ' twan .

text: Who also honoured us with many honours ; and when we departed , they laded us with such things as were necessary .
text2: Nkimnototakwnanuk , pic cI wamaci ak ; nkiminkonanuk ke ' ko tsome ' ne ' siak .

text: And after three months we departed in a ship of Alexandria , which had wintered in the isle , whose sign was Castor and Pollux .
text2: IcI kakish nsokisIs nkiposmIn . E ' ne ' kse ' nte ' ne ' , tshI napkwan , shi mnIshe ' iuk katshu ponshumkuk e ' shkInwacIkate ' k Ke ' stIn , ipi Ponuks .

text: And landing at Syracuse , we tarried there three days .
text2: IcI kakupaiak shi Sayne ' kusuk , nkinwashmomIn , shi nsokwun .

text: And from thence we fetched a compass , and came to Rhegium : and after one day the south wind blew , and we came the next day to Puteoli :
text2: ShicI nkipie ' ocImacimIn , nkipie ' kiwtashnImIn nkipiamIncI Niciumuk , icI kakish nkot konkuk , e ' sha ’ wnu , uk kiw tanmIt , icI wiapuk nkipiamInshi Piwtionayuk .

text: Where we found brethren , and were desired to tarry with them seven days : and so we went toward Rome .
text2: Shi nkimkawamIn nikane ' inanuk , ipi nkintuwe ' nmukwnanuk , nouktsokwun shi e ' wIiIiak , icI e ' ki shiaiak ociiukwan Nom e ' shnukate ' k .

text: And from thence , when the brethren heard of us , they came to meet us as far as Appiiforum , and The three taverns : whom when Paul saw , he thanked God , and took courage .
text2: Pic cI ki nikane ' inanuk kanotake ' wat shi kiw cI pie ' k , nkipie ' nkwe ' shkaknanuk , shi E ' piay Ponumuk ipi ni NswI na ’ w e ' shiw okumkwe ' n pic Pan kawapmat , we ' we ' nI okine ' nman , Kshe ' mIne ' ton , ipi kiwishkIte ' - e ' .

text: And when we came to Rome , the centurion delivered the prisoners to the captain of the guard : but Paul was suffered to dwell by himself with a soldier that kept him .
text2: Pic cI kapiaiak Nom - uk o kapte ' n , okipkItnum wsn , ni ke ' pakwuukasnIncIn , ni otI kapte ' nmowan , ki e ' kowapcuk , NIshcI win Pan kipkIte ' nma nshuke ' e ' wiwicat ni shi shumaknIshIn kakuwapmukwcIn .

text: And it came to pass , that after three days Paul called the chief of the Jews together : and when they were come together , he said unto them , Men and brethren , though I have committed nothing against the people , or customs of our fathers , yet was I delivered prisoner from Jerusalem into the hands of the Romans .
text2: OtI cI kanomkuk kakish nsokwnukuk Pan kintoman ni otokumamwan ki Cwiuk , e ' maosmomat pic cI kamaoce ' tinIt , otI okinan , NInituk ipi nikane ' ituk , e ' kiianwI pwamcIt otwukwa ki nIshInape ' k tanake ' otIsh cIke ' onuwa ki kosnanuk ke ' iapI nkiwcIpkItnukas ke ' pakwukasot shi Cinose ' ne ' muk , nkipkItnukas onIciwak ki Nome ' n nInwuk .

text: Who , when they had examined me , would have let me go , because there was no cause of death in me .
text2: Pic cI katpakwnawat , ntakipkItnukok osam co okimkIsinawa , taocI nshuwat .

text: But when the Jews spake against it , I was constrained to appeal unto Caesar ; not that I had ought to accuse my nation of .
text2: NIshcI , pic ki Cwiuk , kamcI tshItmowat , iw kaocI kItian e ' wi tpakwnIt Sise ' , cowi e ' miane ' nmukwa , ki nicie ' ishIshmoiuk .

text: For this cause therefore have I called for you , to see you , and to speak with you : because that for the hope of Israel I am bound with this chain .
text2: OtI cI ie ' i we ' cntomnukon , e ' wiwapmInkon , ipi e ' wiknontIikon , osam , i opukose ' nmowun , IsniIn , otI we ' ctkop soian iw piwapuk .

text: And they said unto him , We neither received letters out of Judaea concerning thee , neither any of the brethren that came shewed or spake any harm of thee .
text2: OtI cI okinawan , coke ' wika msInukInIn nkiwcI otItnIsimIn , shi Cwtie ' uk e ' witshumkon , coke ' wIiI ki nikane ' inanuk kapiacuk , kimcItshum kosik .

text: But we desire to hear of thee what thou thinkest : for as concerning this sect , we know that every where it is spoken against .
text2: NIshcI nkintuwe ' ntamIn e ' wi nota ke ' iak e ' ne ' ntumIn otI e ' shte ' pwe ' ie ' ntumuk nkuke ' ntamIn cak nkoci mcIcshIckate ' .

text: And when they had appointed him a day , there came many to him into his lodging ; to whom he expounded and testified the kingdom of God , persuading them concerning Jesus , both out of the law of Moses , and out of the prophets , from morning till evening .
text2: Pic cI kakumowawat e ' kishkiwnunuk mce ' sh kipie ' naskakon , e ' citat , okiwitmowan , ipi okimnwactumwan i Kshe ' mIne ' to otokmauwun ; okukatonan e ' shumat CisusIn , shiw tpakwnuke ' onuk Mosus , ipi ni NakanacimoncIn ; kukishie ' p nash e ' nmupkonianuk .

text: And some believed the things which were spoken , and some believed not .
text2: AnIt cI ki okite ' pwe ' ie ' ntanawa , i kashuknontwa ; kicI anIt cokite ' pwe ' ie ' ntusik .

text: And when they agreed not among themselves , they departed , after that Paul had spoken one word , Well spake the Holy Ghost by Esaias the prophet unto our fathers ,
text2: Pic cI kapwamnone ' ntawat kinmumacik kakish Pan , kikitot otI kikitowun , We ' we ' nI kikito , PanakwsIt Cipam , win Ise ' us Nakanacimot kanat KosnanIn .

text: Saying , Go unto this people , and say , Hearing ye shall hear , and shall not understand ; and seeing ye shall see , and not perceive :
text2: OtI kikIto , Shian ; e ' ciiuwat kote ' nIshInape ' k , ipi otI kInak ; Notake ' ie ' k , knotake ' m , cocu kInsItake ' sim , ipi wapke ' ie ' k , kawapke ' m , cokInsItwe ' nke ' sim .

text: For the heart of this people is waxed gross , and their ears are dull of hearing , and their eyes have they closed ; lest they should see with their eyes , and hear with their ears , and understand with their heart , and should be converted , and I should heal them .
text2: KotIsI nIshInape ' k , ote ' ’ iwan , mukwitmomkItnI e ' pic miante ' nuk , oto ’ wkawan iapie ' tsimkItInI , e ' winotake ' wat , ipi kie ' pikwe ' nwuk e ' kwtumwat , e ' wiwapke ' wat , w ’ shkishkowan , ipi anInotake ' k shiw to ’ wkawak , ipi ansItake ' k shiw te ' ’ iwak , icI taocI kwe ' kapowat , icI tacI ne ' se ' ukwa .

text: Be it known therefore unto you , that the salvation of God is sent unto the Gentiles , and that they will hear it .
text2: Kuke ' ntumok otI , oke ' skonwe ' wun Kshe ' mIne ' to , nitaak , ki Me ' ikIscIk , ipi okInotanwa .

text: And when he had said these words , the Jews departed , and had great reasoning among themselves .
text2: Pic cI kakishkItot notI , kikitonIn , ki Cwiuk kinmumacik , icI kikcI knontik winwa tpInwe ' .

text: And Paul dwelt two whole years in his own hired house , and received all that came in unto him ,
text2: IcI Pan kite ' wak tpInwe ' ka ’ wuwe ' t wikwam shiw nishpon , ipi okipitke ' nan , caye ' k kapie ' naskakwcIn .

text: Preaching the kingdom of God , and teaching those things which concern the Lord Jesus Christ , with all confidence , no man forbidding him .
text2: E ' mnwactuk , i Kshe ' mIne ' to otokmawun , ipi e ' knomake ' t notI ke ' ko , iacm umIt ni Te ' pe ' nke ' nIt Cisus KnaystIn , caye ' k iw wishke ' ntumwun , cocu wIiI nInwun okiknumakwsin .
